{"id": "5553", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5553", "title": "AR-23A Liberator Carbine", "text": "The AR-23A Liberator Carbine is an assault rifle found in in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" \nA shortened version of the &lt;a href=\"AR-23%20Liberator\"&gt;AR-23 Liberator&lt;/a&gt;, the AR-23A enjoys a 50% boost to it's RoF, at the cost of noticeably increased recoil. It also sports an open reflex sight, instead of the multi-role optical sight found on most other assault rifles, which gives it a better field of view up-close.\nThis particular version is customized by the Viper Commando Team of the SEAF, sporting undergrowth camo, a receiver-mounted tool kit, and an improvised egronomic grip for comfort.\nIt can be unlocked on the first page of &lt;a href=\"Viper%20Commandos\"&gt;Warbond: Viper Commandos&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nShifting away from the balanced nature of the AR-23, the AR-23A is fully committed to burst damage, possessing a high RoF similar to machine guns set on their highest setting. It is capable of dealing the second-highest burst DPS of any assault rifle, only behind the &lt;a href=\"AR-61%20Tenderizer\"&gt;AR-61 Tenderizer&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith these in mind, the Liberator Carbine is best used for close defense. As the higher recoil it possesses does not lend itself well to marksmanship."}
{"id": "3409", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3409", "title": "AR-23C Liberator Concussive", "text": "The AR-23C Concussive is a variant of the standard &lt;a href=\"AR-23%20Liberator\"&gt;AR-23 Liberator&lt;/a&gt;. It features a red-dot sight, as well as explosive rounds that stagger enemies who are hit. \nIt is unlocked in the first page of &lt;a href=\"Steeled%20Veterans\"&gt;Warbond: Steeled Veterans&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe AR-23C is a crowd-control weapon. It is designed to be shot at priority targets to stun and knock them back. This is especially useful for enemies with a special attacks, like terminid spewers and automaton rocket devastators, who's special attacks can be canceled with a successful hit. It can also stop fast enemies like stalkers, from closing the distance.\nIt is best paired with a high-damage weapon, as the Concussive Liberator's low RoF makes it struggle with actually killing enemies.\nUpdates.\n&lt;a href=\"Updates%20%26amp%3B%20Patch%20Notes%23September%2017th%202024\"&gt;Patch 01.001.100&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;\n\u2045 Changed magazine from a standard 30 round box magazine to a 60 round drum magazine\n&lt;a href=\"Updates%20%26amp%3B%20Patch%20Notes%23April%202nd%202024\"&gt;Patch 01.000.200&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;\n\u2045 Trait list has been updated to represent previous updates\n&lt;a href=\"Updates%20%26amp%3B%20Patch%20Notes%23March%206th%202024\"&gt;Patch 01.000.100&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;\n\u2045 Renamed from AR-23E Liberator Explosive to AR-23C Liberator Concussive &lt;br&gt;\n\u2045 No longer deals Explosive Damage to weak spots (Undocumented)"}
{"id": "3761", "revid": "52293559", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3761", "title": "AR-23P Liberator Penetrator", "text": "The AR-23P Liberator Penetrator is an assault rifle in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It's a variant of the standard &lt;a href=\"AR-23%20Liberator\"&gt;AR-23 Liberator&lt;/a&gt;, featuring a scope as well as the ability to penetrate medium armor.\nThe weapon is unlocked on the sixth page of &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%20Mobilize\"&gt;Warbond: Helldivers Mobilize&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nAs a medium armor penetrating automatic rifle, this weapon is effective against more heavily armored enemies than the standard Liberator, while still fulfilling a similar role -- handling large numbers of relatively small and weak enemies.\nDespite its armor penetration, shots which pierce medium armor deal noticeably reduced damage. As such, it is recommended to aim for weak spots, much like with the standard Liberator. However, even shots that do not hit a weak spot can still deal some damage. This can be useful against enemies like &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastators&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hive%20Guard\"&gt;Hive Guards&lt;/a&gt; and could go as far as to damage and destroy &lt;a href=\"Gunship\"&gt;Gunship&lt;/a&gt; engines.\nBurst is recommended when dealing with close range enemies while semi-auto is recommended when aiming with the scope.\nFull auto is situationally useful, but the increased recoil will result in poor accuracy. It does you no good if the only thing you pump full of lead is the ground.\nUpdates.\nPatch &lt;a href=\"Updates%20%26amp%3B%20Patch%20Notes%23April%202nd%202024\"&gt;01.000.200&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;\n \u2045 Added Full-Auto firing mode"}
{"id": "3372", "revid": "57985", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3372", "title": "AR-23 Liberator", "text": "The AR-23 Liberator is the standard dispenser of democracy in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" Filling the primary weapon slot, it is a light armor penetrating weapon with three modes: auto, burst, and semi-automatic. It is also equipped with a flashlight with three modes: auto (which activates the flashlight only in low light conditions), on, and off.\nIt is unlocked upon character creation and automatically equipped. Three other variants of the weapon are available in the game: the &lt;a href=\"AR-23P%20Liberator%20Penetrator\"&gt;AR-23P Liberator Penetrator&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"AR-23C%20Liberator%20Concussive\"&gt;AR-23C Liberator Concussive&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"AR-23A%20Liberator%20Carbine\"&gt;AR-23A Liberator Carbine&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Liberator is the default balance primary (as the autocannon is for support weapons), combining high damage vs. durable, fire rate, magazine capacity, accuracy, and handling. With accuracy it can easily kill any non-massive unit because of its vs. durable damage against weakspots. One clip on full auto is also sufficient to quickly drop any illuminate shield."}
{"id": "4807", "revid": "57183", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4807", "title": "AR-61 Tenderizer", "text": "The AR-61 Tenderizer is an Assault Rifle utilized in Helldivers 2.\nIt is unlocked in the first page of Warbond: Polar Patriots.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nAs of update 1.000.400, the AR-61 is the most powerful assault rifle in the armory. Possessing the highest damage per-shot AND burst DPS of any assault rifle currently available, while simultaneously being more controllable than the AR-23, and having higher stagger strength. Its only drawbacks are that it can only penetrate light armor and middling magazine size.\nThe weapon overall functions as a bridge between the &lt;a href=\"AR-23%20Liberator\"&gt;AR-23 Liberator&lt;/a&gt; and the heavier &lt;a href=\"BR-14%20Adjudicator\"&gt;BR-14 Adjudicator&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3852", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3852", "title": "ARC-12 Blitzer", "text": "The ARC-12 Blitzer is a unique type of energy shotgun that fires a barrage of electrical currents over a short distance. Unlike other \"infinite\" ammo primary weapons, only the Blitzer has true infinite ammo, as it does not have a heatsink that has to be swapped out incase it overheats.\nRole.\nThe Blitzer excels both at clearing hordes of fodder enemies, and taking down medium-armored threats up-close. It not only also stuns enemies briefly, it also cancels some of their actions, potentially immobilizing entire groups. The gun however, is short-ranged, only remaining viable within 50m, due to this it excels primarily against Terminids, able to kill multiple Scavengers, Hunters and sometimes even Warriors with a single shot. It also works well against lighter Automaton enemies, able kill multiple Troopers with a single shot as well as stun-lock all Devastator types."}
