{"id": "4886", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4886", "title": "Acamar IV", "text": "Acamar IV is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt;. After the inauguration of the Terminid Research Preserve, Acamar IV was been left under \"Terminid\" control, while in reality just serving as a experimental craddle for Terminids to be studied \"in the wild\". As such, it was under Super Earth control but appeared as Terminid controlled on the Galactic Map.\nOn November 12th, a massive breach in the Terminid Research Preserve occured and Acamar IV immediately returned to total Terminid control, which triggered Terminid assaults on all of the planets connected to Acamar IV.\nTopography.\nAcamar IV is a rugged and wild planet, with dramatic mountain peaks and rocky highlands. The defining feature of the planet is its mountains, which cover much of the landscape. These are broken up by green and fertile valleys and a jagged mist covered coastline.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nSupercolony Spore Outbreak.\nThe planet of Acamar IV was initially able to avoid the worst of the second galactic civil war, until massive bug outbreaks suddenly erupted across the planet, along with nearby &lt;a href=\"Heeth\"&gt;Heeth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Veld\"&gt;Veld&lt;/a&gt;. The spores that caused these outbreaks being identified as originating from the &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridian Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;, which was producing far more spores than other infested planets, leading to unpredictable outbreaks within its vicinty. The researchers of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; set to work searching for an effective countermeasures, though in the meantime Helldiver Corps was ordered to contain these outbreaks, before they could spread out of control.\nIn these efforts, they were partially successful, with the outbreaks on Heeth, Angel's Venture and Veld being brought under control. However the outbreak on Acamar IV was only partially contained when the major order finally expired, with the &lt;a href=\"terminids\"&gt;terminids&lt;/a&gt; spawning yet more agents of tyranny. Even worse however is what kind of effect these spores will have on the planets topography, though if Meridia is any indication, it can't be anything good.\nAs such, evacuation orders were issued for all nearby planets in the Jin Xi Sector and beyond. The citizens of Super Earth were forced to flee their homes, with only the clothes on their backs and their family flags. Yet this is unlikely to be the last of the necessary evacuations or outbreaks, which must be contained until the Ministry of Science finds a way to combat the Supercolony.\nDespite the valiant, unmeasured efforts of the Helldivers, Acamar would end up being too late for liberation. The Ministry of Humanity wants all readers to allocate 1 full minute of their lunch break in order to commemorate all the lives lost in this unforeseeable, inevitable calamity.\nOperation Enduring Peace.\nAcamar IV, while being lost during the initial Supercolony Spore Outbreaks, would not be lost outright, instead enduring several weeks of liberation campaigns and recaptures due to the persistent connection to the Meridia Supercolony. However, its salvation would come from a dangerous, unlikely source. Scientists in Moradesh had been tasked with manufacturing a new type of super-weapon, rooted in recovered technology from the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;: The Dark Fluid, a weapon capable of artificially creating black holes.\nOn May 28, 2184, the Super Earth High Command made the decision to deploy the Dark Fluid on Meridia, which would obviously and regrettably mean its destruction. From May 28 to May 29, the Helldivers fought to hold a line of planets that connected Moradesh to Meridia, which were &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt;, Turing and &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;. Then, from May 29 to May 30, the Helldivers would fight tooth and nail to deploy the Dark Fluid, keeping away the hordes of Terminids as they drilled the Dark Fluid into the surface of the Supercolony. By the afternoon of May 30, the Dark Fluid had managed to reach critical mass and collapsed into a black hole, destroying the Terminid Supercolony for good and siphoning away all of its spores into itself, crippling the Terminid advance and paving the way for a counter-attack.\nFrom May 31st on, Acamar IV, along with Erata Prime, Turing and Phact Bay, are on the sights of Super Earth, their liberation now imminent. The Major Order was completed on June 6th.\nFalstaff and Jin Xi Lockdown.\nFrom June 6th onwards, Acamar IV would see mostly peace, with only occasional Terminid assaults touching it, mostly coming from neighboring Gacrux. Even as other planets like Pandion XXIV and Phact Bay saw much worse invasions, Acamar IV would remain mostly untouched and would spend the majority of the major order under firm Super Earth control.\nOperation Righteous Expunge (July 18th - July 21st).\nAcamar survived most of the anti-bot operation in tenuous peace. On morning of July 20th, SEAF infrastructure reported Terminid Spores reaching the planet surface. Bugs immediately begun spreading, and the Terminids inside E-710 farms went rabid as hivemind established itself on planet. Scant SEAF forces were overwhelmed on following day.\nOperation Glorious Xenocide (July 21st - July 23rd).\nDuring the break between Major Orders, majority of Helldivers redeployed onto Acamar to contain the bug infestation before it could spread further into &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi&lt;/a&gt; sector, as well as &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut&lt;/a&gt;. Shortly thereafter, a major Terminid Spore Barrage has hit neighboring &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt;, winch was swiftly defended. Following in their decisive strike, full planetary control over Acamar was re-established in morning of July 23rd, and any runaway bugs were herded back into their sufficiently sized pens.\nOperation Brute Force.\nFollowing its liberation, Acamar IV would spend the rest of July and the 2 weeks of August in well-earned freedom, with the only minor interruption being a Terminid outbreak that would be quickly repelled during Operation Benevolent Sanitation. However, it would be during Operation Lighthouse that Acamar IV would face the new horrors that the Terminids were bringing. With the apparition of &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt;, the Terminids were now bolstered and began to launch multiple successive assaults, with Acamar IV being assaulted at the same time as &lt;a href=\"Erata%20Prime\"&gt;Erata Prime&lt;/a&gt;. Acamar IV's defense would honorably sacrifice itself in order to allow the Helldivers to concentrate on Erata Prime so that the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Barrier Planets&lt;/a&gt; remained unsurpassed. Acamar IV would fall to the Terminid infestation and remain as such for 4 long, horrid days as the Helldivers were ordered back towards the Automatons as they advanced into the &lt;a href=\"Marspira%20Sector\"&gt;Marspira Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, once the robotic threat was repelled, the Helldivers would be ordered back to the Terminid Front. After the sabotaging of Operation Prometheus, Super Earth High Command was detecting rapid spreading of the Gloom's intergalactic Terminid spores. As such, they issued a major order in order to hold back the incoming fascist nebula while culling as many Terminids, and especially &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Titan\"&gt;Bile Titans&lt;/a&gt;, as possible.\nWhile Acamar IV was not part of the operation's targets, it wound up being liberated on August 24th, shortly after nearby Crimsica. Acamar IV's liberation would happen at just the right time since, some hours later, the Terminids would begin a dual assault onto &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt;, which would enjoy all of the Helldivers' attention now that the Gloom was beginning to slow down its expansion in the face of the mighty Super Earth.\nOperation Leap Forward.\nAcamar IV would remain free for the rest of August and most of September. However, the Terminids would not allow that freedom to last. On September 24th, mere days after being righteously dislodged from Pandion XXIV, the Terminids launched an assault onto the underdefended Acamar IV. Due to the required focus on the Automaton-controlled &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Clasa\"&gt;Clasa&lt;/a&gt;, Acamar would fall to Terminid control the next day.\nOperation Alcubierre-II.\nHowever, this would not be the end of it as, pretty much a day later, the Terminids at Acamar immediately made a move for Turing. However, this move couldn't have been timed any worse, as Super Earth had just issued plans for the construction of a Xenoentomology Center in order to make the Super Destroyers' Alcubierre Warp Drives more efficient in their E-710 consumption. As such, the Helldivers were ordered to hold Turing by all means. After a whole 2 days of defending the planet, the unusually resilient Terminid onslaught was repelled and sent back to Acamar IV, where part of the Helldiver Corps gave chase but couldn't really make much breakthroughs, as the Bugs had managed to deeply entrench themselves into Acamar IV.\nOnce the Helldivers repelled the assault on Turing, they immediately set up Acamar IV's liberation as a secondary objective for the operation, as Acamar IV presented the most immediate threat against the construction of the Xenoentomology Center. For 6 days, the Helldivers fought tooth and nail over Acamar, making slow but steady progress towards the grassy planet's liberation until, on October 3rd, Acamar IV would be liberated almost on tandem with the nearby defensive victory at Turing, which completely crushed the Terminids and allowed the Xenoentomology Center to be completed, granting the Helldivers victory.\nOperation Ring of Freedom.\nShortly after the victory at Operation Alcubierre-II, the Xenoentomology Center would see a special need to study the Terminids on a \"natural\" environment. However, the SEAF was wary of the Terminids being left unchecked. As such, a Terminid Research Preserve had to be constructed in a planet neighboring Turing. And the best fit was Acamar IV, which had been recently liberated.\nThis research preserve was to be heavily guarded and monitored, as Terminids would be carefully seeded into the planet and continuously monitored and contained with electrified fences and armed guards. However, for this to work, Acamar IV had to be completely detached from the main Terminid broods at its adjacent planets. As such, on October 11th, the order was given for all of the planets connected to Acamar IV to be taken and held by the Helldivers for 6 days while the Terminid Research Preserve was constructed.\nAfter some initial pacification efforts and the preventive closing of FTL Supply Lines, Acamar IV would be designated as a \"Demilitarized Terminid Zone\", meaning that it would appear as if it was under Terminid control on the Galactic Map but its FTL Supply Lines were still usable by all Super Earth vessels.\nOn October 18th, Acamar IV's supply lines had been secured and the Terminid Research Preserve had been opened. Terminids had been seeded carefully into the planet and were heavily monitored by SEAF Wardens at all times of the solar cycle, contained with electrified fences both above and below ground and, in case of a Terminid outbreak, nuclear bombardment was set to automatically initiate upon the first signs of a containment breach.\nFor the civilian population, a new section called the \"Tyranny Park\" was opened, meant to allow the bolder civilians among the population to visit and even participate in tours called \"Big Tyrant Hunts\", meant to fund the Terminid Research Preserve and encourage the general population to deepen their understanding of the Terminids' horrid fascism and, obviously, how to appropriately deal with the insects.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nAcamar IV would have remained pretty much untouched after the inauguration of the Terminid Research Preserve. In the weeks that proceeded it, many advancements were made and the Democracy Space Station would be completed thanks to its contributions. However, not everything was going to go right for the grassy planet. On October 24th, Gacrux and Pandion-XXIV fell to a Terminid attack from &lt;a href=\"Partion\"&gt;Partion&lt;/a&gt;, which left Acamar IV exposed to the main Terminid territories and the Gloom's influence until both planets were liberated 6 days later. At the time, it seemed nothing had happened, but this lack of caution would be the spark that ultimately spelled disaster for Acamar IV.\nOn November 12th, in the middle of a busy day for the Tyranny Park, a massive underground Terminid hive erupted spontaneously, leading to a bloody massacre of visitors and park staff alike. Acamar IV was overrun in mere minutes, which prevented the nuclear security measures from being activated and allowed the Terminids to take over the planet without any impediment. Once Acamar IV fell, it launched 5 simultaneous attacks onto all of the planets connected to it. This catastrophe could not have been any more poorly timed, as the Automaton Jet Brigade had also just returned in massive numbers and destroyed the DSS Logistics Hub on &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe painting was clear on the wall that the Helldivers had to act quick before more damage had to be done. Despite Acamar's positioning, High Command gave the indication to protect the Xenoentomology Center at Turing by all means, as it still contained critical research material on the Terminids, pretty much dooming Acamar IV and all of its attached planets to perdition.\nWhile Turing was able to be saved, the tragedy at Acamar IV was a complete military disaster, product of dissidents among the Helldiver Corps that caused their attention to be divided and their focus to be lost in the moment when it counted most.\nAs Acamar IV's liberation campaign is underway, millions of refugees poured into the Celeste Sector through Turing, fleeing from the violence as their homes burned and the SEAF scrambled to alleviate the situation.\nOn November 17th, Acamar IV would be liberated, shortly after the arrival of the Democracy Space Station. With it, the Helldivers would manage to quickly contain the Terminids and secure control of what little remained of the Terminid Research Preserve, as well as the ruins of the now devastated Tyranny Park."}
{"id": "5976", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5976", "title": "Achernar Secundus", "text": "Achernar Secundus is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Borgus%20Sector\"&gt;Borgus Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It is also the location of a major Factory Hub operated by Admiral Defense (AM), a defense company with a proven history of constructing top-of-the-line armaments for &lt;a href=\"SEAF\"&gt;SEAF&lt;/a&gt; line units, with the factory's construction marking their expansion into providing Helldiver weaponry. Production at the Complex focuses mainly on the construction of &lt;a href=\"M-102%20Fast%20Recon%20Vehicle\"&gt;Fast Recon Vehicles&lt;/a&gt; (FRVs).\nOn December 19th, Achernar Secundus became the first planet ever to be attacked by 2 different factions, as the sent an invasion force onto the planet.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Oshaune\"&gt;Oshaune&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Ring of Freedom.\nAchernar was, like many other planets of its type, a peaceful planet colony off the Eastern Galactic Fringe that was settled by Super Earth at some point after the First Galactic War. Its colonists, for the most part, dedicated themselves to agriculture and fishing while inhabiting its green pastures.\nHowever, the would soon throw their plans off schedule when, on October 13th, pretty much immediately after capturing Gar Haren, they invaded Achernar Secundus, as they raced to flank the SEAF's hardened defense at through &lt;a href=\"Achird%20III\"&gt;Achird III&lt;/a&gt; in order to reach &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt;, the home of the newly built Xenoentomology Center. However, the bugs didn't count with the resilience of Super Earth's colonists. For 12 hours, they valiantly held the lines side by side with their brethren of the Colonial Defense Forces and a contingent of Helldivers that had decided to support the ongoing defense. However, as the hours passed, the situation looked bleaker and the casualties began to mount.\n16 hours into the assault, the situation looked desperate. Civilians were being evacuated in disarray while the SEAF was preparing to evacuate the planet. All hope seemed lost until, on October 14th, at 3:45 SEST, Darius II was liberated and soon, an additional 30,000 Super Destroyers showed up en masse to relief the besieged defense of Achernar Secundus.\nBy 13:00 SEST, the last remaining Terminids of the invading force had been repelled and Achernar was successfully defended, cleansing the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; off the Borgus Sector.\nOperation Bughammer.\nOn the 11th of December, 2184, the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defense&lt;/a&gt; officially awarded a multitrillion-Supercredit contract to Admiral (AM) Defense to expand production of high-quality military equipment for the Helldivers. It should be noted that AM Defense has a proven history of constructing top-of-the-line armaments for SEAF line units, and their expansion to providing Helldiver weaponry marks the beginning of an exciting new chapter in the Defense-Marketplace Partnership.\nTo begin this new chapter, AM Defense began construction of a massive, multi-complex Factory Hub on &lt;a href=\"Achernar%20Secundus\"&gt;Achernar Secundus&lt;/a&gt;, which would create millions of exciting labor opportunities for Super Earth citizens. However, temperature readings shows an increase of Terminid activity in the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sten%20Sector\"&gt;Sten&lt;/a&gt; Sectors, seemingly in response to this momentous project. Indeed, this lead credence to the theory proposed by many Terminid experts that the alien race may instinctively sense and attack areas with heavy Democratic activity. Never the less, the Helldivers were ordered to ensure the construction of the AM Defense Factory Hub continued unabated, in order to protect the investments of the Ministry of Defence's security partners.\nHowever Operation Bughammer was swiftly cancelled following the 's return to the galaxy and the invasion of &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;, with the majority of Helldiver and SEAF forces being redirected to the galactic &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Front\"&gt;south&lt;/a&gt; to meet this new threat head on. Fortunately for the galaxy, they were successful and the Admiral Defense (AM) Factory Hub didn't need their protection after all, with construction being completed on the 17th of December. Production of &lt;a href=\"M-102%20Fast%20Recon%20Vehicle\"&gt;Fast Recon Vehicles&lt;/a&gt; (FRVs) for all Helldiver battlespaces was on schedule to begin within the following days and soon become available just in time to take part in the defense of &lt;a href=\"Genesis%20Prime\"&gt;Genesis Prime&lt;/a&gt; against another &lt;a href=\"illuminate\"&gt;illuminate&lt;/a&gt; incursion.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nAchernar Secundus, being left completely unattended due to the ongoing crisis in the southern sectors, would quickly be put under siege, as the Terminids advanced onto &lt;a href=\"Gatria\"&gt;Gatria&lt;/a&gt; and then Gar Haren. Things were looking pretty grim as the SEAF Garrison began to build up its defenses in preparation for a Terminid attack. However, the threat upon them would come from the last side anyone could have prepared them for.\nOn December 19th, shortly after the Illuminate raid at &lt;a href=\"Gemma\"&gt;Gemma&lt;/a&gt;, an Illuminate raiding party turned up on the planet's surface and began to attack the more urbanized settlements of the planet, aiming to plunder the resources and personnel that AM Defense had brought in order to build the multi-complex factory hub.\nFearing the worst, the Helldivers immediately deployed onto Achernar, in hopes that a victory over the Illuminate would not only prevent interruptions to AM Defense's vehicle production but also deter future Terminid incursions. This raid would only end in disaster for the Illuminate, as the Helldivers managed to succesfully repel the raid in less than 6 hours.\nTrivia.\nThe system bears the traditional name of Achernar (sometimes spelled Achenar), derived from the Arabic \u0622\u062e\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0647\u0631 \"\u0101khir an-nahr\", meaning \"The End of the River\".\nAchernar is the brightest star in the constellation of Eridanus and the ninth-brightest in the night sky.\nSecundus is the Latin word for \"second.\" However, it also had the meaning of \"favorable\" or \"lucky.\" It functions both as a proper name and a numeral title."}
