{"id": "5977", "revid": "56358", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5977", "title": "Achird III", "text": "Achird III is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Borgus%20Sector\"&gt;Borgus Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nAchird III is an arid, rocky planet featuring great shallow basins, sunken deserts, picturesque buttes and mesas, and rare verdant sections of valley. By and large though the planet is dominated by a series of continent mesas and plateaus, some of which are the size of skyscrapers. This has created an unexpected challenge for Helldivers operating on the planet, as this geography has been reported to obstruct some stratagems.\nIron minerals, and particularly hematite, are responsible for coloring the planet's sedimentary rock layers, which when combined with the planet's seismic instability has created large quantities of dust due to soil surface disturbance. This combined with strong winds has resulting in a fine layer of red dust that covers most of the planet which has also been known to clog up both unprotected machinery as well as lungs.\nThe majority of plant life on the planet consists of dry grasslands and shrub lands, with the arid nature of Achird III also driving the evolution of exceptionally efficient water usage in its various organisms.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Alcubierre-II.\nAchird III had been, up until September 2184, just another colony of Super Earth in which not many events worthy of remark had occured. During the early Terminid outbreak in February, the colonists at Achird III narrowly avoided devastation thanks to the Colonial Overseer's careful move of cutting their planet's FTL Line with Turing, which was under heavy attack from the Terminids. But, this move was not going to keep the colonists at Achird III safe forever.\nFrom February to September, the colonists at Achird III watched attentively how the war came at went from their doorstep at nearby Turing. But then, an unexpected surprise struck at them. On September 29th, neighboring Darius II would fall to a sudden Terminid attack from &lt;a href=\"Phact%20Bay\"&gt;Phact Bay&lt;/a&gt;. Then, during the early morning of September 30th, the Terminids hopped from Darius to Achird III, sending a massive attack in order to flank the SEAF defensive line at &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt; to try and attack the Xenoentomology Center at Turing.\nHowever, this attack would ultimately turn out unsuccessful, as the Helldivers managed to gather enough manpower to repel the Terminid assault under 12 hours.\nOperation Ring of Freedom.\nAchird once again came under attack shortly after announcement of Operation Ring of Freedom. Despite not being the target of the Major Order, its position as a stepping stone towards Turing made it obvious bugs would use it as staging ground for their next infestations. Helldivers mobilized enmasse to save this planet from facist incursion.\nDespite the importance, the defense was suffering from lack of reinforcements, as the majority of divers continued their work on Pandion XXIV. It was only during the early hours of October 12th, that divers begun to move towards Achird III, as more and more begun to realize the defense is possible. \nWith heroic fervor, Helldivers fought with guns and nails to save the world, eventually turning the tide of battle less than 2 hours before bugs amassed critical mass on the surface. With less than 8 minutes to spare, the \"Achird Miracle\" was declared with the chorus of Divers across the entire planet, as last nests were destroyed, and last bugs, slaughtered.\nThe defense of Achird III once again proved just how powerful liberty can become against the evils of tyranny. Super Earth High Command would commemorate the remarkable and admirable defense of the planet, stating that this level of high valor and bravery by the Helldivers had not been seen since much earlier in the Second Galactic War in the Battle of &lt;a href=\"Mort\"&gt;Mort&lt;/a&gt; against the . To all the soldiers who participated and gave their lives in the defense of Achird III, particularly into the nighttime and morning hours of the battle, this here stands as their recognition and commemoration of their service in the most high stakes of situations."}
