{"id": "5855", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5855", "title": "Alaraph", "text": " is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Akira%20Sector\"&gt;Akira Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Its landscape generally consists of dead, coral-like flora with the occasional purple parasitic flower growing on top of it, similar to &lt;a href=\"Penta\"&gt;Penta&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nivel%2043\"&gt;Nivel 43&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt;\nTopography.\nA cold, grey and rocky world with a nitrogen-oxygen atmosphere. Permafrost covers most of the surface except for the more temperate equatorial regions. The low temperatures cause evaporation of water to be slow. Much of the planet experiences seasonal rain and fog in the summers, as water gathers in bogs and ponds. A stable biosphere exists but vegetation is mostly limited to mosses, lichens and violet flowers seen on other primordial worlds.\nHistory.\nAlaraph is a unremarkable Super Earth colony on the outer fringes of the galactic rim."}
