{"id": "5987", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5987", "title": "Andar", "text": "Andar is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Akira%20Sector\"&gt;Akira Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Kerth%20Secundus\"&gt;Kerth Secundus&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nAndar was, ever since its colonization during the Great Democratization, a peaceful colony far off in the Southern Galactic fringe, without many events in its history being worthy of any mention.\nPresumably, Andar gained enough wealth at some point to build more urbanized settlements, with a grid of paved roads, pipes to carry drinking water, waste management services, an electrical power supply and most importantly, green grass lawns on which the citizens of Andar could proudly pitch their Super Earth Flags on for Liberty Day.\nHowever, an ancient enemy stared at this humble community from the darkness of space. The , envious of such calmness, would make a return after their banishing from the Milky Way at the end of the prior century. On December 18th, 2184, Andar and &lt;a href=\"Acubens%20Prime\"&gt;Acubens Prime&lt;/a&gt; would both be attacked simultaneously, as the Illuminate were conducting a series of raids across the southern sectors of the galaxy.\nHaving already defeated them at &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bellatrix\"&gt;Bellatrix&lt;/a&gt; and Kerth Secundus, the Helldivers rallied together to take on the alien invaders, determined to end this odious plundering of their fellow citizens' resources and the senseless bloodshed of Freedom-loving patriots."}
{"id": "3305", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3305", "title": "Andromeda Sector", "text": "The Andromeda Sector is a sector found on the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Front\"&gt;Western Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It contains 5 habitable planets. The sector gets it's name from \nAndromeda, the beautiful daughter of King Cepheus and Queen Cassiope of Joppa in Palestine (modern day Mega City 5) and wife of Perseus. Cassiope offended the Nereids by boasting that Andromeda was more beautiful than they, so in revenge Poseidon sent a sea monster to devastate Cepheus' kingdom. In the end, Andromeda was given a place amongst the stars by Goddess Athena."}
{"id": "3642", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3642", "title": "Angel's Venture", "text": "Angel's Venture is one of the seven planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Orion%20Sector\"&gt;Orion Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Whilst originally a sparsely populated world, the planet became a major training ground for the Super Earth Armed Forces following the official declaration of the Galactic War on Tyranny -- although this facility has since been shut down and turned into a campground for the Democratic Youth Scouts.\nAfter enduring tremendous suffering during Operation Enduring Peace, Angel's Venture now stands as the \"Heroic Diamond of the Orion Sector\"\nTopography.\nPossessing a boreal climate, Angel's Venture is chilly though not uncomfortably so. Continent-sized forests with towering trees and mountains cover vast tracts of land across surface of the planet, with mining, timber and agricultural products being its main exports.\nThe planet's lush green surroundings stand in stark contrast to the hideous rock-like hive structures of the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;. Initial estimates of the damage done by the bugs to the planet's ecosystem range anywhere between 20% and 60%, with conservation efforts being undertaken by Colonial Authorities to preserve and restore its remaining natural beauty.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations prior to the Second Galactic War.\nEarly Terminid Outbreaks.\nAngel's Venture was the epicenter of heavy fighting during the February Counter-Offensive, when it was engulfed in Terminid spores along with &lt;a href=\"Heeth\"&gt;Heeth&lt;/a&gt;. Though the colonial militias were initially overwhelmed, both planets were successfully defended from the fascist menace through the valiant efforts of the Helldivers.\nDisaster of Meridia.\nIn the late weeks of April and the first week of May 2184, &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; tragically became a Terminid Supercolony due to the failure of the &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Control%20System\"&gt;Terminid Control System&lt;/a&gt;. Though the rest of the TCS was quickly dismantled, massive outbreaks began on planets close to Meridia, Angel's Venture among them. The Helldivers were sent to these planets in order to contain the breach. While Angel's Venture, Heeth, and Veld were successfully defended, the containment operation was unsuccessful, as Acamar IV could not be cleansed.\nSecond Galactic War.\nThe Galactic War on Tyranny was officially declared on May 15, 2184 in response to hostile actions by the Terminids and the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;. Angel's Venture was selected as one of four planets (alongside neighboring Heeth, &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aesir%20Pass\"&gt;Aesir Pass&lt;/a&gt;) that would host SEAF Training bases in order to allocate the millions of voluntary conscripts that had selflessly rushed to service.\nOperation Emancipator.\nAngel's Venture would remain secured for a while, even being spared the worst horrors that the war brought onto other planets. However, that was not to be the end. Shortly after the loss of the Vernen Wells Forward Base, a Terminid assault put Angel's Venture under siege while the Helldivers rushed to free &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt; and its crucial \"Petrafactory\". Despite the diversion of manpower, the Helldivers managed to effortlessly repeal the Terminid assault on Angel's Venture \"and\" liberate Varylia 5, a typical show of the Helldivers' immaculate tactical skill and cunning.\nOperation Enduring Peace.\nAngel's Venture was relatively spared from most of the cruelties of the war for some time. It saw one or two assaults from the Terminids, but these were easily repelled by the SEAF. Shortly after Operation Emancipator was completed, new orders came in: the Helldivers were to hold Angel's Venture, Fenrir III and Turing in order to create a safe passage for &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;a new weapon&lt;/a&gt; that had been developed in order to permanently end the Meridia Supercolony. The skillful defense of Angel's Venture allowed the Helldivers to judiciously deploy this weapon across Meridia, resulting in its collapse into a black hole and ending the Supercolony once and for all.\nOperation Starslayer.\nWith emergency recruitment levels swelling ranks to targeted numbers, training throughput requirements have been reducing. In light of this change, the surviving emergency SEAF Training Facilities on &lt;a href=\"Heeth\"&gt;Heeth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt; were shut down and converted into recreational campgrounds for the Democratic Youth Scouts.\nOperation Courageous Exodus.\nDuring Operation Courageous Exodus, Angel's Venture, alongside &lt;a href=\"Cirrus\"&gt;Cirrus&lt;/a&gt; and the recently reconnected &lt;a href=\"Terrek\"&gt;Terrek&lt;/a&gt;, was chosen as one of the 3 sites from which millions of colonists, displaced by &lt;a href=\"the%20Gloom\"&gt;the Gloom&lt;/a&gt;, would be processed and relocated onto the Democracy Space Station in order for them to staff it. As such, this major order designated them as targets to be held throughout the duration of it.\nHowever, since the Terminids never got to any planets connected to Angel's Venture, it wouldn't see any need for protection, allowing its colonists to continue their daily democratic lives in unimpeded freedom."}
{"id": "3930", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3930", "title": "Anti-Air Emplacement", "text": "The Anti-Air Emplacement is an &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; tactical asset that disables the use of all &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle-1&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; in an area around the outpost. The location can be easily determined from their tracers as they engage &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle-1&lt;/a&gt; when it is called to deliver a strike nearby. Although &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle-1&lt;/a&gt; strikes can still be used in other areas of the map it is best to deal with these emplacements as soon as possible to regain the use of the valuable &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagems&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnti-Air Emplacements will have between two and four turrets. The emplacements can be near objectives and outposts, thus becoming a nuisance when engaging nearby structures and hostiles. Like outposts, it is also possible to find ammo and &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Samples\"&gt;samples&lt;/a&gt; at these locations. \nOddly enough, disabled &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle-1&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; slots are displayed in the same manner as if they were affected by a &lt;a href=\"Stratagem%20Jammer\"&gt;Stratagem Jammer&lt;/a&gt;. "}
