{"id": "5988", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5988", "title": "Asperoth Prime", "text": " is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Akira%20Sector\"&gt;Akira Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bore%20Rock\"&gt;Bore Rock&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Clasa\"&gt;Clasa&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nAsperoth Prime was a peaceful colony in the southern galactic rim, having been colonized after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; but without much other events to really highlight since. However, things weren't fated to remain in this state of calm stillness for much longer.\nOn December 21st, 2184, the launched an assault onto Asperoth, hours after their prior raid at &lt;a href=\"Elysian%20Meadows\"&gt;Elysian Meadows&lt;/a&gt; had begun. Even though the Helldivers had orders to secure the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt;, a contingent would divert to help repel the Illuminate raid at Asperoth Prime, hoping to prevent the plunder of its resources and guarantee the safety of its citizens."}
{"id": "4838", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4838", "title": "Assisted Reload", "text": "Assisted Reload or Team Reload allows a pair of &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; to make efficient use of certain . Crew-served weapons such as the Recoilless Rifle have a much faster fire rate when using assisted reload, even faster than two individuals handling their own weapons.\nAssisted reload requires a fairly high level of coordination between citizens. As such, training is provided on the nearest battlefield.\nHelldivers.\nCertain support weapons are delivered with a Support Kit backpack:\nThe backpack is capable of resupplying either weapon.\nHelldivers can request an assisted reload from a teammate carrying a Support Kit by using the 'Reload' button (X on the PlayStation) while standing next to them. This does not work, however, if the player needing an assisted reload is also carrying a Support Kit themselves. In this case, hitting 'Reload' will initiate the slow self-reload instead.\nBear in mind that the player who needs a reload must have the Recoilless Rifle weapon in their hands for another to be able to assist. The decrease in reload duration of over 80% means that taking advantage of this feature is extremely highly advised (as long as there are at least two Helldivers on the mission).\nHelldivers 2.\nCertain support weapons come with a dedicated ammo backpack:\nWhen another Helldiver carries the ammo backpack, they can press Interact ([E] on PC) to perform the Assisted Reload for a player using the weapon, when facing the gunner's right side. The loader will track the gunner's movement and stance, but can look around to spot for threats. The loader is responsible for refilling the backpack using loose supply containers, &lt;a href=\"Resupply\"&gt;Resupply&lt;/a&gt; Pods, or &lt;a href=\"Backpacks%23Supply%20Pack\"&gt;Resupply Packs&lt;/a&gt; provided by another player.\nEither player can break formation to use their other weapons, recommended when melee attackers infringe on your liberties.\nWhile a Helldiver may carry both weapon and backpack themselves, they forego the valor of assisted reload in exchange for being able to use their weapon independently. Should two Helldivers both carry the same support weapon and backpack, they can take turns performing assisted reloads for each other, with twice the ammo capacity.\nThe gunner can elect to carry a different backpack."}
