{"id": "5967", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5967", "title": "Aurora Bay", "text": "Aurora Bay is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It is the second planet in the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt; to have begun liberation since the Reclamation, allowing &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; to fight in the heart of Automaton territorry.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nAurora Bay wasn't a part of the war until April 9th, 2184, during The Reclamation being captured by the sociopathic &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; overnight. Previously thought to have been defeated, a disgusting, new fleet of &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; arrived via FTL Jump and completely took over the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt; entirely, undoing Liberty's work.\nAurora Bay could do nothing but watch in horror as the insidious toasters laid seige to SEAF Defenses and Communications to all nearby planets, and was subsequently captured in little less than an hour.\nOperation Crop Dust.\nNow deep within enemy territory, it was unable to feel the insurmountable light of Freedom again until December 5th, 2184, following the liberation of &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt;, after the failed &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders\"&gt;Major Order&lt;/a&gt; to find and destroy the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; Jet Brigade factories. All &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; operating on &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; fully retreated to Auorora Bay, like the cowards they are. But the now-liberated &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; allowed divers to FTL jump to Aurora Bay and begin liberation of the planet for the first time in the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, pursuing the retreating clankers, showing them the true meaning of freedom.\nSome Helldivers speculate if this planet could possibly yield any &lt;a href=\"FTL%20Lines\"&gt;FTL Lines&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;, and if the liberation of this planet could possibly lead to taking back &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;, crippling the pathetic Automaton's defenses."}
