{"id": "5943", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5943", "title": "Bashyr", "text": "Bashyr is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Gallux%20Sector\"&gt;Gallux Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;ministry of Science's&lt;/a&gt; galactic topography database previously listed Bashyr as a lifeless grey rock, who's surface was interrupted only by the violet flowers that grow from strange, parasitic outcroppings. However this has recently been discovered to be a mischaracterization, with the planet iactually being a \"Foggy Swamp\" planet similar to &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt;. This error has since been fixed.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nBashyr had been, for most of its democratically recorded history, a peaceful planet colony of Super Earth. Having been settled after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, Bashyr was a planet that was notoriously difficult to inhabit, as there was little fertile, stable land and too much bog and swamp to traverse.\nYet despite all of the difficulties, the colonists of Bashyr got to work, which eventually bore fruit in the form of pristine urbanized colonies that now cover Bashyr's surfaces. However, a race filled with envy stared from the depths of the endless abyss.\nThe , a race of aliens that had once tried and failed to defy humanity, had returned from their exile and was now waging war against Managed Democracy once more. On December 20th, Bashyr would fall prey to an Illuminate raid, being attacked alongside &lt;a href=\"Skaash\"&gt;Skaash&lt;/a&gt;. After the Helldivers had defeated these aliens at Achernar Secundus, they were decided to deliver another defeat onto them. As such, they immediately deployed onto Bashyr, determined to break these Illuminate invaders.\nHowever, the Helldivers at Bashyr could not fully repel the Illuminate invaders, as the force was split between Bashyr and Skaash. As the hours passed, Bashyr would be sidelined in favor of rescuing the front at Skaash in hopes of ending the Illuminate offensive as quickly as possible. While the defenses at Bashyr caved in, the Illuminate would be forced to retreat after the Helldivers destroyed their forces on Skaash, granting them victory."}
{"id": "3878", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3878", "title": "Behemoth", "text": "The Behemoth is a large, heavily-armored &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; that is a variation of the &lt;a href=\"Charger\"&gt;Charger&lt;/a&gt; that has more armor, and is easily distinguishable from the normal charger by its elongated horn/tusk like armor on its head. They are found as the &lt;a href=\"Elimination%20Target\"&gt;Elimination Target&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Medium difficulty&lt;/a&gt; or sometimes guarding the &lt;a href=\"Shuttle%20Bay\"&gt;Shuttle Bay&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Emergency%20Evacuation\"&gt;Emergency Evacuation&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs of update 1.000.400, Behemoths will now start spawning randomly in higher difficulties, alongside regular chargers."}
