{"id": "5989", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5989", "title": "Bellatrix", "text": "Bellatrix is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Guang%20Sector\"&gt;Guang Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Oshaune\"&gt;Oshaune&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draupnir\"&gt;Draupnir&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nBellatrix was an ancient colony of Super Earth from the very first days after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. Having been identified in times before Managed Democracy, it had always been a fixture in the charts of space navigators. However, with the ongoing war and the lack of FTL Travel Technology, it was unable to be settled until after the invention of the Alcubierre Drive and the victory of Super Earth over its alien enemies.\nOnce an inhabitable planet was identified in the Bellatrix system, some of the Federation's bravest took on the challenge of settling it and claiming it for the cause of Liberty, labouring its cliffs and grasslands for many solar cycles until, through their hard labor, the colonists of Bellatrix managed to earn enough wealth to build urbanized settlements with commodities such as working electricity, paved roads, working water and waste management and, most important of all, pristine grass lawns on which to pitch Super Earth Flags and Helldiver Memorials.\nHowever, an ancient foe lurked in the shadows, wishing to tear down all that which the children of Managed Democracy had so proudly built. The , blighted by their xenophobic hatred of humankind and blinded by their mystical fervor to their death space cult, could only writhe in envy as it watched such resplendent prosperity.\nOn December 17th, hours after they had devilishly plundered the colonies of &lt;a href=\"Genesis%20Prime\"&gt;Genesis Prime&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mog\"&gt;Mog&lt;/a&gt; off their resources and an important portion of its populace, they would initiate an invasion of Bellatrix's own settlements, decided to crush the object of their envy. However, they had stirred the righteous wrath of the Helldivers, who were now thirsting for retribution over their plundered compatriots.\nFor 12 hours, the Helldivers fought to the best of their ability in order to fend off the Illuminate invaders. After some 6 hours of combat, the Squ'ith raiders would be successfully repelled, preventing further damage to Bellatrix's beautiful settlements."}
{"id": "5694", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5694", "title": "Berserker", "text": "A primitive actualization of barbarity, the Berserker has CPUs in each chainsaw that are programmed to solve one problem: closing the space between saw and target as quickly as possible."}
{"id": "4653", "revid": "55039596", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4653", "title": "Beverages", "text": "\"The Ministry of Prosperity ensures every colony has access to the latest beverages, extending libationary ingenuity to all Super Earth's citizens.\"- Vending Machine interaction\"\nBeyond quenching thirst, beverages serve as crucial elements in enhancing the quality of life for all citizens of Super Earth. Especially on colony worlds, vending machines brimming with both soft drinks and alcohol are ubiquitous, serving to uplift the spirits of industrious colonists forging new paths on the frontier. Regrettably, the ravages of the Second Galactic War have rendered many of these machines defunct, leaving them dormant and unused.\nSoft Drinks.\nThe Ministry of Prosperity offers two prominent brands of soft drinks, namely A Taste of Freedom and A Taste of Democracy, each housed in distinct color-coded vending machines. Curiously, despite their branding differences, both machines seem to stock the same array of beverages.\nSome of the offered drinks include:\nWhile the precise flavors remain a mystery, Dr. Democracy is known to contain a blend of 17 seasonings and additives, leaving room for speculation regarding the contents of the other beverages.\nAlcohol.\nLike the abundance of vending machines, cases of alcohol are commonplace in colonial residences and extraction sites. Dominating the market is \"Democracy Drafts\" Premium Light Beer, though its labeling reads A Taste of Democracy, likely indicating an affiliation with the brand. The cases prominently display warnings advising against consuming the beverage while operating heavy machinery."}
{"id": "3346", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3346", "title": "Bile Spewer", "text": "The Bile Spewer is a moderately armored and sized &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Medium difficulty&lt;/a&gt; and higher. They appear to be the adult form and third of its fourth evolutionary periods following the &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Spitter\"&gt;Bile Spitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nursing%20Spewer\"&gt;Nursing Spewer&lt;/a&gt;, followed by the &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Titan\"&gt;Bile Titan&lt;/a&gt;.\nBile Spewers spit streams of highly corrosive acid called \"Bile\", which can slow down Helldivers and be extremely fatal if exposed to enough acid. \nSuper Earth propaganda claims that certain Terminids produce this Bile due to the exposure to the toxic runoff E-710 farms, but many believe that this strain of Terminids is the result of Super Earth genetically altering the Terminids to produce more E-710.\nOn Extreme difficulty and higher, Bile Spewers gain the ability to fire a mortar-like volley of bile into the air, increasing the Bile Spewer's range and lethality.\nAnatomy.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nVariations.\n&lt;a href=\"Nursing%20Spewer\"&gt;Nursing Spewer&lt;/a&gt;:\nThis variation of the Bile Spewer is believed to either be a sub-adult of the Bile Spewer, or a gravid female with abdomens bursting with eggs, easily identified via its yellow-orange coloring."}
{"id": "3849", "revid": "52407671", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3849", "title": "Bile Spitter", "text": "The Bile Spitter is an adolescent form of the &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Spewer\"&gt;Bile Spewer&lt;/a&gt; that can be found on &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Easy difficulty and higher&lt;/a&gt;.\nBile Spitters appear in small numbers within patrols, attacking using their claws and bile spit. The spit projectile can slow a &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver&lt;/a&gt; while slowly damaging them, and will explode if their abdomen is attacked, damaging nearby organisms."}
{"id": "3347", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3347", "title": "Bile Titan", "text": "The Bile Titan is a massive, heavily-armored &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; that appears to be the final growth stage of a &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Warrior\"&gt;Bile Warrior&lt;/a&gt;. They can be found on &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Challenging difficulty (4)&lt;/a&gt; as an &lt;a href=\"Elimination%20Target\"&gt;Elimination Target&lt;/a&gt; and begin to spawn naturally at &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Extreme difficulty (6)+&lt;/a&gt; and more frequently as difficulty increases.\nDespite its size, it can quickly catch up to &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt;, spewing its lethal bile onto them. Helldivers near it can also be crushed or speared by its hulking claws.\nWARNING: As the name implies, Bile Titans are massive. Though they can be destroyed, their death throes are no less dangerous than the attacks they unleash whilst alive; oftentimes a Helldiver who is unfortunate enough to find themselves underneath a Bile Titan as it is falling will most likely perish on the spot due to the massive weight crushing down on them."}
{"id": "3855", "revid": "56089012", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3855", "title": "Bile Warrior", "text": "The Bile Warrior is a lightly armored, medium-sized &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt;. It is a variant of the &lt;a href=\"Warrior\"&gt;Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, whose body appears to overproduce caustic chemicals like the &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Spitter\"&gt;Bile Spitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Spewer\"&gt;Bile Spewer&lt;/a&gt;, and is believed to be a sub-adult of the &lt;a href=\"Bile%20Titan\"&gt;Bile Titan&lt;/a&gt;. They can be recognized by a green bile sack on its underbelly, and they only appear on some missions of &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Challenging difficulty and higher&lt;/a&gt;. It has the same traits as the Warrior, but due to their unstable body chemistry, when they are killed, it will cause a small bile explosion that can severely injure a nearby Helldiver. It is recommended not to kill them at point-blank range."}
{"id": "6189", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6189", "title": "Biomes", "text": "Biomes.\nThere are 23 biomes in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; spread across 261 planets. Biomes determine many factors about operations for a Helldiver, such as what kind of armor to wear, what type of hazards to expect, and what type of strategy they should approach with.\nClick the dropdown boxes to see more detailed information about each biome.\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Acidic Desert=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Dense, toxic fumes from deep within the planet's crust seep out of cracks in the earth and coat the ground in a sickly haze.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Arctic= \n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Submerged in eternal winter, this world's frosty peaks glimmer in the light of its too-distant star.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Ashland=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"The lifeless grey of this planet is interrupted only by the violet flowers that grow from strange, parasitic outcroppings.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Beginner\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Barren Moon=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"A rocky, lonely moon with extremely valuable mineral deposits underneath the surface.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Beginner\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Copper Desert=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"The arid, rocky biome covering this world has driven the evolution of exceptionally efficient water usage in its various organisms.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Beginner\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n= Ethereal Jungle=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"This world teems with ethereal, boundless, and peculiar plant life that spreads silent and uninterrupted across its entire surface.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Foggy Swamp=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Squelching mud, twisting roots; the odor of rot and anarchy. A teeming, endless morass.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Experienced\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Frozen Boneyard=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Ice and moss-covered rock can be found across most of the surface of this planet.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Beginner\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nFrozen Moon\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Ice and moss-covered rock can be found across most of the surface of this planet.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate \n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Grassland=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Rocky outcroppings punctuate fields of tall grass in a planet dominated by misty highland terrain.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Beginner\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Ionized Grassland=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"A crimson algae has propagated wildly across this entire planet, coating its rocky hills with a constant red that masks the spilt blood of the heroes who defend it from tyranny.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Beginner\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Quake Desert=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"A desert planet prone to unpredictable and dangerous sand twisters.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Sandy Mesa=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"A blazing-hot desert planet, its rocky mesas are the sole interruptions to the endless sea of dunes\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Scorched Wasteland=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Scorching temperatures, high winds, and low precipitation cause a near-constant cycle of fires to sweep this planet, punctuated by short bursts of lush rebirth between infernos.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Experienced\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Shadowed Jungle=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"The strange subversion of photosynthesis that sustains the oddly-hued flora that flourishes on this planet remains an intriguing mystery to the Super Earth's greatest exo-biologists.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Experienced\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Sparse Jungle=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Abundant with life, this wet planet is covered in deep oceans, thick forests, and tall grasses.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Supercolony=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Entirely unforeseeable mutations from the Termicide led to hyper-accelerated bug growth on this planet, turning it into a Supercolony. It is corrupted beyond saving. The bugs infest every inch of it, down to the mantle, spawning trillions of spores every day.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: OPERATIONAL PRIORITY\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Swamp=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Tall, gnarled trees flourish across the surface of this forested world. Sunlight filters past dangling vines, to the saturated undergrowth below.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Intermediate\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Tundra=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"A perennially chilly climate has allowed short, colorful shrubs to flourish across this planet's surface.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: Beginner\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Biomes.\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Black Hole=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"This dark abyss is all that remains of the verdant paradise that was once Meridia. Its breathtaking forests and abundant resources were corrupted and destroyed by the Terminids, leaving no choice but to use Dark Fluid to destroy it completely. Now, this singularity remains as a memorial, reminding us all of the consequences of defying Freedom.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: SAFE\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=City=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Super Earth is the blinding beacon that shines the light of democracy through the stars. The sprawling heart that beats in time to mankind's quest of liberation. Here live the wealthy, important and proud. Here live those who have pulled themselves up by their bootstraps and achieved their dreams. Here live the citizens of Super Earth.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: UNKNOWN\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=Frozen Wasteland=\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Once the stronghold of the Cyborg traitors, Cyberstan is now ruled by the Automaton Legion.\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nOperational Experience Recommendation: UNKNOWN\n&lt;br&gt;\nTrivia.\n__NOEDITSECTION__"}
{"id": "5932", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5932", "title": "Blistica", "text": "Blistica is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Imber\"&gt;Imber&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"P%C3%B6pli%20IX\"&gt;P\u00f6pli IX&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nBlistica was, for most of its history since the First Galactic War, an unremarkable desertic planet, far off in the galactic fringe. For one reason or another, it was spared the horrors of the First Galactic War, since it does not appear in any records for the Gellert Sector, meaning that this planet probably wasn't able to be colonized until the end of the First Galactic War allowed Super Earth to attain the technology necessary to settle this planet.\nAs such, Blistica spent much of its time during the Second Galactic War forgotten by the light of Super Earth, as its remoteness and apparently lack of resources simply didn't merit the Federation's attention. But this relative freedom was also something that attracted the envy of the Federation's enemies.\nAfter the fall of Cyberstan in April 2184, the Gellert Sector had cut off what little FTL connections it had, leaving it essentially insulated from the war, with what little colonists remained being completely unaware of the ongoing chaos and bloodshed.\nHowever, this peace would be shattered without warning when, on October 28th, 2184, the Automatons mounted an offensive into the Gellert Sector, restablishing the downed FTL Supply lines from Yed Prior and &lt;a href=\"Zefia\"&gt;Zefia&lt;/a&gt; into both this planet and its neighbor Mintoria. Due to the then-Major Order asking the Helldivers to liberate &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;, coupled with efforts to liberate &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; in the Terminid front, very few Helldivers would join the defense of either Mintoria or Blistica, and the Automatons easily captured both planets by the next day. Since then, no liberation attempts have been made at either of the planets, with both remaining under the iron grip of the robots ever since.\nOn November 25th, 2184, &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt; would be attacked by the Automatons, and due to the Helldivers not prioritizing the planet's defense, it would fall 2 days later, which fully locked away access to both Blistica and &lt;a href=\"Mintoria\"&gt;Mintoria&lt;/a&gt;, ending their liberation campaign and locking them fully in the hands of the despotic socialist Automatons.\nOperation Crop Dust.\nOn December 5th, 2184, orders were given to liberate Blistica, along with &lt;a href=\"Mintoria\"&gt;Mintoria&lt;/a&gt; as-well as &lt;a href=\"Esker\"&gt;Esker&lt;/a&gt;, all of which are locked behind enemy lines. Such mentioned planets have been identified as being rich in salt-mines, which is needed in order to rectify the shortage of chlorine and finally commence the production of MD-8 Gas Mines and its requisition to all Super Destroyers. However, like Mintoria, all of Blistica's supply lines lead to Automaton space, and &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt; had to be liberated first in order to restart Blistica's liberation campaign and allow for its liberation. Following Zzaniah's liberation, the Automaton forces in the Gellert Sector had been sent on the run and what little had been left behind would concentrate on Blistica, preventing early liberation efforts from seeing much success.\nThese early delays, combined with the Helldiver Corps' focus on planets like Esker and Mintoria made it so that, by the time the main fleet finally reached Blistica, they would be unable to make progress towards its liberation in time to meet the operation deadline. While Operation Crop Dust failed, Blistica was still liberated by December 10th, successfully quashing the last remnants of the Automatons in the Gellert Sector."}
{"id": "6913", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6913", "title": "Booster", "text": ""}
{"id": "3589", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3589", "title": "Boosters", "text": "Boosters are bonuses that can be applied for duration of a mission, enhancing the abilities of and resources available to the Helldivers. Boosters are not single-use and can be used on every mission. Boosters can be unlocked on the various pages of &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbonds&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhile preparing to drop for a mission, players can equip a booster in the stratagem loadout screen. Each Helldiver can equip 1 booster. With a full squad, 4 unique boosters can be active at the same time, one for each Helldiver. A Booster applies the effect to all Helldivers, not just the one who has it equipped. If a Helldiver leaves the mission, the effect of the booster in their personal loadout ceases its effect. "}
{"id": "5586", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5586", "title": "Bore Rock", "text": " is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Falstaff%20Sector\"&gt;Falstaff Sector&lt;/a&gt;. This planet resides on the southern border with only one current FTL lines to the nearby planet of &lt;a href=\"Esker\"&gt;Esker&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nA veritable green maze, Bore Rock flora is dense and everpresent. Planet features frequent but small elevation changes from rocky hills into waterlogged channels and reservoirs. Helldivers should exercise caution, as the waters are treacherous. What from distance may look like ankle deep water, is in reality a very deep lake that one can very easy drown in mere seconds after stepping off from the shoreline. The planet is also dotted in ancient fossilized trees, some reaching far above the current tree line. Massive amounts of trees block sight, but due to sheer amount of them, they can be use as reliable cover.\nThis planet features a network of gas vents, located randomly throughout the surface. Yellowish in color and emiting a green smoke, any kind of fire or bullet ignites it, causing a fiery explosion in their proximity.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Falstaff &amp; Jin Xi Lockdown.\nHelldivers would set foot on Bore Rock for the first time during Operation &lt;a href=\"Falstaff%20Sector\"&gt;Falstaff&lt;/a&gt; &amp; &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi&lt;/a&gt; Lockdown, an operation in which many planets within the &lt;a href=\"Falstaff%20Sector\"&gt;Falstaff&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi&lt;/a&gt; sectors would experience sudden Terminid outbreaks arising from previous operations.\nBore Rock would be defended in two occasions on June 2184 without much incident occuring.\nOperation Glorious Xenocide.\nDuring Operation Glorious Xenocide, the Terminids at Esker would launch a third assault at Bore Rock, this time succeeding due to the Helldivers' prioritization of other liberation campaigns and their focus on culling as many Terminids as possible.\nOperation Benevolent Sanitation.\nAfter its fall on July 25th, Bore Rock would remain under Terminid control, mainly due to its isolation during that time since its only FTL Line was the one with Esker. However, Bore Rock's salvation would come from an unlikely source: &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt;, a neighboring planet in its sector which, up until August 6th, had isolated itself and cut all of its supply lines. However, once its SEAF Outer Reconnaisance Outposts were overrun and the distress beacons began to cite new Terminid strains, Super Earth immediately issued a Major Order calling for not just Socorro's defense, but for the establishment of a quarantine zone on both Esker and Bore Rock, which marked the planet for liberation.\nBore Rock would be liberated on August 10th, with pretty much no resistance from the Terminids, as they had been isolated away from the rest of the Terminid broods much like Bore Rock had been cut away from the FTL Network before.\nOperation Courageous Exodus.\nFollowing its final liberation in August, Bore Rock has remained under Super Earth control without much incident, as the Gloom would make the war shift south towards the Jin Xi Sector. During this time, Bore Rock would establish new FTL Lines with Erata Prime and Terrek, finally ending its dangerous reliance on Esker.\nHowever, Bore Rock wouldn't be completely safe as, on November 6th, the Terminids would launch a triple attack aiming to conquer it, alongside &lt;a href=\"Heeth\"&gt;Heeth&lt;/a&gt; and Esker. Since the operation's focus was the protection of Terrek, Cirrus and Angel's Venture, Heeth would be defended first. Then, with Bore Rock's immediate connection to Terrek at stake, the Helldivers would turn up in massive numbers to aid in the defense of the planet.\nHowever, it would be attacked one final time on November 8th, shortly after the victory at Crimsica. With this miscalculated blunder, the Helldivers would concentrate their forces on Bore Rock, the Terminids increasing their numbers soon after. For 20 hours, the battle carried on throughout the swamps and marshes of the planet as the Helldivers gave everything they had in order to drive the Terminids back into the Gloom. By November 9th, the assault had been repelled and the Terminids had been decisively defeated, their hatcheries collapsing and reducing the resistance levels of nearby planets.\nOperation Jetclipper.\nBore Rock would remain free of any attacks after November 9th, giving its colonists some respite. However, this freedom would be very shortlived as the Helldivers would be ordered away from the Falstaff sector in order to conduct an offensive against the Automatons. With their guard low, the Terminids launched an assault onto Bore Rock on November 28th. The Colonial Defenders would hold their ground, with small Helldiver contingents providing sporadic support. However, the defenses eventually cracked and Bore Rock would fall to the Terminids on November 30th.\nOperation Crop Dust.\nOn December 5th, 2184, Operation Crop Dust was ordered to all Helldivers. MD-8 Gas Mines needed chlorine, for which an odd disappearance of colonial labor had severely hindered the supply of, bottlenecking the production of the stratagem. In order to rectify that shortage, the Helldivers were ordered to liberate 3 planets identified to be rich in salt-- one of those being &lt;a href=\"Esker\"&gt;Esker&lt;/a&gt;, which was inaccessible due to the fall of Bore Rock 5 days earlier. In order to access Esker, the Helldivers needed to liberate Bore Rock. The fight ensued for the next day, with moderate resistance, and on December 7th, 2184, every bug nest was eradicated and Super Earth declared victory over Bore Rock, the light of liberty now embracing the swampy planet once more.\nOperation Wormhole Spaguetti.\nBore Rock would spend the following weeks recovering from its time under Terminid control. However, before long, they would be plunged right back into the heat of the conflict on December 23rd, as the Terminids that had captured Esker immediately went on to attack Bore Rock. However, this move would be poorly timed, as the Helldivers had just finished securing Erata Prime and &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt;, the 2 targets of the ongoing major order."}
