{"id": "4353", "revid": "54324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4353", "title": "CB-9 Exploding Crossbow", "text": "The CB-9 Exploding Crossbow is a unique weapon introduced in the &lt;a href=\"Democratic%20Detonation\"&gt;Democratic Detonation&lt;/a&gt; warbond. It functions as a repeating crossbow which fires exploding bolts.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe CB-9 is a \"silenced\" grenade launcher. The weapon is silent and, provided the shooter is not seen, enemies will have a hard time pinpointing the source of the shot. This can be useful for luring enemies into traps or to distract them, though the user should be warned this will put the enemies on alert making them more likely to spot Helldivers.\nThe weapon itself is very powerful, capable of taking out groups of clustered light infantry and is capable of killing most medium-armored enemies with a handful of shots."}
{"id": "6788", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6788", "title": "CQC-19 Stun Lance", "text": " \nThe CQC-19 Stun Lance is a Melee sidearm added with the Urban Legends update that can be purchased for Medals on Page 1 of the &lt;a href=\"Urban%20Legends\"&gt;Urban Legends&lt;/a&gt; Warbond.\nRole.\nLike its smaller counterpart, the &lt;a href=\"CQC-30%20Stun%20Baton\"&gt;CQC-30 Stun Baton&lt;/a&gt;, the Stun Lance replaces the Helldiver's sidearm to let the user get up close and personal. It is fully capable of stunning most enemies, locking them in a weakened state and unable to fight for a short moment, allowing the Helldiver to get some serious damage inflicted upon those unlucky enough to get within arms length. It has a long reach, allowing the user to make swift and safe stabbing motions to make quick work of chaff-type hostiles and harassing the higher tiered enemies. Damage examples using &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; as the constant, it can take an average of three hits to the body, or one straight to the head, to kill them.\nHelldivers should beware that swinging the lance will use a small portion of the users stamina, however it will not cause a slower swing speed or have less effects if the user's stamina bar runs out, allowing the user to keep swinging away."}
{"id": "6786", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6786", "title": "CQC-30 Stun Baton", "text": "The CQC-30 Stun Baton is a Melee sidearm added to the &lt;a href=\"Superstore\"&gt;Superstore&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Urban%20Legends\"&gt;Urban Legends&lt;/a&gt; update that can be purchased for Super Credits.\nRole.\nLike its larger counterpart, the &lt;a href=\"CQC-19%20Stun%20Lance\"&gt;CQC-19 Stun Lance&lt;/a&gt;, the Stun Baton replaces the Helldiver's sidearm to let the user get up close and personal. It may seem practically harmless at a distance, but its more than capable of taking on hordes of &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; in the right hands without the user getting a scratch. While it does less overall damage and has less range than the Stun Lance, the baton makes up for it by being significantly faster to swing and covering a wider area. The Helldiver swings the baton in a wide sweeping motion, allowing for multiple enemies to be hit at once. It can hit at least three to four Voteless on average at a single time, whereas each thrust of a Stun Lance can hit two at best.\nHelldivers are advised that swinging the baton will use a small portion of the user's stamina. If the user's stamina bar runs out, however, it will not cause a slower swing speed or have less effects, allowing the user to keep swinging away."}
{"id": "5953", "revid": "46883485", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5953", "title": "Calypso", "text": " is one of the four planets in the &lt;a href=\"Saleria%20Sector\"&gt;Saleria Sector&lt;/a&gt;. On December 12th, it was the first planet to be attacked by The in the Second Galactic War as well as the first planet upon which they tasted defeat for the first time in a century.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Fori%20Prime\"&gt;Fori Prime&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt;, being a primarily arid and rocky world with an environment that has driven the flora and fauna to become extremely water efficient.\nA long time colony of the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, Calypso is a highly developed colony by the standards of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Expansion\"&gt;Ministry of Expansion&lt;/a&gt;, with urban centers both large and small being found across much the planets surface. Unfortunately this large population has just meant more citizens for the cursed to take freedoms away from, transfiguring them into little more than cannon fodder in the Squ'ith war machine.\nCalypso's pre-invasion invasion cities were a mixed sprawl of suburban housing developments and mixed-use buildings. Helldivers deployed to Calypso quickly learned that urban warfare is very different from conventional combat in the open which they are used to out on the sparsely developed &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;eastern&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Western%20Front\"&gt;western&lt;/a&gt; fronts. A battle which was not only up close, but also much more personal.\nTight streets, visibility-obstructing buildings, Illuminate lightning traps, and variations in height advantage are just some of the perils Helldivers faced against the Illuminate invasion. Many a helldiver have run down an alleyway to escape a &lt;a href=\"harvester\"&gt;harvester&lt;/a&gt; only to run headlong into a horde of &lt;a href=\"voteless\"&gt;voteless&lt;/a&gt;. In addition, whilst the steel an concrete constructions that made up Calypsos' buildings could be knocked down with sufficient ordinance (or direct impact from a ) even a bomb-shattered ruin could pose a major obstacle for either side. Fortunately Calypso's cities also possessed many &lt;a href=\"SEAF\"&gt;SEAF&lt;/a&gt; facilities, including &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20Artillery\"&gt;Artillery emplacements&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20SAM%20Site\"&gt;SAM Sites&lt;/a&gt; which proved devastating for the illuminate &lt;a href=\"Warp%20Ship\"&gt;Warp ships&lt;/a&gt;. Each city also possessed significant stockpiles of ammunition, medical supplies and weapon caches, which proved to be a major boon for the SEAF defenders.\nIn stark contrast to the urban sprawl, the terrain beyond Calypso's walled Cities is a mostly arid frontier, consisting of massive dust dunes and rocky canyons that shelter thorny shrubs -- breaking up the otherwise bleak and lifeless wasteland. Shrouded in endless dawn and dust, red sands cake every inch of this untamed land, with dust constantly whirling in the air causing constant visibility issues. Compounding this is the planets rotation, which makes a proper day-night cycle is near impossible. Combined with the dust, skies are often either shrouded in hues of red and orange, while what little daylight does reach the surface reveals the copper oxidization taking hold in the sky as it turns a tealish-green -- creating an aurora borealis effect.\nNotably in depressions in the ground there can be found pools of steaming and filthy ground water creating expansive mud marshes that slow movement considerably. It should be noted however that neither the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Expansion\"&gt;Ministry of Expansion&lt;/a&gt; have clarified yet whether these pools are created by naturally occurring springs being fed by natural underground springs or industrial runoff from nearby cities. In addition to the above mentioned points, the planet also suffers from considerable geological instability.\nFrequent continental shifts results in frequent tremors that can cause entire regions to shake anywhere from several seconds to almost a minute, causing dust to be hurled into the air after the brief periods it is allowed to settle. As a result, most buildings have been reinforced to handle these frequent earthquakes and locals are generally used to such quavers from their home planet. However it has been noted by many Helldivers that being robbed of higher thought by the Squ'ith has done a number on the ability of the &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; to balance themselves, locking them in place when these tremors hit... usually.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nCalypso was a peaceful planet colony in the Saleria Sector much like its neighbors, having been settled at some point after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, becoming a highly developed urban world. Additionally thanks to the planet's distance from both the eastern and western fringes, Calypso would avoid the worst of the second galactic war, at least for most of the first year of active fighting at least.\nDuring November of 2184, rumors from the frontier filtered back to Super Earth that colonists were going missing. Although the loss of some brave frontiersmen to untamed local fauna, poisonous flora and rugged wilderness is to be expected on furthest frontiers, the sheer number of missing people was enough to grab the attention of the wider federation, with Strohmann News running a story on the disappearances. However these disappearances were quickly assumed to be because of adventurous comic books encouraging more reckless behavior -- an assumption that would cost the federation, humanity and most of all managed democracy dearly.\nCalypso's peace would come to a bloody end when a foe long thought defeated revealed themselves to the galactic stage. On December 12th, an event long thought completely impossible occurred.\nThe , a race of sapient cephalopod humanoids that had once defied Super Earth during the First Galactic War and been banished from the Milky Way after their defeat, revealed themselves to have to have returned to the galaxy. Though how and why they have returned is not currently known, what is clear is that they intend to wage war on humanity once more.\nThe ongoing Operation Bughammer would be immediately aborted by High Command, as LIBCON 1 was issued to all available members of &lt;a href=\"SEAF\"&gt;SEAF&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver Corps&lt;/a&gt; -- all of whom were immediately directed to Calypso. Although the Helldiver's lacked the support of the DSS thanks to suspected sabotage, over 100,000 Helldiver &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyers&lt;/a&gt; transferred immediately to Calypso and began deployment onto its urbanized areas, with the number rising as high as 170,000 throughout the day. With valiant courage, they put down the hordes of &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; citizens that the odious aliens had abducted out of their undemocratic misery and stared down the waves of &lt;a href=\"Overseer\"&gt;Overseers&lt;/a&gt; and Walking &lt;a href=\"Harvester\"&gt;Harvesters&lt;/a&gt;, even in the face of their Obliteration beams.\nHowever despite having the largest force assembled by the Super Earth Armed Forces since the final liberation of &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt; behind them, the enemy numbers and strength were far greater than any seen thus far, with SEAF Analysts putting the strength and Defense Condition for the invading Squ'ith fleet at around level 96 -- the highest for any single invasion seen to date, 38 levels stronger than the previous largest invasion fleet, the &lt;a href=\"Automatons%23Jet%20Brigade\"&gt;Jet Brigade&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt; which was noted as a level 58 defense condition. Additionally, the majority of Helldivers in active service had been called up for and only participated in the Second Galactic War, meaning that most of them lacked experience against this old enemy.\nHowever as with many things: The Light of Liberty graced our Federation once more. Despite the lack of knowledge combating the Illuminate (as well as the servers of the GWW struggling to coordinate so many Helldivers on one planet) the over 150,000 active Helldivers present on Calypso were able to hold the planet against all odds, with exactly 8 minutes and 59 seconds to spare before &lt;a href=\"SEAF\"&gt;SEAF&lt;/a&gt; defenses collapsed entirely. This would be marked as one of the closest any planet has been saved before defense collapse in the war so far, with only the defense of &lt;a href=\"Achird%20III\"&gt;Achird III&lt;/a&gt; against the being a closer race with under 5 minutes left on the deadline.\nWith the resurgent Illuminate repelled by the Helldivers, order was quickly restored on Calypso and victory finally declared on the 16th of December, 2184. Super Earth High Command immediately launched an investigation and assessed that a small cell of the Illuminate forces survived their eradication at the end of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, staying hidden until now. Recent Democratic activity may have made their discovery imminent, precipitating the recent attack.\nThe shocking invasion of Calypso left colonies in ruins. Thousands remain unaccounted for, with multiple units reporting human-like combatants on the battlefield, with investigations into these reports of '&lt;a href=\"voteless\"&gt;voteless&lt;/a&gt;' ongoing. Yet despite the audacity of this shocking and unprovoked assault, the Helldivers once again proved their unmatched martial prowess.\nWith the enemy retreating in defeat, SEAF recon units were dispatched to hunt down any remnants left behind in their retreat, with orders to eradicate them as soon as they are located. Whilst Helldiver Corps may have suffered over 38 million casualties during the 3 day long defense of Calypso -- for comparison, 27 million Helldivers were killed in 9 weeks on &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt; -- the illuminate would suffer much more with over three billion kills confirmed by SEAF. However it should be noted that the vast majority of these casualties are the mind controlled &lt;a href=\"voteless\"&gt;voteless&lt;/a&gt;, with actual Squ'ith casualties being around five million. Even so, it should also be remembered that this is still a high price to pay for a species on the verge of extinction."}
