{"id": "4882", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4882", "title": "Charbal-VII", "text": "Charbal-VII is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt;. This planet was theorized to be on path of &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; attempting to reach &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; from their once existing position in &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Officially, the Second Galactic War arrived to this planet on\nTopography.\nThe planet is covered in brown rocks and sand, stained yellow from the constant acidic environment. The skies are dense and dark and stained a teal color. Many mushroom shaped mountains and hilly structures cover the landscape, with rough flatter land in between. The lowlands are often filled with acid filled craters and terraced lakes. &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; should be aware of the threats posed by low visibility, acid rain, and potential drowning risks.\nThe Cavern of Death is a natural bottleneck on the northern eastern side of Charbel-VII, it sits in the lowlands section of the planet to the right side of a Major Automaton Command Bunker. It is infamous for its extremely high amount of deaths associated with its drastic change of combat. In the lowlands, the planet offers a dune-like topography with minimal visibility, often cloaking the Cavern of Death with a acidic haze which attributes to its high death count. \nThe Cavern of Death is less than a quarter mile in length, and about 8ft wide at its shortest point. Its walls from right to left stand almost 30 feet high. Many helldivers have succumbed to death within the Cavern, given the rapid change in combat conditions, as its drastic change to extreme CQB combat is not common for the planet as a whole. While it does have a secondary exit point directly east, its incline is incredibly steep, slowing down any attempt to escape.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan (April 2184).\nCharbal-VII was attacked by small automaton invasion force on early hours of April 22nd, 2184. Helldivers were by then split between besieged &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Choepessa%20IV\"&gt;Choepessa IV&lt;/a&gt; together with Liberation of &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;The Wells&lt;/a&gt;. With decision being made that Charbal is of low priority, only small detachment of Divers stayed and assisted SEAF. Planetary forces were overwhelmed the next day.\nOperation Righteous Expunge (July 18th - July 21st).\nLight of Liberty has returned to this part of Andromeda Sector on July 20th. The encircled Automatons without any material support from Cyberstan, were not able to push back our forces, making every gain permanent. With last socialist gone on evening of July 20th, Helldivers redeployed to last target of operation - Choepessa IV."}
{"id": "3348", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3348", "title": "Charger", "text": "The Charger is a large, heavily armored &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; that can first appear on &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Medium difficulty&lt;/a&gt; as an &lt;a href=\"Elimination%20Target\"&gt;Elimination Target&lt;/a&gt; or sometimes guarding the Shuttle Bay in &lt;a href=\"Emergency%20Evacuation\"&gt;Emergency Evacuation&lt;/a&gt;. It spawns naturally and more frequently as difficulty increases.\nIt is unclear where the Charger fits in the Terminid's life cycle, but it is believed that when &lt;a href=\"Hive%20Guard\"&gt;Hive Guard&lt;/a&gt; reaches a certain age or some other environmental pressure, it will molt into a Charger. The head crest of the Charger is very similar to that of an , only smaller. This leads some to believe that Super Earth genetically altered the Impaler Terminid strain to make them less dangerous, which they both succeeded in and failed.\nLiving up to their name, Chargers charge at Helldivers in an attempt to bash or trample them, dealing a significant amount of damage. This can concuss and potentially launch Helldivers. Chargers will also use their claws at close range.\nVariations.\n&lt;a href=\"Behemoth\"&gt;Behemoth Charger&lt;/a&gt;: has more armor and is easily distinguishable from the standard charger by its elongated horn/tusk-like armor on its head.\n&lt;a href=\"Spore%20Charger\"&gt;Spore Charger&lt;/a&gt;: a bile form of the charger and has a cloud of fog around it. It has more weak spots than a normal charger."}
{"id": "4409", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4409", "title": "Charon Prime", "text": "Charon Prime is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Ingmar\"&gt;Ingmar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ubanea\"&gt;Ubanea&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nCharon Prime had been a peaceful planet colony of Super Earth for around a century after the First Galactic War, its colonists thriving among the lush fields of its distinct crimson algae. However, the Automatons, programmed to destroy Democracy and hate freedom, would prove incapable of appreciating their lifestyle.\nOn April 3rd, a mere 2 days after their righteous extermination after the victory at &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;, the Automatons returned with a massive fleet, larger than the one seen months before. From deep space, they would first take over the Valdis Sector and conquer Cyberstan, then would begin to slowly spread their filthy mechanized socialism all over the Western Galactic Rim, one planet at a time.\nWhile the Helldivers had managed to stop the Automaton advance at the &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;-&lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt; Line, the Automatons had decided to push southwest, towards the location of their previous occupations. After switfly capturing Matar Bay and Martale, the Automatons lunged at Charon Prime while the Helldivers, now split between the crisis produced by the failure of the TCS Towers and the Automaton invasions, were occupied defending other planets. Charon's colonial defenses put up an excellent fight, but would inevitably collapse to the robotic onslaught, allowing Charon Prime to be occupied and allowing the Automatons to spread towards the Trigon Sector through Choepessa IV and into Charball-VII, from where they'd later attempt a return into the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nOperation Andromeda.\nCharon Prime would remain occupied from May to July, with the Helldivers unable to help it and its colonists having to resist their socialist occupiers for months in order to avoid capture (and, almost assuredly, guaranteed execution). It seemed that all hope was lost but, as Liberty would have it, a chance would glimmer from the horizon.\nAfter a series of key victories at &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt; and the Xzar Sector, the Automatons' iron grip upon their odious fief, now spanning a vast expanse of planets from Vandalon IV to Merga IV, had revealed itself as a great weakness against the righteous, steadfast force that were the Helldivers, unshakeable in their convictions despite all the adversities they had faced so far. With this weakness fresh in the mind, Super Earth High Command would issue an order asking for the capture of &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;, Martale, &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt; and the recently fallen &lt;a href=\"Aesir%20Pass\"&gt;Aesir Pass&lt;/a&gt;, said planets being in a line formation that could split the bot forces in half, leaving all of their western domain disconnected and ripe for liberation.\nAfter successfully liberating Aesir Pass on the 14th, Matar Bay on the 15th and Marfark at the early hours of the 16th, Martale would be captured right before the midnight of July 17th, successfully severing the Automaton Forces in half, leaving the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda&lt;/a&gt; Sectors completely disconnected from Cyberstan, which would cripple the garrisons in all of their planets, leaving them unable to reverse any progress done towards their liberation.\nOperation Righteous Expunge.\nThe campaign to liberate Charon Prime began immediately after the liberation of Martale and, shortly after, Super Earth High Command would issue a major order for its liberation, alongside with Choepessa IV and Charbal-VII. On the midnight of July 18th, Charon Prime would be liberated."}
{"id": "6612", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6612", "title": "Chemical Agents", "text": "Chemical Agents, released on September 19, 2024, is the seventh Premium &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbond&lt;/a&gt; available in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. Like the other Premium Warbonds, it has three pages and cost 1000 &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Super%20Credits\"&gt;Super Credits&lt;/a&gt; to unlock.\n&lt;br&gt;\nto Unlock All Pages\nto Complete Warbond\nPAGE 1.\n&lt;br&gt;\nPage 2.\n&lt;br&gt;\nPage 3.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "4585", "revid": "46883485", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4585", "title": "Choepessa IV", "text": "Choepessa IV is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nChoepessa IV is a cold, desolate graveyard of colossal bones and moss-covered rock which covers most of the surface of this planet. However, geological and historical record indicates that the climate of this world was not always so bleak and that one hundred years ago during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, Choepessa IV was a lush jungle world covered in vibrant vegetation and large bodies of liquid water.\nDuring the first war, the planet was overrun by the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;, but thanks to the valiant efforts of the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; the planet was not only liberated but also blessed with large deposits of element E-710 which can still be found buried under its surface to this day.\nHowever in the century between the first Galactic War and the second, the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; has noted a rapid shift in the planet's climate from tropical humidity to sub arctic. This has been caused by a chain reaction of positive feedback triggered by periodic changes in the planets orbit around the systems star, and the occlusion of the sun for a lunar cycle due to debris from orbital bombardment, which has rapidly changed the planets climate. Less sunlight reaches the northern latitudes. Temperatures dropped and more water froze into ice, expanding the polar glaciers which reflected more sunlight and cooled the planet even further. The whole planet \u2014 including it's oceans \u2014 froze over, killing off 98.7% of native plant and animal life.\nIn layman's terms, Choepessa IV is going through a completely natural ice age, one which is totally unrelated to resource extraction and manufacturing operations by the human colonies on the planet, and aforementioned lunar cycle without direct sunlight, naturally.\nHistory.\nFirst Galactic War.\nLiberation of Choepessa IV.\nNot much is known about Choepessa IV during the First Galactic War. It used to be a planet with tropical jungles, volcanoes and large bodies of water and, inevitably, the Bugs would spread to it and overrun it, leaving massive deposits of E-710 underneath its surface that, once the Helldivers had contained the Bug outbreak, would be exploited by Super Earth Colonists. However, in the years after the conflict in 2084, Choepessa IV's orbit around its eponymous sun began to change, which led to a quick shift from a tropical climate to a permanent sub-arctic one, which triggered a glaciation and froze over virtually all organic life on the planet, leaving it a snowy, barren wasteland.\nAccording to the description of the \"Purifying Eclipse\" cape, so much orbital ordnance was used on during the liberation of the planet that the resulting cloud of debris and ash would occlude its sun for an entire lunar cycle (around a super-month). No doubt this heavy bombardment that caused the planet's orbit to shift, as well as turn the once lush jungle world covered in vibrant vegetation into a frozen boneyard that few now tread.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Reclamation of Cyberstan.\nChoepessa IV had remained a peaceful planet for more than 100 years, even as neighboring planets such as &lt;a href=\"Ustotu\"&gt;Ustotu&lt;/a&gt; had fallien prey to the initial Automaton Expeditions. However, peace was not to last. Shortly after Operation Swift Disassembly concluded, a large Automaton Fleet conquered Cyberstan and the rest of the Valdis Sector, reigniting the conflict on the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Front\"&gt;Western Front&lt;/a&gt;. The SEAF scrambled as planets fell to the robotic tide, with Choepessa falling shortly after the Menkent Line had been established.\nWhile it had not yet been lost, mostly thanks to the combined efforts by the Helldivers and the remaining Colonial Defenses, Choepessa IV would become stuck in an asymmetric, low-intensity liberation campaign, as the Helldivers have had to constantly divert resources and attention away from it, and from the Automaton Front at large.\nOperation Emancipator.\nShortly after, Choepessa IV would be a launching pad for the Automatons' attempt at reclaiming their old position, as from it, they would launch an assault into Varylia 5, then onto Ustotu and the rest of the Trigon Sector. While the fall of the Trigon Sector was unable to be prevented, the Helldivers managed to secure the Petafactory in Varilya 5, temporarily preventing the complete takeover of the sector.\nOperation Valiant Resistance.\nThe victory at Varylia 5 would then launch the Helldivers onto another victory at nearby Wasat. However, while they were occupied with the retrieval of Database One, the bot garrison on Choepessa IV sent a second assault onto Varylia 5, which would be held off successfully. Then, as the Helldivers returned to their rearguard at &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt; to heroically rescue trapped children, the Automatons then launched a third assault that would succeed due to the lack of proper defenses.\nFrom here, the Automatons would reinforce their garrison at Ustotu and take over &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt;, completing their odious settlement of the Trigon Sector, as now they had very much secured Vandalon IV. \nOperation Righteous Expunge.\nChoepessa IV would remain behind the southern Automaton Vanguard safely from June to Mid July 2184, when the Helldivers would successfully capture &lt;a href=\"Aesir%20Pass\"&gt;Aesir Pass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;; which sat right in the middle of a defensive line of planets going from &lt;a href=\"Curia\"&gt;Curia&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt;, the former being a fortified Super Earth forward base and the latter having been secured alongside &lt;a href=\"Meissa\"&gt;Meissa&lt;/a&gt; during Operation Starslayer. This strategic victory would instantly send all of the Automaton garrisons in the Ymir, Trigon and Andromeda into disarray, rendering them unable to defend themselves against the righteous Helldivers.\nSuper Earth High Command, with time running out and with the momentum behind them, issued a major order for the liberation of Choepessa IV, alongside with Charbal-VII and Charon Prime. The first planet to be liberated was Charon Prime. Then, Charbal-VII followed. And finally, on July 21, with few hours to spare, Choepessa IV would be liberated, allowing for further liberation throughout the encirclement area."}
{"id": "4139", "revid": "54761251", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4139", "title": "Choohe", "text": "Choohe is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Lacaille%20Sector\"&gt;Lacaille Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Choohe is the gateway to &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt; and beyond, with the securing of the planet being vital to open a frontline into &lt;a href=\"Aurora%20Bay\"&gt;Aurora Bay&lt;/a&gt; and, by extension, the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It was on this planet when, on October 13th 2184, the Automaton Jet Brigade was first sighted.\nTopography.\nChoohe's landscape is typical of a desert planet on the outer fringes of Federation space, comparable to similar planets like &lt;a href=\"Durgen\"&gt;Durgen&lt;/a&gt;. Blazingly-hot, its rocky mesas are the sole interruptions to the endless sea of dunes which cover it's entire surface. Whilst they usually last only a few minutes, Choohe's massive sandstorms kick up large amounts of blinding, choking sand which obscures the vision of man and machine alike. Blinding local SEAF and Helldiver forces whilst also confusing the sensors of the invading &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe Socialist War Machines have taken advantage of Mesa formations to build their bases on high ground with clear lines of sight. However these same rocky formations also provide much needed cover for assaulting Helldivers.\nThe only true life to be found on this sand trap planet were the small but hardy verity of Desert scrub and the just as hardy human colonists of Super Earth, who were all massacred by the socialist machines in their bio-processors.\nEver since its conquest, the robotic scourge has turned this planet into an important foundry from which they launch their nefarious war machines onto the galaxy, the Jet Brigade standing as the most hideous of them all.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nBy April 2184, Choohe was just another desert planet colony of Super Earth like many others across the Federation, with nothing worthy of note in its record. However, this peace would be quickly shattered by a previously unseen foe.\nDespite a valiant resistance, SEAF forces were defeated and ultimately forced to abandon the planet during the early phases of Enduring Bulwark. The planet's fall opened up FTL lanes to &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;, making it's loss all that much harder to bare.\nOperation Legitimate Undertaking.\nYet despite the Automaton's unjust and brutal occupation, the loyalty and bravery of Super Earth's surviving citizens shined through. Despite being trapped on Choohe, they were able to test a new Fortification System, vital to the survival of the federation: &lt;a href=\"MD-17%20Anti-Tank%20Mines\"&gt;MD-17 Anti-Tank Mines&lt;/a&gt;. These mines are designed to destroy heavily armored vehicles such as walkers and &lt;a href=\"Tank\"&gt;tanks&lt;/a&gt;, something desperately needed halt the Automaton's armored spearhead. However with Automaton's closing in on the last survivor enclaves of both Choohe and &lt;a href=\"Penta\"&gt;Penta&lt;/a&gt;, time is running out for surviving personnel and equipment for both planets.\n&lt;a href=\"Penta\"&gt;Penta&lt;/a&gt; would be liberated first, securing it's stores of caustic chemicals and experimental air-burst rocket launchers. Unfortunately the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;, in their calculated oppression and hardwired avarice, have stymied our valient efforts to liberate &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt;. The loss of the indispensable explosives on the planet will mean significant delays to the production of Anti-Tank Mines. The explosive technicians on &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; have almost certainly been torn to pieces by the vicious blades of the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;. All will agree that every possible resource was directed towards their salvation. Their sacrifice is hereby honored.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Jet Brigade.\nChoohe would remain under Automaton occupation ever since its failed liberation in April, as the robots used its location to pivot westward, flanking the Menkent line and managing to expand all the way to &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt; before being split in two and severely defeated during Operation Andromeda in July 2184. With this operation, Choohe would find itself back on the frontlines of combat. However, its months under Automaton occupation had rendered it into a horrid foundry of mechanized tyranny, with the Automatons having heavily fortified the planet, which made it very difficult to liberate it.\nHowever, this foundry of terror would not show its nefarious tricks until October when the Automatons unleashed their new abominations onto the galaxy: The Jet Brigade, a hideous metallic chimera force made out of stolen SEAF jet packs and plundered metal from across their odious fiefs, welded together with the suffering of all the innocent, oppressed human colonists beneath their iron foot.\nThis horrendous enemy force would go on to violently reconquer Matar Bay and, after that, &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;, killing many righteous Helldivers before they were finally stopped at the heroic defense at &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt; on October 22nd.\nOperation Jetclipper.\nFollowing the apparition of the Jet Brigade, Choohe remained a target of interest for Super Earth Tactical Command, as many in the Helldiver Corps believed that Choohe, being the staging ground from where the Jet Brigade first appeared, was directly linked to the factories at which the Jet Brigade units were being assembled by the socialists.\nFollowing this hunch, Super Earth High Command would take a bold risk and issued a major order, tasking the Helldivers with liberating Choohe and killing 150,000,000 Automatons, as they believed that there could be intel hidden in any of the CPUs of any Automaton, meaning that it was statistically probable that they would find clues regarding the Jet Brigade's factories once they managed to find this figurative needle in the robotic hay stack.\nHowever, things would soon take an interesting turn as, within a day of Choohe capturing Matar Bay and, therefore, preventing any access to the SEAF, the Helldivers voted Choohe as the next DSS Target Planet, upon which it would cast an Orbital Blockade, marking the first instance in which the DSS was not accompanied by the Helldiver Corps.\nThe only company that the DSS would get would be a stranded Helldiver force of 629 Super Destroyers. While their efforts would not accomplish much progress towards Choohe's liberation, their bravery in the face of insurmountable odds is nothing but exemplary of the ways of Super Earth.\nThe DSS would leave Choohe, going back to Matar Bay to help with liberation efforts.\nThe real fighting would begin on December 2nd, after Matar Bay was liberated. The Helldivers would deploy en masse, deploying up to 63% of the entire corps at the time, with up to 26,000 Super Destroyers in orbit. Despite this, progress on Choohe was slow, for it had been severely reinforced by the Automatons during the many months it spent under their occupation. Combined with rogue platoons of Helldivers diverting towards other, non-essential planets, the campaign for Choohe looked increasingly grim as time wore on.\nOperation Jetclipper would be regarded as a failure, as Choohe was only at 85% liberated at the deadline's expiration. With the Major Order over, Helldivers would slowly redeploy to other planets, until a Terminid attack on &lt;a href=\"Terrek\"&gt;Terrek&lt;/a&gt; on late afternoon on December 4th, drained the remaining forces for defense. According to Ministry of Defense statistics, Liberation of Choohe was abandoned at around 90%, as remaining garrison was not able to stop the automaton counterattack. Yet there remains a slither of hope still, as Helldivers begun massive in between action of communicating the importance of finishing the proper campaign.\nHowever, despite the failure of operation Jetclipper, the Helldivers persisted on Choohe, managing to liberate it by the afternoon of December 5th, after the Automatons withdrew to Aurora Bay.\nFor the first time in several months, Choohe was free from the odious grip of the Automatons."}
{"id": "4142", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4142", "title": "Chort Bay", "text": "Chort Bay is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Lacaille%20Sector\"&gt;Lacaille Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\n\"Chort\" is a Slavic language term for a devil or imp, which given the topography of the planet is appropriate. The planet is covered by a sickly moor, characterized by it's high temperatures and abundant toxic fumes, which seep up from the planets crust. \nAcid storms regularly sweep the planets rocky surface, reducing visibility and leaving behind abundant pools of acidic water, which whilst not acidic enough to burn through a &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; uniform, are unlikely to be safe for human consumption (bottled water is recommended for long deployments). Some hardy plant life does somehow survive on the planet, though certainly not thrive, with only some sparse grasses and shrubbery managing to cling to life. \nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nFighting began on Chort Bay on April 9th when Automaton forces arrived from an unknown location by FTL jump. Chort Bay was initially a frontline planet, but did not see heavy action. The planet was in full Automaton control following the Helldiver retreats later in April, but became a major battleground on April 27th-28th. Helldiver forces assaulted the planet following the liberation of Penta, all part of Operation Legitimate Understanding. Chort Bay is the gateway to the world Choohe, which is the objective of this offensive. Despite fierce enemy resistance, the barren planet is being retaken very quickly. "}
{"id": "5196", "revid": "54761251", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5196", "title": "Cirrus", "text": "Cirrus is one of the seven planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Orion%20Sector\"&gt;Orion Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Nivel%2043\"&gt;Nivel 43&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Enduring Peace.\nCirrus had been spared the majority of the horrors that had ensued throughout most of the Special Military Operations from February to April 2184, as well as the beginning of the Second Galactic War in the first 2 weeks of May 2184. However, peace was not to last. The fascistic Terminids, helped by their horrid Supercolony at nearby &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt;, would launch a surprise attack on this planet on the midnight of May 28th, as Supercolony Spore Activity rose to critical levels.\nWith the liberation of Turing being at the highest priority, it was left to fend on its own, regrettably falling to the Terminid offensive but being liberated just 12 hours later.\nCirrus is the closest system to Super Earth that the Terminid pest has conquered. \nOperation Courageous Exodus.\nCirrus, alongside with Terrek and &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;, was chosen as one of the 3 sites from which millions of colonists, displaced by &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt;, would be processed then relocated into the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt;, where they would become its permanent staff.\nHowever, since the Terminids never got to any planets connected to Cirrus, it wouldn't see any need for protection, allowing its colonists to continue their daily democratic lives in unimpeded freedom"}
{"id": "6749", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6749", "title": "City", "text": "We got city maps bois!"}
{"id": "5997", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5997", "title": "Claorell", "text": "Claorell is one of the six planets that reside in the &lt;a href=\"Tanis%20Sector\"&gt;Tanis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It is the home of the Deep Mantle Forge Complex, a facility necessary for the production of the metal plates and other components needed for the construction of the Democracy Space Station\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Maia\"&gt;Maia&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Curia\"&gt;Curia&lt;/a&gt;, old, rocky moon. Its topography is composed of a cratered, hilly landscape with occasional cliff formations. It is entirely grayscale, possessing little to no color other than non-natural structures. Its terrain, while hilly, is quite open, making it relatively easy to traverse. This also provides excellent long-distance visibility.\nClaorell is also home to extremely valuable mineral deposits underneath it's surface, which has attracted the attention of the Automaton's who've set up deep-mantle mining operations on the planet, creating a deep-mantle mining complex which has polluted the moons already thin atmosphere.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Titanium Belt.\nClaorell was, up until September 2184, a peaceful lunar colony of Super Earth that relied on the export of many minerals valuable to the main industrial sectors of Super Earth. However, the Automatons, boundless in their greed, would not spare Claorell from the horrors of war in their quest to capture Imber's titanium deposits. On September 11th, after a couple tactical miscalculations by the Helldivers gave the Automatons control of &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt; and Vog-Sojoth, the Automatons would make one final push towards Imber by sending a dual assault from the two previously mentioned planets, with Claorell being the second planet to be assaulted.\nThe Helldivers would be forced to leave Claorell to its own devices, as the Colonial Overseer scrambled to mount a defense with the weapons the planet already had and with the few Helldivers that did turn up for support. During the first 16 hours of the defense, the situation looked lost. But a spark of hope would glimmer in the horizon as the Helldivers, in a glorious display of democratic fervour, would crush the attack at Imber after just 14 hours then began to immediately redeploy onto Claorell, beginning to turn the situation around, with less that 4 hours remaining before the planet's defenses caved in.\nClaorell would be spared and the order would be won, successfully prebventing the Automatons from acquiring Imber's titanium deposits.\nOperation Liberty Tide.\nFor a week, Claorell's colonists would be able to rest and recover, while the Helldivers were diverted back towards Tarsh and Mastia in order to secure important polystyrine deposits, which allowed for the fleetwide deployment of &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Napalm%20Barrage\"&gt;Orbital Napalm Barrages&lt;/a&gt;. However, shortly after, the Helldivers would be forced to draw a huge chunk of their available forces towards the Terminid front, due to difficulties faced at &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gatria\"&gt;Gatria&lt;/a&gt;. As such, the Automatons at neighbouring Vog-Sojoth found an opportunity to easily cut off Helldiver access to their garrison and, on September 18th, sent dual attacks onto both Clasa and Claorell.\nDue to the logistical struggles related to the unusually resilient Terminid hives at Pandion, both Clasa and Claorell were overwhelmed by the incoming Automaton forces, as there weren't enough Helldivers to help repel them. Claorell would fall but, surprisingly, the bots would not occupy it, instead opting to concentrate their forces at Clasa in order to expand further into the Tanis Sector.\nAs such, the Helldivers spotted a unique opportunity to take back Claorell, seeing as it was left underdefended. It would be reliberated on September 22nd, shortly before the liberation of Trandor allowed for more manpower to be available.\nHowever, this would not be the last time Claorell would see action, as the Automatons immediately launched an attack onto Claorell during the night of September 23rd. This attack would prove successful, as the Helldivers would be unable to provide support due to a newly issued major order.\nOperation Leap Forward.\nDuring Operation Leap Forward, the Helldivers had to concentrate almost exclusively on the liberation of Gaellivare. This meant that the fall of Claorell was a sacrifice that had to be undertaken for the greater good. With Imber having fallen days prior, Claorell's defense collapsed and, subsequently, became completely unable to be liberated, as its supply lines all led to Automaton-controlled planets.\nOperation Freedom's Forge.\nFor the past several weeks, development of the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt; has proceeded on-schedule. However the next step to construct the powerful battle station is the establishment of the Deep Mantle Forge Complex. This Deep Mantle Forge will use extreme heat and pressure near a planet's core to create an extremely strong and ductile chronium-cobalt-nickel alloy. The powerful alloy will be required to withstand the acceleration of the immense DSS to warp speeds.\nSuper Earth was able to identify -- based on atmospheric readings -- that the Automatons were already engaged in deep-mantle mining operations on the moon of Claorell. Thus liberating their mining tunnels and repurposing their facilities became top priority, as it would greatly accelerate the construction of the Deep Mantle Forge. Further, it would deny the Automatons their own access to the high-cost mine network, and reveal insight into their larger intentions. Thus the Helldivers are directed to liberate Claorell and its deep-mantle mining complex from the Automatons.\nAfter 2 days of battling, Imber's defenses collapsed, allowing for its swift liberation, whichthen allowed the Helldivers to move onto Claorell with haste. With merely hours to spare, the Helldivers spared no bullet in liberating the barren moon, managing to liberate it on October 7th, mere hours before the Automatons managed to bring reinforcements onto the planet and securing the tunnel system for Super Earth's miners to build the Deep Mantle Forge Complex, which will allow for the creation of a brand new alloy that will permit the DSS to withstand FTL Warp Jumps.\nHowever, it was also discovered that the Automatons were also developing new alloys in these tunnels in order to create new types of armor plating. More on this development is being investigated by the Ministry of Intelligence.\nOperation Bulwark of Democracy.\nThe colonists at Claorell would have to come back right into the heat of the battle. Even after its peaceful and righteous liberation, the Automatons refused to concede and, as such, mounted an offensive with the intent of retaking Claorell and its deep space mining complexes. Fittingly, Super Earth High Command ordered for Claorell to be defended, as well as for the Helldivers to hold the line against the Automaton menace while the Deep Space Forge Complex was under construction.\nOn October 8th, the already tried and tested colonists of Claorell had to take on the role of miners and frontline soldiers, fighting shoulder to shoulder with both Colonial Defense soldiers and Helldivers alike, hurling super-dynamite at the mechanized Hulks and impaling the evil Devastators with their shovels.\nBy October 9th, Claorell had been defended against the Automatons, allowing the colonists to take a break and resume their democratic work while the Helldivers moved on to defend other planets from the robotic menace.\nIn the early hours of October 10th, Claorell was attacked again. However, once more, the Helldivers would mobilize en masse in order to defend what rightfully belonged to the citizens of Super Earth. After an entire day defending, the Helldivers would successfully repel the second attack onto Claorell with minimal casualties, while also dealing a heavy blow to the robotic offenders.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nClaorell would remain under Freedom's control ever since its last assault, its Deep Mantle Forge burning bright as it churned out batch after batch of chromium-cobalt-nickel (CCN) alloy plates as the Democracy Space Station began to undergo its construction, with the planet's economy seeing a massive boost and an influx of new colonists.\nHaving been denied of such wonderful prosperity, the Automatons began to scheme. Claorell was free itself, but its neighboring planets in the Tanis Sector were all still in bondage under the occupation of the socialist machines. As such, it was only a matter of time before the Automatons turned their eyes towards Claorell once more.\nOn October 28th, the Automatons began to expand further into the Tanis Sector, as well as into the neighboring Gellert Sector to the galactic north. However, once the Automatons were successfully repelled at &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt; on October 31st, and then rebuked once again at Demiurg on November 1st. This left the Automatons with only one place left to go before they ran out of options to expand in the Tanis Sector, a planet that they had already failed to hold several times: Claorell.\nShortly after the successful defense at Demiurg, the Automatons at Clasa, using the remainder of their forces, would send out an attack at Claorell. Knowing that the loss of the Deep Mantle Forge Complex would delay the completion of the Democracy Space Station, the Helldivers immediately deviated the majority of the corps towards the defense of the planet, which would make the initial defensive operations much easier for the SEAF.\nAfter 16 hours of fighting, the Helldivers would successfully drive the Automatons off Claorell once more, keeping the Deep Mantle Forge Complex safe."}
{"id": "5998", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5998", "title": "Clasa", "text": "Clasa is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Tanis%20Sector\"&gt;Tanis Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Liberty Tide.\nClasa was, much like X-45, a sort of forgotten planet colony of Super Earth, far off into the Western galactic fringe. However, unlike X-45, Clasa had managed to be colonized and settled some time after the First Galactic War, as well as remaining inhabitable and productive. However, the Automatons, in their hatred of Super Earth's capitalist might, could not stand such a simple existence, for their drive to pollute planets with socialism was embedded into their transistors.\nBy September 2184, the Tanis Sector had become a frontline region of the Automaton front, shortly after the Helldivers had decisively repelled the Automaton attacks against Imber. However, the Helldivers weren't sufficiently manned and the Terminids continued to spread their fascism, which led to the Helldivers having to constantly bounce between fronts. Amidst an unusually difficult liberation campaign on &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt;, the Automatons at Vog-Sojoth decided to launch a dual attack and, on September 18th, launched assaults at both Clasa and Claorell, with the bulk of the Automaton forces falling at Clasa.\nAfter the fall of Clasa on September 19th, it became the new forward operations base for the robotic armies in the Tanis Sector, as its stood at an important chokepoint that cut off Zefia, Demiurg and Yed Prior from the rest of the FTL Network, making it a critical planet to control.\nYet, despite its critical location, the Helldivers have been continuously driven away from any serious liberation efforts on Clasa, mostly due to its remoteness and the constant surge of higher priority objectives.\nInterim (Sept. 19th-).\nSince the fall of Clasa in September, the swampy planet had fallen under full Automaton control. Between the months October to December, the heavily reinforced garrison at Clasa would go on to send assaults towards Zefia, Yed Prior, and Demiurg in the time ever since. While the Helldivers were able to repel the attack at Demiurg, they were unable to protect Zefia and Yed Prior from falling to the bots. In turn, the fall of the aforementioned planets would strike a disaster for the SEAF, as the Automatons would reestablish FTL lines between the Tanis Sector and its northern neighbor, the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The bots would mount an offensive into &lt;a href=\"Blistica\"&gt;Blistica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mintoria\"&gt;Mintoria&lt;/a&gt;, before combining those forces into a sizable assault at &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt;. All 3 planets would fall under Automaton occupation and the bots' control over the Tanis and Gellert Sectors would become more and more inevitable by the day."}
{"id": "6771", "revid": "52847180", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6771", "title": "Cognitive Disruptor", "text": "The Cognitive Disruptor is an &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; structure that affects a Helldiver's ability to call in &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagems&lt;/a&gt;. While it does not completely block stratagem use in the way an Automaton &lt;a href=\"Stratagem%20Jammer\"&gt;Stratagem Jammer&lt;/a&gt; does, it can still produce unwanted effects.\nAppearance.\nA Cognitive Disruptor appears to project a massive pastel-colored energy field across much of the map, often visible as Helldivers first arrive into a mission. The two-pronged tower measures roughly a hundred meters in height. It vaguely resembles a sword in shape.\nIn a disturbing encroachment on providence, Cognitive Disruptors are generally connected to humankind's energy grid, corrupting one's very desires in service of tyranny.\nTactics.\nWhen approaching within 200 meters of a Cognitive Disruptor, one begins to notice their Stratagem display becomes difficult to read, and that input codes are frequently replaced every three (3) seconds. The input codes may even resemble those used by other stratagems. Defeating this mental attack requires concentrating on the official MoD-standard symbology for Stratagems, and inputting the given code before it is cycled. Failure to properly input a code may result in a different stratagem being called.\nEven closer to the Cognitive Disruptor, one may notice additional sensory disturbances. In the ten-meter radius of the tower, the Helldiver needs to locate four energy conversion panels attached to colonial power equipment.\nStratagems that deliver heavy fire over a moderate area are effective against a Cognitive Disruptor:"}
{"id": "3359", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3359", "title": "Commissar", "text": "\"A crude simulation of military leadership, the Commissar is augmented with slightly faster processing and a crude command subroutine. The Commissar stays out of combat if possible, as despicably cowardly as it is unequivocally non-sentient.\"\nCommissar is a unique &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; unit that appears to be in the leader position of Automaton infantry squads. Further exemplifying its cowardice, its most important responsibility is, almost immediately upon one of its squadmates engaging a Helldiver in combat, to fire a &lt;a href=\"Spawn_Mechanics%23Reinforcement_Spawns\"&gt;signal flare&lt;/a&gt; into the sky to call for reinforcements."}
{"id": "4907", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4907", "title": "Conduct Geological Survey", "text": "The Conduct Geological Survey mission is one of the handful of missions that can be found on nearly every difficulty. It has a bare minimum of two steps: Deploy and Activate Seismic Probe and Deploy and Activate the Prospecting Drill. The Seismic Probe is always the first step, and if playing on higher difficulties, can require multiple probes be deployed before the Helldiver can go to the Drilling objective.\nGameplay.\n&lt;br&gt;\nStep 1: Seismic Probe(s)\n&lt;br&gt;\nFirst, the Helldiver must go to the designated location(s) shown on the map to deploy the Seismic Probe(s). Once in the area, an Objective Stratagem will become available and must be called to deploy the Probe. Once the Probe has landed, the Helldiver must interact with the terminal and input the proper directional code to begin the probing process. It should be noted that once the Probe begins its process, a single bug breach will occur and the Helldiver must defend themselves until the breach has been cleared or the probe has finished its deployment process. Once the process is complete, and if there are no other Probes that need to be deployed, the final objective will become active and the Helldiver must make their way to it.\nStep 2: Prospecting Drill\n&lt;br&gt;\nOnce at the designated objective area, once again another Objective Stratagem will become available to the Helldiver to call in the Drill. Once it has landed, the terminal must be interacted with several times to complete the objective. The drill has three harvesting phases, each one requiring the Helldiver to manually start after the previous one has completed. It should be noted that similar to the Seismic Probe, each time the Helldiver starts a new drill, a new bug breach will occur and they must defend themselves from the ensuing onslaught. Once all three harvests have been completed, the Helldiver must upload each via the terminal and the objective will be completed."}
{"id": "3389", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3389", "title": "Crimsica", "text": "Crimsica is one of the three planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Draco%20Sector\"&gt;Draco Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Its landscape is scattered with rocky biomes topped with crimson grass.\nTopography.\nCrimsica's topography consists of large, open swaths of rocky hills, intersected by large mountain ranges. Its only flora is the crimson red algae which covers most of its surface. It is devoid of trees or any other large flora. The surface is lightly covered in a medium-thick greenish-gray fog, which somewhat reduces visibility. It is also prone to sudden bursts of rainshowers.\nIts geography is mostly mountainous stretches of rocky terrain, with both small and large hilltops covered in boulders. While Crimsica does have oceans, they are uncommon and are often surrounded by large cliffs.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations prior to the Second Galactic War.\nOperation CBCT Protection.\nCrimsica, like neighboring &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt; and the rest of the Draco Sector, was largely unreachable by the SEAF until the successful installation of the Terminid Control System (TCS). Shortly after &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Prime%20Liberation\"&gt;Operation Prime Liberation&lt;/a&gt;, Civilian Biomass Collection Teams (BCTs) were deployed to Crimsica to gather and process inert Terminids for research. The Helldivers were tasked with liberating the planet to protect them, which they did effortlessly.\nAfter the withdrawal of both BCTs and Helldivers, Crimsica fell back into the Terminids' claws. The planet became a low-priority target as SEAF personnel were shifted to other areas, defending against Terminid offensives on neighbouring Estanu and participating in Operation Swift Disassembly against &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin&lt;/a&gt; Sectors.\nOperation Rearing.\nOnce Operation Swift Disassembly concluded, Super Earth High Command took steps toward the provision of more efficient services, which required condtructing improved E-710 plants. Crimsica, alongside &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt; and neighbouring Estanu, was selected as one of the recipients of these new farms.\nDespite the operation's success, the peace would not last. As the Automaton Invasion of &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; reignited the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Front\"&gt;Western Front&lt;/a&gt;, Crimsica continued to be assaulted by the fascistic insectoids. It was the site of much of the slaughter during Operation Organic Harvest, in which the Helldivers valiantly and mercilessly exterminated two billion Terminids in under 24 hours.\nDuring Operation Enduring Bulwark, Crimsica and neighboring Estanu saw the conducting of constant liberation and defensive operations. Despite the indescribable suffering and destruction caused by the Terminid menace, the colonists of Crimsica would not yield, not once faltering in the face of the mindless, ravenous insect hordes.\nFailure of the Terminid Control System.\nAfter the unexpected failure of the TCS, the Draco System was sadly overwhelmed by the reinforced bug onslaught. After evacuating the surviving colonists, Super Earth was forced to withdraw from the Draco Sector, with Crimsica being lost to the fascist menace.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Enduring Peace.\nCrimsica and the &lt;a href=\"Draco%20Sector\"&gt;Draco&lt;/a&gt; Sector remained under Terminid occupation through the month of May 2184, with the planet seeing serious damage to its environment. However, the horrors would not last, as Crimsica's salvation would come from an unlikely source. On May 30th, the Helldivers would make use of a new superweapon in order to destroy the Terminid Supercolony: The Dark Fluid.\nImmediately after &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; was destroyed, the Helldivers opened two fronts for a counterattack on the &lt;a href=\"Draco%20Sector\"&gt;Draco&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mirin%20Sector\"&gt;Mirin&lt;/a&gt; Sectors: One being a liberation campaign on &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt;, the other being simultaneous liberation efforts on both Crimsica and &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt;.\nOperation Hive Breaker.\nAfter reestablishing freedom on the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut&lt;/a&gt; Sector and some much needed victories on the Automaton Front, the Helldivers would receive a major order requiring the liberation of 5 planets: &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fori%20Prime\"&gt;Fori Prime&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nivel%2043\"&gt;Nivel 43&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt; and Crimsica. Crimsica would be fortunate enough to be chosen as the first planet to be liberated from the fascist alien insectoids, with its liberation arriving on June 16th.\nFalstaff and Jin Xi Lockdown.\nHowever, it would not last for long. Fori Prime, always rebellious and very resistant to Liberty, would fall sometime around June 28th and then, almost by instinct, would send a Terminid spore barrage right towards Crimsica, where it made landfall on June 29th. The Helldivers, focused on securing the neighboring sector of Jin Xi at the time, could not heed its calls for aid and, comprehensively, Crimsica would fall once more, remaining under Terminid control since.\nOperation Starslayer.\nDuring Operation Starslayer onwards, Crimsica would remain under Terminid control, causing further complications in the Terminid front. During the final week of June and the first 2 weeks of August, Crimsica's brood of Terminids would make repeated attempts to invade Acamar IV, none of them succeeding and, at a certain point, allowing the Helldivers to push back into Crimsica, getting it all the way up to 98% liberation before Operations Liberty Crush and Vengeful Cleansing ordered the Helldivers away, sparing the Terminids in Crimsica from obliteration at the last minute.\nOperation Prometheus.\nHowever, showing mercy to the fascistic insects would, as always, prove to be a grave mistake. When the Helldivers did an extraordinary display of mercy, the Bugs spat on Liberty's face and launched an assault onto Estanu on August 13th, now being bolstered by the malevolent &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;Gloom&lt;/a&gt;, its putrid aura of intergalactic Terminid spores apparently giving them more fuel to the fire that is their innate hatred for Freedom. With the Automaton Front being in a more stable position and with &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt; having been successfully rescued from the bugs, Super Earth High Command would issue a major order requesting the collection of 10 million Rare or Super Rare samples on Crimsica.\nHowever, as always, treason would spell doom for Crimsica. Not even 30 minutes into Operation Prometheus, traitors submitted a high number of counterfeit samples, provoking the abortion of the Operation and snatching Crimsica's chance for liberation out of its grip since now that the Helldivers didn't have any orders, they chose to divert towards the defense of Estanu, leaving Crimsica's liberation to lose all of its progress.\nOperation Brute Force.\nCrimsica would have to endure another 4 days of horros as, while the Helldivers were diverted towards &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt;, they also had to help defend and repel Terminid attacks on other planets, which pretty much left Crimsica helpless. However, its chance for liberty would soon appear, as the Helldivers would be promptly turned back towards the Terminid Front in order to contain the ever-growing Gloom, which was now growing uncontrollably.\nOn August 22nd, Crimsica would be finally liberated from Terminid occupation, which helped prevent further Gloom expansion.\nOperation Ring of Freedom.\nCrimsica remained a stalwart frontier world against the Terminids ever since its liberation, being right at the edge of the Gloom in the Draco Sector yet experiencing an uneasy armed peace, as Fori Prime's unknown status still presented a threat to its safety. Its proximity to &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt;, the site of a newly built Xenoentomology Center devoted to the creation of new Alcubierre Drives for the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt;, and its direct FTL line to Acamar IV, which was designated to be the new Terminid Research Preserve, meant that Crimsica would be designated as a priority target for the Helldivers during Operation Ring of Freedom.\nCrimsica would be suddenly attacked from within the Gloom on October 16th, alongside Estanu. Given Crimsica's connection to Acamar IV, the Terminids would concentrate mostly on attempting to capture Crimsica, which meant that the Helldivers were forced to abandon Estanu to its own devices. Crimsica would be successfully defended on October 17th, after heavy casualties and 22 hours of fighting.\nOperation Courageous Exodus.\nWith Crimsica secured, the Terminid Research Preserve could continue its work unimpeded. However, this situation would not last long. Following the apparition of the Jet Brigade on the Automaton Front, Gacrux and Pandion-XXIV would fall, which left Acamar IV exposed to the Gloom's influence. However, the Helldivers would manage to plug this gap before any significant damages were made by the bugs.\nDespite this, the Terminids would redouble their efforts and, aided by a spore surge from within the Gloom, would launch a massive offensive onto the Barrier Planets. On November 7th, shortly after the fall of Esker, Crimsica would be assaulted alongside Estanu, the Terminids still determined to breach the Terminid Research Preserve.\nFor the first 18 hours of the assault, it looked like Crimsica had been abandoned to its own devices by the Helldivers, as the bugs made tremendous advances. However, once Estanu fell, the Helldivers began to relocate to Crimsica immediately as the Bugs had begun the final, slower phase of their assault. The defense was tense and chaotic, as the Helldivers rushed to take over crucial positions in Crimsica as quickly as possible, scuttling several Super Destroyers in the process in order for the crashing wrecks to take out as many of the fascist insectoids as possible.\nAfter 4 hours of intense orbital bombardments and on-the-ground combat, the Helldivers managed to miraculously repel the assault less than 30 minutes before the Terminids managed to reach the threshold of fascism necessary to take over Crimsica.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nCrimsica would remain free following its liberation, as the Terminids had been seemingly repelled and they made no additional attempts on Crimsica. However, beyond its sector's borders, Crimsica's perdition had been brewing all along.\nOn November 12th, in the middle of a busy day for the Tyranny Park, a massive underground Terminid hive erupted spontaneously, leading to a bloody massacre of visitors and park staff alike. Acamar IV was overrun in mere minutes, which prevented the nuclear security measures from being activated and allowed the Terminids to take over the planet without any impediment. Once Acamar IV fell, it launched 5 simultaneous attacks onto all of the planets connected to it. This catastrophe could not have been any more poorly timed, as the Jet Brigade had also just returned in massive numbers and destroyed the DSS Logistics Hub on &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe painting was clear on the wall that the Helldivers had to act quick before more damage had to be done. Despite Acamar's positioning, High Command gave the indication to protect the Xenoentomology Center at Turing by all means, as it still contained critical research material on the Terminids, pretty much dooming Acamar IV and all of its attached planets to perdition.\nExpectedly, with the Helldivers focused on saving the critical research material at Turing, Crimsica would be lost to the Terminids by the afternoon of the following day, in a massive disaster that took millions of lives and undid all the progress achieved in the past 3 months.\nOperation Balance of Liberty.\nFollowing the disaster at Acamar IV, Crimsica was left to fall to the Terminid invasion, as the Helldivers had to return to the Automaton front in order to secure the DSS. For 9 days, Crimsica was stuck in a deadlock, as the Helldivers battled against the Terminids at Acamar IV and the Jet Brigade at &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt;. It wouldn't be until the liberation of Imber on November 20th that the Helldivers would finally be able to resume containment missions back in the Terminid Front.\nGiven Crimsica's symbolic status within the Helldiver Corps as a twin planet to Estanu, the Helldivers would choose to deploy the main fleet and the Democracy Space Station on it first, even enacting an Orbital Blockade as an additional preventive measure. After 24 hours of grueling combat, Crimsica would be liberated once again."}
