{"id": "5928", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5928", "title": "Curia", "text": "Curia is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Marspira%20Sector\"&gt;Marspira Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Maia\"&gt;Maia&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nPrelude.\nCuria was a strategically important planet since April 2184. When the Automatons launched their invasion of &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and began to push towards &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, Curia was part of the supply line connecting Super Earth to the Western Front via Aesir Pass. During the numerous times &lt;a href=\"Aesir%20Pass\"&gt;Aesir Pass&lt;/a&gt; was attacked and occupied, Curia ensured supply access to the planet. With Aesir Pass haven fallen under Socialist occupation for several weeks by July, their forces were rapidly recovering from their previous &lt;a href=\"Encirclements%23Matar_Bay_Encirclement\"&gt;encirclement&lt;/a&gt; disaster. Curia was the only clear way forward in the backwards minds of the red pest.\nOperation Lighthouse.\nCuria had been, up until August 2184, a stalwart front against the Automaton offensive, always standing strong against the consistent incursions from the Automatons. For several months, its colonists watched as, time and again, the Automatons would reach Aesir Pass, only to be repelled. However, as the war took its toll on the Helldivers and they began to be diverted back to the Terminid front amidst the appearance of &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt;, the Automatons would put Curia through its hardest test yet.\nAs the Helldivers managed to rescue &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt;, the Automatons, in a desperate attempt to rescue what little remained of their odious fief in the Trigon Sector, launched an assault on Curia on August 10th, punching through their defenses by the morning on August 11th.\nOperation People's Shield.\nCuria would not remain under the cruel grip of the Automatons for long. With Operation Prometheus being aborted due to counterfeit samples being delivered, Super Earth High Command would shift its focus towards the imminent Automaton threat that loomed on Curia. Deeming it intolerable for the robotic menace to advance any further, they would issue an order calling for the liberation of Curia while repelling any and all Automaton attacks. \nCuria's liberation became more desperate on August 17th, as the Automatons attempted a massive onslaught on Tarsh, with Curia as their point of attack. During the first day of Tarsh's defense, the situation seemed disfavorable, as the Automaton forces, now equipped with more advanced Scout Striders and Missile-Firing tanks, would begin to crack Tarsh's defense. However, the Helldivers spotted a crucial opportunity on Curia. With Curia close enough to full liberation for it to be done in under 24 hours, the Helldivers would strategically split in two, with one group holding the Automatons back in Tarsh while the other went for Curia in order to accomplish a masterful gambit strategy that paid in spades.\nOn August 18th, Curia would be liberated, cutting the assaulting bots in Tarsh off their supply line to Cyberstan and granting Super Earth a much needed victory, as Curia's liberation would signify the complete liberation of the Marspira Sector and the successful deflection of the craven mechanized assault. However, this would not be the end of Curia's problems, as the Automatons that survived would withdraw to Vernen Wells and, on August 20th, sent a second assault onto Tarsh through a newly formed FTL line connecting Vernen Wells and Tarsh, while also launching an assault onto Curia, in a desperate attempt to hold on to their vanguard at the Marspira Sector.\nOperation Ecological Immolation.\nThe Helldivers would manage to turn the tide and defend Curia, from where they then went on to capture Aesir Pass and Vernen Wells, leaving neighboring Tarsh cut off from the larger Automaton frontline which, eventually, paved the way for the complete liberation of the Marspira Sector during the last weeks of September.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nEver since its final defense on August 21st, Curia remained under firm control of Super Earth, once more standing as a bastion of peace in a region of space consistently plagued by the socialist Automatons. However, the Automatons now had revenge subroutines programmed into their systems and, after their blunders with the Jet Brigade at Marfark and their efforts in the Tanis and Gellert Sectors being successfully stopped, the Automatons would desperately launch an assault onto Curia on November 2nd, as they seeked to expand again.\nHowever, the Helldivers were now able to manage both fronts at once and, having a Major Order with the objective of preventing Automaton expansion by all means, they turned up en masse to assist with Curia's defense. The initial defensive operations turned out exceedingly successful."}
{"id": "3664", "revid": "56460482", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3664", "title": "Currencies", "text": "Various currencies are used in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; to purchase in-game items.\nAll currencies can be earned through regular gameplay. Super Credits used to purchase access to &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbonds&lt;/a&gt; or armor sets in the &lt;a href=\"Superstore\"&gt;Superstore&lt;/a&gt; may also be purchased with real-world funds.\nAll currencies have a cap beyond which further currency will not be earned. The player may receive reminders through the &lt;a href=\"Ship%20TV\"&gt;Ship TV&lt;/a&gt; system or HUD urging them to spend such currency.\nRequisition.\nRequisition Slips are a currency used in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; for acquiring &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ship%20Modules\"&gt;Ship Modules&lt;/a&gt;. The maximum amount of Requisition Slips a player can hold is 50,000.\nMedals.\nMedals \u00a0\u00a0 are a currency used in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; for unlocking &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbond Content&lt;/a&gt;. Picking up Medals from &lt;a href=\"Points%20of%20Interest\"&gt;Points of Interest&lt;/a&gt;s will automatically add them to all present helldivers without the need to extract.\nThe maximum amount of Medals a player can hold is 250. Note that notifications informing the player of earned medals will begin to show 0 medals earned once the cap is reached.\nSuper Credits.\nSuper Credits are a Currency used in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Superstore\"&gt;Superstore&lt;/a&gt;. They can be used to purchase &lt;a href=\"Armory%20%28Helldivers%202%29\"&gt;armor sets&lt;/a&gt; from the Superstore or to unlock &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbonds&lt;/a&gt;. Picking up Super Credits from &lt;a href=\"Points%20of%20Interest\"&gt;Points of Interest&lt;/a&gt;s will automatically add them to all present Helldivers without the need to extract. There is no known maximum capacity for Super Credits.\nSamples.\nSamples are a currency used in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; to permanently upgrade your &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt; by acquiring &lt;a href=\"Ship%20Modules\"&gt;Ship Modules&lt;/a&gt;. Three types of samples exist: Common Samples, Rare Samples, and Super Samples (or Super Uranium).\nUnlike other currencies, all types are directly carried by the Helldiver that picked them up. They are dropped on the ground if the carrier dies, or chooses to drop them using the Drop Menu. They will need to be picked up again as needed and carried all the way into the extraction vehicle to be gained at the end of the mission. Dropped samples can be picked up by any squadmate, being added to their own container.\nTo reduce risk, it may be preferable to spread the pickups between players in the group. Samples can also be dropped at the Extraction Zone should the squad cross it before completing the mission.\nThe total amount of samples that can be found and the amount currently carried in the mission is displayed on the HUD depending on settings (by default, the counter will only display briefly whenever a sample is picked up). The amount of samples generated per mission depends on difficulty and mission type (short missions like &lt;a href=\"Eradicate\"&gt;Eradicate&lt;/a&gt; typically will have far less and possibly not even of every type that should be available, if any at all).\nAs with the other currencies, all Helldivers will gain all samples earned at the end of the mission, regardless of who was carrying them into the extraction vehicle. Successful extraction of samples is the only way to obtain them.\nCommon Samples are found on any difficulty. The maximum amount of common samples the player can hold is 500.\nIn the area of operations, they look like plant-like bulbs on a stalk, small cases (prepared earlier by research teams), small worms in Terminid-controlled planets, or like small machinery in Automaton-controlled planets. \nRare Samples are found on Challenging Difficulty and higher. The maximum amount of rare samples the player can hold is 250. They can be acquired at:\nRare samples take the form of several crystallized stones and flowers. They may appear in locked areas such as secured bunkers, shipping containers, or ejection pods.\nSuper Samples , which look like liquid metal bulbs defying gravity, are found on Extreme Mission Difficulty and higher. The maximum amount of Super Samples the player can hold is 100.\nThey can only at be found at a very distinct &lt;a href=\"Points%20of%20Interest%23Silvery%20Rock\"&gt;rock formation&lt;/a&gt;. The number of super samples found depends of the current difficulty and can vary slightly.\nThis rock has a bile-infused variation that has a chance to have the Super Samples. There is a chance to have multiple Super Sample rocks in a mission, typically 2, very rarely 3. The samples will only ever be at one of these locations, never split between them, therefore if you find one of these rocks but it has no samples then there's another one somewhere on the map that holds them.\nSpecial items found in &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Nest\"&gt;Mega Nests&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Automaton%20Outpost\"&gt;Fortresses&lt;/a&gt;\u2014namely, the Mutated Egg and an Automaton head filled with Confidential Data\u2014will credit Helldivers with 2 Super Samples and 4 Rare Samples if delivered to an &lt;a href=\"Extraction\"&gt;Extraction Shuttle&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3862", "revid": "4493069", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3862", "title": "Cutting Edge", "text": "Cutting Edge is the second Premium &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbond&lt;/a&gt; which released on the 14th of March, 2024. It has 3 pages, containing various cosmetics, armor, weapons, and batches of Super Credits exchangeable for &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Medals\"&gt;Warbond Medals&lt;/a&gt;.\nContent.\nPage 1.\nTotal Medal cost: 93\nPage 2 - Spend 60 Medals to unlock.\nTotal Medal cost: 217\nPage 3 - Spend 230 Medals to unlock.\nTotal Medal cost: 362\nTotal Medal cost for Warbond: 672"}
{"id": "4033", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4033", "title": "Cyberstan", "text": "&lt;tabber&gt;\nCyberstan is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Cyberstan is an ice world, as well the former home world of the during the first galactic war, before they were defeated and locked up safely in the mines of the planet, where they remained until the invasion in the Second Galactic War by the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;.\nCyberstan is a planet that resides in the Cyberstan Region. It is the homeworld of the during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nTopography.\nA planet slightly too far from its sun, with temperatures constantly cold creating deep layers of snow and ice. Prominent geographic features faced by Helldivers in the first Galactic War included vast open snowfields and frozen lake beds, as well as scattered mountain ranges and open pools of exposed arctic water that could freeze a careless Helldiver in seconds. Despite its inhospitable environment, this barren on the galactic fringe was once the homeworld of the abominations of humanity, known as the Cyborgs.\nHistory.\nFirst Galactic War.\nCyberstan was the homeworld and capital of the Cyborg separatists during the events of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. Though their origins are unclear, what is known is that the human colonists of the planet had (possibly due to the harsh conditions of the planet) become obsessed with the manipulation of their bodies, replacing their skin with machines that according to them, gave them a higher meaning in life.\nWhen the planet was conquered by Super Earth, the Cyborgs were \"democratized\" once again, volunteered into the voting booths by the threat of losing their civil rights. Super Earth's Army Tactical Command stationed troops on the planet for a period of 5 years to \"keep the peace and \"run government positions\"\", after which period the Cyborgs' culture is supposed to have transitioned to a \"fully democratic\" one. Meanwhile, the Super Earth Construction Company (SECC), a government contractor, took over the massive forges and industrial complexes of Cyberstan.\nThe Cyborg separatists were finally broken in both body and spirit. Cyberstan had been conquered by Super Earth for the last time, with the Cyborgs themselves being secured away in the mines of Cyberstan, their homeworld becoming a new rehabilitation facility for them. \nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nOn April 9, 2184, a large force of &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; invaded Cyberstan and all planets connected by &lt;a href=\"FTL%20Lines\"&gt;FTL Lines&lt;/a&gt; to it. The Automatons were thought to have been eradicated from the Galaxy after their harsh defeats at the hands of &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Humanity's champions&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt; during operation Swift Disassembly. Unfortunately, the bulk of their forces were lurking in the darkness, waiting to strike at the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth domains&lt;/a&gt; while the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; were occupied on the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;Terminid Front&lt;/a&gt;.\nInvestigations into what happened are currently ongoing. What is known is that the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; Invasion Fleet, comprised of tens of thousands of warships, arrived from FTL jump to the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt; and overran nearly every planet in just hours, with attacks on communications networks delaying the SEAF response. The Federation of Super Earth initiated Libcon 1, with SEAF reserves being hastily scrambled whilst all Helldivers were called to deploy immediately to the defense of the sector.\nCurrently the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Ministry of Truth&lt;/a&gt; refutes the claim that the Automatons have an emotional drive to retake Cyberstan, as Automatons are unfeeling machines. The correct reason for their coward attack is their vile hatred towards freedom and managed democracy. Where the Automatons hid their invasion fleet and what their true objectives could be, are questions that must be asked later.\nCyberstan currently serves as the main base of operations for the Automatons, the Children of the Cyborgs as known based on a decoded data intercept. The level of overall Cyborg involvement is unknown and whether the Automatons are merely the servants of some unknown Cyborg survivor group which evaded capture and are hellbent on revenge, or the Cyborgs as a whole is unknown."}
