{"id": "5975", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5975", "title": "Darius II", "text": "Darius II is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Borgus%20Sector\"&gt;Borgus Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Esker\"&gt;Esker&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slif\"&gt;Slif&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Alcubierre-II.\nDarius II had managed to avoid most of the horrors that ensued during the initial Terminid outbreak, mainly because of Achird III's very crucial move to cut its supply line with Turing early on in February. However, Darius' Colonial Overseer was able to see that this measure would not keep their sector safe. He immediately moved to sever all supply lines leading into the Jin Xi Sector, due to his dangerous proximity to both Turing and Acamar IV. This move would prove wise once the Terminids shifted their focus towards the Falstaff and Jin Xi sectors. But as usual, the fascist insects would find a way to bring a once peaceful planet colony of Super Earth into the war by force.\nOn September 28th, 2184, The Terminids would unprovokedly attack Darius II, in an attempt to reinforce their attack on &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; by flanking through Achird III. Darius' colonists had spent almost 6 months reinforcing their planet home, digging trenches alongside the towering plateaus and stockpiling weapons in stashes buried all over the green, acidic dunes of the planet. However, even with all that preparation, they began to falter, as the Terminid assault was too strong and, as such, they were forced to call on the Helldivers for assistance.\nDespite 60% of the entire corps assisting with Darius' defense, it would prove too late to save and, consequently, Darius II would be lost to the Terminids by the afternoon of September 29th, the Bugs now having deeply entrenched themselves into the acidic planet, following a pattern of hard defenses and difficult subsequent liberations that had been eating away at the Terminid Front for some weeks by then.\nOperation Ring of Freedom.\nDespite Darius' valuable position, the Terminids never made a move out of Darius after their failure to take Achird III on September 30th. As such, they instead burrowed themselves into the planet and began to build up their strength and numbers in order to reattempt an attack on Achird III once more. On October 11th, the Terminids on Darius sent a barrage of spores at Achird III and began an assault onto the planet. \nFor the first 12 hours of the invasion, the Terminids seemed to be having the upper hand, as the defenders on Achird III began to get overwhelmed. However, Achird's defenders managed to hold on for long enough that the Helldivers managed to liberate Pandion-XXIV, freeing them up to relief Achird III immediately. With a mere 20 minutes remaining before complete planetary infestation, the Helldivers managed to repel the assault on Achird III and, now knowing for certain that Achird III's flank on Turing was far too valuable to lose, the Helldivers immediately began deployment onto Darius II.\nFor 2 days, the Helldivers battled across the acidic dunes of Darius, knowing it to be such a critical position that they would be forced to let &lt;a href=\"Gar%20Haren\"&gt;Gar Haren&lt;/a&gt; fall in order to ensure Darius II was fully captured. By October 14th, Darius II was liberated, freeing the Helldivers up to relief a struggling defense on Achernar Secundus and, consequently, freeing the Borgus Sector from the Terminid scourge once and for all.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nDarius would remain free of any Terminid presence after its liberation. It would seem that, after all, things hadn't come to boil despite the tactical miscalculation at &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; during Operation Crossroads. But the seeds of fascism had already been sown on the Terminid Research Preserve, and it was only a matter of time before their bore their nefarious fruits.\nOn November 12th, in the middle of a busy day for the Tyranny Park, a massive underground Terminid hive erupted spontaneously, leading to a bloody massacre of visitors and park staff alike. Acamar IV was overrun in mere minutes, which prevented the nuclear security measures from being activated and allowed the Terminids to take over the planet without any impediment. Once Acamar IV fell, it launched 5 simultaneous attacks onto all of the planets connected to it. This catastrophe could not have been any more poorly timed, as the Jet Brigade had also just returned in massive numbers and destroyed the DSS Logistics Hub on &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe painting was clear on the wall that the Helldivers had to act quick before more damage had to be done. Despite Acamar's positioning, High Command gave the indication to protect the Xenoentomology Center at Turing by all means, as it still contained critical research material on the Terminids, pretty much dooming Acamar IV and all of its attached planets to perdition.\nExpectedly, with the Helldivers focused on saving the critical research material at Turing, Darius-II would be lost to the Terminids by the afternoon of the following day, in a massive disaster that took millions of lives and undid all the progress achieved in the past 3 months.\nOperation Iron Rain.\nAfter the disaster at Tyranny Park, Darius-II had been left in ruins. Its settlements colonized by Terminids as its patriotic colonists watched amidsts desperate evacuations. However, after every thunder, the sunlight of Liberty always rises. Despite the immense losses at the Terminid Front, the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt; was successfully fueled. And despite a chaotic initial deployment, it would ultimately be harnessed into a weapon of peace and freedom like none before it. With its mighty alloy plates, it rained planetary armaggedon onto &lt;a href=\"Mastia\"&gt;Mastia&lt;/a&gt;, swaths of righteous Eagles onto &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt; and was indispensable in the campaign to recover Acamar IV, preventing further chaos and keeping the flame of hope alive.\nWith Operation Balance of Liberty, the Helldivers managed to recapture &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt; and finally eradicate the Jet Brigade at &lt;a href=\"Imber\"&gt;Imber&lt;/a&gt; before then further inflicting damage onto the robotic menace on &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt;. These victories bolstered the Helldiver Corps and, most importantly, freed them up for alternative endeavors in regards to Galactic Liberation.\nFollowing a thwarted attack by the Terminids on &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt; on November 24th, Operation Iron Rain was declared, as the Ministry of Defense sought to conduct an efficacy review on the then-available machine guns that the SEAF had access to. With Fenrir III being successfully defended, the Helldivers turned towards the only planet left that stained the Borgus Sector with the stench of Terminid Fascism.\nFrom November 25th to November 27th, the Helldivers deployed en masse to liberate the acidic planet, with many colonists even contributing with their shovels, break-action shotguns and some with machine guns of their own. Alongside the DSS' support, the battle for Darius-II would see amounts of ammunition expenditure ranging in the hundreds of billions of bullets. After 2 days of battling, the Terminids would be sufficiently eradicated, as the last Terminid broods were vaporized through the forceful opening of sufficient concentrations of bullet holes."}
