{"id": "6054", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6054", "title": "Dark Fluid", "text": "Dark Fluid is a form of synthesized exotic matter (taking the form of a dark-colored substance) liberated from the following the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. This mysterious fluid has some physics-defying properties, the most notable of which is creating unstable gravitational singularities that turn into miniature black holes.\nDue to the sudden and unexpected rapid &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; infestation on the planet of &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; after the deployment of the Terminid Control System facilities, the Super Earth government was forced to contain the situation by using vast amounts of Dark Fluid created on the planet of &lt;a href=\"Moradesh\"&gt;Moradesh&lt;/a&gt;, being pumped into Meridia's crust. The end-result after a grueling conflict was a planet-sized black hole forming where &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; used to be, plunging the Terminids and their spores into an inescapable gravity well.\nBesides creating black holes, there are currently no other known side-effects of deploying Dark Fluid. Unfortunately it's also a feat that is unlikely to be repeated in the near future as the Federation's reserves of captured Dark Fluid from the first galactic war have been expended."}
