{"id": "4736", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4736", "title": "Deactivate Terminid Control System", "text": "The Deactivate Terminid Control System mission is a limited time event that begun on April 29th, 2024 following the failure of &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Legitimate%20Undertaking\"&gt;Operation Legitimate Undertaking&lt;/a&gt;. It consists of Helldivers dropping into locations hosting previously activated Termicide towers and deactivating them while slaughtering the infestation that has grown in its confinements. \nThere are two objectives that are of equal importance: Deactivating three corrupted battery silos, which in turn deactivate the dispersion tower in the center; and destroying at least 17 egg nests that are scattered across the entire area of operation. "}
{"id": "5999", "revid": "54761251", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5999", "title": "Demiurg", "text": "Demiurg is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Tanis%20Sector\"&gt;Tanis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \u00a0It's position at the border between the Tanis and &lt;a href=\"Arturion%20Sector\"&gt;Arturion&lt;/a&gt; Sectors makes it a very strategically valuable planet, as it effective is the only barrier between the and the ever encountering one another.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Shelt\"&gt;Shelt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nDemiurg was, for pretty much all of the Second Galactic War, just another planet colony of Super Earth without anything particularly worthy of note. Its scattered colonies undertook a myriad of activities, from logging to farming to mining, without much oddities occurring in their everyday lives. But if the Automatons hate something, it is the simple things such as the calm and comfort that abound in the galactic fringe. \nWhen the Automatons first invaded the Valdis Sector in April, the Tanis Sector preventively cut all of its FTL Supply Lines in order to prevent the robots from spreading towards the Terminid Front, as many SEAF strategists feared the unpredictability of such an encounter. This outcome would put Demiurg through a hard time; as it also meant that, given its position of remoteness even in its own sector, Demiurg could not really fortify or stockpile supplies in case of an invasion.\nThese worries would become validated when, in September 2184, the Automatons managed to capture Clasa after the Tanis Sector's FTL Lines had been restored, which effectively left Demiurg completely isolated, caught between the metaphorical wall that was the now-disconnected Arturion Sector's planets and the very literal sword that was the Automaton Forward Base that was growing more and more fortified in Clasa, as the socialist menace prepared to continue its expansionist campaigns.\nShortly after Liberty Day, Demiurg would find itself even more isolated, as &lt;a href=\"Zefia\"&gt;Zefia&lt;/a&gt; and now &lt;a href=\"Yed%20Prior\"&gt;Yed Prior&lt;/a&gt; fell against attacks coming from Clasa. It was now only a matter of time before the Automatons turned their sights onto Demiurg, as it was the only remaining planet in the Tanis Sector that hadn't rebuked them, all while &lt;a href=\"Claorell\"&gt;Claorell&lt;/a&gt; had grown too fortified for the Automatons to push for.\nThe Automatons initiated their invasion of the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt; on October 28th, with the twin invasions of &lt;a href=\"Blistica\"&gt;Blistica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mintoria\"&gt;Mintoria&lt;/a&gt;. So far, it seemed like the Automatons would continue all the way to &lt;a href=\"Zosma\"&gt;Zosma&lt;/a&gt; and conquer the Gellert Sector, which would buy Demiurg much needed time, but then the Helldivers managed to repel the Automatons at &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt;, which forced them to turn the concentrated remains of their forces towards the only planet that they hadn't yet attempted to invade so far.\nOn the early hours of October 31st, SEAF Colonial Defense Network channels began to flood with calls for aid coming from Demiurg's garrison. Having been under siege for a month and having been unable to prepare ever since they had been cut off the FTL Network on April, Demiurg was pretty much incapable of either evacuating nor repelling the invaders and, comprehensibly, called for immediate Helldiver support.\nWith the Helldivers having orders to prevent further Automaton expansion, Demiurg would see half of the Helldiver Corps, around 22,000 Super Destroyers, show up in droves to support the besieged planet."}
{"id": "3807", "revid": "36178975", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3807", "title": "Democracy Officer", "text": "The Democracy Officer in Helldivers 2 is responsible for conducing tactical support for the Helldivers during their operations, which includes motivational quotes to prevent un-democratic thoughts taking root in the Helldivers. He is located next to the planning table.\nGeneral Notes.\nThe Democracy Officer, judging by his name and voicelines by him and other crew members, most likely serves as a political officer for the Ministry of Truth, enforcing Managed Democracy and the ideals of Super Earth among the Helldiver Corps. Additionally, the &lt;a href=\"Helldiver%20Contract%20of%20Employment\"&gt;Helldiver Contract of Employment&lt;/a&gt; does state that the Democracy Officer can, as member of the \"Authorized Command Structure\", terminate the contract for any reason at their discretion, meaning they are considered the Helldivers' superior officer. Besides this, they mention how they regret \"having one ship's worth of lives to give to our cause\", meaning that the Democracy Officer is involved, at least in part, in the process of ensuring that the Super Destroyer gets extra reinforcement Helldivers.\nBeyond ideological enforcement, it would seem as if the Democracy Officer otherwise behaves like any non-commissioned officer would, as they seem to be of rank-and-file and, depending on which variant of the Democracy Officer one gets, has seen combat prior to becoming a Democracy Officer, and probably still sees combat judging by how they wear armor unlike the &lt;a href=\"Ship%20Master\"&gt;Ship Master&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Service%20Technician\"&gt;Service Technician&lt;/a&gt;.\nJudging by how they aren't mentioned in Broadcast Announcements or any of the civilian propaganda, with these 2 instead pointing citizens towards their \"Loyalty Officer\", it may be possible that Democracy Officers are exclusive to the military.\nQuotes.\nThe following voicelines can be rolled at any time. While the NPCs can occasionally gain time-limited voicelines, they will not be listed here.\nTrivia.\n__NOEDITSECTION__"}
{"id": "6470", "revid": "46883485", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6470", "title": "Democracy Space Station", "text": "Considered a great leap forward for Managed Democracy, the Democracy Space Station is an interplanetary battle-station based on liberated First Galactic War Era battle plans. The DSS promises to be a powerful strategic tool for reshaping the Galactic Map - democratically directed by the Helldivers themselves. With the Helldivers protecting it, the Democracy Space Station will soon be ready to rain down the will of the people on any who would stand in its way.\nGeneral.\nDetails on the exact layout of the interior of the DSS are currently unavailable and it's capabilities are naturally highly classified. Even so the construction site of the space station orbiting around &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt; is an order of magnitude larger than the standard &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt; and utterly dwarfs anything else which Super Earth has put into orbit so far -- save perhaps the shipyards that orbit &lt;a href=\"Mars\"&gt;Mars&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis large size however came at a cost as it was well beyond the capacity of Super Earth's current Alcubiere Warp Drives to transport without astronomic E-710 consumption. Thus the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; established a new, state-of-the-art Xenoentomology Center on &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; in order to prototype and develop new High-Efficiency Alcubiere Drives, capable of effectively transporting gigastructures like the DSS. Even then the DSS still requires a 20-story reusable fuel tanks, and key personnel have to input the long and highly confidential activation code at their designated terminals whenever the space station is activated.\nIn addition the station's protective plating required a (relatively) lightweight but above all durable material capable of surviving immense warp speeds during FTL travel. In the end, Super Earth's engineers chose a alloy of &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.newscientist.com/article/2350789-toughest-material-ever-is-an-alloy-of-chromium-cobalt-and-nickel/\"&gt;chromium, cobalt and nickel&lt;/a&gt;, the toughest material ever tested. Fortunately, SEAF Command were able to identify atmospheric readings on &lt;a href=\"Claorell\"&gt;Claorell&lt;/a&gt; indicating that the Automatons were already engaging in deep-mantle mining operations on the planet. Thus the Helldivers liberated their mining tunnels and facilities, which not only greatly accelerated the construction of the Deep Mantle Forge but would also deny the Automatons their own access to the high-cost mine network.\nThe stately behemoth also requires a similarly behemoth number of able bodied crewmen. Though applications from patriotic, detail-oriented team-players have been pouring in, the DSS requires over 1.3 million skilled workers. The &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Humanity\"&gt;Ministry of Humanity&lt;/a&gt; has therefore authorized the relocation of an unprecedented number of colonists from &lt;a href=\"Terrek\"&gt;Terrek&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cirrus\"&gt;Cirrus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;. When polled, those affected by recent bug attacks proved the most eager to serve, with citizens of all ages being safely evacuate to the DSS. Since then these evacuees have all been put on generous contracts and underwent accelerated bootcamps in orbital weapons handling -- experiencing the glory of the warfront, the freedom of space, and the camaraderie of dormitory living.\nWhilst the unfinished DSS construction site was highly vulnerable to attack from the enemies of Super Earth, as the station's armor plating has not been fully installed and its extensive defensive systems had not yet come online, this is no longer an issue since the station's completion and activation. Not only is the station protected by hardened (but lightweight) alloy plating, but also a suite of 77 PRESIDENTIAL-Class Cannons, a massive fleet of Eagle fighters housed in an equally massive three-tiered Convocation Bay and of course it's Zero G Anti-Ship Missile System. Truly, no other ship in the Super Earth Navy can compare to the firepower of this fully armed and operational battle-station!\nHistory.\nWhilst the details of the project remain highly classified, during the first Galactic War an advanced weapons lab on the planet of &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt; was working on the development of a powerful interplanetary battle station. However, the project was abandoned along with the laboratory (and the planet) due to high levels of radiation on X-45 -- possibly following the responsible use of planet-wide nuclear weapons bombardment.\nAfter a little over two months of intense research on the 25th of September, 2184, construction of the Democracy Space Station was finally ready to begin. The DSS promised to be a powerful strategic tool for reshaping the Galactic Map \u2014 democratically directed by the Helldivers themselves. However to actually construct the DSS, an orbital construction site must first be secured.\nOf the planets within Super Earth's reach, only two have large enough &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetosphere\"&gt;magnetospheres&lt;/a&gt; for safe construction: &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Clasa\"&gt;Clasa&lt;/a&gt;. Ultimately, the Helldivers would liberate Gaellivare from the Automatons', with a &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;DSS Logistics Hub&lt;/a&gt; being set up nearby to manage the massive inflow of resources and manpower to the new construction site.\nHowever, to build a weapon of mass liberation of this size, the Helldivers will need to make significant advancements in three key areas: zero-g materials science, FTL propulsion, and gigastructure staffing. The Helldivers will be indispensable in achieving these breakthroughs. Helldivers are advised that failing any DSS-related order will cause delays in construction. A project of this scale cannot be concealed indefinitely; if construction drags out too long, our enemies will eventually discover its location, and attempt to destroy it. However, our citizens need not fear. With the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; protecting it, the Democracy Space Station will soon be ready to rain down the will of the people on any who would stand in its way.\nAdditionally, during construction, the DSS will be extremely vulnerable to attack, so long-term defensibility is paramount. The DSS could change the course of the war. Its ultimate success or failure lies in the hands of our greatest heroes: the Helldivers.\nPhase 1.\nUpon liberation, a DSS Logistics Hub on &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt; was built to support the mass scale of the construction; Super Earth High Command determined that zero-g materials, FTL propulsion, and gigastructure staffing needed significant advancements to make the DSS a reality. High Command also reminded Helldivers that they would be crucial in the defense of the DSS should it come under attack, and any failures to do so would delay its construction.\nSoon after establishing the DSS, High Command began tasking the Helldivers to liberate planets to establish facilities for the advancements needed for the DSS. &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; was selected to build the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science's&lt;/a&gt; new Xenoentomology Center for high-efficiency Alcubierre drives. Helldivers quickly liberated the planet from the Terminid scourge while also defending Tarsh's Logistics Hub. High Command noted that the Center would still need to be defended from any potential attacks or research will be lost.\nTo create FTL-resistant alloy for the DSS, a deep-mantle forge would be required due to the extreme heat and pressure. Luckily, High Command found that the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Claorell\"&gt;Claorell&lt;/a&gt; already had a deep-mantle mining complex. Seeking to repurpose it into something more democratic, High Command ordered the Helldivers to liberate Claorell and seize the complex. They would be successful, filling the mines with Super Earth's own in the new Deep Mantle Forge Complex. However, High Command found intel that revealed that the Automatons were creating &lt;a href=\"Automatons%23Jet%20Brigade\"&gt;exceptionally light metal for armor plating&lt;/a&gt;. Not long after, the Automatons attempted to take back Claorell, accompanied by cyberattacks on DSS-related servers. The Helldivers would be successful in defending Claorell; the cyberattacks revealed the DSS project to the Automatons, but the DSS's exact location remains a mystery to them--for now.\nPhase 2.\nWith the Xenoentomology Center and Deep Mantle Forge Complex built, the DSS moved into Phase 2. Due to the DSS's scale, it would require significant amounts of E-710, leading to the establishment of the Terminid Research Preserve on &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;. It would provide research capabilities and another source of E-710. The Helldivers would need to liberate and hold the nearby planets of Crimsica, Turing, Darius II, Pandion-XXIV, and Gacrux to establish a planetary quarantine zone around Acamar IV. The Helldivers would successfully create the quarantine needed for the construction of the Terminid Research Preserve, furthering E-710 research.\nThe peace following Super Earth's victory would not last long, as the Automatons would launch an assault group, the Jet Brigade, onto numerous planets, in search of the DSS. In a war of attrition, the Helldivers bravely fought against the relentless Jet Brigade. Though the Jet Brigade managed to capture &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;, they were eventually weak enough to be stopped on &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the Helldivers' efforts, the Automatons were unable to find the DSS and its related facilities.\nTo further protect the DSS, High Command determined that liberating &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt; would provide a defensive buffer for the DSS against a potential Jet Brigade assault. However, a sudden &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; outbreak on &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; threatened the newly-built Terminid Research Preserve. The Helldivers were then left to decide which to prioritize, in which they chose to liberate Lesath. Another Terminid outbreak would occur on Pandion-XXIV, eventually leading to its fall alongside Gacrux. The DSS will continue to stay protected, but the Terminid Research Preserve is now dangerously close to heavy Terminid presence.\nPhase 3.\nThe continued protection of the DSS has allowed it to advance to its final construction phase before its long-awaited completion.\nCompletion.\nThe DSS construction was declared complete on November 11, 2184. All that remains is the necessary E-710 to bring it online. Around 10000 Helldivers have deployed to &lt;a href=\"Trandor\"&gt;Trandor&lt;/a&gt; in order to get the necessary fuel to power the ship. At the DSS itself, the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; have re-launched the Jet Brigade, and are still trying to find out the DSS\u2019s location. They have attacked the logistic hub of &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;, and while we may lose the planet, as long as Gaellivare itself is under our control, there should be no issues. Only time will tell if the planet is attacked, and Helldivers are to be on high alert in the coming days for any other attacks.\nActivation.\nFinally, on November 13th, 2184, at 21:37 SEST - EST, the required amount of E-710 for the DSS Activation was completed, allowing the Helldivers to vote on the Democracy Space Station's first deployment and donate samples towards its functions.\nAmong its first actions was supporting a counterattack on &lt;a href=\"Mastia\"&gt;Mastia&lt;/a&gt;, from which the &lt;a href=\"Automatons%23Jet%20Brigade\"&gt;Jet Brigade&lt;/a&gt; launched its attack on Gaellivare, having discovered the DSS' location a few days prior. Despite a ferocious day of continuous orbital barrage, Mastia remained under Automaton control. DSS administrators noticed a troubling increase in Helldiver and civilian deaths despite orders to take shelter indoors. Helldiver deployments were increased to bring the death toll back to an acceptable level. Use of the &lt;a href=\"FX-12%20Shield%20Generator%20Relay\"&gt;FX-12 Shield Generator Relay&lt;/a&gt; was also authorized.\nThe next day, the DSS returned to Gaellivare to support the planet's defense. Here too, operations were difficult as an Eagle Storm deployed to the surface initially targeted inactive areas. High Command ordered Eagle wings to more directly support Helldivers, resulting in a successful Major Order, yet still posing a risk of losing Gaellivare only shortly afterward, and another spurious surge in Helldiver casualties.\nThe Helldiver Corps then voted to send the DSS to &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt; to impose a blockade, despite no active attacks by Terminid forces. Successfully taking it out of the reach of the Automatons as Gaellivare was left to it's fate. \nSabotage, De-activation and Repairs.\nOver the coming weeks, the Democracy would prove itself an invaluable -- if temperamental -- weapon of mass liberation. Yet despite bringing freedom and managed democracy to over a dozen worlds, the dissident enemies of managed democracy will stop at nothing to stop Super Earth's noble mission. Following multiple catastrophic system failures in the middle of Operation Bughammer, the Democracy Space Station would be forcibly (and hopefully temporarily) taken offline. Naturally sabotage is suspected, with all 1.3 million personnel aboard the DSS to undergo security screenings whilst the station is locked down for repairs. \nHowever whether by design or pure coincidence, shortly after the Democracy Space Station was shuttered for refit, the Federation would face it's greatest challenge yet as the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; returned to the Galaxy and invaded &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; on December 12th, starting a new and deadly \"&lt;a href=\"Southern%20Front\"&gt;Southern Front&lt;/a&gt;\" to the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;second galactic war&lt;/a&gt;. Never the less, freedom waits for nobody and so the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; will have to make do fighting off the xenophobic squids without their greatest weapon for the time being... \nTactical Actions.\nThe Democracy Space Station possesses 3 Tactical Actions. Players can donate resources to help activate any of the 3 functions for the next 24 hours, but only 1 tactical action can be active at a time. The amount of resources, as well as the type they can donate, can be found below. \nOrbital Blockade.\nVoting.\nEvery 24 hours, the Helldivers can vote to move the DSS to a different planet or keep it at its current location. After the 24 hours have passed, the planet with the most votes becomes the new DSS location and new votes can be cast. Helldivers may not change their vote after submitting, so it is recommended to think twice before voting.\nThe list of possible DSS locations does NOT currently update alongside the Galactic War Map, instead appearing to function on a \"snapshot\" mechanic, where the list will be created using only the planets that were accessible in the moments after the DSS moved. This can lead to discrepancies, such as the Helldivers being able to vote for the DSS to be sent to a planet that may be inaccessible, such as when the DSS was sent to &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Jetclipper\"&gt;Operation Jetclipper&lt;/a&gt; despite Choohe being cut off the FTL Network. As such, caution is advised when voting.\nJudging by how the Democracy Space Station came online on November 13th, 2024, at 21:37 EST (18:37 PST / 3:37 CET in Stockholm, Sweden / 2:37 GMT in London, United Kingdom), it may be prudent to check in at this time daily in order to donate resources and vote for the next DSS Location again. This recommendation will be rescinded once there is more information regarding how the 24-hour limit works for the DSS functions."}
