{"id": "3362", "revid": "57557", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3362", "title": "Devastator", "text": "The ironclad Devastator seeks to crush opponents of the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; totalitarian worldview with a diverse array of heinous weaponry: arm cannons, arm shields, arm-machine guns, and shoulder-mounted rocket pods. \nThey can be divided into three types: \nSimilarly to the lowly Trooper, it seems an increasing percentage of all Devastator types are replaced with tougher \"Elite\" variants on higher difficulties. Unlike Troopers, who seem to have different loadouts for their Elites, the only visual difference between the regular and Elite Devastators is that regular Devastators have light grey heads, while Elite variants have maroon heads.\nTrivia.\nThe standard Devastator has a gear above its head, which could reference the Iron Halo, a personal shield generator that high-ranking Space Marines wear. The Heavy Devastator, with its shield and heavy cannon, could refer to a common loadout of Terminator marines: an Assault Cannon and a Storm Shield. The Rocket Devastator\u2019s top-mounted rocket pods look almost identical to a Terminator\u2019s Cyclone Rockets."}
