{"id": "6550", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6550", "title": "EAT-17 Expendable Anti-Tank", "text": "\"A single-use weapon specialised for damaging vehicle armour targets. Discard after every use.\"\nThe EAT-17 Expendable Anti-Tank is one of the &lt;a href=\"stratagems\"&gt;stratagems&lt;/a&gt; available to the player at Level 3.\nThe EAT-17 behaves as a single-use, low commitment version of the &lt;a href=\"GR-8%20Recoilless%20Rifle\"&gt;GR-8 Recoilless Rifle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"LAS-99%20Quasar%20Cannon\"&gt;LAS-99 Quasar Cannon&lt;/a&gt; unlocked later on. All 3 of these weapons deal the same damage, but have different ammo and reload mechanics. With a quick restock time, two rockets per stratagem, and no need for a Backpack, the EAT-17 is a major boon for even higher-leveled players on harder difficulties or on the move. Be aware that the &lt;a href=\"GR-8%20Recoilless%20Rifle\"&gt;GR-8 Recoilless Rifle&lt;/a&gt; is substantially more effective during objective defenses, though, as only having two rockets and no ability to restock from supply or ammo packs means the player may be caught with no more ammunition, and depending on strategem roster, few other high effect options against hard targets.\nIf standing on an objective for an extended period of time, it is recommended to call down as many EATs as possible in order to stockpile them for extra uses.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this single-use &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:"}
