{"id": "5954", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5954", "title": "Elysian Meadows", "text": " is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Guang%20Sector\"&gt;Guang Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Valmox\"&gt;Valmox&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nElysian Meadows was a peaceful colony of Super Earth that resided in the southern sectors of the Milky Way, which spared it much of the horrors of the Second Galactic War. Much like other planets around it, such as &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bellatrix\"&gt;Bellatrix&lt;/a&gt;, the colonists at Elysian Meadows would first struggle but then, as they became more accustomed to their environment, they began to find success and prosperity until they managed to accumulate enough wealth to build urbanized settlements on which to house its ever-growing population. However, the colonists at Elysian Meadows were being stalked from within the endless depths of space.\nThe , an ancient foe of Super Earth that had been defeated once during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, had now returned and was seeking revenge. On December 21st, the Illuminate would send a raid onto the planet, amidst a major order centered on the &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridian Singularity&lt;/a&gt;. The Helldivers that could were immediately deployed onto Elysian Meadows, while the bulk of the force focused on holding the line at &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Erata%20Prime\"&gt;Erata Prime&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nElysian Meadows is a reference to the \"Elysian Fields\" or \"Elysian Plains\", which is a conception of the afterlife that developed over time and was maintained by some Greek religious and philosophical sects and cults. It was initially separated from the Greek underworld \u2013 the realm of Hades. Only mortals related to the gods and other heroes could be admitted past the river Styx. Later, the conception of who could enter was expanded to include those chosen by the gods, the righteous, and the heroic. They would remain at the Elysian Fields after death, to live a blessed and happy afterlife, and indulge in whatever they had enjoyed in life.\nThe name Elysian Meadows suggests that the planet is quite pleasant and implies that it is a location where many veteran SEAF and Helldivers have retired to after completing service and are exceptionally democratic individuals."}
{"id": "5124", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5124", "title": "Emergency Evacuation", "text": "Emergency Evacuation is a mission that can be found on almost every difficulty. It shares the likeness of the &lt;a href=\"Retrieve%20Essential%20Personnel\"&gt;Retrieve Essential Personnel&lt;/a&gt; mission, however instead of simply evacuating the personnel, the Helldiver must do 1-2 sub objectives before being able to do so.\nA similar Evacuate Colonists mission appears on planets threatened by &lt;a href=\"The%20Illuminate\"&gt;The Illuminate&lt;/a&gt;. Building layouts are adapted for the urban environment, but the mission progresses in a similar manner.\nGameplay.\nAt the start of this mission, an Evacuation Shuttle will approach the site and land in its Shuttle Bay. It will wait there until the mandated number of civilians have been collected.\nStep 1: Establish Communication Uplink(s).\nBefore being able to evacuate the civilians the Helldiver must first activate the designated Communications Tower(s) to notify the civilians that help is on the way. There will always be at least one of these sub objectives, however on Suicide Mission (7) + there will be guaranteed two that must be completed before initiating the evacuation. \nWhen entering the area of a Communications Tower the Helldiver will be granted access to the \"SSSD Delivery\" stratagem that is required to call in to progress the sub-objective. It is recommended to call this in immediately, that way the SSSD is at the ready when needed. There will be a nearby terminal that the Helldiver must log in to using the standard directional inputs. After logging in, they will be required to open the SSSD Hatch on the nearby uplink box. From there they must take the SSSD that was dropped via stratagem and insert it into the uplink box and then use the terminal to align the communication signal to 100% strength. Once finished, the Helldiver must put in one final directional code to finish the sub objective.\nStep 2: Evacuate Priority Citizens.\nOnce the sub objective(s) has been completed the Helldiver may go to the designated location to begin the evacuation process. Upon arrival there will be a handful of hostiles to be eliminated, after which it is recommended that Helldivers deploy defensive stratagems such as turrets and mortars. During this time the Helldiver can see an evacuation shuttle fly down from orbit and land inside the evacuation building. \nWhen the Helldiver is ready, they can access the Terminal located in front of said evacuation building by logging in, setting the evacuation coordinates, and opening the shuttle bay door. From there the Helldiver must go to the local shelter doors and hit the button located just outside of them, notifying the civilians inside that they may move to the evacuation building. There will always be two shelter doors to access civilians from, whereas there are always three on the Evacuate Essential Personnel mission. Each shelter door can be accessed once every 33 seconds, and will deploy three civilians that will run to the evacuation building. It is the Helldivers' job to ensure their safety and get them there alive. Once the required amount of civilians have made it to the evacuation building, the mission will be considered complete and the Helldiver can watch the evacuation shuttle leave the building and fly into orbit."}
