{"id": "5788", "revid": "58010", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5788", "title": "Encirclements", "text": "An Encirclment is a regions of a faction that is surrounded by an enemy faction. Most Encirclements during the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; are destroyed but some like the Ymir Encirclment hold on long enough for them to be broken out and join the main force.\nYmir Encirclement.\nThe Ymir Encirclement was a region of Super Earth space from May 21st to June 10th and from June 11th to July 16th. It was created when &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt; was invaded by the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; cutting the only &lt;a href=\"FTL%20Lines\"&gt;FTL line&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt; also was invaded blocking FTL access to the Sector. After &lt;a href=\"Vega%20Bay\"&gt;Vega Bay&lt;/a&gt; fell, &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt; was the only planet under Super Earth control in the sector. Vega Bay would be liberated during Operation Firewall making to so X-45 was not surrounded by Automaton controlled world but it did not have FTL lines to any of them intel 3 days later. &lt;a href=\"Ustotu\"&gt;Ustotu&lt;/a&gt; would be attacked cutting the only FTL line again. Little happened after this and before Operation Starslayer accept &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt; being invaded. During Operation Starslayer the Automatons would take Wezen and Bega Bay reaching X-45 but being beaten back. Operation Andromeda was the Operation to finally end the Ymir Encirclment and free the forces trapped inside, ending with the liberation of &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;.\nMatar Bay Encirclement.\nThe Matar Bay Encirclement was a region of Automaton space from July 14th to August 14th, 2184 that was cut of from &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and the main Automaton force. During Operation Andromeda, the pocket was formed by the successful captures of &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;. The latter half of Operation Andromeda, as well as Operation Righteous Expunge were dedicated to clearing the &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt; of resistance. Operation Liberty Crush was the largest offensive against the encirclement, pushing it to only three planets. Further efforts in August during Operation Lighthouse led to the complete destruction of Automaton forces in the pocket.\nHistory.\nOn July 14th, this entire region of space was separated from &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan's&lt;/a&gt; supply lines with the fall of Matar Bay. After Operation Starslayer's successful defence of Super Earth holdings in the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir sector&lt;/a&gt;, the Automatons were left weakened and vulnerable. Only Aesir Pass and Matar Bay were left to connect their supply lines in the far west. On July 11th, the Helldivers began the offensive to form the pocket. By the end of the operation, &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt; were retaken from the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;. \nOn July 17th, the operation came to an end. The severely weakened state of the Automaton forces meant that small groups of Helldivers could make progress even without a major order to direct them. By July 18th, small forces ranging from 200 - 1000 had made ~4% of liberation progress on &lt;a href=\"Vega%20Bay\"&gt;Vega Bay&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt;. Operation Righteous Expunge targeted Charon Prime for liberation, a task already well underway by remnants of the attacking force on Martale.\nBy July 21st, Operation Righteous Expunge had seen the liberation of &lt;a href=\"Choepessa%20IV\"&gt;Choepessa IV&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII,&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charon%20Prime\"&gt;Charon Prime.&lt;/a&gt;\nOperation Liberty Crush began on July 27th, 2184 with the aim of clearing out this region. Prior to this, significant parts of &lt;a href=\"Choepessa%20IV\"&gt;Choepessa&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt; were occupied by the enemy. This operation saw the recapture of Wasat shortly thereafter, but just as Vega Bay was almost retaken, X-45 came under attack on the 30th. This assault would reconnect Automaton forces to the pocket if Vega Bay was not captured. By the end of this operation, only &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt; remained in enemy hands.\nOn August 10th, the final campaign to end the Matar Bay Encirclement began. Wezen was captured in the previous days without a Major Order. Operation Finest Phalanx dictated that Troost and Vandalon IV must be captured by August 15th. Vandalon fell rapidly, with Troost near defeat on the 13th.\nThe encirclement was finally destroyed with the fall of &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt; on August 14th. Celebrations broke out across free space, with citizens burning scrap metal to celebrate this final defeat.\nMarspira Encirclement.\nThe Marspira Encirclement was a region of Automaton space that was cut of from &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and the main Automaton force from September 1st to September 8th. The Encirclement was created when &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt; was liberated cutting of &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mastia\"&gt;Mastia&lt;/a&gt; from the main Automatons forces. This would continue for 7 days intel &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt; fell to the Automatons and re-connected it to &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;.\nTanis Encirclment.\nThe Tanis Encirclement was a region of Automaton space that was cut of from &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and the main Automaton force from October 25th to November 22nd and November 25th to December 27. The Encirclement was created when &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt; was liberated cutting all FTL line to Cyberstan to the Sector. The Encirclment was made of three planets &lt;a href=\"Vog-Sojoth\"&gt;Vog-Sojoth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Clasa\"&gt;Clasa&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Zefia\"&gt;Zefia&lt;/a&gt;. Instead of Enemy Resistance falling to 0.00% the planets stayed at 2% or 1.5%, this is why &lt;a href=\"Yed%20Prior\"&gt;Yed Prior&lt;/a&gt; was able to be invaded by encircled forces on October 27th and &lt;a href=\"Blistica\"&gt;Blistica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mintoria\"&gt;Mintoria&lt;/a&gt; on the 28th, extending the Encirclment into the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt;'s invasion was repelled on the 31st and &lt;a href=\"Demiurg\"&gt;Demiurg&lt;/a&gt; on the 1st. Nothing would happen in the encirclement intel &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt; was invaded on the 21st of November, with its fall a day later Automaton forces were re-connected with the main force ending the encirclement. Not 3 days later Lesath would be liberated re-cutting the &lt;a href=\"FTL%20Lines\"&gt;FTL line&lt;/a&gt; this also coincided with the second attack on Zzaniah Prime which succeeded, but after this the front when silent intel Operation Crop Dust this would kick out the Automatons from the Gellert Sector, the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;DSS&lt;/a&gt; was deployed the Zzaniah Prime then Mintoria and then Blistica liberated all three in three days. After this the DSS was deployed the Vog-Sojoth and was then sabotaged unable to leave the system. Nothing happened after this and the return of the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; intel the 26th when Lesath was attacked, the defence failed and the encirclement was over.\nGar Haren Encirclment.\nThe Gar Haren Encirclement was a region of Terminid space that was cut of from the main Terminid force from from October 29 to November 22nd. The Encirclement was created when &lt;a href=\"Phact%20Bay\"&gt;Phact Bay&lt;/a&gt; was liberated during Operation Adamant Resolve cutting &lt;a href=\"Gar%20Haren\"&gt;Gar Haren&lt;/a&gt; of from the Terminid FTL network. Gar Haren would stay as encircled for nearly a month intel the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;DSS&lt;/a&gt; was deployed to Gar Haren quickly liberating it and ending the encirclement.\nMartale Encirclements.\nThe Martale Encirclement is a region of Automaton space that is cut of from &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and the main Automaton force since October 30th. There have been two Martale Encirclements. The First Martale Encirclements was after &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt; was liberated cutting of access to &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt; during Operation Adamant Resolve and ended when Matar Bay was reinvaded by the Automatons 1 month after they left. The Second Martale Encirclements was after Matar Bay was liberated again cutting of access from Cyberstan, the encirclement has not been broken and Enemy Resistance on Martale has remained at 0.00%. "}
{"id": "6219", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6219", "title": "Enemies", "text": "\nThe &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; are a fast-spreading insectoid species that wreak havoc among the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; dominion.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; are ruthless, remorseless, Democracy-hating robots that thrive on killing Super Earth Civilians and are hell-bent on destroying everything that Super Earth has built.\nOnce thought to be eradicated during the First Galactic War nearly a hundred years ago, the Illuminate has resurfaced out of thin air, wreaking havoc in the Super Earth settlements."}
{"id": "6002", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6002", "title": "Enuliale", "text": "Enuliale is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"L%27estrade%20Sector\"&gt;L'estrade Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nUnknown. Similar to &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gatria\"&gt;Gatria&lt;/a&gt;, judging by its appearance on the Galactic Map before the appearance of The Gloom\nDue to the appearance of the Gloom, Enuliale has disappeared from the Galactic Map, making it impossible to know for certain how it may look presently. For convenience, the pre-gloom aspect will be preserved\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nEnuliale was one of the first planets to fall during the initial Terminid outbreak in February 2184. It has remained unreachable to Helldivers from the start, leaving its residing Terminid pests a horror yet to be cleansed off the face of the galaxy.\nEnuliale would lay in relative inactivity for several months, as the Terminids moved back and forth between &lt;a href=\"Omicron\"&gt;Omicron&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Barrier Planets&lt;/a&gt;. However, its Terminid Brood would seemingly be up to only one thing: Spreading Fascism throughout the entire galaxy.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Benevolent Sanitation.\nOn August 6th, 2184, SEAF Outer Reconnaissance outposts in nearby &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt; would report the apparition of new Terminid variants alongside a strange space cloud composed of an unusually high concentration of intergalactic Terminid spores. As such, Super Earth High Command would issue an order to the Helldivers to quarantine the &lt;a href=\"Falstaff%20Sector\"&gt;Falstaff Sector&lt;/a&gt; and conduct immediate eradication operations on Socorro III, as it faced the greatest Terminid onslaught of the war so far.\nThis would be the first time that Super Earth's scientists would spot &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt;. From Enuliale, this fascist nebula has spread its spores throughout the L'estrade sector unopposed, now encroaching upon more planets in the neighbouring sectors.\nAt some point, SEAF Satellites would be unable to continue monitoring the Gloom, due to the increase of spore concentration in the Gloom."}
