{"id": "5152", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5152", "title": "Evacuate High-Value Assets", "text": "The Evacuate High-Value Assets is a limited-time mission that was playable during the Reclamation Event that started April 9th 2024. It serves as a form of tower-defense mode where the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; hold a defensive line against an onslaught of hostiles while several rockets filled with Helldivers in cryo-sleep get sent to orbit.\nGameplay.\nThe mission begins with the Helldivers dropping to the designated area as they are given 1 minute and 30 seconds to set up their defensive positions; this can be bypassed by manually activating the evacuation via a button panel near the rocket launch pad. The general layout consists of several blast doors that can be manually opened and closed in a tight path that leads to the evacuation rockets. These blast doors act as a form of barrier to help keep the enemy out as they would have to destroy it to get past it, backing up enemy traffic and making them easy targets to obliterate. Multiple &lt;a href=\"E/MG-101%20HMG%20Emplacement\"&gt;HMG turrets&lt;/a&gt; can be found on walls that can be utilized against the attacking forces, however they have limited ammunition so it's advised to use them wisely.\nThe primary objective is to hold the onslaught back until all rockets have been sent to orbit, from there the Helldivers are tasked with an immediate evacuation order and are extracted via &lt;a href=\"Pelican-1\"&gt;Pelican&lt;/a&gt;. The enemy's main goal is to break through the Helldiver's defenses and destroy two exposed generators that power the evacuation rockets that lie underground. If they are destroyed, the mission is considered an absolute failure and the Helldivers are forced to either extract or die."}
