{"id": "4094", "revid": "31024592", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4094", "title": "Factions", "text": "In Helldivers 2, there are multiple factions, most of them being hostile and with the only one able to be played being the only correct one, Super Earth.\nBelow, some of the factions have been listed.\nFaction Overview.\n\"For more information, consult the article on the Terminids by clicking the title above\"\nThe Terminids are a race of alien insects that descend from the from . Much like their ancestors, the Bugs' main prowess are their sheer quantity, as they rely mostly on swarm attacks and melee combat with very few exceptions.\n\"For more information, consult the article on the Automatons by clicking the title above\"\nThe Automatons are a legion of murderous robots originating from deep space. They heavily resemble the from Helldivers 1, but it is still unconfirmed what relationship they may have with the exactly. However, it can be assumed that the Automatons were created by the Cyborgs in order to wage war against Super Earth once again.\nThe Automatons are focused on more conventional military tactics, relying on artillery and firepower to engage and kill Helldivers from a distance. When engaging with the Automatons, the best approach can be to find cover and shoot or to strike and scatter, so long as neither tactic ends up extending the fight for too long before the enemy fire inevitably overwhelms the players.\n\"For more information, consult the article on the Illuminate by clicking the title above\"\nThe are an alien species dedicated to xenophobia and mysticism, preying on innocent frontier colonists to mutate and brainwash them into hordes of mindless slaves. Originally defeated during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, they were presumed extinct. However, on December 12th, 2184, the Illuminate would return from their presumed extinction, decided to get their revenge on Humanity.\nThe Illuminate present a balanced mixture of both the frenetic, fast-paced hordes of the Terminids in the form of the hordes of the &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt;, while also posing a vastly amplified threat at range with their specialized units, requiring Helldivers to remain able to adapt to any situation at any moment.\n\"For more information, consult the article on the Federation of Super Earth by clicking the title above\"\nThe Federation of Super Earth is the player faction. After a century of peace following the end of the First Galactic War in Helldivers 1, it finds itself besieged once again by fascist bugs and socialist robots who seek to destroy the human race. Fittingly, Humanity has called upon its mightiest heroes in order to fight back against these villainous aliens: The &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3900", "revid": "57246", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3900", "title": "Factory Strider", "text": "Called \"Walkers\" by some Helldivers, the Factory Striders are giant, heavily armed behemoths of steel and socialism. As walking Factories on legs, Factory Striders can be found at Automaton outposts or be dropped into battle, firing their cannons and dual miniguns at Helldivers and fabricating batches of Standard &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastator&lt;/a&gt;s, or roam across the planet's surface providing supporting fire wherever it can. Due to their functionality, it is unsurprising that Automatons can quickly deploy and spread on Super Earth colonies. \nFactory Striders are extremely tough targets, with many Helldivers reporting they can survive several 500kg bomb direct hits. \nOn April 16th, Reports confirmed that the Factory Striders encountered during the latter stages of Operation Swift Disassembly were prototypes on test runs and are now being mass-produced. Reports have also confirmed that factory striders can be transported and dropped off by dropships. The Super-Earth command has approved new missions targeting the destruction of factory striders."}
{"id": "3290", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3290", "title": "Falstaff Sector", "text": "The Falstaff Sector is a sector found on the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;Eastern Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It consists of 4 planets. The sector likely gets it's name from &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Falstaff\"&gt;Sir John \"Falstaff\"&lt;/a&gt;, a fictional character who appears in three plays by William Shakespeare and is eulogised in a fourth."}
