{"id": "6367", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6367", "title": "Federation of Super Earth", "text": "The Federation of Super Earth, commonly referred to as , The Federation or Super Earth Federation, is the largest faction in the Milky Way, consisting of 261 &lt;a href=\"Planets%20and%20Sectors\"&gt;planets&lt;/a&gt; grouped into 55 Sectors. Super Earth follows a system of government called Managed Democracy, in which citizens must fill out a form from which an AI will take the answers and produce who you truly want to vote for. The population of the Federation is centered around &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, with small colonial outposts scattered about the Galaxy. The &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;Super Earth Armed Forces&lt;/a&gt; (SEAF) have billions of active personal and an elite &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers Corp&lt;/a&gt;, millions strong.\nGalactic Geography.\nThe Federation spans billions, if not trillions of kilometers of the Milky Way, split up into 55 Sectors. The size of the sectors and number of planets inside of them vary. The sectors furthest away from Super Earth have a larger distance between planets, but have around the same amount of planets as ones next to Super Earth. The abundant amounts of resources owned by the Federation grows the industrial capability and fuels the colonization of the galaxy.\n&lt;a href=\"Biomes\"&gt;Biomes&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Federation is home to many exotic biomes with many different life forms. Super Earth has observed 20 different biomes inside of their borders. \nColonial Outposts.\nOn nearly every planet on the Galactic Frontier, colonial outposts are inhabited by Super Earth citizens and are established by the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Expansion\"&gt;Ministry of Expansion&lt;/a&gt;. These outposts are the lifeline of future expansion of Managed Democracy and are seen as a major priority by the SEAF, which has dedicated many troops to these areas of space. The outposts mostly consist of cutting-edge facilities inhabited by the bravest, strongest and most capable members of the Federation.\nUrban Colonies.\nOn some economically successful planets, such as &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kerth%20Secundus\"&gt;Kerth Secundus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mog\"&gt;Mog&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Genesis%20Prime\"&gt;Genesis Prime&lt;/a&gt; among others, many urbanized settlements have been built, complete with streets, parks, tall apartment buildings, offices, working electricity, water and waste management infrastructure, Anti-Air Defenses, SEAF Artillery Batteries and all the commodities expected in urban life. These thriving worlds are among the most shining examples of the prosperity that Managed Democracy can bring to all the worlds it touches.\nHistory.\nThe Great War.\nThe Great War, or the Third World War, was a nuclear conflict that reduced the majority of the Northern Hemisphere into a radioactive wasteland. It is unknown when the war occurred, but it was likely sometime between the years 2015 and 2044. The war was presumably between two superpowers, most likely the United States of America and China and their allies. Russia and the United Kingdom were almost entirely destroyed during the nuclear exchange, along with sections of Alaska and Canada. However, the United States of America and China survived, seemingly unscathed.\nProclamation of the Federation of Super Earth.\nAfter the presumed collapse of social order as a result of the worldwide destruction caused by the Great War, the world was left in a state of disarray, with abundant misinformation, disinformation, and information, causing a state of \"democratic anarchy\". Amidst this anarchy, a new idea emerged as the Democratic Council came together to form a new government and publish the first and final draft of a new way forward for mankind: Managed Democracy. This council went on to form a new globe-spanning government and would gain control of what remained of Earth. They then proclaimed the birth of the greatest nation in Human history, the Federation of Super Earth.\nFirst Contact and the First Galactic War.\nIn the year 2044, as humanity began to venture into space thanks to the invention of the Alcubierre Drive a decade prior, they came into contact with two hostile alien species: the and The . First contact turned sour and war broke out. Another front eventually opened up with the , socialists who disagreed with the ways of Managed Democracy and were subsequently outcast to a barren snowy wasteland of a planet, which they named &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;. To survive these harsh conditions, the Cyborgs replaced their body parts with cybernetic implants. After detonating a massive bomb on a Super Earth city-planet, killing thousands, they were brought into war with the Federation. After 40 years, the Galactic War raged on until Super Earth began enlisting highly elite solders called &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt;. Within just 40 days of the Helldivers entering the war, all enemies of Managed Democracy were defeated in a decisive Super Earth Victory. The Bugs were relegated into farms to be contained, bred, and harvested for E-710. The Cyborgs were enfranchised in the mines of &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;, and The were driven from the galaxy.\nThe Great Democratization.\nAfter the swift victory of Super Earth at the end of the First Galactic War in 2084, the Federation had become the New Galactic Order, unquestioned across the stars. FTL technology that had been liberated from the The during the war was now used to colonize the galaxy in the name of Super Earth. This period would be come to be named as the \"The Great Democratization\". For 100 years, this period of peace, freedom and democracy allowed Humanity to expand and develop. FTL travel required E-710, so &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; farms were created to safely contain them and harvest the E-710 that they produce at an industrial scale. \nSecond Galactic War.\nOn February 8th, 2184, two massive simultaneous attacks on the Federation took place. To the East, the , now , broke out of their farms and wreaked havoc on the colonists living there. , robotic machines resembling the from 100 years ago, invaded the &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Immediately, the Helldiver Corps was remobilized at such a scale not seen since the last days of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. The war has been going on for 8 months now, with no end in sight. The Automatons have invaded &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;, the Terminid Control System has failed, and a &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; has been created and destroyed. A mysterious spore cloud called &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt; engulfs system after system, emitting from Terminid territory and getting closer to &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. The Automaton are now only one sector away from the home of Managed Democracy.\nThen, an event previously thought impossible would heighten the stakes of the Second Galactic War like nothing did before. In the midst of another Terminid offensive, the ongoing major order would be immediately aborted, as all Helldivers were immediately ordered into LIBCON 1 as a distress signal came from &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;. The unthinkable had just ocurred... The , thought extinct ever since their banishing after the First Galactic War, had returned and, worst of all, had begun abducting citizens and stripping them off their freedom, turning them into hordes of &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; zombies that ran rampant across Calypso's urban colonies.\nDecember 12th, 2184, would be a date that would go down in infamy, as every Helldiver in the Corps would immediately deploy onto Calypso to face this returning foe once again. After 3 days of battle, the Helldivers managed to repel the Illuminate at Calypso but, instead of surrendering, the squids continued to assault Super Earth colonies.\nChronologically uncertain events.\nOutbreak of the Carcino-Plague.\nWith the addition of the \"Chemical Agents\" warbond, a new event is mentioned in the descriptions of the \"Patient Zero's Remembrance\" and \"Standard of Safe Distance\" capes, which is the \"Outbreak of the Carcino-Plague\". It is unknown when this outbreak took place, with the only thing certain being that it must have occurred prior to the Second Galactic War, as no such illness is mentioned by any of the NPCs, nor has it been brought up in any major order at all.\nAt some point, the outbreak became bad enough to warrant the interment of those infected into quarantine zones, from which the SEAF would then recruit certain members for a new army division dubbed \"Division Zero\", a division specialized in biological warfare by having its soldiers spread their illness on the battlefield.\nJudging by how this illness is described, it is (or maybe was) a highly contagious disease, as its carriers are described to have been conscripted into the SEAF for the express purpose of spreading it. However, given that people infected with said disease were conscripted, it is possible, however unlikely, that the disease itself wasn't virulent enough to kill or seriously incapacitate its host (at least, not human hosts).\nGiven by how this disease is not mentioned anywhere else in either Helldivers 1 or Helldivers 2, it is possible that this outbreak occured during the 100 years between both games. It is also possible that the Carcino-Plague was eradicated during said time period.\nGovernment and Politics.\nSuper Earth is the galaxy's oldest known &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unitary_state\"&gt;unitary&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sovereign_state\"&gt;sovereign&lt;/a&gt; state, governed by the core values of prosperity, liberty, and democracy. All of its political institutions are headquartered in Prosperity City. Super Earth's government is composed of many administrative-level branches of government. \nCitizens of the Federation of Super Earth use automated voting software; they answer a few questions on the Galactic Wide Web (GWW) and the computer votes for them based on their answers. The GWW is a network of interlinked communication devices that transmits data using quantum communication, \"very elementary stuff\" according to the ship's C.O.\nNational Government.\nBranches of Government.\nThrough the many hints delivered throughout both games, it is safe to assume that Super Earth has some sort of separation of powers, as it is stated to have a \"President\" and \"Senators\" such as John W. Killjoy, and \"House Representatives\" such as Powley Colle. A \"Democratic Council\" is also mentioned in Helldivers 2 in one of the Broadcast Announcements and in one of the official lore videos, which most likely serves as a possible judiciary organ, thus establishing a possible Judicial branch.\nExecutive Branch.\nPresident.\nThe President of Super Earth serves as either the head of state or the head of government of the Federation, if not both. This information is not made clear in either of the games. Another piece of information that is unclear is the hierarchy of the government of Super Earth. The only executive role mentioned besides that of the President of Super Earth is that of the respective Colonial Overseers that can be found across the various planets one visits.\nSo far, the only president of Super Earth that is known to have canonically existed is Hannah S.C, the former president of Super Earth whose name can be found in commemorative plaques etched onto certain monuments that can be found in urban colonies. Who the current president of Super Earth is isn't know.\nColonial Overseer.\nColonial Overseers are the people responsible for making sure that planetary colonies remain stable, loyal, and productive. It is explained through in-game ads and posters that each Colonial Overseer is elected through suffrage, and that the Colonial Overseers often receive instructions from the SEAF to remain on their respective planets to help with their defense. This can be inferred by the SEAF Communication Devices that are found across the many planets in Helldivers 2.\nMinistries.\n\"The following is an excerpt from a bigger article, which can be found &lt;a href=\"Ministries%20and%20Megacorporations\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;\"\nEach ministry dedicates itself to the continued sovereignty and progress of Super Earth in their own unique ways. It is never explained how these ministries came about or who their respective ministers are and how they are chosen. The most likely explanation is that the President/Democratic Council is responsible for selecting them.\nThe ministries of Super Earth are listed in order below: \nLegislative Branch.\nThe Legislative Branch of Super Earth is composed of two main bodies. The Super Earth House of Representatives and the Super Earth Senate. It is unknown if these two exist independently or exist as two parts of a collective Congress, as is the case in many real life countries that follow a system of separation of powers.\nSuper Earth House of Representatives.\nA very small glimpse of this portion of the government is shown in Helldivers 1 through House Representative Powley Colle, a character mentioned briefly whenever a new war is declared against the . This character's title of \"House Representative\" inherently implies the existence of a House of Representatives. It can be assumed that the Super Earth House of Representatives is where legislation is drafted and debated before being sent to the Senate in order for said legislation to then be sent to the President and be signed into law.\nWhile Helldivers 1 only gives the very brief spotlight to Powley Colle, it is very possible that there are multiple House Representatives.\nSuper Earth Senate.\nA small bit of information that is shown in Helldivers 1 about this portion of the government is through Senator John W. Killjoy, as his title of \"Senator\" directly implies the presence of a Super Earth Senate.\nIt is safe to assume that the Super Earth Senate is in charge of reviewing laws passed by the Super Earth House of Representatives so that the President can sign them into law, assuming that Super Earth's government operates in the same way that a real life federal government of this style would.\nWhile Helldivers 1 only introduces John W. Killjoy as Senator, it is very possible that there are many more senators.\nJudicial Branch.\nThe Democratic Council.\nFollowing the release of an &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.youtube.com/watch%3Fv%3DtOWwJXwxqIA\"&gt;official lore video for Liberty Day&lt;/a&gt; on October 23rd, 2024, it was confirmed that the Democratic Council is the organization responsible for publishing and presumably interpreting the text that composes the ideals of \"Managed Democracy\". The Democratic Council is stated to have presented the \"first and final draft\" of Managed Democracy, meaning that Managed Democracy serves as both the ideals of Super Earth and the basic law by which all other legislation must abide by in the Federation. This also establishes the Democratic Council as the judiciary in charge of settling legal disputes with the gentle touch of an iron fist.\nPolitical Climate.\nIt is made clear at several points in Helldivers 1 and in some of its descriptions that the government of Super Earth has a history of brutally suppressing dissidents. \nThe above means it is likely that (a portion of) early Super Earth riot police were fully-trained military assassins and reconnaissance specialists \"before\" Super Earth unified -- \"and\" that the Ministry of Defence also either acted as or supplemented a police force.\n\"Fun fact: the was \"developed by Dr. Junko under the 2079 act of self-defence research and has been tested extensively on live targets\". The DLC description for the also notes the following: \"Sometimes shunned by fellow Helldivers for their use of inhumane warfare, many a Helldiver is happy to have them on the mission when it comes down to life or death. It's not like the enemy is Human after all.\"\"\nForeign Relations and Diplomacy.\nHelldivers 1 consists of an endless series of wars against three factions: the , and The . As soon as one war is won (or lost), another one immediately starts. The admiral on the ship's bridge pretty much admits to this, stating: \"[...] of course, when we have won this war, there will be another to fight, and after that - another! After that? Another! I could go on, but you get my point - let us focus on this war.\"\n/&lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton Legion&lt;/a&gt;.\nSuper Earth's usual \"case for war\" against the Cyborg Nation is that a cybernetically augmented human, in an act of terrorism, detonated explosives in the centre of District 48 of Super Earth, killing 8 citizens. Those who doubt the official story run the risk of being labelled \"cyborg sympathizers\". One should note that although the initial explosion may have killed thousands, every war with the Cyborgs in the game's is caused by a much, much smaller-scale terrorist attack.\n&lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;, the Cyborg Nation's homeworld, is a barren on the galactic fringe. Whenever it is conquered by Super Earth, the Cyborgs are then \"democratized\" by force, coerced into the voting booths by threat of losing their civil rights. Super Earth's Army Tactical Command invariably stations troops on the planet for a period of five years to \"keep the peace and \"run government positions\"\", after which the Cyborgs' culture is supposed to have transitioned to a \"fully democratic\" one (by Super Earth standards). Meanwhile, the Super Earth Construction Company (SECC), a government contractor, takes over the massive forges and industrial complexes of Cyberstan. Eventually, inevitably, another bombing begins this whole cycle anew.\nCyborgs are often depicted by the Super Earth government as socialists, and they're not helping their case with their choice of logo: a red star. Constantly shouting battle cries and muttering to themselves in a variety of languages, Cyborg troops gleefully deride the Helldivers and Super Earth as, among other things, \"plutarch scum\".\nRumours about the Cyborgs circulate among the ship's crew members; some (or all) of these rumours could be the result of Super Earth propaganda. According to one of the Privates, \"a crazy scientist started replacing body parts on people she had kidnapped.\" The threat of being taken away by Cyborgs for these \"perverse modifications\" is apparently used as a boogeyman.\nIn Helldivers 2, Super Earth's posture towards the , the successors of the , is a very stark escalation, as Super Earth rightfully treats them as an existential threat to their way of life, while the Cyborgs were at least given the chance to reintegrate into society. As such, Super Earth refuses to recognize the Automaton Legion's claims in the Milky Way, instead referring to it as an \"illegal occupation\". This position infers that, while Super Earth very much does not like the Automatons, they still recognize them as a separate country.\nThe are a sentient extraterrestrial species, their form reminiscent of very large Earth insects, arachnids, or crustaceans. As far as the scientists of Super Earth know, their homeworld is &lt;a href=\"Kepler%20Prime\"&gt;Kepler Prime&lt;/a&gt;, a on the eastern fringe of the galaxy.\nBugs are known to generate \"vast quantities\" of oil during decomposition, similar to how Earth's pre-human lifeforms provide us with fossil fuel sources. During the announcement of each new war against the Bugs, mention is made of \"lost oil pumps\" that the Helldiver Corps is to reactivate. These oil pumps (which, as shown in the game's intro, prominently feature a Helldiver skull emblem over an oil drop) are also found on &lt;a href=\"Kepler%20Prime\"&gt;Kepler Prime&lt;/a&gt;. The implications of this are that the Helldiver Corps is responsible for at least part of the resource-gathering process, and that they have been to &lt;a href=\"Kepler%20Prime\"&gt;Kepler Prime&lt;/a&gt; before \u2013 possibly triggering the Bugs to attack Super Earth.\nSuper Earth propaganda depicts the Bugs as a threat that will infest the entire galaxy if not suppressed. However, when the war against the Bugs is won, the tune is quickly changed; suddenly, the Bugs are a rare and valuable species that is a potentially unlimited supply of fossil fuel resources for Super Earth, and eliminating them \"just wouldn't be right from a moral perspective\". Following this, a certain scientist called Dr. Henk Ploeg then works on a way to safely breed the Bugs in a controlled manner. Since there is always a new war after the current one, and a new one after that, and so on, it can be inferred that this \"safe breeding\" of Bugs tends not to work out very well.\nBy the time of Helldivers 2, the , being more evolved forms of the Bugs from the prior century, are still treated the same as the Bugs that came before them, treated as a scourge to be cleansed until it is beneficial for Super Earth to contain, herd, and breed them again for E-710 harvesting.\nThe , or Sq'uith as they call themselves, are an advanced extragalactic race which, for millennia, has had settlements in the south quadrant of the galaxy. If Super Earth propaganda is to be believed, the aliens consider themselves enlightened beings (hence the name \u2013 but why would they call themselves the Sq'uith then?). Originating from the ocean, The Illuminate species makes use of bio-electronics and nano-powered devices. According to the ship's science officer, they still sting slightly when touched because of their vestigial electrolyte glands: \"The Illuminate went down the path of electricity in the same way we did from rocks to bullets\".\nThe blue-skinned species was first encountered in the late 21st century, when Illuminate recon craft were frequently sighted. These sightings were dismissed as folklore back then, but after a time, the Illuminate came forward with a peace offering. This was declined by the government of Super Earth when it was found out that the mollusk-like aliens had \"large quantities of world-destroying devices\", nicknamed \"obliterator bombs\" by Super Earth. This was deemed sufficient cause for a preemptive strike aimed at removing their presence from the galaxy and obtaining their highly-advanced technology. To quote Senator John W. Killjoy: \"The statement sends a clear message to all would-be threats to Super Earth; if they have more advanced technology than us, be prepared to pay the price\".\nAfter successfully defending against a region capital assault from the Illuminate, the ship's admiral reminds the player that there is solid evidence that the Illuminate were planning to use a planet-destroying device. However, lost region capitals can be recaptured from the Illuminate. Considering that Super Earth is \"destroyed\" and then moved to a new planet whenever the war is lost, the capitals could indeed have been destroyed and a new one with the same name set up; it could also simply mean that the Illuminate are not as willing to use their weapons of planetary destruction as the citizens of Super Earth are led to believe.\nSuper Earth deals with those who take a more tolerant stance towards the Sq'uith (describing the aliens as \"ancient and wise\") by means of public executions. The Helldivers are sent in to disarm or preferably capture any WMDs and other potentially useful technologies that eclipse what Super Earth has at its disposal.\nUpon their defeat, Super Earth forces the Illuminate to sign a treaty which disallows them from creating an armed forces branch and requires them to turn over all of their weapons technology to Super Earth. According to Dr. Henk Ploeg, PhD, \"the amount of technology we are going to receive will accelerate our technology tenfold and allow us to create \"peacekeeping devices\" that have the power to destroy entire planets!\"\nHowever, it would seem as though the weren't content with being extinct as, 100 years after being banished, they would seemingly return with a thirst of vengeance. In the months leading up to December, they would begin abducting several super earth citizens off of frontier planets, in order to turn them into the Voteless, hordes of possessed zombies under the control of the Illuminate. Then, on December 12th, 2184, at 22:42 SEST - EST, the Illuminate unleashed an invasion fleet onto the urbanized colonies of the planet &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;, effectively forcing their entry into the Second Galactic War.\nMilitary.\nThe military of super earth is known as the \"&lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;Super Earth Armed Forces&lt;/a&gt;\", collectively referred to as S.E.A.F. They are the defenders of Super Earth and her colonies. Split into several branches, the S.E.A.F. work tirelessly across the galaxy to uphold liberty, prosperity, justice, and assure every star system knows the sweet liberation of Managed Democracy. The Super Earth Armed Forces are commanded by the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defence&lt;/a&gt;, who provide them the critical information and funds required to protect and serve across the galaxy.\nSEAF HIGH COMMAND.\nThe S.E.A.F. High Command, sometimes referred to as \"Super Earth High Command\", stands as the tip of the spear for all Super Earth Armed Forces. Working in conjunction with the various ministries within the government, primarily the Ministry of Defence, High Command's purpose is to direct the Super Earth Armed Forces to assure they meet the demands of Super Earth across the galaxy. During times of war, High Command distributes &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders\"&gt;Major Orders&lt;/a&gt; to all forces within the S.E.A.F. The Helldivers particularly are given the most critical orders and are demanded to accomplish these tasks, no matter the odds.\nBranches of the S.E.A.F.\n\"The following section is an excerpt from a bigger article, which you can find &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;\"\nThe S.E.A.F. is divided into several branches and special forces organizations, each required to help successfully bring defend Super Earth and spread Managed Democracy. \nAdditional, Unspecified Roles.\nSomewhere alongside the S.E.A.F. hierarchy are certain specific roles that cannot be precisely attached to the military apparatus due to certain technicalities. These roles are the following: \nEconomy.\nIt is made very clear that Super Earth sees itself as a capitalist society, given how their enemies, the and the among them, align themselves with socialist ideology. However, in reality, it is also likely that Super Earth uses a planned economy model, given how the Ministry of Humanity controls the food supply and the Ministry of Prosperity takes care of distributing luxuries such as soda. While there are private enterprises and businesses, such as the Super Earth Construction Company, the Morguson Company, Permacura, Strohman News, and others, it is possible that these are state-operated businessses.\nE-710 Extraction.\nOne of the main means through which the Federation of Super Earth sustains its way of life is through the extraction of E-710. This activity takes place inside specialized E-710 farms that are constructed on planets with previously existing Terminid populations.\nIn these farms, Terminids are carefully herded, bred, experimented with and harvested due to the fact that they produce large amounts of E-710 after dying. E-710, being stated to be a vastly more efficient fuel source than anything else found in the galaxy so far, serves as the literal and metaphorical gasoline driving the Federation.\nE-710 itself is can be considered to be petroleum. It primarily exists in liquid form, as most of the facilities where it can be found consist of valves, pipes and liquid storage tanks. Its extraction and transportation also relies on hoses, pumps, and transport aircraft equipped with said items.\nMilitary Manufacturing.\nAnother means through which Super Earth drives its economy is through the manufacturing of weapons, both for civilian and military markets. This is best displayed through one of the TV Ads for the Morguson Company, which promotes hunting products like the &lt;a href=\"SG-225%20Breaker\"&gt;SG-12 Breaker Assault Shotgun&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, Super Earth produces vast amounts of &lt;a href=\"Armory%20%28Helldivers%202%29\"&gt;armours&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Weapons\"&gt;munitions&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;spacecraft&lt;/a&gt;, all of which are meant to sustain the war effort against the enemies of Freedom.\nAgriculture and Fishing.\nAnother industry in Super Earth that can be seen heavily in Helldivers 2 is the agricultural market, as players will often come across abandoned farms in pretty much every planet they visit. While some are obviously meant to serve as subsistence farming for individual colonists, players will sometimes find large, fully grown fields of crops during certain missions, indicating that some colonies can perform some level of commercial farming.\nAnother aspect of this market is shown through several soda vending machines that can be found scattered across the galaxy. \"Brewed Freedom\" and \"Taste of Democracy\" are among the most common soft drinks sold, with \"Taste of Democracy\" being voted the \"#1 Soft Drink in the Galaxy\". \"Democracy Drafts Premium\" Light Beer packs can also be found laying around in some objectives, indicating the presence of a brewing industry.\nOne company that is given a special spotlight is the C.O.B. Corporation, which manages some of the radar station terminals that players can occasionally find in missions. Their logo can be seen in many abandoned boxes and appliances that can be found left behind on the planets that the players visit. \nJudging by how its logo resembles a corn cob, the C.O.B. Corporation must be a big part of the food industry, while its additional DNA-double helix imagery suggests it may also dabble in genetically-modified organics, if not genetics entirely, most likely as part of the ever-growing colonization efforts of the Ministry of Expansion.\nIn one of the voice lines by the Service Technician, it is mentioned that \"fish and chips\" can occasionally be served at the chow hall of the Super Destroyer during certain \"fish fry nights\". In another voiceline, the Service Technician mentions how the Super Destroyer receives a \"shipment of Purples\", while also pointing out their personal dislike of such fruits. These 2 voicelines hint at the possibility of certain planets being able to fish at a commercially viable scale, as well as also being able to farm fruits and grow orchards successful enough to allow for interplanetary commerce. These voicelines both hint at different Super Earth planets producing different types of export goods, with some planets exporting fish and others exporting fruits.\nAdditionally, those that pre-ordered &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; were given access to the TR-7 Ambassador of the Brand armor, which is explicitly stated to be made as a \"promotional armor for SUMY Corp, as part of a highly successful marketing campaign for frozen yogurt\"\nMining.\nA very prominent industry in Helldivers 1 and 2 is the mining industry. Not only is Cyberstan explicitly stated to be a mining colony in Helldivers 1, but it is also shown in Helldivers 2 that many planets often conduct mining operations at scales big enough to require forklifts and freight containers.\nWith the issuing of &lt;a href=\"Helldiver%20Operations%23Operation_Freedom%27s_Forge\"&gt;Operation Freedom's Forge&lt;/a&gt;, it has been revealed that Super Earth is capable of building and operating mining complexes at the mantle level of a planet, which allows it to build massive \"Deep Mantle Forge\" complexes intended for massive metalworking projects, such as those required for the creation of the Democracy Space Station.\nConstruction and Terraforming.\nOne industry that is given a special mention is the construction industry. As mentioned before, whenever Super Earth defeats the in , they allow the Super Earth Construction Company to take control of the planet's forges and industrial facilities.\nWith the introduction of Urban Colonies in the Omens of Tyranny update, it was also revealed that Super Earth has a specialized individual, the M.C.S.E (Monument's Commissioner of Super Earth), in order to commission the construction of commemorative plaques and possibly other monuments.\nAdditionally, it is hinted that Super Earth has terraforming technology, at least capable of terraforming lunar bodies.\nService Industry.\nWith the introduction of Urban Colonies in the &lt;a href=\"Omens%20of%20Tyranny\"&gt;Omens of Tyranny&lt;/a&gt; update, some of the new buildings that can be found feature signs indicative of them being private businesses, as they read \"Opening Hours: 1pm-2pm\", which could indicate that these building house more office-like businesses such as consultancy firms. These buildings, alongside some other buildings that more closely resemble office blocs and the existence of the &lt;a href=\"Ministries%20and%20Megacorporations\"&gt;Trustor&lt;/a&gt; corporation in the game suggest the existence of a robust service industry across the Federation.\nPharmaceutical.\nAnother industry that is given a small but special spotlight is the pharmaceutical industry, as it is explicitly stated that the Stims used by the Helldivers come from a company called \"Permacura\". Permacura manages the production and distribution of the Stims that Helldivers use, though judging by the training manual tips' quote, it would appear Permacura also serves a role in civilian society, given how this last disclaimer added very much seems to exist for the purposes of marketing.\nAdditionally, certain products such as the \"Eagle Sweat\" deodorant sold by Trustor are stated to \"literally rewrite your DNA to make you smell like a Hero of the Federation\", as per their own advertising that can sometimes be seen in the ship's broadcasting screen above the Acquisition Center.\nTechnology.\nTransporation and Electricity.\nA highlight of Super Earth's economy is its technology. After the First Galactic War, Super Earth gained the ability to build starships which are capable of faster-than-light travel, which served as the primary driving force of the 100 years of explosive expansion and exploration before the Second Galactic War. Additionally, Super Earth boasts a number of impressive technologies such as the Galactic Wide Web, interplanetary battle stations, terraforming technology, and many others.\nFrom what can be seen in the introductory cinematic of Helldivers 2, the people of Super Earth mostly make use of clean energy, as every house seen has an array of solar panels on the roof. Additionally, some buildings on other planets can be found which utilize wind turbines, as well as other buildings which have solar farms next to them. \nSomething that is also made visible in both Helldivers 1 and 2, although it is missing in the gameplay for the latter, is that Super Earth still uses automobiles. The ones used in 2184 are most likely electric, given how these do not show any emissions in the introductory cinematic, as well as all the prop cars that can be seen in the urban colonies that were introduced with the return of the Illuminate. \nBesides the introduction cinematic, players in Helldivers 1 can call in an assortment of various vehicles, ranging from tanks to motorcycles. Meanwhile, in Helldivers 2, players can call in two varieties of combat &lt;a href=\"EXO-45%20Patriot%20Exosuit\"&gt;exosuits&lt;/a&gt;, also known as \"walkers\". Super Earth also makes regular usage of space-capable aircraft, with the most salient examples being the Eagle fighter and the Pelican transport ship. As well, players can also make use of the &lt;a href=\"M-102%20Fast%20Recon%20Vehicle\"&gt;Fast Recon Vehicle&lt;/a&gt;, though this vehicle still makes use of liquid combustible fuel, possibly E-710. \nBesides the usable vehicles, Helldivers will often encounter a multitude of different civilian cars whenever they fight in planets with urban settlements. These cars range from pickup trucks, to lorries to 4-door sedans that are all very curvy in their shape but that are otherwise similar to the cars used in our modern day society. One thing worthy of note is that these cars do not feature any visible exhaust pipes or gasoline ports, which may be a product of optimization although it could also be indicative of them being a new type of electric car. This implication would also indicate that E-710 is somehow more efficient than electric vehicles, as the Fast Recon Vehicle runs on a limited amount of liquid fuel.\nWhile not explicitly shown, it is made clear that Super Earth is accustomed to utilizing nuclear energy for transportation, as certain armors are reported to have plutonium batteries. \nTime Standard.\nSuper Earth's official time is \"Super Earth Standard Time\", remaining almost uniform across all planets under its control. One can notice this by looking attentively at the clock overlayed over any planet that the Helldiver may feel like diving into. Daylight Savings Time is called \"Freedom Savings Time\". Clocks are set back one hour to compensate, even on &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;super destroyers&lt;/a&gt;. By 2184, this is still preserved, as the Service Technician sometimes remarks how setting the clocks on the Super Destroyer back gives them extra time to maintain their tools. However, this is in stark contrast to the lack of a day-night cycle aboard Super Destroyers.\nGalactic Wide Web.\nThe Galactic Wide Web, sometimes shortened to the GWW, is the Federation's evolution of the ancient World Wide Web from the late 20th and early 21st centuries. Utilizing a complicated network of quantum computers and interlinked particles, this network can transfer all types of information, from sound to video to text, back and forth between Super Earth and any other point in the galaxy, be it to Super Destroyers, Intergalactic Battle Stations, distant planetary colonies, any vessels performing FTL jumps, and even spaceships performing deep space exploration.\nGiven its nature, the GWW surprisingly has little to no lag. However, some lag is added in because of the constant surveillance performed by the Democratic Investigation Agency and others, due to the necessity of the Ministry of Truth to effectively expunge any and all alien sympathizers,\nThere are many ways to access the Galactic Wide Web, ranging from &lt;a href=\"Objectives\"&gt;on-the-ground&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20Artillery\"&gt;terminals&lt;/a&gt; to portable communication devices that players can often find at minor points of interest, such as SEAF Communication Devices.\nCitizenship Classification Structure.\nThe Citizenship Classification Structure, known for its acronym \"CCS\", is a nation-wide &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_Credit_System\"&gt;social credit rating system&lt;/a&gt;. The CCS, judging by the lines of dialogue by the Service Technician, works through a system of tiers going downwards from Class A to Class C. The higher the citizenship class, the better the quality of available services becomes and the greater the opportunities become for things like housing and education. Something that is hinted at by the Service Technician is that military service can serve as a pathway to upgrading one's citizenship class.\nAdditionally, this system seems to support its own currency of \"Citizenship Points\", which citizens can use to purchase certain benefits, such as improved healthcare, access to a pet license, and other commodities. Citizenship Points can be earned through various means, with one of the known ones being to simply just report any suspicious behaviour or conversations in one's workplace, possibly even extending into reporting illegal activities or rhetoric happening within one's own family, groups of friends, or even one's own community.\nGiven its nature, it is possible that this system is managed by the Ministry of Humanity, in conjunction with the Ministry of Unity, with the infrastructure being run through the Galactic Wide Web in order to allow monitoring by the Ministry of Truth. In this way, the hands of liberty are intertwined.\nCulture &amp; Society.\nSuper Earth boasts a culture of extreme patriotism, to an extent that some (mostly its enemies and their sympathizers) would call \"fanatical\". Its citizens always display utmost devotion and loyalty to Super Earth and the ideals of Freedom and Managed Democracy, going so far as to denounce their own children, parents, relatives, neighbors, and close friends if they ever discover them committing treasonous acts or failing to perform certain signs of loyalty. Loyalty to the government of Super Earth is not only something that every citizen of Super Earth actively partakes in, but is also heavily incentivized by the government, as Democracy Officers will often reward those that report any signs of disloyalty.\nIt is often said through TV ads that all citizens are equal on Super Earth, meaning that there is no such thing as intolerance or discrimination of any kind towards anyone that is not an enemy of Humanity or a dissident that has abandoned the ideals of Super Earth. However, one aspect is made very clear: everyone is equal. But the Helldivers are the most equal of all.\nThe minimum legal age at which any citizen of the federation can work is at seven years of human age. From hereon out, citizens can freely volunteer into any field of the industry, from weapons manufacturing to mining and farming. Citizens over the 16 years of age can enlist into the Super Earth Armed Forces.\nSuper Earth is a highly militaristic society. All children are given a bolt-action rifle (which is also used by the Super Earth Armed Forces as a ceremonial rifle) when they turn 16 to encourage military service, and SEAF personnel are always well treated, if not revered, in civil society. It is possible that the government often supplies the M2016 Constitution to its citizens for free, if not other weapons such as the &lt;a href=\"Points%20of%20Interest\"&gt;Break Action Shotgun&lt;/a&gt;, a double barrel shotgun that is only able to be found at Minor Points of Interest in Helldivers 2. By 2184, the M2016 Constitution has been replaced by the R-2124 Constitution, a modernized version of the M2016. \nCapeless Helldivers patrol the streets with &lt;a href=\"AR-23%20Liberator\"&gt;AR-23 Liberators&lt;/a&gt; in hand in order to preserve peace and order. \nHelldivers are considered celebrities in civil society, as the Service Technician will often remark their disbelief (and that of their civilian loved ones/relatives/etc.) at getting to work so close to Helldivers, having Helldiver posters in their bedroom as a kid and with many promotional ads showing children wearing Helldiver helmets and costumes.\nEvery morning, all citizens must swear a Pledge of Allegiance to Super Earth. Crews assigned to Super Destroyers, colonies, or otherwise found away from the safe embrace of Super Earth must orient themselves towards the exact position of Super Earth. The Service Technician will remark that they always feel like they can tell where Super Earth is, meaning that getting Super Earth's location in relation to one-self is imperative when taking the Pledge.\nAdditionally, both the &lt;a href=\"Service%20Technician\"&gt;Service Technician&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ship%20Master\"&gt;Ship Master&lt;/a&gt; admit to never having been to Super Earth themselves, implying that many of the Federation's citizens are born on planetary colonies.\nThe Illuminate, and the Cyborgs before them, are used as the boogeymen in cautionary tales for kids, according to voicelines by both the Ship Master and the Service Technician. However, in both cases, it can be noticed that this only occurs with factions that Super Earth believes to have decisively and indisputably defeated, which explains why both the Service Technician and the Ship Master explain how much disbelief they have regarding the return of the Illuminate.\nDemographics.\nMost, if not all of the citizens of Super Earth are humans, obviously. However, a small portion of the population has taken on adapting cybernetic augmentations onto their bodies (often, illegally). These people are the , and whenever they aren't trying to secede, they are acknowledged to be a minority within Super Earth society. \nThey are often persecuted, mostly due to the terrorist bombings that some of their members engage in and the socialist ideology adopted by the Cyborg Separatists. Certain Helldivers, referred to as the \"Steeled Veterans\", have mechanical augmentations, with some of their limbs replaced with prosthetics. However, this is implied to be due to the fact that they have lost their limbs in combat, and not by choice, like the Cyborgs.\nThe Federation is also inhabited by a vast quantity of . Obviously, they are not considered to be citizens due to their fascistic nature, and as a result are safely contained in E-710 farms where they are able to be safely and productively harvested. Terminids, when not being farmed, are also a popular tourist attraction for the human citizens of Super Earth, as seen by the famous Tyranny Park on &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;.\nEducation.\nSuper Earth's educational system seems to be much more advanced by the late 21st and early 22nd centuries than it was in the days prior to the Great War. Many subjects, such as quantum computation and space travel, are considered \"elementary stuff\" by the Ship's C.O in Helldivers 1.\nC-01 Perm.\nThe C-01 PERM (pronounced \"cee-one-perm\") child permit form is required for citizens of Super Earth to legally reproduce. According to the NPC Privates on the ship's bridge, these forms are not easy to fill out. Interestingly, the female Private also mentions having a wife (in text, but not in the spoken dialogue). If this is not an oversight (considering that the Privates mostly have the same lines), it can be inferred that same-sex relationships are not considered a taboo in Super Earth culture. Procreation applications typically require a 180-day review process.\nAccording to one of the loading tips in Helldivers 2, one must fill out a C-01 Perm before \"any act that could result in a child\", implying that the C-01 permit is also meant as a permit for sexual intercourse. Judging by the amount of cryogenically frozen Helldivers that are allocated per Super Destroyer (24 Reinforcements maximum with the &lt;a href=\"Boosters\"&gt;Increased Reinforcement Budget&lt;/a&gt; booster, but more can be procured if the allotted 24 reinfocements are spent up to a theoretical maximum of 44 helldivers per mission) and the many rockets carrying frozen Helldivers that can be seen at the end of the tutorial, it is safe to assume that the C-01 Permit is the single most submitted form in the galaxy.\nFestivities and Holidays.\n&lt;a href=\"Liberty%20Day\"&gt;Liberty Day&lt;/a&gt;.\nA key festivity that is often mentioned in both Helldivers and Helldivers 2 is Liberty Day. Liberty Day is celebrated by the citizens of Super Earth every year on the 26th of October. In real life, The \"HELLDIVERS\" community also celebrates Liberty Day, and Arrowhead Studios has released free DLC, available to everyone, on this date consistently (as of 2018).\nIn-universe, citizens light scarecrows called \"Liberty Pires\", which are shaped after Super Earth's enemies and place presents beneath them for children. \nLiberty Day commemorates the anniversary for the publication of the first and final draft of \"Managed Democracy\" ever written by the Democratic Council.\nLiberty Day is also when Class B Citizens are given an hour off of work so that they can watch the Liberty Parades. Strohman Media holds a 24-hour livestream from the Wall of Martyrs. Famous Helldivers give interviews, and civilians have a chance to meet them. Dissidents are executed for the public's enjoyment.\nFestival of Reckoning.\nOn December 2024, Helldivers 2 introduced the Festival of Reckoning, which now is the official replacement for the ancient celebration of Christmas in the Federation. It is a 3-day festival during which the Helldivers are issued special thematic weaponry and stratagems according to each day's theme. The more kills that the Helldivers get, the higher the discounts that the citizens of Super Earth get.\nFor the December 2184 edition, the First Day of the Festival of Reckoning issued a fleetwide deployment of &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Napalm%20Barrage\"&gt;Orbital Napalm Barrages&lt;/a&gt;. As well, the &lt;a href=\"StA-X3%20W.A.S.P.%20Launcher\"&gt;StA-X3 W.A.S.P Launcher&lt;/a&gt; was also made available. Following that, the &lt;a href=\"FLAM-40%20Flamethrower\"&gt;FLAM-40 Flamethrower&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Mines%23Incendiary%20Mines\"&gt;MD-14 Incendiary Mines&lt;/a&gt; were all issued, one after the other.\nOn the Second Day of the Festival of Reckoning, a holiday song would be sent through the Dispatch System. Lyrics are as follows:\n&lt;syntaxhighlight&gt;\nAll Helldivers are invited to join in the classic holiday carol \"Here They Come a'Reckonin':\"\nOh, here they come a'Recknonin',\nO'er hill and vale,\nChildren play, bombs away,\nSuper Earth we hail!\nHere they come a'Reckonin',\nJustice justly served,\nFlowers grow, blood will flow,\nPeace on Super Earth!\n&lt;/syntaxhighlight&gt;\nOther Holidays.\nOther festivities often mentioned throughout many TV ads are \"Martyr's Day\", most likely meant to commemorate those who have given their lives in service to freedom, and \"Voting Day\", which is a holiday to celebrate the idea of voting.\nA festivity often brought up by the Service Technician is All Heroes' Eve, which is possibly an adaptation of ancient Halloween, given how the Service Technician details how \"the adults would all dress up as \". Another festivity brought up by the Service Technician is Heroes' Day. \nAfter the final liberation of &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;, the President of Super Earth officially recognized April 3rd, the first full day of peace on the planet, as Malevelon Creek Memorial Day. Every year on this day, Super Earth citizens will unite for a full 3 minutes of their lunch break in solemn remembrance of those who gave their lives to free Malevelon Creek. \nIn addition, all Helldivers were issued a special commemorative cape, so they may carry the memory of their fallen companions into battle.\nArchitecture.\nSuper Earth's architecture, judging by the urban colonies found at &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; and other planets following the resurgence of the Illuminate, mostly consists of neo-modernist buildings with round-cornered square buildings. Colonies are built car-centric and streets are at least 4 lanes wide, with 2 lanes in each direction. These colonies all have functioning power grids and water management systems, as working fire hydrants, sewage channels, transmission towers, functioning street lights and vending machines can be found. As well, lots of parkland with decorative trees and bushes can be found, most of which heavily feature flags and Helldiver statues in all their splendor.\nIn urban colonies, most buildings are 2 or more stories tall at their lowest and 5 stories at their highest, however, there are many shifts in elevation which require public stairs to be constructed. Additionally, SEAF defensive structures, such as the &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20SAM%20Site\"&gt;SAM Site&lt;/a&gt; or spaceports that can sometimes be used for evacuation, are embedded into the colonies' infrastructure, most likely for protection against incoming invaders and ease of use, while things such as the SEAF Artillery battery are kept on the outskirts, though they will still be embedded between buildings if there is no more space.\nA feature common throughout every urban colony, regardless of biome, are the flat green grass lawns that can be found on parks and in private home lawns. While these are most likely artificial, they are a notable fixture of Super Earth lifestyle.\nBuildings are built relatively close together, although there still are many buildings with alleyways in between. Urban colonies are surrounded by a protective wall, possibly to deter alien wildlife from attacking their citizens. It is worth noting that planet colonies feature a heavy absence of public transportation vehicles or infrastructure, such as buses, metro stations or even taxi cabs; indicating that these colonies may not reach a population high enough to warrant the construction and maintenance of said services.\nHowever, in most other planets across the Federation, even some planets closer to Super Earth such as &lt;a href=\"Shallus\"&gt;Shallus&lt;/a&gt;, the colonies are mostly undeveloped, with scattered buildings, dwellings and complexes dotting the otherwise untouched wilderness.\nThe most prominent structures of the Federation has outside of the urban colonies are mainly those used for objectives, such as the spaceports used in most extraction sites, Emergency Evacuation missions, all the tilesets used for the Evacuate High Value Asset defense missions, certain tilesets of the objective site in Spread Democracy missions, all the variants for the Terminate Illegal Broadcast and Destroy Rogue Research Station objectives and some of the possible variants of the generator sub-objective.\nBesides those, most of the visible infrastructure Super Earth's colonies show is purely utilitarian, consisting mostly of oil rigs, storage silos, radio towers and military facilities such as the SEAF Artillery, the Radar Station and the SEAF SAM Site.\nHowever, despite their remoteness, the colonists of Super Earth still take care to proudly fly the flag of the Federation, as well as to erect tall stone statues of the Helldivers, some issued with commemorative metal plaques. Unfortunately, the enemies of Super Earth also make sure to desecrate and defile any Super Earth infrastructure they come across.\nSome unique structures that Super Earth is said to have but that aren't seen are those used for Major Order objectives, such as the Super Citizen Anne's Hospital for the Very Sick Children, which used to be located in Vernen Wells before it was destroyed by the Automatons during Operation Trolley Problem. While the hospital nor its ruins can be found in the planet, it is worth mentioning. Similarly, locations such as the Xenoentomology Center at Turing, the Deep Mantle Forge Complex at Claorell, the Terminid Research Preserve and Tyranny Park at Acamar IV or the AM Factory Hub at Achernar Secundus aren't able to be found in-game either.\nThe enemies of Super Earth will often defile symbols of Super Earth, mostly Helldiver Memorials. Automatons often place their red star banners around the Helldiver statues and further defile these monuments by digging mass graves before them. This is most noticeable in a certain variant of the \"Spread Democracy\" objective site, which preserves some abandoned houses and a Helldiver statue in the middle.\nThe Terminids simply dig their putrid nests inside of the abandoned dwellings, filling them with web-looking yellow strings and filth, which is specially noticeable in certain variants of the medium and heavy nests, as well as some variants of the Shrieker Nest, all of which feature piles of corpses and destroyed houses.\nThe Illuminate often pitch their decadent monoliths and nefarious altars on top of destroyed buildings and parks, which can be noticed very well during urban colony missions. As well, they often park their warp ships on top of public parks and leave mountains of civilian corpses at the base of their monoliths.\nSymbols of Super Earth.\nFlag of Super Earth.\n\"The following is an excerpt from a bigger article, which can be found &lt;a href=\"Flag%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;\"\nThe Flag of Super Earth, affectionally named \"The White, Yellow, Blue\" by the majority of the population, is the official national banner of the Federation of Super Earth, symbolizing the union of all Humanity under Managed Democracy. It is proudly flown, hung, or otherwise displayed and plastered on every place where Freedom's presence can be felt. So far, between 2084 and 2184, there have been up to 3 versions shown throughout both and &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\nGoing by traditional vexillological analysis, it is possible to assume what each color may represent in the flag of Super Earth. The Blue in the flag would represent the vastness of space, with an azimuthal equidistant projection of Super Earth, centered on Prosperity City, being emblazoned right in the center to represent Super Earth's role as the galaxy's shinning beacon of Freedom.\nThe White in the flag would symbolize the pacifying nature of Managed Democracy, as well as humanity's unfaltering love for peace, as well as Super Earth's pacifying mission, reminding its citizens about why they fight and reminding their enemies of the futility of their struggle against humankind. Some versions of the flag include simplified wreaths guarding Super Earth, further hinting at this potential meaning.\nLastly, the yellow in the flag would stand for the Prosperity brought on by Managed Democracy, with the vast expanse of the Federation and the might of not just its armed forces but the product of the free, hard labor of all its citizens standing as tangible demonstrations of exactly how humanity will triumph and flourish over any adversary, be it natural or alien, with no cost being too high and no sacrifice too great.\nThere are a total of seven, evenly separated stars beneath Super Earth, laid in a horizontal line with size decreasing from the central star outwards. Each of the 7 stars possibly represents each of the 7 sectors of Super Earth, once more hinting towards the union of all mankind under one banner: The Banner of Liberty.\nAnthem of Super Earth.\nThe Anthem of Super Earth, officially named the \"Super Earth National Anthem\" is the official national anthem of the Federation of Super Earth. Its lyrics are made up of 11 verses, accentuated by one final proclamation.\nIn real life, the Super Earth National Anthem was composed by Wilbert Roget II, with the lyrics being written by Ross Tregenza, as part of the official soundtrack for &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;, which officially released on September 20th, 2024. The lyrics can be found below and a link to the anthem can be found at the top of this page in the information box, as well as in &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.youtube.com/watch%3Fv%3D4z77WIELtpA\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;\nLyrics.\nFREEDOM MUST REIGN OVER EVERY LAST STAR\nTHROUGH CITIZEN'S BLOOD SPILLED IN OUR RIGHTEOUS WARS.\nHONOR THEIR DEATHS, DO YOUR PART FOR THE CAUSE.\nSTEADFAST SUPPORT OF OUR REGIME\nIS HOW HUMANKIND WILL REIGN SUPREME.\nNO QUESTIONS OR DOUBTS SHALL BE ALLOWED\nTRAITORS WILL ALL BE DISAVOWED.\nMANAGED DEMOCRACY IS THE TRUE PATH\nALL WHO RESIST IT SHALL SUFFER OUR WRATH.\nWHITE, YELLOW, BLUE FLYING ON ALL THE WORLDS.\nJUSTICE AND HOPE ARE FOREVER UNFURLED.\nOUR WAY OF LIFE, GALAXY WIDE,\nPAVED WITH THE SKULLS OF THOSE WHO'VE DIED.\nUNSLAKEABLE TIDE, OF SUPER EARTH PRIDE,\nA TORRENT THAT CAN'T BE SATISFIED.\nWE SACRIFICE, FOR PARADISE,\nANYTHING LESS WILL NOT SUFFICE.\nCITIZENS RISE! LIBERTY RISE!\nSUPER EARTH RISE UP TO THE SKIES.\nSTAY FREE!\nSports.\nA sport mentioned in one of the TV ads is \"Freedomball\". Judging by the name, it is possibly a version of &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Football\"&gt;Football&lt;/a&gt;, as the introduction cinematic shows a soccer ball in the front porch of the broadcast announcer's house before his family is slaughtered.\nAnother sport that is mentioned in the description of the CE-35 Trench Engineer armor is \"Fence-Smashing\", a local pastime in &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt;. Whether this activity is a sport or not, is unknown.\nMedia.\nSuper Earth allows for media such as film, videogames, and songs to be commonplace, as famous actors such as Chip Messiter and Jen Shriver are brought up in the descriptions of certain armors that are available in the Super Store, while some popular songs are mentioned in the TV Ads, such as \"Can't Ration My Love\" and \"Our Love is like Liberty (Indestructible)\". Musicals are also popular in Super Earth, such as \"Lost My Heart to a Man in a Helmet\" and \"Hazard Pay: The Musical\".\nLiterature in Helldivers is mostly comprised of novels and comic books, with the vast majority of them revolving around tales involving military units, such as the mystery novel \"Truth Enforcers: Enforcers of Truth\", the \"Tales of the Viper Commandos\" comic book series, the \"Call of the Frontier\" comic book series and the \"Amazing Democracy\" magazines.\nTV Shows are also a commonplace piece of media in Super Earth, with some examples being \"Jen Shriver : The Science Diver\"\nAs for videogames canon to the Helldivers universe, the only one known that has also made an appearance as a minigame is the \"Stratagem Hero\" an arcade minigame that is only available to those that buy the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Citizen%20Edition\"&gt;Super Citizen Edition&lt;/a&gt; in Helldivers 2.\nA plausible conclusion can be made that all media must be first approved by the Ministry of Truth. It seems that the Ministry of Truth allows criticisms of things such as supply rationing, war, and other themes, so long as the blame is placed upon the enemies of Super Earth, who are the real culprits, after all.\nReligion.\nJudging by the voicelines uttered by both the Helldivers and most NPCs, like the civilians in the rescue missions and the Democracy Officer, it is safe to assume that \"Liberty\", sometimes referred to as \"Lady Liberty\", is personified and venerated to an extent where people will often say \"Liberty-Forsaken\" instead of something like \"God-forsaken\" and \"Sweet Liberty!\" instead of something like \"Oh my god!\". \nHowever, in rare occasions, players and NPCs will also sometimes say \"flag-forsaken\" instead. Despite this, it can be safely assumed that Super Earth is a secular state, as these expressions never show up in any Major Order briefings, nor does the Ship Master use these expressions in any of their voicelines, implying that secularity is enforced throughout the military command chain.\nDemocracy Officers may engage in celibacy, as the Democracy Officer will admit to having no significant other if they speak with the Helldiver. "}
