{"id": "3260", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3260", "title": "Fenrir III", "text": "Fenrir III is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Its general landscape consists of subzero temperatures and open lands peppered with large craters.\nTopography.\nFenrir III's surface is dominated by grey, rocky plateaus. Though the moon is largely barren, sparse amounts of bush-like vegetation have been known to survive its frigid climate. Intermittent meteor storms have left Fenrir III pock-marked by craters. Citizens are advised to stay indoors to avoid such meteor impacts.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nFenrir III was, up until February 2184, a peaceful mining colony of Super Earth in the Fenrir System, its barren landscape standing just far away enough from its star to be habitable yet cold, as its colonists rotated between shifts at the mines and taking shelter from the occasional Meteor Storms that constantly befell this planet.\nHowever, among these Meteor Storms came one that would permanently scar this planet more than any other. On February 10th, 2184, Fenrir III would be overwhelmed by the landfall of several onto its surface, during one of the very first engagements between Super Earth and the alien insects.\nWith casualties mounting and Terminid numbers rising, the Colonial Overseer called upon the broader SEAF for reinforcements. Luckily for him, with the ongoing Terminid outbreak, Super Earth High Command had just issued an order for the reactivation of the mightiest force of them all: The Helldivers.\nOperation Valiant Enclosure.\nThe very first Helldiver Operation was to repel the advancing Terminid forces at Heeth and &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;, key chokepoint planets that are crucial to getting past the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt;. However, the Helldivers would demonstrate peak combat readiness and, while taking on the hordes at both planets successfully, they also managed to advance into Fenrir. By the 14th, the Helldivers had easily secured both of the objective planets but the fighting at Fenrir hadn't ceased, just as it hadn't ceased anywhere else.\nWith the appearance of the on the &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers would have to divert towards &lt;a href=\"Ubanea\"&gt;Ubanea&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Draupnir\"&gt;Draupnir&lt;/a&gt;, as the newly appeared foe began to encroach upon more and more planets. Due to this untimely foe interfering with the Helldivers, Fenrir III would only be fully liberated by February 18th.\nOperation Veld Containment.\nHowever, Fenrir III would be unable to rebuild its defenses, as too many able-bodied citizens had been slain in the defense of their homes. Fittingly, once the Terminids made a second attempt against Fenrir on March 1st, it fell immediately, leading to its total capture before the Helldivers could even heed its call for aid. As such, amidst the operation to liberate &lt;a href=\"Veld\"&gt;Veld&lt;/a&gt; from the nefarious bugs, Fenrir III would be liberated on March 2nd without much incident.\nBut the Terminids persisted and, before any defense could be mounted, attacked Fenrir III yet again and recaptured it, requiring a second subsequent liberation campaign that would come to an end on March 3rd. Yet, after 2 defeats, the odious insects continued further, attacking once more and taking over the planet, requiring a third liberation campaign that only came to an end on March 4th.\nBut even still, after 3 defeats, the Terminids persisted and, on March 4th, the Terminids attacked Fenrir III a fourth consecutive time, this time managing to hold onto the planet.\nInstallation of the Terminid Control System.\nWhile the Terminids desperately tried to latch onto Fenrir's barren surface, Super Earth's scientists had devised a solution for the odious fascist infestation. The TCS (Terminid Control System) was a network of towers capable of dispersing industrial amounts of the novel \"Termicide\", a neurotoxin engineered to exclusively kill Terminids while leaving all other lifeforms unharmed. As such, Super Earth High Command issued a major order to capture not just Fenrir III, but all of the Umlaut Sector in order to install the TCS towers on them, making the Umlaut Sector into a network of Barrier Planets that would prevent further Terminid Expansion.\nOn March 13th, Fenrir III would be liberated for a sixth consecutive time, allowing for the installation of the Terminid Control System and putting an end to the early Terminid outbreak, allowing Fenrir's colonists respite and relief as they were finally able to return to their sufficiently sized dwellings.\nFailure of the Terminid Control System.\nFor the first time in 2 months, Fenrir III would enjoy prosperity and freedom like it had never done before. Safe from any further Terminid incursions, the population of the colony exploded and its economy boomed, as the Ministry of Expansion conducted several efforts into the nearby &lt;a href=\"Draco%20Sector\"&gt;Draco&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mirin%20Sector\"&gt;Mirin&lt;/a&gt; Sectors, installing new infrastructure and settling new planets as Fenrir III slowly began to serve more and more as a handy transport hub planet through which flowed an important portion of travel and resources that then went onto other sectors.\nAs the Automatons were finally purged from the Severin Sector on April 3rd, the people of Fenrir celebrated the righteous victory at Malevelon Creek while the President of Super Earth officially declared it the Malevelon Creek Memorial Day. However, fascism is an ever-present threat, its treachery seeping and growing in the tiniest of shadows.\nOn April 6th, the Automatons would return from deep space, invading &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and taking over the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Then, on April 29th, catastrophe ensued upon the Barrier Planets.\nThrough an unknown process known as &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hormesis\"&gt;hormesis&lt;/a&gt;, a minuscule portion of the Terminids that still remained at Fenrir for farming purposes had developed immunity to the Termicide. These Terminids slowly began to breed more and more rapidly until, on April 29th, they surprinsingly overran all Barrier Planets at once, with Meridia's broods managing to reproduce at an alarmingly fast rate, up to 20 times faster than normal.\nMeridia would fall to the Terminids, only for the savage, base insectoids to make a show of their hatred, as they gruesomely terraformed the once beautiful Jungle planet into a horrid nest of putrefaction, a Terminid Supercolony.\nFearing that the rest of the Barrier Planets were soon to follow, the Helldivers were ordered to deactivate the Terminid Control System, hoping that this would prevent Fenrir III and the other barrier planets from meeting the same grizzly fate.\nFenrir III would be secured on May 1st, allowing its colonists to breathe a short sigh of relief as they realized what had just begun.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Outbreak.\nAided by the Terminid Supercolony, the bugs ran wild across the Eastern Galactic rim, invading more and more planets as they poured onto the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt; like the plague they are. Fenrir III would be attacked by Terminids on May 9th, its rebuilt defenses crumbling upon the tidal wave of insectoids pouncing at it. The Helldivers would manage to liberate Fenrir by May 11th, but its colonists wouldn't be able to really rebuild much, letting it fall to the Terminids again on May 16th, only for the Helldivers to dislodge the insects off the planet 8 hours later.\nThen, on May 19th, Fenrir III would be attacked again, but the Helldivers managed to repel the assault without much other incident.\nOperation Emancipator.\nHowever, Fenrir III was still in constant danger, as it stood next to the Supercolony. Amidst an operation to capture and repurpose an Automaton Petafactory on &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;, Fenrir III and Angel's Venture were both attacked. On May 25th, the Helldivers had to leave Fenrir III to its own devices in order to appropriately ensure that the SEAF Training Facilities at Angel's Venture were properly secured, leading to Fenrir III's fall once more.\nHowever, shortly the operation concluded, Fenrir III would be quickly rescued by the Helldivers, leading to Fenrir III's liberation on May 27th, shortly after nearby Heeth had also been defended from the Terminids.\nOperation Enduring Peace.\nWith Fenrir III liberated, Super Earth High Command spied an opportunity to definitely end its issues with the Terminid Supercolony. On May 26th, 12 scientists at &lt;a href=\"Moradesh\"&gt;Moradesh&lt;/a&gt; were spaghettified during trials of a new superweapon: &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;The Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt;, an technology that had been rescued from the treacherous squids after the end of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis superweapon would appear to be the only remaining option to effectively deal with the Terminid Supercolony, as many scientists had observed that the Terminids were already too deep inside Meridia's crusts for orbital bombardments to be effective, even if they were to be done using nuclear munitions.\nAs such, Super Earth High Command issued the order for Fenrir III, Angel's Venture and &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; to be held, as these 3 planets would serve as the main path through which to transport all the Dark Fluid necessary to destroy Meridia.\nThen, on June 1st, the green light was given, as the Helldivers deployed onto Meridia in order to drill the Dark Fluid into its surface.\nFenrir III would not see much incident during this operation. However, as the Dark Fluid began disrupting the Supercolony, its spore production increased, leading to many attacks at neighboring planets, Fenrir III among them.\nThen, on June 2nd, 2184, at 15:25 SEST, Meridia would be no more, as the Dark Fluid drilled into it reached supercriticality and provoked Meridia to collapse into itself, forming a black hole that destroyed the entire Meridia system and syphoned away all Terminid interstellar spores within billions of kilometers, leading to the collapse of the Terminid offensive and letting Fenrir III's citizens breathe a sigh of relief.\nOperation Glorious Xenocide.\nFollowing the Destruction of Meridia, Fenrir III would remain largely unharmed, as the Terminids were forced to retreat away from the Umlaut Sector. While Fenrir III would be attacked on July 24th, the ongoing operation to cull Terminids would see many Helldivers aid its defense, which helped quickly repel the infestation.\nOperation Lighthouse.\nAmidst this operation, Fenrir III was attacked. On August 11th, with orders to prevent further Terminid advance, the Helldivers deployed onto Fenrir III once more, repelling the insects once again and securing the lives of its colonists once more, while still helping the cause of Liberty.\nOperation Ecologic Immolation.\nFenrir III would have enjoyed 2 months of well-deserved freedom by this point. The Terminids had been successfully contained and the Automaton front was slowly being pushed back. However, it is when Freedom's guard is at its lowest when it is the most vulnerable. And as such, Fenrir III was attacked on August 30th, amidst an operation to liberate &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt; and killing Automatons for scrap metal.\nWith the Helldivers away at the Western Galactic Rim, Fenrir III would fall to the Terminids the following. However, once the operation concluded, the Helldivers deployed en masse on Fenrir III, liberating it by September 1st.\nOperation Courageous Exodus.\nAfter those small bouts, Fenrir III stood strong and resilient, its colonists hardened after all the hardships endured. Even in the face of the horrid nebula that had appeared called &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt;, the strength of Fenrir's colonists didn't wain or waver, instead hardening their resolve.\nThis new resolve would be put to the test when; on November 5th, after 2 months of uninterrupted tranquility, the Terminids attacked Fenrir III, aided by a spore surge coming out of the Gloom. In a mighty show of their courage and resolve, Fenrir III was defended from the Terminids, ensuring that the relocation of colonists displaced from their homes by the Gloom onto the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt; continued unimpeded.\nOperation Iron Rain.\nFollowing this last bout with the Terminids, not much else would occur in Fenrir III, its colonists continuing their lives without much incident. However, the Terminids, with their unbridled hatred for peace, would attack Fenrir III without provocation. While this attack was not its cause, Operation Iron Rain would be declared mere hours after the Terminid forces made planetfall, pretty much giving the Helldivers a blank cheque to eradicate any and all bugs through the usage of machine guns, as per the request of the Ministry of Defense in order to conduct research on its efficiency.\nAfter some 30 hours of combat, the Terminids would be successfully rebuked, allowing Fenrir III's population a smooth return to its well-earned respite.\nOperation Wormhole Spaghetti.\nFollowing the conclusion of Operation Squid Game, Astronomers reported novel anomalous phenomena in the form of fluctuations in the event horizon and electromagnetic flares in the vicinity of the Meridian Singularity. Since the exotic substance known as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt; was found on Illuminate worlds at the end of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; and was used to collapse the planet into a black hole, High Command concluded that the recent changes to the Meridian Singularity, so shortly following the reappearance of the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt;, may indicate a deeper connection.\nIndeed the Meridian Singularity may be no ordinary black hole, as many leading government experts have long suspected. Naturally these developments demanded further investigation. High Command thus ordered the construction of a new Center of Science on &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt;. Thanks to decisive Fascism-repulsion operations by the Helldivers in vicinity of Fenrir III, the construction of a new Center of Science was completed safely. Top &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astrophysics\"&gt;astrophysicists&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; immediately convened there to closely study the Meridian Singularity and instantly the project yielded valuable insights.\nThe Singularity was not, as many uninformed laypeople had assumed, a typical black hole. It is, in fact, the first observed instance of a wormhole: a tunnel in spacetime connecting two disparate points in space. Much more remains to be investigated as it is likely that the wormhole was formed following the implosion of Meridia by dark matter unclear if the wormhole formed recently, or if it has existed for some time already. A connection to the recent &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; attacks is one of many threads being pursued."}
