{"id": "3326", "revid": "55287310", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3326", "title": "Ferris Sector", "text": "The Ferris Sector is an inhabited area of galaxy found &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It is located on Galactic South East from &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; and it consists of 4 planets. \nTogether with other sectors in galactic south, it was invaded by \u00a0 in middle of December 2184. The Squ'ith have descended upon said sectors in series of pillaging raids, aimed to abduct as many civilians as possible."}
{"id": "6936", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6936", "title": "Festival of Reckoning", "text": ""}
{"id": "3603", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3603", "title": "First Galactic War", "text": "The First Galactic War, also sometimes referred to as the First Intergalactic War or shortened to GW1, was an intergalactic armed conflict waged by the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation Of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; against the , a race of alien insectoids, the , a race of extra-terrestrial highly advanced, semi-humanoid cephalopods and, after the start of the war, the , an insurgent force comprised of cybernetically-enhanced terrorists that were driven mad by their prosthetic enhancements. \nThe events that occurred in this war are mostly depicted in , as part of the ; however, in Helldivers 2, certain events in the First Galactic War are established to be canon to the franchise's history, leaving the canonicity of the Galactic Campaign uncertain.\nCasus Belli and the Start of the War.\nNot much is known about the specific conditions in which the First Galactic War started, as Helldivers 1 itself opens 40 years after the start of the war. However, some details are given that could shed some light into the specifics of how each faction got into conflict with Super Earth.\nNot much is known about how humanity first entered into contact with the Bugs. A possible explanation is that, during the early expansion of mankind, some colonists unknowingly disturbed a Bug nest, prompting them to attack, which ended up in a cycle of escalation that culminated in the war.\nAt some point, the issue of the Bugs became such that the Helldivers were called in to help, as all other measures had effectively failed to contain the bugs\nThe Illuminate are unique, as they are the only faction that is admitted to have attempted a peace deal before Super Earth delivered the first strike, obviously in self-defence.\nFrom what is told in Helldivers 1, the Illuminate would have been spotted during the early 21st century, as there would be frequent sightings of Illuminate recon spacecraft that would then be passed as folklore. However, at some point between the end of the Great War and 2044, the Illuminate would make the first contact with humanity. \nWhile the government of Super Earth, loving peace as it always does, was more than happy to accept, it would end up making a gruesome discovery: The Illuminate possessed large quantities of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;world-destroying devices&lt;/a&gt;, nicknamed \"obliterator bombs\" at the time. Fearing for the safety of its citizens and for the future of Managed Democracy, the government of Super Earth would successfully dispel the malicious illusions of the squid-like beings and launched a pre-emptive strike, knowing that Liberty would not be safe so long as these aliens had more advanced technology than humanity. \nThe only faction that is explicitly stated to have attacked Super Earth first are the Cyborgs. The usual stated reasons for conflict are because of the supposed \"Oppression\" of Cyborgs by the government of Super Earth, which then prompts a terrorist bombing that then forces Super Earth to declare war against the Cyborg Insurrectionists. However, it is also possible that these terrorist incidents are false flag operations, staged in order to allow the Federation a reasonable justification to exterminate cybernetically enhanced citizens.\nNevertheless, in all 3 cases, the common conclusion is the same: Super Earth, in its need to defend Democracy, calls upon the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; for aide in bringing back freedom to a galaxy riddled with tyrants, fascists and socialists that hate liberty.\nCurrently Confirmed Battles &amp; Events of the War.\nIn Helldivers 2, the 3 currently available characters, being the Ship Master, the Service Technician and the Democracy Officer, will sometimes mention the First Galactic War or certain battles from the First Galactic War when the player asks to speak with them. As well, players can sometimes find mentions of certain battles and events taking place during the war when checking the descriptions of certain armors, helmets and weapons. These are the following\nBattle of Liberty Peak.\nOne battle that is brought up in-game is the Battle of Liberty Peak. Not many details are given about it, with the only piece of information that can be inferred being that it was an engagement between the Helldivers and the Bugs, with the obvious result being a decisive Super Earth Victory. The location of Liberty Peak is not shown in the Galactic Map, meaning that this battle perhaps took place at a location with such name inside of one of the planets available in either Helldivers 1 or Helldivers 2. \nOne thing that is known is that the \"Savior of the Free\" Armor is the closest glimpse available at the kind of armor that the Helldivers present that day were outfitted with, as its description states it to be a faithful replica of the armors worn that day. \nBattle of &lt;a href=\"Nublaria%20I\"&gt;Nublaria&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnother confirmed battle in the First Galactic War is the Battle of Nublaria, which presumably took place in &lt;a href=\"Nublaria%20I\"&gt;Nublaria I&lt;/a&gt;, a currently inaccessible planet in the Celeste Sector. Judging by the description, this was an armed engagement between the Super Earth Armed Forces against the Bugs, as the aforementioned \"Jackle 6\" is specified to be a veteran of the \"Viper Commandos\", a military unit of which neither game has ever made any mention of prior to the addition of this armor, though it is possible that this was a special Helldiver Unit given its availability to Helldivers.\nGiven the current state of peace and prosperity on Nublaria, it can be inferred that the Battle resulted in an undisputed victory for Super Earth, with Jackle 6's actions most likely being crucial to this development.\nBattle of Cyberstan.\nA battle that is confirmed in game both through dialogue and by the game itself is the Battle for Cyberstan, a crucial battle between the Super Earth Armed Forces and the Cyborg Separatists. While in Helldivers 1 it is possible to lose this battle, in Helldivers 2 it is shown that the canon result of this battle was a Super Earth victory.\nAfter signing their surrender, the Cyborgs would be sent to the voting stations by force under threat of losing what remained of their civil rights. After the voting, Cyberstan would then be under military occupation for 5 years to prevent further rebellion and lawlessness and, following the occupation, Super Earth would then leave the Cyborgs under \"rehabilitation\" at the mines of Cyberstan, under the ownership of the Super Earth Construction Company.\n&lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt; Advanced Weapons Laboratory.\nDuring Operation Starslayer, Super Earth High Command would issue a major order mandating that the Helldivers maintained control of X-45 while search and recovery teams investigated the lightly irradiated ruins of an old weapons lab from this war, its research focused on the production of Interplanetary Battle Stations, meaning it was probably a Super Earth Navy Facility. It is also likely that this facility was a joint military base, intended to house research/other non-combat personnel of the Super Earth Navy and serve as an outpost for Helldiver Commandos, as a cache of fully operational &lt;a href=\"MLS-4X%20Commando\"&gt;MLS-4X Commando&lt;/a&gt; Missile Launchers and blueprints for Tier 5 Super Destroyer upgrades were also found in the planet during the operation, which allowed their fleetwide deployment after the operation concluded.\nThe conditions of how this facility became irradiated and abandoned are never stated, but given the proximity of the planet to Cyberstan it is likely that it was directly related to the conflict that was going on between Super Earth and the Cyborg Insurgency in 2084. Whether it was due to the fallout from a nuclear meltdown or nuclear bombardment is up for debate.\nWhat is made clear is that X-45 was uninhabitable due to the radiation for the 100 year period between the First and Second Galactic Wars, which explains why the planet didn't have any FTL Supply lines connecting it to the rest of its sector until July 2184.\nBattle of &lt;a href=\"Choepessa%20IV\"&gt;Choepessa IV&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnother confirmed battle of the First Galactic War is the Battle of Choepessa IV, also known as the \"Liberation of Choepessa IV\". This engagement would see the Bugs fight against the Helldivers over control of the once lush, green jungle planet, as its location can make it a handy forward base. According to the description of the \"Purifying Eclipse\" cape from the \"&lt;a href=\"Freedom%27s%20Flame\"&gt;Freedom's Flame&lt;/a&gt;\" Warbond, this battle saw such a heavy usage of orbital ordnance that the resulting cloud of debris and ash would occlude the planet's sun for an entire lunar cycle (29.5 days).\nGoing by the name, it can be inferred that the Bugs would initially overwhelm the planet's defenses but would then be liberated after an unknown amount of time. Judging by the \"heavy usage of orbital ordnance\", it perhaps was shortly after the initial assault.\nJudging by Choepessa IV's status prior to the Second Galactic War and the name it is described by on the previously mentioned source, it is safe to say that this engagement resulted in victory for Super Earth, while also being a possible cause for the glaciation that made Choepessa IV into the icy boneyard planet it is by 2184.\nBattle of &lt;a href=\"Squ%27bai%20Shrine\"&gt;Squ'bai Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nA battle that is not mentioned anywhere in Helldivers 2 but makes an appearance in Helldivers 1 is the Battle of Squ'bai Shrine, the homeworld of the Illuminate during the First Galactic War. While in Helldivers 1 it is possible for the community to be defeated in this battle, the current state of the galaxy in Helldivers 2 confirms that this battle ended in victory for Super Earth. After being defeated, the Illuminate would sign a peace treaty with the Federation of Super Earth and subsequently abandon the Milky Way, never to return.\nSqu'bai Shrine is currently not present in the Galactic War Map.\nBattle of &lt;a href=\"Outpost%2032\"&gt;Outpost 32&lt;/a&gt;.\nOutpost 32, a planet in the Saleria Sector, was presumably part of the Cyborg front during the First Galactic War. Not much is known about how this battle developed, as it is only mentioned through a poster than can sometimes appear plastered on buildings in Helldivers 2. The poster depicted of an Automaton Devastator overlooking the burning ruins of a Super Citizen's home, along with a ragged, flag in the middle and the phrase \"Remember Outpost 32\" could imply that Outpost 32 was either a great defeat that would eventually be corrected after the Battle of Cyberstan or a victory that came at a tremendous cost (for SEAF standards).\nIt should be noted that Outpost 32 is not even a possible planet to play on Helldivers 1, which raises questions about whether or not this battle even occured or if it was fabricated by the federation in order to raise support for the campaigns against the Automatons in the Second Galactic War.\nNevertheless, this battle is now grimly present in the minds of the colonists of not only Outpost 32, but also the entire Saleria sector, given the return of the nefarious Illuminate.\nBattle of &lt;a href=\"Kepler%20Prime\"&gt;Kepler Prime&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnother battle that is not mentioned anywhere in Helldivers 2 but makes an appearance in Helldivers 1 is the Battle of Kepler Prime, the homeworld of the Bugs during the First Galactic War. While it is possible for the community to be defeated in this battle, the state of the galaxy prior to February 2184 in Helldivers 2 confirms that this battle ended in victory for Super Earth.\nKepler Prime is currently not present in the Galactic War Map.\nEnd of the War.\nBy 2084, Super Earth had successfully defeated all of its enemies. The Bugs would be successfully contained into E-710 farms, in which they would then be subjected to genetic experimentation and selective breeding in order to increase E-710 production, with the result being the Bugs' rapid evolution into the present in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Cyborgs, as previously mentioned, would be defeated and interned in Cyberstan as punishment until a new foe, the would seemingly invade the planet, their current fate being unknown.\nThe Illuminate, after the battle of Squ'bai Shrine, would end up signing a peace treaty with Super Earth, the terms of which forced them to surrender all of their technology and weapons to the Federation of Super Earth, amongst which was technology allowing for Faster-Than-Light travel and the Dark fluid, a mysterious superweapon capable of collapsing planets into black holes, as displayed in &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. However, having spent 100 years in exile, these Squ'ith would then come back to enact vengeance onto Super Earth once more, as the suddenly attacked the urban colonies of &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; on December 12th, 2184.\nAftermath and Consequences of the War.\nThe years following the First Galactic War saw the rapid and unopposed expansion of Super Earth through the Milky Way, in part thanks to the FTL Travel Technology obtained from the Illuminate. As the years passed, the Helldivers were deactivated as a new era of peace and prosperity ushered in for humanity, as they believed they would not need to call upon the Helldivers again.\nAccording to the PA Announcer in one of the randomized TV Ads in the Super Destroyers in Helldivers 2, the Bugs were responsible for 189,000,000 civilian casualties, with a significant portion of those being human babies. This could explain why, by the time of the Second Galactic War, civilian society is so accustomed to the glorification of violence towards the Terminids.\nThe Illuminate and the Cyborgs, thought decisively defeated by Super Earth, would be reduced to mere boogeyman for parents to use across the Federation in cautionary tales they would recite to their children as they raised them into proper citizens of the Federation.\nWhile it is not shown in neither game, the canonical result of the Battle of Cyberstan suggests that the few Cyborgs that remained not only continued to suffer discrimination, but would also be held under bondage (if not complete subservience) to the Super Earth Construction Company, being mostly relegated to concentration camps within Cyberstan's surface."}
{"id": "6314", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6314", "title": "Flag of Super Earth", "text": "The flag of Super Earth is the National banner of the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;.\nDesign.\nThe flag of Super Earth is a 2:3 rectangular banner featuring a Blue (Hex Code: #59779A) field and a white-yellow (HEX CODES: #FFFFFF &amp; #DACB1C) emblem in the center.\nThe emblem consists of an azimuthal projection of Earth. In 2084, this projection was centered around the Caribbean, specifically on the Gulf of Mexico close to Sector 7, while in 2184, the flag was updated, now featuring an azimuthal projection of Earth centered on Prosperity City, the capital of the Federation (formerly called Stockholm). Both versions of this projection are in white\nCrowning said projection of earth is a (possible) depiction of the Presidential Palace, which has been datamined but has never been shown in game.\nAs its supporter, there is a simplified yellow wreath, with a sequence of 7 starts right underneath, serving as its compartment.\nPossible Meanings.\nAffectionately named \"The White, Yellow, Blue\" by the majority of the population, the Flag of Super Earth's design has many potential interpretations. Here, some of the most plausible has been listed.\nAccording to traditional vexillology, the Blue field could represent the vastness of the cosmos, in which Super Earth stands at its center, serving as a beacon of hope, peace, liberty and prosperity that all other alien species should aspire to.\nThe white emblem could represent Super Earth's role as an agent of order and harmony, dispensing peace upon all planets and sectors within its reach, as well as serving as a reminder of its mission to pacify the galaxy so that all sentient human species may coalesce and exist in harmony and Managed Democracy.\nThe yellow wreath featured since 2184 may represent the prosperity which Super Earth has accomplished after its grandiose victory, as well as the prosperity it aims to disseminate across the known universe. It could also represent the Helldivers themselves, who are the guardians of humankind and heroes of Super Earth.\nThe 7 stars at the bottom of the emblem could represent each of the 7 sectors, while the crowning symbol at the top could represent the President of Super Earth or the Democratic Council.\nHistory.\nThe first flag of Super Earth during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; used a different emblem with no stars, a white wreath and centred on the Caribbean. This flag was most likely adopted upon the Proclamation of the Federation of Super Earth and, given the many decades that this conflict lasted, it was preserved due to convenience. \nThe second version of the flag has the seven stars in a straight line getting smaller for the centre instead of being curved around the globe, there is also four towers at the top of the emblem instead of three. It can be seen at &lt;a href=\"Objectives\"&gt;Main Objectives&lt;/a&gt;, houses, &lt;a href=\"Extraction\"&gt;Extraction&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers 2 background, the &lt;a href=\"Escalation%20of%20Freedom\"&gt;Escalation of Freedom&lt;/a&gt; background and the galactic war table.\nThe third version of the flag has no gold rings and was seen on the mission accomplished poster after the defeat of the Automaton Vanguard.\nThe Fourth version of the flag is seen in the games intro, it has a altered emblem that is missing the Mediterranean Sea. It is theorised that Super Earth drained the Mediterranean but this is false as it can be seen on the World Map.\nIn during the Capture Area , the flag used had the helldivers colours with the Super Earth emblem in the middle."}
{"id": "3785", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3785", "title": "Fori Prime", "text": "Fori Prime is one of the three planets that resides within the &lt;a href=\"Draco%20Sector\"&gt;Draco Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It is a planet similar to Vernen Wells, with red sand and tall, imposing plateaus. It serves as one of the 2 border planets with the neighbouring Mirin Sector (the other being nearby &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt;), as it has the only FTL Line towards &lt;a href=\"Oshaune\"&gt;Oshaune&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nMuch like the previously mentioned &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt;, Fori Prime is an arid red desert, rich in iron and other minerals that have given the sand its velvet color. Amidst the crimson dunes, tall plateaus dot the horizon, as they can span sizes similar to Super Earth's continents, suggesting possible ancient aquatic activity. Most of the flora consists of dry bushes and shrubs, and the occasional small dead trees.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nFori Prime would be under Terminid occupation from the very start of the year 2184. It would endure horrors beyond description that, for the purposes of brevity, we will forgo describing. Fori Prime would lay in bondage, yearning for liberation until the light of Liberty shun on it from the horizon. Shortly after the installation of the Terminid Control System on the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Barrier Planets&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers would finally be able to push farther east, allowing them to access the Draco and Mirin Sectors.\nOperation Prime Liberation.\nAs demand increased for civilian population expansion and energy sources, Super Earth would see the opportunity to fulfill these needs in the Draco and Mirin Sectors. As such, Super Earth High Command issued a major order for the liberation of Fori Prime and &lt;a href=\"Zagon%20Prime\"&gt;Zagon Prime&lt;/a&gt;. While Fori Prime would be easily captured, Zagon Prime proved unable to be captured on time, which led to all C-01 forms being denied until further notice.\nOperation CBCT Protection.\nDespite the previous failure, a new order would be issued. The Helldivers were to obtain and maintain control of Fori Prime, alongside &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt;, for 3 days while Civilian Biomass Collection teams acquired inert Terminids for research purposes. While most of the other planets were relatively easy to keep under control, Fori Prime and Hellmire would prove challenging to maintain, with Fori Prime's defense being consistently tested due to constant assault from Oshaune.\nOperation Enduring Bulwark.\nThings would only turn for the worse for the remote red planet, as the war soon escalated. Shortly after their complete obliteration on Malevelon Creek in April, the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; would return in even bigger numbers on the West, taking over Cyberstan and the rest of the Valdis Sector. And to make matters worse, the Terminids, in an act of sinister coordination with the mechanized foes, would also launch one great offensive in the East.\nDespite this incredible, dual-fronted assault, the Helldivers would once more prove themselves the unbreakable shield of mankind, managing to hold the line against dozens of assaults, both bot and bug, with planets like Estanu withstanding up to 5 consecutive assaults. Fori Prime would see its own Terminid Assault during this operation, with its defense resulting in a huge success, in part thanks to the timely liberation of neighboring &lt;a href=\"Oshaune\"&gt;Oshaune&lt;/a&gt;, which was the main supply source for the Terminid assault on Fori Prime.\nFrom here on, Fori Prime's situation would go from a matter of occupation to a matter of holding Fori Prime for as long as possible. Due to its remoteness and other, bigger developments throughout April and especially May of 2184, Fori Prime would see virtually all Helldiver presence in it cease completely, leaving it undefended and, eventually, allowing it to be captured by the Terminids.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAs May 2184 rolled in, things soured in the Terminid Front. With the failure of the Terminid Control System and the apparition of the &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridian Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;, the Terminid onslaught in the East reached a critical, intolerable level. Fori Prime and the rest of the Draco Sector quickly fell to the bolstered bug assault and would remain in bondage for the whole month.\nIt would have seemed that all hope was lost for the red planet, which had so far only tasted but a drop of the glorious ambrosia of Managed Democracy. However, Liberty's will was for Fori Prime to have a second chance.\n12 scientists would be tragically spaghettified at Moradesh on May 29th, as the SEAF gave the green light to Operation Enduring Peace. It's goal: To use the Dark Fluid, an Illuminate superweapon capable of collapsing planets into black holes, on Meridia. Then on the late hours of May 30th, the news would break: The Helldivers had successfully destroyed the abominable Supercolony, crippling the augmented Terminid wave and allowing for a counterattack.\nOperation Hive Breaker.\nAfter a swift re-establishment of freedom on the Umlaut Sector and some much needed victories on the Automaton Front, Super Earth High Command would give a new major order. The Helldivers were to reliberate Hellmire, Estanu, Crimsica, Nivel 43 and Fori Prime.\nCrimsica would be liberated first, on June 16th. Then followed Estanu on the 17th. Then, finally, Fori Prime would be liberated once again on June 18th, with Oshaune and Hellmire being selected as the next targets for liberation. However, the Terminids were determined to maintaining their hold over the red planet, as they quickly launched a counterattack on Fori Prime on the morning of June 19th. After a great deal of death, Super Earth held the planet and it is now classified as a \"Frontline World Against Evil.\"\nFalstaff and Jin Xi Lockdown.\nAnd true to its new classification, Fori Prime would soon endure another assault. However, the planet would only find misfortune, as it would be assaulted while the Helldivers were diverted to the defense of the Xzar Sector. It would fall shortly and then get stuck in a deadlock for a couple days before then, around June 29th, sending an outburst of Terminid Spores towards Crimsica, which successfully overwhelmed its defenses.\nOperation Andromeda.\nFori Prime would remain resistant to liberation and, once the Helldivers were diverted away to fight the Automatons, it would serve as a launching pad for the Terminids to invade Estanu yet again in July, successfully cutting Fori Prime off."}
