{"id": "6886", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6886", "title": "Free Colony", "text": "To deny the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; the vast resources of the voting public, Helldivers are tasked to Free Colonies threatened by Illuminate tyranny.\nGameplay.\nRaise Flag of Super Earth.\nAs with the &lt;a href=\"Spread%20Democracy\"&gt;Spread Democracy&lt;/a&gt; missions, Helldivers are to fly the colors of Super Earth at pre-determined locations to re-assert Managed Democracy over threatened colonies.\nOne layout consists of a small plaza surrounded by large structures. This prevents vehicles and massive enemies from interfering with the ceremony, allowing defenders to focus on the &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; undoubtedly attempting to remind themselves of Liberty's love.\nThere does not appear to be a requirement to clear enemies from the radius of the flag, only for Helldivers to stand true.\nOn higher difficulties, it may be necessary to raise more than one flag.\nDestroy Monolith.\nThe Illuminate have somehow constructed bizarre Monoliths in certain cities. Before we can learn their secrets, the Monoliths must be brought down.\nThe monoliths have attracted the &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; in such numbers that they form piles at their base. Such unsanitary conditions cannot be tolerated. &lt;a href=\"Illuminate%20Tesla%20Tower\"&gt;Illuminate Tesla Tower&lt;/a&gt;s are often placed around monoliths, perhaps to rid themselves of nuisance Voteless, or perhaps to subdue them for some future calling.\nUntil the Ministry of Truth can ascertain their purpose, Helldivers are advised not to touch the Monolith. Conventional weapons do not appear to have any lasting effect on a Monolith, and so require a &lt;a href=\"NUX-223%20Hellbomb\"&gt;NUX-223 Hellbomb&lt;/a&gt; to clear."}
