{"id": "4016", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4016", "title": "GL-21 Grenade Launcher", "text": "The GL-21 is one of the &lt;a href=\"stratagems\"&gt;stratagems&lt;/a&gt; available to the player. It is an infantry-carried semi-automatic grenade launcher, fed using a short belt of 10 grenade shells.\nThe weapon has great destructive potential against light and medium-armored enemies due to its power and AoE, but struggles against heavy units. Still, its high stagger potential and low recoil allow it to deal lots of unanswered damage in a short time."}
{"id": "4695", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4695", "title": "GP-31 Grenade Pistol", "text": "The GP-31 is a breach-loaded grenade launcher module, affixed to a compact stand-alone platform to turn it into a sidearm.\nIt fires one explosive impact grenade, comparable to that used by the &lt;a href=\"GL-21%20Grenade%20Launcher\"&gt;GL-21 Grenade Launcher&lt;/a&gt;, and needs to be reloaded every shot. The weapon's ammunition is extremely limited, 1 in the tube + 6 spare grenades in total, requiring them to be used sparingly. Ammunition pickups will only replenish 2 grenades, while supply pickups restore 4. It is heavily recommended to deploy with the &lt;a href=\"Boosters\"&gt;Hellpod Space Optimization&lt;/a&gt; booster as the player only deploys with 4 extra grenades for the launcher, which is hard to top-up completely due to the low replenish rate.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn addition to the obvious destructive applications, the weapon can still be used to seal bug holes and destroy automaton fabricators, as you could with the GL-21. As a pistol, it is a one-handed weapon and can be fired on the move, or while holding an object.\nSince it counts as an impromptu impact grenade, using the GP-31 gives Helldivers an option to take another type of grenade into battle as this already covers their explosive needs, expanding one's tactical flexibility, at the cost of reliable close-range defense."}
{"id": "3780", "revid": "54411", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3780", "title": "GR-8 Recoilless Rifle", "text": "\"A recoilless rifle effective against vehicle armor. Includes support backpack required for reloading.\"\nThe GR-8 recoilless rifle is one of the &lt;a href=\"stratagems\"&gt;stratagems&lt;/a&gt; available to the player.\nDesign.\nThe GR-8 is a man-portable, shoulder-fired anti-armor launch, firing user-selectable ammo-types of High Explosive Anti Tank(HEAT) and Hight Explosive(HE), for both defeating heavy armor vehicles/personnel and crowd/obstacle reduction. Reloaded via the breech of the launcher assembly using a locking-lever to seat and unseat the shell case from the chamber. Rounds are reloaded one at a time and the user must stop to complete the task. However, can be team assisted in reloading easily doubling the rate of fire to spread Democracy.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this single-use &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:"}
{"id": "5569", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5569", "title": "Gacrux", "text": "Gacrux is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nA veritable green maze, Gacrux flora is dense and ever present. Planet features frequent but small elevation changes from rocky hills into waterlogged channels and reservoirs. Helldivers should exercise caution, as the waters are treacherous. What from distance may look like ankle deep water, is in reality a very deep lake that one can very easy drown in mere seconds after stepping off from the shoreline.\nThe planet is also dotted with ancient fossilized trees, some reaching far above the current tree line. The Massive amounts of evergreen block line of sight, but they can be use as reliable cover thanks to their sheer thickness. Additionally, the planet features a network of gas vents, located randomly throughout the surface. Yellowish in color and emiting a green smoke, any kind of fire or bullet ignites it, causing a fiery explosion in their proximity.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nLocated in remote part of Jin Xi Sector, this planet avoided the wave of &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; infestation during the &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Firebreak\"&gt;Meridian Supercolony Crisis&lt;/a&gt; that spilled from &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt; in early June of 2184. Once the crisis receded, its FTL Supply Lines would be restored on June 13th.\nOperation Hive Breaker.\nOn June 20th, 2184, local colony officials confirmed landing of Terminid Spores, later calculated to have arrived from &lt;a href=\"Fori%20Prime\"&gt;Fori Prime&lt;/a&gt; through what appears to be a newly created FTL Line. The defenses collapsed on the midnight of June 21st, prompting the immediate calls for a liberation campaign of the swampy planet. The planet has sadly been stuck in a stalemate ever since, as other operations with higher priority have required Helldivers be diverted away from it.\nOperation Glorious Xenocide.\nFrom June 21st onwards, Gacrux had been stuck in a deadlock thatonly helped sabotage the valiant peacekeeping efforts of the Helldivers, mostly by helping reignite any outbreaks in the Jin Xi Sector. However, its fate would be sealed once its assault onto Acamar IV was flipped on its head. After its spores hopped from Acamar IV onto &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt;, they would be quickly repelled and, as Operation Righteous Expunge was completed, the Helldivers would launch an assault onto Acamar IV, which would result in its liberation on the late hours of July 22nd. Then, on July 23rd, a surge of Helldivers turned up to Gacrux to finally put an end to its wretched Terminid problem once and for all.\nGacrux would see lots of bloody combat, as the Terminids put on display their unfettered savagery. Nevertheless, the Helldivers would come out victorious, liberating Gacrux on the evening of July 24th.\nOperation Lighthouse.\nFrom July 24th to August 13th, Gacrux would remain under the warm embrace of Super Earth, its colonists doing what they could to rebuild their settlements and refortify their colonies, left in ruins after the Terminid outbreak. However, these works would be cut short as, due to the diversion of the Helldivers towards the final liberation of the &lt;a href=\"Encirclements%23Matar_Bay_Encirclement\"&gt;Matar Bay Encirclement&lt;/a&gt;, Gacrux would be left underdefended. With The Gloom looming over the galactic horizon, the Terminids would use their new nebulous cover to prepare their fiendish plans. \nOn the early hours of August 12th, the Terminids in &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt; and Fori Prime launched a dual assault onto Acamar IV and Gacrux. The Helldivers that remained in the Eastern Front would flood into Acamar IV, hoping for a quick liberation so that they could also liberate Gacrux before resuming the campaigns in the Western Front. However, the Terminids at Acamar IV would present heavy resistance to the application of peace and, consequently, delayed the success of Acamar's defense enough to make Gacrux fall into their devious appendages by the early hours of August 13th, mere hours after Acamar IV's defense successfully repelled its own Terminid assault.\nOperation Ring Of Freedom.\nGacrux would remain caught in a bloody stalemate for months on end, never being either fully lost nor liberated for any significant period of time, with the only time gap where it didn't see Helldiver presence being from August 22nd to August 24th. Throughout the course of the Galactic War, many operations would surge that would keep Gacrux at the very bottom of the list of objectives, even as The Gloom appeared and encroached upon Fori Prime and threatened to expand upon it.\nHowever, fate soon would change for the swampy planet as, soon, the Helldivers would begin to work towards the construction of the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt;, and with it came the construction of the Xenoentomology Center at Turing that was required for the research and development of better Alcubierre drives to allow the new DSS to perform FTL Warp Travels. And this new Xenoentomology Center required a Terminid Research Preserve in order to study the Terminids and how to make them produce the most E-710 possible.\nBut this preserve couldn't be allowed to be connected to the main Terminid brood and much less to the Gloom. As such, a safety perimeter was to be established around Acamar IV.\nDespite Gacrux's immediate proximity to Acamar and to The Gloom through its FTL line with Fori Prime, it wouldn't see any significant Helldiver action until October 14th, shortly after the victory at &lt;a href=\"Darius%20II\"&gt;Darius II&lt;/a&gt; and the defense of &lt;a href=\"Achernar%20Secundus\"&gt;Achernar Secundus&lt;/a&gt;. Being the last objective planet and infamous for its swamps, the Helldivers rushed to capture Gacrux as quickly as possible so that they wouldn't need to stay on it longer than needed. As such, Gacrux would see up to 35,000 Super Destroyers, around 67% of the Helldiver Corps at the time, exclusively devoted to deploying ordnance onto the planet.\nBy the morning of October 15th, Gacrux had been thoroughly liberated, with its security seemingly assured given how The Gloom had stopped expanding weeks prior. \nOperation Crossroads.\nHowever, it wasn't fated for Gacrux's liberty to last. A mere 9 days after its liberation, the Terminids, aided by a spore surge coming out of the Gloom, would mount an offensive headed directly for the Terminid Research Preserve. However, this offensive took place around the same time that the Jet Brigade had shown signs to be planning an offensive, with &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt; appearing to be from where it would launch. Having been given the decision of whether to capture Lesath or defend the Terminid Research Preserve, the Helldivers made the difficult choice of abandoning the Terminid Front in order to capture Lesath and secure it from a potential Jet Brigade attack.\nGacrux would be attacked on October 23rd from Partion, with Pandion-XXIV being attacked from Phact Bay merely hours later. Despite a detachment of Helldivers being left behind, the Terminid attack managed to punch through by October 24th, leaving the Terminid Research Preserve Vulnerable.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nGacrux would remain under Terminid occupation for 6 days, as the Helldivers were forced to fight through Phact Bay and Pandion-XXIV before getting to the swamp planet, as the FTL Line from Acamar IV had been pre-emptively shut down in order to prevent an outbreak in the Terminid Research Preserve. However, Gacrux's liberation would be delayed because of ongoing offensives in the Automaton front constantly diverting huge chunks of Helldivers away in order to keep them from expanding.\nGacrux's liberation would come too late, as the constant delays in its liberation; product of the difficult fight against the Automatons at Matar Bay, Demiurg and Curia, would ultimately slow down Gacrux's liberation enough for the order's time limit to pass, making Operation Adamant Resolve a technical failure. However, the Helldivers would still wind up liberating the planet on November 3rd, securing the Terminid Research Preserve against any attacks for the time being.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nGacrux would remain free of any Terminid presence after its liberation. It would seem that, after all, things hadn't come to boil despite the tactical miscalculation during Operation Crossroads. But the seeds of fascism had already been sown on the Terminid Research Preserve, and it was only a matter of time before their bore their nefarious fruits.\nOn November 12th, in the middle of a busy day for the Tyranny Park, a massive underground Terminid hive erupted spontaneously, leading to a bloody massacre of visitors and park staff alike. Acamar IV was overrun in mere minutes, which prevented the nuclear security measures from being activated and allowed the Terminids to take over the planet without any impediment. Once Acamar IV fell, it launched 5 simultaneous attacks onto all of the planets connected to it. This catastrophe could not have been any more poorly timed, as the Jet Brigade had also just returned in massive numbers and destroyed the DSS Logistics Hub on &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe painting was clear on the wall that the Helldivers had to act quick before more damage had to be done. Despite Acamar's positioning, High Command gave the indication to protect the Xenoentomology Center at Turing by all means, as it still contained critical research material on the Terminids, pretty much dooming Acamar IV and all of its attached planets to perdition.\nExpectedly, with the Helldivers focused on saving the critical research material at Turing, Gacrux would be lost to the Terminids by the afternoon of the following day, in a massive disaster that took millions of lives and undid all the progress achieved in the past 3 months."}
{"id": "5968", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5968", "title": "Gaellivare", "text": "Gaellivare is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Talus%20Sector\"&gt;Talus Sector&lt;/a&gt;. After being liberated on September 27th, 2184, it was chosen as the main construction site for the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt would see the construction of the Democracy Space Station through and, from November 13th to November 17th, was the site of a great battle between the Helldiver Corps and the Automaton Jet Brigade. Despite the defeat, the Helldivers managed to safely evacuate the DSS away from the Automatons, guaranteeing its safety and safeguarding its power well within Super Earth's control.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Mantes\"&gt;Mantes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Meissa\"&gt;Meissa&lt;/a&gt;. The climate on Gaellivare is both very humid and very wet, with lots of precipitation. Helldivers deployed to the planet will find that it rains\u2026 a lot, to say the least.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Titanium Belt.\nGaellivare had been a peaceful colony of Super Earth for many decades at this point, having been settled at some point after the end of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. Its colonists thrived throughout the many jungles and prospered thanks to the fertility of the soil around the volcanoes. However, the Automatons, in their unquenchable thirst for resources and their innate hatred for Super Earth, would thrust Gaellivare into the war by force.\nWhen the Automaton Legions invaded the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt; and began their territorial expansion in April and May 2184. Gaellivare's Colonial Overseer would order that all of its supply lines leading into neighboring sectors were closed, which helped safeguard the Talus Sector against the horrors that the Automatons had brought upon other planet colonies farther away.\nAs the months passed, Gaellivare's colonists would fortify their settlements and stockpile weapons, with the hopes of the Helldivers rescuing them as the robotic threat built up in Lesath, right at the doorstep of their new home planet.\nThey hoped that they would not need to use their defences against the robots. But little did they know that these defences would pave the way for their salvation.\nOn September 6th, 2184, the Automaton forces in Lesath, mere days after their vanguard in &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt; and Mastia was cut off, would launch an assault onto Gaellivare, timed almost perfectly with a secondary assault that the Automaton vanguard in Mastia launched onto &lt;a href=\"Shelt\"&gt;Shelt&lt;/a&gt;, as the Automatons seeked to utilize Imber's vast deposits of titanium in order to construct a new, unknown fighting force.\nSince the colonists in Shelt had been unable to properly prepare, the Helldivers would see themselves in the need to deploy to Shelt immediately in order to rescue its under-prepared defenders and prevent the Automatons from getting to Imber. However, this would leave Gaellivare to their own devices until Shelt could be secured.\nHowever, despite the victory at Shelt, the Helldivers were unable to successfully defend Gaellivare, with the assailants having already made too much progress in their invasion to really be driven back. Gaellivare would fall on the 8th of September, immediately starting an assault on Imber, as the Automaton forces punched through the planet. Through Gaellivare, the Automatons would go on to resupply their vanguard at Mastia before attempting 3 assaults at Imber, with the last one happening shortly before the end of Operation Liberty Tide and causing the loss of both the planet and the major order.\nOperation Leap Forward.\nAfter months of intense research, on the 25th of September, 2184, construction of the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt; was finally ready to begin. The DSS promised to be a powerful strategic tool for reshaping the Galactic Map \u2014 democratically directed by the Helldivers themselves. However to actually construct the DSS, an orbital construction site must first be secured.\nOf the planets within Super Earth's reach, only two two have large enough magnetospheres for safe construction: Gaellivare and &lt;a href=\"Clasa\"&gt;Clasa&lt;/a&gt;. Both of which were under &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; control.\nThough the final choice of which to liberate was ultimately left to the Helldivers, Gaellivare was the more strategically viable choice. Although the planet would no doubt receive counter attacks from &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Imber\"&gt;Imber&lt;/a&gt;, Gaellivare was also much closer to the active galactic front-line when compared to Clasa, which would have required the liberation of both &lt;a href=\"Vog-Sojoth\"&gt;Vog-Sojoth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Claorell\"&gt;Claorell&lt;/a&gt; to properly defend, not to mention the marked distaste of swamp planets amongst the corps. Thus the majority of helldivers deployed onto Gaellivare.\nDespite the losses of Imber, &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt; on the Terminid Front and Shelt throughout the 4 days during which the Helldivers fought over an unusually fortified Automaton force at Gaellivare, it would be finally captured on September 27th. Once the DSS Logistics Hub would be built on &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt; in order to streamline the allocation of construction materials and resources towards the Democracy Space Station.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nGaellivare would see the Automatons for the last time on September 27th, as the Helldivers secured it for the construction of the Democracy Space Station. For 2 months, Gaellivare enjoyed peace and prosperity like no other, as its population centupled and its economy flourished, with millions of construction workers pouring in from all over the galaxy as the construction went on smoothly.\nHowever, it would be at the last second when Gaellivare would see its 2 months of well-earned peace come to an end. On November 11th; just as the Democracy Space Station was about to come online, the Jet Brigade, a special strike force of the Automatons that had been crafted through the use of metal gathered from throughout their fief and the desecration fallen Helldivers off their Jump Packs, would return. Having been defeated at &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt; on September 22nd, this repugnant force had been rebuilt and given 58 Automaton Battalions with one express purpose: Conquering Gaellivare and destroying the Democracy Space Station.\nOn November 12th, the Jet Brigade would brutally conquer Tarsh and destroy the DSS Logistics Hub, then on November 13th followed Mastia, despite a heroic sacrifice from an SEAF platoon from Lesath.\nThen, hours after the fall of Mastia's defense, the Jet Brigade attacked, with 47 Automaton Battalions behind it. Gaellivare's SEAF garrison, having enjoyed lots of time and resources to reinforce and prepare for the eventual return of the Automatons, would send the call for Helldiver aid, as they estimated that they would last about 48 hours before the Automatons took over the planet. However, events would soon take a wild turn from a side they did not expect.\nAmidst the heroic defense of Gaellivare, at 21:37 SEST, the Helldivers would manage to acquire enough E-710 to activate the DSS, having acquired it after the collapse of the Terminid Research Preserve at Acamar IV. With the Democracy Space Station active, Gaellivare would be able to defend itself against the Automatons.\nFor the rest of the night and into November 14th, the Helldivers and the SEAF fought valiantly to repel the Automaton Jet Brigade, but the situation continued to look more and more grim. However, High Command would spy an opportunity in Mastia, as its capture would possibly end the assault on Gaellivare, as the Jet Brigade would be cut off from its supply line.\nAs such, the Helldivers voted to move the Democracy Space Station to Mastia, where they would then enable the Planetary Bombardment. For the rest of November 14th, the defense at Gaellivare would continue to fight the Jet Brigade as best as it could, as the main fleet of the Helldivers moved back to Mastia to attempt its capturing before it was too late. Some dissidents have suggested this manoeuvre was more motivated more motivated by strategic miscommunication to the nature of the DSS's voting system &amp; that splitting Helldiver forces between 2 hard fought warzones was a catastrophic blunder, fortunately Ministry of Truth officials were able to quickly crack down on such thoughtcrime, even during the conflict.\nHowever, this effort still would not be enough, as Mastia was still too reinforced to break in time. As such, the Helldivers had to get creative and voted to move the DSS back to Gaellivare, where they would then activate the Eagle Storm. With the assistance of the Democracy Space Station, the advance of the Jet Brigade would be slowed to a halt, which allowed the Helldivers to relocate back to Gaellivare to continue fighting, now being able to properly counterattack and, hopefully, come out victorious. This also resulted in the majority of Helldivers following the DSS back to Gaellivare, abandoning the Gambit at Mastia thus rendering the previous days fighting a waste of time whilst. \nThis comment redacted for treason.\nWhile Gaellivare would be held within the operation's timeframe, the battle was still not over. The fate of Gaellivare, and the Democracy Space Station, still depended on the outcome of this defense.\nHowever, dissidence had grown among the Helldiver Corps, and with dissidence came indecision to violently replace the Helldivers' usual focus and efficiency. For many hours, they fought against the paralyzed Jet Brigade, racing to try and take enough ground to gain the upper hand before the Democracy Space Station's blockade had to be lifted. Yet, the enemy numbers where just too great.\nDespite all of the many millions of lives lost after 3 days on continuous battle, the Helldivers had been unable to overtake the Jet Brigade. The enemy was incredibly numerous and the Helldivers hadn't been able to properly manoeuvre around them despite all their best efforts.\nOnce the Democracy Space Station left for &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;, the main Helldiver fleet went away with it. Gaellivare was doomed.\nEven with all of their might, the Helldivers had managed to fight the Jet Brigade for long enough to move the Democracy Space Station beyond their reach but not long enough to defeat them. Gaellivare would ultimately fall at 6:22 SEST - EST, leaving the Helldivers greatly defeated and all of the heroic martyrs that gave their lives for Super Earth waiting to be justfully avenged.\nWhile Operation Spark of Liberty would be successful, as Gaellivare was still within Super Earth Control for long enough to allow the DSS to escape from the Automatons, this small victory had come at a cost too great: The complete collapse of the Terminid Front, product of the disastrous breach at Acamar IV, and the campaign against the Jet Brigade itself had resulted in the loss of 8 planets across 5 sectors, with the civilian casualties in the hundreds of millions and the damages very well into the tens of billions of Super Credits.\nOperation Spark of Liberty, despite its pyrrhic victory, was a complete military disaster.\nOperation Balance of Liberty.\nIn order to recoup the brutal yet absolutely necessary losses sustained while Super Earth focussed on the DSS's construction, the Ministry of Defense put the vital superweapon to immediate use retaking lost ground, putting out a Major Order to all Helldivers to Liberate more planets than they lost over the orders duration. \nStill stinging from the desperate battle for Gaellivare, the Helldivers immediately cast their gaze back to the lost world as their first target of attack, voting the DSS back into the planets orbit a day after it left to stubbornly ensure the planet's liberation. \nHowever, as the Jet Brigade left to assault nearby Imber. The valiant liberation of Gaellivare would become an even more valiant endeavour, retaking Gaellivare while the Jet Brigade where still using it as a staging grounds would cut their assault force off from their supply lines. Not only resulting in the ensured freedom of both worlds, but wiping clean the stains of both the loss of Gaellivare &amp; the failed Mastia Gambit.\nThe fighting on Gaellivare would be as bitter as it was a few days prior, with vengeful Helldivers refusing to back down a second time, High Command would deploy free Airburst Missile Launcher to all Helldivers during this time in order to observe if the rate at which they caused tragic yet unavoidable friendly fire incidents was still at acceptable levels, most would be put to use here, blasting devastator &amp; diver alike to smithereens in a brutal battle to save 2 planets at once.\nTragically Gaellivare would only be liberated to 95% by the time it's neighbour fell. Returning to Liberty's arms but a few hours too late to save Imber from tyranny. \nDespite this, the victory at Gaellivare would effectively sever the Jet Brigade off their supply line, leaving them encircled at Imber, their numbers severely demolished from their string of odious conquests. As such, with the DSS now operational, the Helldivers would begin to reroute their forces towards Imber, as the contingent left at the Terminid front began to re-route towards &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt;. "}
