{"id": "3313", "revid": "55287310", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3313", "title": "Gallux Sector", "text": "The Gallux Sector is an inhabited area of galaxy found &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It is located on Galactic South East from &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; and it consists of 6 planets.\nTogether with other sectors in galactic south, it was invaded by in middle of December 2184. The Squ'ith have descended upon said sectors in series of pillaging raids, aimed to abduct as many civilians as possible."}
{"id": "6004", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6004", "title": "Gar Haren", "text": " is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Overrun.\nGar Haren was a relatively isolated colony of Super Earth that, ever since its initial colonization, hadn't really engaged in contact with the rest of the Jin Xi system. Given its foggy, swampy environment, its colonists spent much of their time paddling makeshift rafts and canoes down the swamps to fish and using the few patches of fertile, livable land to build their settlements and farms.\nHowever, despite its innocuous, peaceful nature, the, being soulless, fascistic insects, would have no appreciation for such simplistic pleasures. During Operation Overrun, Gar Haren's FTL Lines to neighboring Gatria and Phact Bay would be restored as the Ministry of Expansion seeked to increase colonization efforts on the otherwise unremarkable planet. \nIt would be because of this interest from the Ministry that the SEAF would be tasked with ensuring Gar Haren's security, alongside with that of Phact Bay and Gatria amidst a Terminid outbreak produced by the Gloom, an intergalactic nebula made up of Terminid Interstellar spores that appeared around Socorro III some weeks prior.\nHowever, Operation Overrun would go remarkably well for the Helldivers, as they managed to successfully repel all attacks that were coming towards both Phact Bay and Gatria despite the massive Terminid numbers. As such, Gar Haren's colonists would mostly only spend their time building light fortifications and stockpiling moderate amounts of weapons that would mostly remained stashed in scattered depots.\nOperation Ring of Freedom.\nHowever, this peace was not going to last forever. As the months passed and the Helldivers were diverted elsewhere, the Terminids seemed to have learned, now pouncing onto planets when the Helldivers weren't looking. Such was the case for Phact Bay, which fell on September 28th after 2 days of fierce fighting against a Terminid assault from &lt;a href=\"Partion\"&gt;Partion&lt;/a&gt;. Then, the Terminids at Phact Bay would go on to successfully invade &lt;a href=\"Darius%20II\"&gt;Darius II&lt;/a&gt; on September 29th.\nThe painting was clear on the wall and, fittingly, the colonists in Gar Haren began to make preparations for an invasion, while the Terminids in Phact Bay would go back to then send another assault onto &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; on September 30th, not even a full week after its excruciating liberation. While this first assault would be repelled, the bugs at Phact Bay would withdray to regain their strength, while an assault from Gacrux would ultimately overwhelm Pandion on October 7th.\nWith Pandion scratched off its list, the only remaining ways for Super Earth to attack the Terminid broods at Phact Bay were Gatria and Gar Haren. However, Gatria had proven to be very defensible against the Bugs, having never been lost to the Terminids through an assault in all of the Second Galactic War so far. As such, using their maleficent instinct, the Bugs instead opted for their other, more strategically valuable target: Gar Haren\nGar Haren had just opened a new FTL line with Achernar Secundus, which itself linked back to &lt;a href=\"Ursica%20XI\"&gt;Ursica XI&lt;/a&gt;, itself linking to &lt;a href=\"Achird%20III\"&gt;Achird III&lt;/a&gt; which, ultimately, led to &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt;, the home of the new Xenoentomology Center that had been constructed as part of the Democracy Space Station project.\nThus, on October 12th, the Terminids launched the first assault ever onto Gar Haren. This assault, despite a valiant defense from the Helldivers, would punch through on October 13th and then immediately head towards Achernar Secundus, as the Terminids aimed to reach Achird III with all they had.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nGar Haren would be under Terminid control ever since its fall, as the Helldivers were constantly diverted away towards other, more important, targets. However, Gar Haren would catch a glance of hope from an unexpected side.\nOn November 14th, after the tragedy at Acamar IV had caused the total collapse of the Terminid front, Gar Haren's Terminid hatcheries experienced a sudden extinction event, and no Terminids eggs would be there to replenish the fallen, which left Gar Haren's Terminid broods unable to undo any progress towards the planet's liberation.\nAs such, a small Helldiver contingent on the planet began to slowly make progress towards the planet, as all other forces were focused on keeping Gaellivare, and the Democracy Space Station, away from the Automatons.\nOperation Balance of Liberty.\nEven after the pyrrhic victory with the Democracy Space Station and all the losses in the Terminid Front, Gar Haren would continue its slow but steady progress towards liberation. However, where a small contingent had picked up the ball and gotten it rolling, the Helldiver Corps would soon get it all the way to the finish line, like a tortoise racing a hare.\nOnce &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt; was liberated on November 20th, the Helldiver Corps immediately rotated towards Gar Haren, hoping to liberate it in time to rotate towards more critical planets such as &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt;.\nGar Haren would be finally liberated on November 22nd without much fanfare or strife, allowing its colonists to resume their peaceful lives.\nInterim (December 16th - ).\nGar Haren would remain in peace following its liberation, without much events happening to it. It would remain safeguarded against a Terminid offensive during Operation Bughammer until, suddenly, all Helldivers were ordered towards &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; and, essentially, left all the fronts unmanned. The reason was nothing short of an event that rightfully demanded every available soldier in the SEAF: The had returned and were now invading Calypso.\nAs such, the Terminids would capture Gatria on December 14th leaving Gar Haren exposed. Then, 2 days later, the Terminids sent a spore barrage onto Gar Haren. However, their attack couldn't have been more poorly timed, since the Helldivers would come out of the battle at Calypso victorious and reinforced. Around 33,000 Super Destroyers immediately set course to Gar Haren, determined to drive the Terminids away from the planet and even farther away.\nFor the first 20 hours of the onslaught, the Helldivers would manage to hold their position with a comfortable ease. However, things would soon turn south when the Illuminate started a second, much larger offensive on the Southern Galactic Rim, requiring all Helldivers to divert back towards the endangered planets and allowing the Terminids an opening, ultimately allowing them to overrun the planetary defenses. However, with the capture of Gar Haren, the Terminids appear to have reached a dead end, as enemy resistance was pretty much null."}
{"id": "5595", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5595", "title": "Gatria", "text": " is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Jin Xi-Falstaff Lockdown.\nGatria was, up until June 2184, a peaceful planet colony in the Jin Xi Sector, its colonists thriving amongst the crimson grasslands, herding Terminids and producing E-710 without much trouble. However, all it takes is one small spark of tyranny for a haystack of freedom to be lost to the flames of fascism.\nDue to unknown reasons, a spontaneous Terminid outbreak would immediately overrun Gatria amidst a lockdown of the Jin Xi and Falstaff sectors, ordered by the Super Earth High Command shortly after victory at &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; during Operation Enduring Peace. The savage insectoids could not have chosen any worse time to pounce onto innocent Gatria with such viciousness.\nStarting on June 30th, shortly after the fall of Crimsica, the Helldivers would begin to send small combat groups towards Gatria in order to begin culling the numbers of the Terminids while the operation was ongoing. Then, once the lockdown was lifted after the successful capture of &lt;a href=\"Erson%20Sands\"&gt;Erson Sands&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers would divert towards Gatria in greater numbers, but still facing heavy resistance, with victory only coming by July 11th after heavy casualties.\nOperation Overrun.\nGatria, given its distance from frontline planets like &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;, would remain peaceful following its liberation, its colonists beginning resettlement and repairs in an attempt to return to normal. However, the Terminids, genetically envious of peace and prosperity, would force Gatria back into the war from a side they would not expect.\nThe nearby Sten Sector had been lost during the initial Terminid outbreak in February 2184. By September 1st, 2184, Gatria hadn't been connected to the Sten Sector for months. However, its colonists would finish their lunch and find a horrid surprise. The Terminids nestled in Trandor had suddenly made planetfall on Gatria and were now invading the planet. Super Earth High Command would issue a Major Order for the defense of Gatria, Phact Bay and recently reconnected Gar Haren.\nHelldivers immediately began deploying to the scarlet world, defending colonists of all citizenship ratings from the fascist menace. The defense was swift, and by the evening of September 2nd, clean up operations would already begin in earnest. But this was just the beginning, as around 06:00 SEST of September 3rd, a massive cloud of spores reached Gatria system from Trandor, heralding another defense campaign. Scanners both orbital and on-the-ground confirmed the density of said cloud among the greatest recorded, only being second to the Terminid Superonslaught encountered in &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt; weeks prior by mere quirk of the numbers. \nThe colonists of Gatria would find themselves fighting shoulder to shoulder with the Colonial Defense Force and almost every Helldiver in the corps as they combined their forces to take on the enormous Terminid onslaught that pounced upon their sufficiently sized homes, for they had already suffered too much just for a pack of alien insects to snatch their hard work off their hands without consequence. \nGatria would successfully repell the second Terminid Superonslaught without much incident, securing it firmly under the control of Freedom for the remainder of the operation. \nOperation Critical Mass.\nGatria would be attacked one more time during Operation Critical Mass. However, this poorly timed attack by the Terminids would only result in failure, as the Helldivers, having orders to cull the bulk of the Terminid forces such as Warriors and Bile Spewers, would deliver a great display of Super Earth's military might, repelling the invading bugs for a fourth time and in under 12 hours.\nOperation Liberty Tide.\nHowever, the Terminids in Trandor seemed to be incapable of surrendering to Managed Democracy, as some 4 days later, they would launch yet another attack onto Gatria. This time, the result would be no different, with the Helldivers successfully repelling a fifth Terminid attack onto Gatria, a feat only achieved once before in &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt; during Operation Enduring Bulwark.\nShortly after, the Helldivers would liberate Trandor, allowing the colonists at Gatria to finally breathe a sigh of relief as justice had finally been delivered upon those that had once brought them terror.\nOperation Ring of Freedom.\nGatria would remain loyal and free ever since its courageous defense during Operation Liberty Tide. However, the colonists of Gatria were not going to be able to fully live in peace as the Terminids soon recaptured Phact Bay and, later, recaptured Trandor. Then, some days later, the bugs captured Gar Haren, leaving Gatria besieged on all of its FTL Supply Lines. Yet, Gatria's colonists stood strong, digging trenchlines along the hillside and building lines of bunkers into the cliffs overlooking its seas. Then, on October 15th, the Terminids launched an assault of Gatria, once more from Trandor.\nAnd as with any lesson that hasn't quite yet been thoroughly taught, the Helldivers would turn up en masse to Gatria's defense as, once again, the attack on Gatria happened mere hours after &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; had been liberated and the 35,000 Helldivers there were now left free to take on any secondary objectives now that the target planets of the Major Order had been secured.\nIn just a little over 12 hours, Gatria had once more been defended against Terminid incursions, marking the 6th consecutive defensive victory on the planet as a whole, earning Gatria and its colonists a reputation of being among the most capable defenders that the Federation has to offer.\nInterim (October 22nd-October 28th).\nGatria would have rebuked the Terminids once more. Yet, despite their victory, the colonists of Gatria were still under siege from all available directions, as neither Gar Haren, Trandor nor Phact Bay had been liberated. As such, they hunkered down in their fortifications, awaiting an eventual attack. This attack would come just 7 days after the previous attacks, timed almost perfectly with an Automaton attack at &lt;a href=\"Zefia\"&gt;Zefia&lt;/a&gt;. However, this attack also happened pretty much an hour before Estanu had been fully liberated once more, which would reflect shortly after the initial defensive operations concluded.\nAs Estanu's last Terminid hives were appropriately cleansed, many Super Destroyers turned up to Gatria's aid en masse, as not only did many Helldivers take a liking for the crimson planet, but Gatria also stood at an important crossroads in the Eastern galactic fringe, in addition to its admirable resistance in the face of Terminid expansion serving as an inspiration for some Helldivers among the corps.\nAfter some 17 hours of fighting, Gatria had once more been defended, though at the cost of losing Zefia to the robotic tide. Nevertheless, once more had the Gatrians defied all odds and defended their home planet from invasion despite being completely surrounded, making an enviable display of their fighting spirit and commitment to the cause of liberty.\nHowever, the Gatrians wouldn't get to spend much time in peace. After some quick reparations, the Gatrians would spend their time restablishing their settlements and, given how their siege still hadn't been relieved, digging more trenches and laying down miles of barbed wire in preparation for a future invasion. On Liberty Day, they would gather together to salute Super Earth and have what little cake and brewed freedom they had in stock, the candles being the only light in the shadow of their defensive bunkers as they celebrated another year of Managed Democracy.\nHowever, this solace would be as fragile as the peace that accompanied it and, on October 27th, the Terminids at Trandor would once more strike at Gatria, the bugs proving to be as relentless as they were foolish, as they had once more picked the wrong time to attack Gatria. Not only had the Helldivers been given a \"license to kill\" during Liberty Day, as no major orders would be issued, but both Gacrux and &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; had been lost a couple days prior, leaving Gatria as the only remaining foothold in the sector. \nAs such, the Helldivers were focused mostly on the liberation of Phact Bay. However, when the defense alerts came from both Gatria and &lt;a href=\"Yed%20Prior\"&gt;Yed Prior&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers opted to defend Gatria, as its loss would signify the complete loss of Jin Xi Sector.\nIn detriment of Yed Prior's defense against the Automatons, the main fleet of the Helldivers Corps turned up on Gatria to aid its defense one more time. By the early hours of October 28th, the Gatrians had defended their home once more against the fascist menace, marking yet another victory for the crimson planet against the Terminid scourge that besieged them on all sides.\nOperation Bughammer.\nGatria would remain unbothered by its neighbors ever since its final defense in October. Once the Helldivers turned the situation around and liberated Phact Bay a day later and then, on November 20th, liberated Gar Haren, Gatria would remain pretty much unbothered, its horrid siege finally being relieved and its citizens able to be resupplied at long last, after 2 long months of constant defiance against the fascist tide. However, true respite was still out of the Gatrians' reach, as Trandor still remained under the control of the Terminids.\nOn December 11th, nearby &lt;a href=\"Achernar%20Secundus\"&gt;Achernar Secundus&lt;/a&gt; had been chosen to become the new site of a multi-complex factory hub for AM Defense, the new defense contractor for Super Earth. In response, the Terminids would launch an offensive in the Jin Xi and Sten Sectors in an attempt to capture Achernar, meaning that planets like Gatria, Phact Bay and Darius-II would become targets of interest for the bugs.\nOn December 12th, mere hours after the Helldivers successfully repelled a Terminid assault at Phact Bay, the Terminids attacked Gatria from Trandor, in a move that the Gatrians had already seen 6 consecutive times by this point. With the help of the Helldiver fleet, the Terminids were expected to be repelled well before the first day of the invasion even passed.\nBut then, the impossible occurred.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nOut of nowhere, all SEAF forces, both active and in reserve duty, got ordered into LIBCON 1. Immediately, every single Helldiver in the galaxy would begin to deploy onto &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; in response to an emergency distress beacon that cited things that would have previously been thought unreal: The were attacking the planet.\nOn the face of such an ancient and dangerous foe, virtually all SEAF forces would mobilize towards Calypso, leaving essentially all other planets completely devoid of any Super Earth military presence. It would be this redeployment what would seemingly doom the defense of Gatria. Yet, the Gatrians were not going to give up their homes, which by now they had given many thousands of lives to defend.\nEven as most other frontline planets were essentially abandoned, a small garrison of Helldivers decided to stick by the side of the Gatrians, determined to at least evacuate as many of them as possible, in order to alleviate the loss of the planet so that it could later be recovered with more ease.\nGatria would fall on December 14th, 2184, after a long battle that, while a defeat for the Gatrians, it didn't mean devastation. Gatria had fallen, but its colonists stood firm and determined to one day reclaim their homes from the horrid hordes that had now pounced onto them.\nGatria fell before its wardens did."}
