{"id": "6452", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6452", "title": "General Brasch", "text": "General Brasch is, according to his own words, \u201cSuper Earth\u2019s oldest and most grizzled war hero\u201d -- being a veteran of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; and the oldest &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver&lt;/a&gt; currently in service. He serves as the instructor for the Helldiver Training program on &lt;a href=\"Mars\"&gt;Mars&lt;/a&gt;, the \u201ctoughest test in the galaxy\u201d where he guides new recruits -- in voice if not in person -- through the test that certifies them as ready for service as Helldivers. The Helldiver Training entails a rudimentary obstacle course, a live-fire crawling exercise, use of first-aid, a practice range with live &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;, Stratagem deployment, terminal usage, and most importantly, flag saluting. Each and every newly-minted Helldiver is (indirectly) presented with their first cape by the general.\nThe Super Ten-Star General is also the voice behind Brasch Tactics, a series of shorts created to encourage all Helldivers to think tactically while slaughtering the enemies of Managed Democracy. Additionally following an error in Super Earth's logistics chain, Helldivers were accidentally granted the SH-32 Shield Generator Packs from General Brasch\u00b4s personal stash. These are reserved for 10-star generals only. The workers at the distribution center have since been sent to re-education camps and regular shields will resume distribution."}
{"id": "5951", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5951", "title": "Genesis Prime", "text": " is one of the seven planets in the &lt;a href=\"Rictus%20Sector\"&gt;Rictus Sector&lt;/a&gt;. On December 16th, it became the second planet to be attacked by the in the Second Galactic War, not even a day after the first battle against the Illuminate at &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Veld\"&gt;Veld&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Merak\"&gt;Merak&lt;/a&gt;, an Ionic Jungle world covered in dense jungle shadowed in a perpetual twilight and troubled by frequent ion storms in the upper atmosphere. However unlike it's contemporaries, Genesis Prime is also highly populated, with urban sprawl similar to that seen on neighboring &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;, meaning that no matter where you go on this world, one can expect fighting to be an up close and personal matter.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nGenesis Prime was an inconspicuous colony in the Southern Galactic Rim. Having been colonized at some point after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, Genesis Prime's history hadn't been very noteworthy. It can be assumed that this colony found enough economic success that it eventually could allow its colonists to build urbanized settlements, complete with water, waste management, electricity and, most importantly, well kept green grass lawns, the pinnacle of any Super Citizen's home.\nHowever, the decadent , rife with xenophobic envy of the human race's achievements, could not tolerate such success. Mere hours after being righteously defeated at &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;, the Squids would make a second attempt at an offensive, attacking the underdefended Genesis with hopes of collapsing its defenses within 12 hours. However, they did not count with the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; and their righteous might who, having rebuked the Illuminate once, were already planning to repeat their feat a second time.\nHowever, the Illuminate would then send a second attack force towards nearby &lt;a href=\"Mog\"&gt;Mog&lt;/a&gt;, another valuable colony full of urban settlements. This development would force the Helldivers to divert towards its aid, as High Command updated orders and now demanded not just for Genesis Prime to be held, but for an additional 7 planets to be defended against the Squ'ith invaders.\nDespite the Helldiver's valuant efforts, they wouldn't be able to stop the Illuminate's sacking of Genesis Prime. Although they did manage to force the Illuminate to retreat, Genesis Prime was left in ruins, its urban colonies turned to smoldering rubble. But as with many things, in due time it shall all be rebuilt."}
