{"id": "6007", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6007", "title": "Hadar", "text": "Hadar is one of the four planets in the &lt;a href=\"Ferris%20Sector\"&gt;Ferris Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Mog\"&gt;Mog&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"New%20Stockholm\"&gt;New Stockholm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vog-Sojoth\"&gt;Vog-Sojoth&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nHadar was just an average planet colony of Super Earth like many others, located far in the Southern Galactic Rim. Having been colonized at some point after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, Hadar's history wasm't very noteworthy in any way, with its colonization most likely occurring due to its more than adequate location in the Galactic Map as part of a line of planets that could be used for the formation of a planetary barrier.\nHowever, the odious , rife with pagan zealotry for their space deities, were unable to bear the sight of Super Earth's citizens being safe from their nefarious appendages. On December 18th, hours after the Helldivers' victory at &lt;a href=\"Andar\"&gt;Andar&lt;/a&gt;, the Illuminate would strike at Hadar, hoping that a coincidentially subsequent attack on &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt; would pull enough numbers away for them to successfully raid this planet like they had done before at &lt;a href=\"Acubens%20Prime\"&gt;Acubens Prime&lt;/a&gt;\nHowever, the Helldivers would see through their devious scheming and would all deploy en masse to Hadar, hoping to dissuade the Squ'ith from ever plundering the fruits of Super Earth's hard labour."}
