{"id": "6009", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6009", "title": "Haldus", "text": " is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Ferris%20Sector\"&gt;Ferris Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;first galactic war&lt;/a&gt;, was a desert moon large enough to be considered it's own planet, the terrain consisting of a dry variation of cliffs and ravines, the temperature ranging from hot to near boiling point. Despite this, the Cyborgs had many habitation modules on the planet and a major military presence, although like other Cyborg strongholds it was eventually overcome by the might of the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, thanks in no small part to the valiance of the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever after the war it was discovered that Haldus was rapidly cooling down, something eventually linked to the core which was rapidly cooling, shutting down the dynamo that sustained its magnetic field which left the world vulnerable to the solar wind, clawed away the atmosphere and leaving it a barren moon for the better part of a century.\nOne hundred years later however, the planet's core was restarted thanks to a team of terraforming drilling to the center of the world and setting off a series of nuclear explosions in order to restart the rotation of the core. After this, a massive terraforming project funded by the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Expansion\"&gt;Ministry of Expansion&lt;/a&gt; transformed the moon of Haldus into a lush, if somewhat humid and morassic, forest world. Life returns to Haldus as sunlight filters past dangling vines hanging from gnarled trees, filtering down to the saturated undergrowth below, much like the prosperity of &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;super earth&lt;/a&gt; itself!"}
