{"id": "6013", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6013", "title": "Heze Bay", "text": "Heze Bay is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Hanzo%20Sector\"&gt;Hanzo Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Zagon%20Prime\"&gt;Zagon Prime&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Durgen\"&gt;Durgen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Phact%20Bay\"&gt;Phact Bay&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mastia\"&gt;Mastia&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nHeze Bay was, much like all of its neighbors, a peaceful colony of Super Earth that had been settled after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. Like many others in the Southern Galactic Rim, Heze Bay's history was relatively uneventful, with its economy being robust enough to allow for the construction of urbanized settlements in order to house the growing populace. However, a resurgent foe was staring in envy, waiting for the moment to strike.\nOn December 25th, 2184, the would send a raid onto Heze Bay. Since the Helldivers had been given complete operational freedom for the Festival of Reckoning, they would immediately dispatch a fleet towards the planet in hopes of repelling the raid and mitigating the damage."}
{"id": "3875", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3875", "title": "Hive Guard", "text": "The Hive Guard is a medium-size &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; sporting medium armor on the front of its body that appears on &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Easy difficulty&lt;/a&gt; and higher. It is a somewhat larger variant of the &lt;a href=\"Warrior\"&gt;Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, with some believed to an in-between development state before it either metamorphosed into a &lt;a href=\"Brood%20Commander\"&gt;Brood Commander&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Charger\"&gt;Charger&lt;/a&gt;. They are often seen defending bug hole entrances, but can also lead patrols on the map depending on operations difficulties.\nA Hive Guard may hunker down when shot at, putting the black armor on the front of its body to use in protection against all light penetration weaponry. This also allows them to function as a shield for smaller Terminids behind them.\nLike Warriors, Hive Guards will attack nearby Helldivers with their claws. Unlike the Warrior, though, Hive Guards will not outlive the loss of their head, though certain medium-armor penetrating weapons will not \"instantly\" kill them with a headshot, instead causing them to bleed out over the course of about a second.\nAnatomy.\nHive Guards have a yellow body with a dark brown armored head. They use the armor to protect bug nests, and when on patrol, they use it to protect &lt;a href=\"Brood%20Commander\"&gt;Brood Commanders&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Charger\"&gt;Charger&lt;/a&gt;s. They have claws on their front legs to cut through enemies and small rocks."}
