{"id": "3451", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3451", "title": "Ingmar", "text": "Ingmar is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nIngmar is a planet that is mostly barren, with little on its surface beyond the occasional ridges and rocks, scattered amongst the sea of the crimson algae that shrouds its hills and valleys. The simplicity of its terrain is both an advantage and a disadvantage, as it leaves little obstacles for any Eagle Airstrikes or Orbital bombardments. However, little obstacles in the environment also translates little cover against the enemies of Super Earth that may reside on this planet.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Expeditions.\nIngmar was one of the first unlucky few to face the horrors brought upon by Super Earth's new but familiar foe. As the Automatons invaded the Western Galactic Rim and occupied the Xzar and Severin Sectors, Ingmar would find its defenses insufficient against the tide of mechanized socialists. Like most of the Xzar Sector, Ingmar eventually fell to one of many unattended Automaton assaults, as the Helldivers were occupied with bigger priority tasks, such as the siege of &lt;a href=\"Tien%20Kwan\"&gt;Tien Kwan&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt would be inevitably lost around the beginning of March 2184, as its supply lines were cut off after the capture of Mort. It would remain under occupation for a number of weeks, as the Helldivers would be required to prioritize the installation of the Terminid Control System in the Eastern Galactic Rim in order to contain the fascist bugs.\nOperation Swift Disassembly.\nOnce the TCS was operational, the tides began to turn against the Automatons. Throughout the month of March and into the first week of April, The Helldivers relentlessly set out on a massive effort to liberate the Xzar and Severin Sectors from the metallic grip of the Automatons' iron fist. Shortly after the victory at Malevelon Creek, the Automaton forces would disintegrate after their main fighting force was split in half. The Automaton holdout in Ingmar would be eradicated before the first week of April 2184 had concluded and Ingmar would once again be a free planet.\nAutomaton Reclamation of Cyberstan.\nIngmar would enjoy its freedom in peace for a grand total of 48 hours, since the Automatons, now with a force 10 times larger, was now attacking the Federation once again. They quickly conquered &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Then, one by one, began to take over the planets that were in the direction of Malevelon Creek. Mort would see one small assault during this time, but this would be the only time before the declaration of the war that Ingmar would see its safety threatened\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Xzar Lockdown.\nIngmar watched in terror as the Automaton forces concentrated in &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charball-VII&lt;/a&gt;, as they prepared for a new offensive out of what the Helldivers had managed to turn around into their entrapment into the Valdis Sector. After a whole 2 months of peace after its occupation, the Automatons launched their offensive into the Xzar Sector once more. After quickly taking over Mort on June 19th, they immediately launched an assault on Ingmar on June 20th.\nHowever, the Helldivers would display quick adaptability, as they managed to repeal the offensive on Ingmar and then liberate Mort once again, which would also cripple an ongoing assault on P\u00f6pli IX. However, this was not to be the end of it all as, on June 23rd, the Automatons opened a new FTL Line from &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt; into Mantes. After their surprise attack on Mantes was successfully repealed by the Helldivers, they immediately launched a second attack on Ingmar. This second attack would then be repealed in the morning of June 24th.\nAs of the time of writing, Ingmar remains under the righteous mantle of Managed Democracy. But with the looming threat posed by the Automatons' position on Vandalon IV and their new capability of creating new FTL lines, it remains in an ever-endangered position."}
