{"id": "5947", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5947", "title": "Iro", "text": " is one of the seven planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Rictus%20Sector\"&gt;Rictus Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Bashyr\"&gt;Bashyr&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nIro had been, for most of its recorded history, a peaceful planet colony of Super Earth. Having been settled after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, Iro was a planet that was notoriously difficult to inhabit due to the vast expanses of unstable mud and the noticeable lack of stable, fertile soil. Yet despite all of the difficulties, the colonists of Iro would manage to succeed, eventually acquiring enough wealth to build urbanized colonies. However, an old enemy stared from within the depths of space.\nThe , a race of aliens that had once tried and failed to defy humanity, had returned from their exile and was now waging war against Managed Democracy once more. On December 28th, Iro would fall prey to an Illuminate raid, following a string of Illuminate raids in the Rictus Sector and other colonies in the Southern Galactic Rim.\nThe Helldivers, having orders to repel all Illuminate raids while killing as many Voteless and Illuminate &lt;a href=\"Harvester\"&gt;Harvesters&lt;/a&gt; as they could, would immediately deploy onto Iro. Decided to avenge the recent raid at &lt;a href=\"Julheim\"&gt;Julheim&lt;/a&gt; and bolstered by their previous victory at &lt;a href=\"Volterra\"&gt;Volterra&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers deployed en masse onto the planet."}
