{"id": "6017", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6017", "title": "Keid", "text": "Keid is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Akira%20Sector\"&gt;Akira Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Heze%20Bay\"&gt;Heze Bay&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nKeid was, much like all of its neighbors, a peaceful colony of Super Earth that had been settled after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. Like many others in the Southern Galactic Rim, Keid's history was relatively uneventful, with its economy being robust enough to allow for the construction of urbanized settlements in order to house the growing populace. However, a resurgent foe was staring in envy, waiting for the moment to strike.\nOn December 26th, 2184, the would send a raid onto Keid. Since the Helldivers had been given complete operational freedom for the Festival of Reckoning, they would immediately dispatch a fleet towards the planet in hopes of repelling the raid and mitigating the damage.\nDespite battling the invaders for 12 hours, the raid could not be repelled, leaving Keid in ruins, its resources plundered and hundreds of thousands of colonists missing.\nYet, the nefarious invaders weren't to even allow the innocent citizens of Keid even a moment of respite or redress as, 3 days later, they would return to Keid for a second time."}
