{"id": "5920", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5920", "title": "Kerth Secundus", "text": "Kerth Secundus is one of the seven planets in the &lt;a href=\"Rictus%20Sector\"&gt;Rictus Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shelt\"&gt;Shelt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Trandor\"&gt;Trandor&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nKerth Secundus was an average colony far off in the Southern Galactic Rim, having been settled at some point after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. It's colorful valleys and its perennial, coniferous trees, alongside is permanently chilly yet habitable climate and its benefitial location in the galactic map would essentially pave Kerth's way towards prosperity. \nKerth's colonists were able to rapidly accumulate wealth, and said wealth quickly manifested into urbanized settlements sprawling up all across the planet, as apartment blocs were built to house the ever growing worker population, while streets were paved, water pipes installed, power supplies connected, waste management handled and most important of all, green grass lawns mowed and well kept so that the Super Earth Flags and Helldiver memorials looked their best when pitched atop of them.\nKerth Secundus is a planet blessed by Liberty like very few others. However, an old foe from decades past stared from far within the abyssal depths of space. The , boiling in pagan anger and xenophobic envy of Super Earth's natural attraction of such fortunes, would lunge at Kerth Secundus decided to rip those blessings for themselves.\nOn December 17th, amidst a series of Illuminate raids across the southern sectors of the galaxy, Kerth Secundus would be suddenly and deliberately attacked by Illuminate invasion fleets. Having succeeded at &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bellatrix\"&gt;Bellatrix&lt;/a&gt; days prior, the Helldivers were decided to stop this odious harassment of their compatriots by the Squids, and as such, deployed en masse onto Kerth. However, they would be forced to split once more, as the Illuminate were also simultaneously invading &lt;a href=\"Valmox\"&gt;Valmox&lt;/a&gt; with the use of their nefarious teleportation technology. \nAfter 7 hours of fighting, the Helldivers were successful and repelled the Illuminate raid, preventing the further plundering of its resources and the further destruction of the products of its hard labor."}
{"id": "6018", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6018", "title": "Khandark", "text": "Khandark is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Guang%20Sector\"&gt;Guang Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science's&lt;/a&gt; galactic topography database previously listed Khandark as a snowball planet, caught in eternal winter. However this has recently been discovered to be a mischaracterization, with the planet in actuality being a \"Foggy Swamp\", that is similar to &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt;. This error has since been fixed.\nHistory.\nAs of the time of writing, Khandark enjoys a secure and democratic existence on galactic South-West of &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;."}
