{"id": "3291", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3291", "title": "L'estrade Sector", "text": "The L'estrade Sector is a sector found on the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;Eastern Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It consists of 7 planets. During August of 2184, the Sector was flooded with Terminid spores.\nTrivia.\nL'estrade is French for \"The Stage\""}
{"id": "5645", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5645", "title": "LAS-16 Sickle", "text": "The LAS-16 Sickle is a laser weapon in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;\", firing momentary beam pulses in rapid succession after a short charge-up period. Effectively a laser assault rifle, like all laser weapons the Sickle forgoes the need for ammunition in exchange for building up heat, which can be dissipated by simply letting off the trigger. If heat buildup exceeds a certain threshold, however, the weapon will eject its heat sink and the user will be required to load in another before the weapon can be fired again.\nThe Sickle can be unlocked from the first page of &lt;a href=\"Cutting%20Edge\"&gt;Premium Warbond: Cutting Edge&lt;/a&gt; for 20 &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Medals\"&gt;medals&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Sickle is an excellent all-purpose primary weapon, dealing respectable damage to lightly-armored targets while being accurate enough to effectively target weak points on tougher enemies like &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastator&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Brood%20Commander\"&gt;Brood Commanders&lt;/a&gt;. The weapon's main limitation is its need to vent heat, and learning to discern when to back off and allow the weapon to cool and when to expend a heat sink is critical to your success. Additionally, environmental factors may impact whether or not you may want to choose this weapon, as like all weapons with the \"Heat\" trait, the \"Intense Heat\" environmental condition will increase the rate at which the weapon heats, while \"Extreme Cold\" will decrease it. The intense heat decreases the time needed to overheat by .50 seconds while the extreme cold will increase the time by .50 seconds for a total of 6.50 and 7.50 seconds respectively."}
{"id": "5643", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5643", "title": "LAS-5 Scythe", "text": "The LAS-5 Scythe is an energy weapon in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%E2%80%8E%202\"&gt;Helldivers\u200e 2&lt;/a&gt;, firing a continuous, concentrated laser beam that deals damage over time. Like all laser weapons, the Scythe builds up heat rather than consuming ammunition, though maxing out the heat capacity will require the user to exchange the weapon's heat sink. It can be unlocked via page 5 of the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%20Mobilize\"&gt;Helldivers Mobilize&lt;/a&gt; Warbond.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Scythe is useful at dealing with light and medium-sized threats, like &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastator&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hunter\"&gt;Hunters&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Brood%20Commander\"&gt;Brood Commanders&lt;/a&gt;. It has practically no recoil and decent damage , making it easy to stay on target and deal damage to them consistently, along with having great sustain due to it being a beam weapon. It is particularly effective against Automaton &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastator&lt;/a&gt;s, as a concentrated beam to their heads will kill them in a few seconds, and it having maximum stability makes training the laser onto their heads an easy affair.\nIt is however, less effective on planets with Intense Heat traits, as this causes the weapon to build up heat much faster than usual."}
{"id": "4021", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4021", "title": "LAS-7 Dagger", "text": "The LAS-7 Dagger is a scaled down version of the &lt;a href=\"LAS-5%20Scythe\"&gt;LAS-5 Scythe&lt;/a&gt;. Like all laser weapons that fire a continuous beam, the Dagger builds up heat rather than consuming ammunition - though maxing out the heat capacity will require the user to exchange the weapon's heat sink."}
{"id": "5646", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5646", "title": "LAS-98 Laser Cannon", "text": "\"A laser weapon firing a continuous beam. Doesn't require ammunition, but will need heat sink replaced if it overheats.\"\nThe LAS-98 Laser Cannon is one of the &lt;a href=\"stratagems\"&gt;stratagems&lt;/a&gt; available to the player. It is a shoulder-fired beam cannon, firing a concentrated beam of white-hot energy, capable of melting through heavy armor.\nMuch like all beam-type weapons, the LAS-98 has near-infinite ammo. As long as it is allowed to cool off between engagements, the shooter can fire it indefinitely. If it is allowed to overheat however, the heat sink is destroyed and has to be replaced, which constitutes the weapon's \"ammunition\".\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this single-use &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:"}
{"id": "3865", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3865", "title": "LAS-99 Quasar Cannon", "text": "\"Charges to fire a powerful, explosive energy burst. Has a long cooldown period after firing.\"\nThe LAS-99 Quasar Cannon is one of the &lt;a href=\"stratagems\"&gt;stratagems&lt;/a&gt; available to the player. The weapon is similar to the LAS-98 Laser Cannon, but rather than firing a sustained beam, it charges up a single shot of explosive energy with the power of an &lt;a href=\"EAT-17%20Expendable%20Anti-Tank\"&gt;EAT-17 Expendable Anti-Tank&lt;/a&gt; round.\nThe Quasar Cannon has infinite ammo. It does not have any magazines, nor heat sinks that have to be replaced, and is capable of safely cooling itself with no threat of overheating. However, it has a particularly long cooldown period between shots, and it cannot be used while it is still venting heat.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this single-use &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:"}
{"id": "3323", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3323", "title": "Lacaille Sector", "text": "The Lacaille Sector is an inhabited area of galaxy found on the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Front\"&gt;Western Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. Localized on galactic North-West from &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; , it \nconsists of 4 colonized systems. The sector is likely named after the ancient French astronomer and geodesist, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicolas-Louis_de_Lacaille\"&gt;Nicolas-Louis de Lacaille&lt;/a&gt;, who named 14 out of the 88 constellations. From 1750 to 1754, he studied the sky at the Cape of Good Hope in South Africa (present-day southern Sector 5). Lacaille observed over 10,000 stars using a refracting telescope."}
