{"id": "3827", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3827", "title": "Launch ICBM", "text": "Launch ICBM is a Terminid and Automaton mission in Helldivers 2. The mission involves re-activating a dormant Intercontinental Ballistic Missile Silo, and launching it's nuclear payload against an enemy target of interest.\nObjectives.\nTo prep the missile for launch, one or all the following (Depending on the difficulty) must be done before the missile can be launched: \nNote that on lower difficulties, one or two missions will not be required anymore.\nLaunching the missile.\nOnce all prerequisite objectives are completed, the ICBM is ready for launch and just has to be primed and activated.\nFirst, operate the terminal to initiate the launch sequence, enter a directional code to access the terminal, then input the 5-digit launch code provided on the objectives screen. The 4 locks on the silo doors must then be manually disengaged. From there, the target coordinates must be entered, finishing the first phase of the launch.\nFrom there, Helldivers must wait for the missile to be raised out of the silo and fueled. It takes around 30 seconds for the missile to be primed for launch (Raising and fueling).\nFinally, the missile launch must be authorized on the terminal. From there, the missile will launch in 5 seconds. It is advised Helldivers should stay clear of the silo, as the missile's rocket boosters will violently injure anyone nearby as it launches. Additionally, Helldivers should not stay near the silo afterwards, as there is now a gaping hole where the missile used to be and falling into it will kill them and lose anything they're carrying to the void.\nAfterwards, the mission is completed, and the team is treated to a brief nuclear-fueled fanfare, accompanied by a massive nuclear explosion in the distance."}
