{"id": "3871", "revid": "26489601", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3871", "title": "MG-206 Heavy Machine Gun", "text": "\"A very powerful but difficult-to-wield machine gun with intense recoil.\"\nThe MG-206 Heavy Machine Gun is a &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;support weapon&lt;/a&gt; available to the player.\nRole.\nFunctioning as man-portable heavy machine gun, a weapon typically seen mounted on gun platforms rather than carried by soldiers, the MG-206 is essentially a modular version of the &lt;a href=\"E/MG-101%20HMG%20Emplacement\"&gt;MG-101&lt;/a&gt;. The weapon has the same damage characteristics as the &lt;a href=\"APW-1%20Anti-Materiel%20Rifle\"&gt;Anti-Materiel Rifle&lt;/a&gt;, penetrating heavy armor and also the weak points of vehicles, such as the visor of Automaton &lt;a href=\"Hulk\"&gt;Hulks&lt;/a&gt; and radiators of most of their vehicles. The handling however, leaves a lot to be desired, and the gun is best fired prone and in bursts due to its recoil and small 75-round magazine.\nUnlike the MG-43 and Stalwart, the HMG is best ran as a true support weapon, instead of a primary. Only being brought out to take out high-priority targets. Due to its power and limited ammo capacity, it excels the most against Automatons, where its anti-armor capabilities are best exploited. It is less suited against Terminids, as the small magazine does not lend itself well against the sheer number of light-armored bodies they bring onto the field.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this single-use &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:"}
{"id": "3406", "revid": "53450", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3406", "title": "MG-43 Machine Gun", "text": "\"A machine gun designed for stationary use. Trades higher power for increased recoil and reduced accuracy.\"\nThe MG-43 Machine Gun is an air-cooled, belt-fed general-purpose machine gun in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;\", and the first &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;stratagem&lt;/a&gt; available to the player. It is automatically unlocked after the tutorial mission.\nRole.\nActing as the General-Purpose Machine gun, the MG-43 is an all-rounder. Its decent damage, armor penetration, and rate of fire, allows it to function well against both factions as an automatic support weapon, mowing down hordes of anything short of heavy-armored units.\nWhile perfectly suited towards both Terminids and Automatons, it shines most against Automatons as an anti-&lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastator&lt;/a&gt; weapon, which they field in vast amounts at higher difficulties. The MG43's bullets can penetrate their chest armor, reducing the need for accurate headshots in tense situations.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:\nTrivia.\nThis gun appears to be similar in appearance to two real-world, usually crew-served machine guns: The MG-42 of Nazi Germany, colloquially known as \"Hitler's Buzzsaw\" due to the sound it made while firing, and the US-made M-60, nicknamed \"The Pig\" due to its \"voracious appetite\" for ammunition and the weapon's overall bulk."}
