{"id": "6072", "revid": "58143", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6072", "title": "Major Orders", "text": "Major Orders serve as the main objectives in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. Players have to complete time-limited community goals in order to make progress in the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. The course of the war is not scripted as outcomes of battles depend entirely on player actions. Due to this dynamic nature of the game, major orders can have various consequences for the Galactic War depending on whether players succeed or fail to complete them. For example, planets can be liberated from or lost to &lt;a href=\"Factions\"&gt;enemy factions&lt;/a&gt;, preventing them from or allowing them to push into further sectors of the galaxy.\n\"Note: Helldivers need to have participated in combat on the planets involved in the order to receive the associated rewards, although many have received rewards despite not having participated due to inactivity or other reasons.\"\n= Major Orders Timeline =\n &lt;ul class=\"monthList\" style=\"margin:0; display: flex; flex-direction: column-reverse\"&gt;\n "}
{"id": "3274", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3274", "title": "Malevelon Creek", "text": " \nMalevelon Creek is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Its landscape generally consists of lush jungles and wide ponds.\nDuring the Automaton Expedition, it became the single most infamous planet on the entire Automaton front, due to the extremely intense and difficult fighting that took place on it and the shock it left on the newly trained Helldivers that deployed in it. \nConstant battles against socialist &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; invaders exacted an enormous human cost.\nAfter its liberation from the Automatons on April 3rd 2184, Malevelon Creek Memorial Day was officially established as an annual event celebrating the establishment of peace on the devastated world.\nTopography.\nMalevelon Creek is largely covered in flora, including thick brush and dense, dark forests. It is covered in persistent fog and heavy clouds, giving the surface an appearance of eternal night. This unique terrain proved very challenging for the Helldivers to maneuver through. Its lush jungles slowed down movement, its dense canopy could block line-of-sight, and its foggy atmosphere and dark shadows obscured vision on the ground. To make matters worse, ion storms are common in the planet's atmosphere, scrambling communications with orbiting Super Destroyers and preventing stratagem deployment.\nHistory.\nThere are countless hells in this galaxy. There is only one Malevelon Creek.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nThe First Battle of Malevelon Creek (Feb. 8th - 28th 2184).\nFighting on Malevelon Creek broke out in February 8th 2184, with small-scale conflict between SEAF forces and the Automatons. \nMalevelon Creek proved uniquely difficult for the SEAF to liberate, despite seeing similar troop deployments to other nearby planets. The Automatons' socialist programming made it easier for them to navigate the dense jungle, and millions of the robots illegally fortified the planet using exceptionally brutal methods. Resourceful Helldivers began to conduct large-scale deployments of napalm on the thick jungles, depriving many cowardly Automatons of cover. \nSlowly but surely, it became clear that more reinforcements were needed. This resulted in the \"Fight for the Creek\" recruitment drive, calling for citizens to enlist and assist their brothers and sisters in bringing Democracy to the jungle. The &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Ministry of Truth&lt;/a&gt; reports that these campaigns were responsible for a 12% increase in enlistments to the Automaton Front.\nAs fighting ensued, the Automatons conducted a savage counter-offensive. On February 28th 2184, Malevelon Creek fell to the socialists along with the entire &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draupnir\"&gt;Draupnir&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Mantes\"&gt;Mantes&lt;/a&gt;. The fall of the Creek was seen as a tragic moment for the war effort, though the Helldivers managed to salvage the situation through the liberation of nearby &lt;a href=\"Mort\"&gt;Mort&lt;/a&gt;.\nSecond Battle of Malevelon Creek (Feb. 28th - Apr. 1st 2184).\nSuper Earth temporarily lost access to Malevelon Creek due to the fall of two connecting planets, Draupnir and Mantes. However, pockets of valiant Helldivers known as \"Creekers\" remained on the planet, slaying legions of robots in a ferocious series of sieges. Thousands fell before the brutal blades of the Automatons, prompting many to rush to support them. \nInitial engagements proved fruitful, as the Helldivers were able to massively damage Automaton positions. However, their advance could not be sustained, as the Automatons quickly regrouped and counter-attacked. Countless heroes of Super Earth were slaughtered in valiant last stands. Where once the Helldivers traded Automaton wrecks for miles, they now traded rivers of patriotic blood for mere inches. Yet still, the Helldivers fought on. The light of Liberty never left them, even as their lives were traded for Freedom. \nOver the course of the battle, Helldivers began to report to High Command that the severed heads and mutilated bodies of their fallen comrades had been positioned in front of Automaton bases as war trophies. Also reported were a higher concentration of \"death camps\" where SEAF personnel had been tortured, killed, mutilated, and/or dismembered. \nThe Ministry of Truth hereby reminds all citizens that Automatons are monsters incapable of morality or empathy, and that they should never be shown mercy.\nOn March 4th 2184, the Helldivers liberated Mantes, allowing reinforcements to more safely enter the Creek. However, the extreme losses taken slowed liberation progress, and many SEAF personnel were reassigned to help liberate neighboring Draupnir. \nFinally, with both Mantes and Draupnir having been liberated, Super Earth High Command issued a &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders\"&gt;Major Order&lt;/a&gt; to free Malevelon Creek from the robots' mechanical clutches. After an all-out push from new recruits and experienced Creekers alike, the planet was heroically liberated on April 1st 2184.\nThis engagement is widely regarded to be the deadliest battle of the three. High Command reports that losses sustained were double that of the first and third battles combined.\nThird Battle of Malevelon Creek (Apr. 2nd 2184).\nThe peace on Malevelon Creek unfortunately lasted only few hours: on April 2nd, the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; launched a dastardly attack in an attempt to reconquer this world. Their offensive was supported by two new foes: flying &lt;a href=\"Gunship%20Facility\"&gt;Aerial Gunships&lt;/a&gt;, and massive walking mechs known as &lt;a href=\"Factory%20Strider\"&gt;Factory Striders&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce again, the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; were called in to rescue civilians and wipe out the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;. In the largest deployment to date, up to 230,000 Super Destroyers heeded the call for freedom, determined to dislodge the socialist scourge off the Creek once and for all. \nJust nine hours into the battle, the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Forces of Mankind&lt;/a&gt; had completely overwhelmed their enemies: the planet's surface had been completely cleared of the murderous machines. The cold, oppressive wreckage surrounding the planet was all that remained of the Automatons, a last grim reminder of what happens to enemies of Democracy.\nOutcome of the Battle.\nApril 3rd 2184, was the first full day of peace on Malevelon Creek since the beginning of the war. The President of Super Earth issued a decree which recognizes this date as Malevelon Creek Memorial Day. All active Helldivers were issued a commemorative cape to honor their fallen companions.\nFrom that day forward, Malevelon Creek has remained quiet and peaceful, the Automaton threat now only a memory for the Super Earth Colonizers who survived it to remember. Despite the flames of war on the planet being long gone, the Creek still serves a purpose: to remind to the Helldivers that even in Super Earth's darkest hour, their might and determination can light up the horizon with the flames of Managed Democracy. \nAs of December 15th, 2184, there are only 10 Super Destroyers in orbit, each carrying a guard of honor at the Helldivers memorial."}
{"id": "3270", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3270", "title": "Mantes", "text": "Mantes is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It compares quite similarly to how &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; used to look like, a former planet on the complete opposite side of the galaxy in the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopology.\nMantes is a tropical jungle planet, populated with lush vegetation and trees and tall grass with the occasional clearing in between. Among the trees, volcanoes may be found on certain occasions which, if they happen to start erupting during an operation, can prove dangerous if not fatal, as the rocks spurted out of them can very well kill anything they catch off-guard, from meager, unfeeling robots to any righteous Helldiver who might just be getting their designated 2.3 seconds per mission to enjoy the scenery.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Expeditions.\nMantes, alongside with Draupnir, would be the first world to suffer the toil of the Automatons. In February 2184, the Automatons launched a surprise attack on the Xzar and Severin Sectors, overwhelming the defenses and taking over multiple planets upon which they would released their mechanized cruelty.\nThe defenses would be fierce and the Helldivers, as usual loyal. They would fight for 3 days to hold the line on Mantes and Draupnir, but to no avail, as the Automatons' trickery once again allowed them to take over the planets and continue their spread of socialism to continue unfettered, as Mantes, and most of the Xzar, Severin and, by that point, Trigon Sectors had become locked in a bloody deadlock, as Helldivers diverted attention away to the East in order to install the Terminid Control System.\nOperation Swift Disassembly.\nWith the Terminid Control System being successfully installed and operational by the end of February, Super Earth High Command decided to refocus back on the Automaton threat that loomed in the West. With strong determination, Operation Swift Disassembly was authorized. Through the entire month of March and into the month of April 2184, the Helldivers relentlessly pushed against the Automaton threat, capturing planet after planet. While Mantes was not part of any of the operation's objective, it would be liberated roughly around the same time as nearby Draupnir and Ubanea.\nWhen the last Automaton forces at &lt;a href=\"Durgen\"&gt;Durgen&lt;/a&gt; were destroyed and the dust had settled, Super Earth rejoiced in celebration. Mantes, and the rest of the Western Galactic Rim, were free at last from the cruelty of the Automatons.\nAutomaton Reclamation of Cyberstan.\nHowever. The Automatons were not going to just embrace Managed Democracy out of the goodness of their motherboards, for there was no such thing in them besides innate evil and hatred for freedom. A mere 3 days after their righteous obliteration, they returned. A massive Automaton fleet, 10 times larger than the one encountered before, was now invading the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;, taking over &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and slowly encroaching onto the neighboring systems.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Xzar Lockdown.\nFrom April to June, the colonists in Mantes watched in fear as, one by one, the Automatons took over the planets in neighboring systems. Then, after they broke the deadlock in &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt;, they launched a third assault onto nearby &lt;a href=\"Mort\"&gt;Mort&lt;/a&gt;. Super Earth could not bear the prospect of the Automatons regaining their old position and, fearing for the safety of its citizens, authorized a major order with one primordial goal: Keep the Automatons out of the Xzar Sector by all means necessary.\nOn June 21st, the Automatons captured &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt;, just as the defense at Ingmar was ongoing. Then, 2 days later, as their offensive on Mort collapsed and took their offensive at P\u00f6pli IX down with it, they revealed their nefarious ace under their robotic sleeve: The Automatons would create a new FTL Line from Vandalon IV into Mantes and began an attack on it on June 23rd.\nWhile Mantes' defense would be successful, with the Automaton advance being halted on June 24th, it has left a new concern burned into the minds of Super Earth Strategic Command.\nIt had to now account for the possibility of both of its enemies now being capable of creating new supply lines to outmanoeuvre them."}
{"id": "4385", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4385", "title": "Marfark", "text": "Marfark is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The name is derived from an Arabic word \u0645\u0631\u0641\u0642 marfaq, meaning \"elbow\". Theta Cassiopeiae -- a solitary star in the northern constellation of Cassiopeia also shares the traditional name Marfark.\nFollowing it's establishment, the Automaton's would attempt to subvert the Menkent Line by attempting to punch through at Marfark. mustering the entirety of their strength for the endeavour. However, despite managing to flank the Menkent Line, the Automatons instead used Marfark to pivot westward and capture the Ymir, Andromeda and Trigon Sectors, holding them for months until Marfark and a series of other planets were recaptured during &lt;a href=\"Helldiver%20Operations\"&gt;Operation Andromeda&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nThe elbow of the &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt;, Marfark, is a planet thrust in an eternal winter, rife with blizards and extreme cold. It's terrain is spread across large ice flows, causing the frigid waters to further disrupt traversal of the battlefield.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Reclamation of Cyberstan.\nMarfark had remained a icy, desolate colony of Super Earth for almost 100 years, its colonists inhabiting its permafrost tundras and thriving amongst the endless frozen oceans and mountainous glaciers. It was of no particular remark, with many other icy moons like it spread across the galaxy. However, if there is anything that the enemies of Super Earth hate...is peace.\nOn April 3rd, 2184, shortly after their crushing, unapologetic defeat at Malevelon Creek and the righteous obliteration of their Expeditionary Forces; the Automatons, through some unknown and most likely tyrannical and undemocratic means, returned to fight Super Earth on force. They quickly overwhelmed and conquered &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt; and began to rush for the neighboring sectors. As the Helldivers scrambled back into the fight against the mechanized menace, the colonists at Marfark saw in horror and despair how, one by one, its surrounding planets fell to the red tides of socialism.\nThen, on April 16th, as the Helldivers managed to stop the Automaton advance at the &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;-&lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt; line, Marfark faced its first robotic assault, as the Automatons rushed to try and outflank the defenses. \nWar had been brought upon their doorstep.\nMenkent Line and Operation Cassiopeia.\nThroughout the months of April and May, Marfark would see 2 assaults that displaced its surviving colonists and destroyed their icy dwellings, as the Helldivers fought tooth and nail to hold the line against the tyrannical machines.\nOn April 16th SEAF forces had managed to liberate half of the Automaton presence on Marfark when uptick in the bots resistance was noticed, including the re-appearance of &lt;a href=\"Factory%20Strider\"&gt;Factory Striders&lt;/a&gt; in large numbers. Not long after the order came in from High Command to hold the planet, in order to secure the vulnerable flank of the Menkent Line. Thus the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; would redouble their efforts against the bots before their main automaton fleet could be redirected to the system, even redirecting forces from the bloody fighting on &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter heavy fighting throughout the remainder of the day and into early hours of the following morning, their efforts would pay off as the last of the Automaton holdouts would be crushed. Although S.E.A.F. forces braced for a possible follow up attack by the Automatons, no further offensives would materialize for the rest of the day (likely due to the toasters loosing their footholds and much of their heavy equipment on the arctic world), with High Command declaring the defense of the planet a resounding success.\nWith Marfark secure, the Helldivers would redirect their efforts to other fronts such as &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Penta\"&gt;Penta&lt;/a&gt;\nHowever, as the Terminid Control System failed in the East, the Helldivers would be forced to divert power in order to contain the now resurgent supercolony, which would ultimately doom Marfark to a fate worse than conquest by the Automatons, as it would be stuck on a deadlock.\nSecond Galactic War.\nMarfark had fallen out of Liberty's grace. As the Terminids and Automatons constantly forced the Helldivers to split and separate, more and more planets fell to the Automaton waves. Marfark would be lost in May, opening the gates for an assault on Aesir Pass that would be unsuccessful. But, such a fate was not to be the end for the icy bastion.\nOperation Trolley Problem.\nBy June, Marfark had been at least 4 weeks under the iron fist of the robots. But, it would be these barbarous occupation what would give it a glimpse of hope. The Automatons had brought to it a large repository of explosives, which would be determined by SEAF analysts to be necessary for the production of MD-17 Anti-tank mines. However, this discovery would occur at the same time that a distress signal came from the ruins of the Super Citizen Anne's Hospital For Very Sick Children at nearby &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt;, leaving the Helldivers with a choice to make: Save the trapped civilians at Vernen Wells or secure the explosives at Marfark, since only the first planet to be liberated would have its civilians or material secured.\nAfter the liberation of Aesir Pass in June 12th, the Helldivers began to dive towards both planets, with the majority picking Vernen Wells. While this may seem to be the end for the explosive caches, the icy bastion of Marfark may have one more chance at enjoying the sweet embrace of Managed Democracy again.\nUnfortunately following the liberation of Super Citizen Anne's Hospital For Very Sick Children on &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; appear to have become aware of our efforts to liberate the &lt;a href=\"MD-17%20Anti-Tank%20Mines\"&gt;Anti-Tank Mine&lt;/a&gt; materials on Marfark, and initiated operations to transport the material off-planet. Despite liberating 65% of the planet's surface, within 24 hours the bots were able to move the explosives cache deeper within their territory.\nMarfark remained in &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; hands, with the federation's &lt;a href=\"MD-17%20Anti-Tank%20Mines\"&gt;MD-17 Anti-Tank Mine&lt;/a&gt; factories being shuttered for the time being, following multiple successive material shortfalls. The adult and pre-adult workers in those factories have been reassigned to other gainful and safe employment.\nOperation Andromeda.\nWith impossible victory achieved in &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defense&lt;/a&gt; decided to (after brief reprise in form of bug killing) reconnect with the stranded SEAF forces. A great liberation operation was called, with intend of both creating a supply line to besieged Ymir sector, as well as cutting the Bot territory in half. First hellpods landed on late afternoon of July 13th, while most of the SEAF was busy liberating &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;. Proper liberation begun the next day, and after 2 days of fierce fighting, Marfark was liberated on morning of July 16th, fully opening the way to a planet that harbored a most shameful SEAF defeat - &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;.\nOperation Jet Brigade and the Miracle at Marfark.\nOn October 18th, 2184, Automaton warships have appeared in massive numbers in the atmosphere of &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;. Multiple SEAF bases fell within hours and by the end of the day so too would the planet. Reports indicate the presence of an augmented Automaton detachment leading the invasion, equipped with jetpack technology. This detachment will be referred to as the Jet Brigade in all communications.\nThe size of this assault was unprecedented, with Super Earth High Command assessing that some loss of territory would be unavailable. Sure enough, Matar bay fell by the end of the day, with a subsequent invasion of neighboring &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt; happening soon after, with that planet also falling to the mechanized socialists. However, every bot decommissioned weakened the strength of their advance, until the Jet Brigade launched an assault on Marfark on October 21st.\nAlthough the automatons were severely weakened by previous engagements, &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;SEAF&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver&lt;/a&gt; forces on the previous two planets, it would take every drop of blood and oil that the unified forces of humanity had at their disposal to hold the planet.\nThough the Department of Heroic Sacrifice Affairs would have much work to do in the following weeks, victory was achieved by the most narrowest of margins on October 22nd, with Marfark becoming the sight of another heroic victory for the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. However despite the Miracle at Marfark, the Jet Brigade remains a significant, albeit diminished, threat. We must remain ever-vigilant against future attacks. But for now, Liberty has won a great victory.\nOperation Jetclipper.\nFollowing the miraculous and righteous defeat of the Jet Brigade at Marfark, the planet's icy and snowy peaks glimmered with the spark of liberty, a beacon in the Federation of Super Earth. However, this peace would soon come under grave threat once more. In the month after the Helldiver victory against the Jet Brigade, Marfark would begin to become encircled as the bots maintained control of &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;, and then went onto easily capture &lt;a href=\"Aesir%20Pass\"&gt;Aesir Pass&lt;/a&gt; once more in the &lt;a href=\"Hydra%20Sector\"&gt;Hydra Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Then, on the morning of November 28th, the Automaton occupiers at the problematic sandy planet of &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; would send 12 battalions toward &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt; in an attempt to regain a foothold in the &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The bots would easily take control of Matar Bay by the next day as the rest of the Helldiver corps was concerned with Operation Iron Fleet against the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe writing was on the wall now for Marfark, as it was now surrounded completely by Automaton-controlled planets in a complete encirclement. The colonists' worst fears would come true as Marfark was once again invaded by the Automatons on the morning of November 29th, with the Automatons sending forces from all of Matar Bay, Martale, and Aesir Pass.\nYet hope was not lost. \nOn morning of November 30th, besieged world was graced by the reinforcements of Helldivers, which managed to agree on course of action after fight for &lt;a href=\"Chort%20Bay\"&gt;Chort Bay&lt;/a&gt; proved inefficient. While the initial predictions remained grim, the brave elite slowly managed to dislodge the sudden toaster occupation, and strike back at invading forces. \nThus, a second Miracle at Marfark has happened, and by early morning of December 1st, last of invading's forces were decommissioned. Yet despite this positive outlook, Marfark remains encircled, and it will be only a matter of time before its icy ramparts will be tested yet again, while the rest of Helldivers on Western Front remain purposefully spread out."}
