{"id": "5908", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5908", "title": "Mastia", "text": "Mastia is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Marspira%20Sector\"&gt;Marspira Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nAs with other planets of its biome (&lt;a href=\"Durgen\"&gt;Durgen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Phact%20Bay\"&gt;Phact Bay&lt;/a&gt;), Mastia offers a lot of open sandy dunes, tall hills and occasional labyrinths of stone mesas, with complete lack of any water holes nor noticeable plant life\nVisibility is often very good, as no clouds are present. However, semi-frequent Sandstorms temporarily reduce the vision to extremely close distances. However, they easily mask Helldiver presence, allowing to strike at enemy, and then withdraw into the storm.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nDuring the first months of the War, Mastia enjoyed its far distance from Automaton advancements, as by then they were interested in gains in &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt;. However, this false sense of safety was soon going to be shattered by the Automatons.\nOperation Brute Force.\nShortly before the noon of August 27th, Mastia was attacked by a small, most likely vanguard force from neighboring Tarsh. Helldivers instantly threw themselves to the defense, as the Major Order active by then was already completed, and planet possessed weather patterns that Helldivers found more democratic than others (As voted in local election by landslide of 80% votes). The attack was repelled in 12 hours, shredding all ships found on orbit.\nOperation Ecologic Immolation.\nHowever, the Automatons were not discouraged, and on the early morning hours of August 29th, they attacked one more time, by similarly sized force. The local governor proceeded to sent a transmission claiming full combat readiness of the planet, indicating it would take Automatons more than 10 days to overwhelm the defenses. This message proved to be false, as the local colonial officials had failed to properly fortify the planet and the planet was taking on far more mechanized fighters than it could handle. \nWith most of forces stuck on &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt;, the desert planet fell the following day, giving the socialist forces a chance to entrench. With liberation of The Wells the following day, both Mastia and Tarsh were cut off from the main Automaton supply line.\nOperation Titanium Belt.\nMastia would remain in Automaton hands, providing a staging ground for further invasions into Talus Sector during Operation Titanium Belt. Despite numerous sacrifices, robots stood firm on the dunes, routing and hunting down the remaining SEAF personnel stuck on surface. During that time FTL lines to Cyberstan were set up through neighboring &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt;, halting any liberation progress.\nOperation Critical Mass.\nWith the announcement of this new operation, and subsequent information that Automatons had placed massive manufactories of polystyrene, Mastia saw a rapid and massive arrival of divers eager to help arm their ships with &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Napalm%20Barrage\"&gt;Orbital Napalm Barrages&lt;/a&gt;. Due to fact that Bots had only recently brought forward the production, most of planet was in disarray, and many tactical assets were still being moved around.\nProper liberation began on September 13th, as massive in-channel campaigns were raised with hopes of additional divers for the cause. High Command suspected that bots would try to evacuate the machines in factories in 3 days of the operation, thus giving divers a tough choice between either permanently equipping themselves with powerful tool, or shooting bugs in hopes of completing the Major Order.\nThe planet returned into Liberty's embrace on evening of September 15th, and manufactories of polystyrene are being repurposed and inspected for future use, with the newly deployed Orbital Napalm Barrages managing to help Helldivers kill enough Terminid Warriors to at least meet 1 of the 2 target quotas for Terminid eradication.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nFollowing Mastia's liberation on September 15th, the planet would see relative peace for nearly 2 months. However, this peace would soon be in peril once more. From November 8th to November 11th, the Automatons would begin amassing Jet Brigade forces on Vernen Wells in the &lt;a href=\"Hydra%20Sector\"&gt;Hydra Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Marspira%20Sector\"&gt;Marspira Sector&lt;/a&gt; would be threatened once more, and on the afternoon of November 11th, the Automatons, led by the Jet Brigade, would launch the single biggest invasion seen during the entirety of the second galactic war so far on neighboring Tarsh, with a force of 58 Automaton battalions. Despite significant resistance from the Helldivers, the Automatons would easily capture Tarsh by the next day, pinpointing the location of the Democracy Space Station at nearby Gaellivare.\nMastia would soon find itself once more under grave threat against the despotic robots. With Mastia standing as the sole obstacle to the Automatons' goal of reaching Gaellivare, it was only a matter of time before the sandy planet would face the deadly strike force. Roughly 9 hours after the capture of Tarsh by the Jet Brigade, the Automatons would invade Mastia at midnight on November 13th, with a still massive fleet of 43 Automaton Battalions.\nThe battle for Mastia was as gruesome as the one that preceded it, with the SEAF and the Helldivers combining all of their strength in order to protect as many citizens of all ratings as possible. But despite this, the situation became more and more untenable. Despite all the sacrifices, the battle began to look lost, while the Jet Brigade didn't seem to lose any strength at all from what they previously had at Tarsh.\nBut when Tyranny's shadow is at its darkest, it is when Liberty's flames shine the brightest. Hours before the collapse of Mastia's defense, a platoon of SEAF reinforcements would come in from the most unlikely of places: &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt;. As an act of gratitude for the liberation of their homes during Operation Crossroads, this heroic platoon would valiantly capture key Jet Brigade positions on the planet, inflicting massive casualties on the invading force. While it is still unknown exactly how much of the enemy force was felled by these courageous warriors, some SESF analysts estimate that at least 10% of the invading force was successfully eliminated thanks to the sacrifice of these noble martyrs.\nThese heroes would have had no trouble breaking through a part of their numbers and escape, no matter how many tens of thousands of Automaton Troopers approached or how many fleets of Dropships encircled them. But they knew very well that this was not the way of Super Earth, as it would very much go against the very meaning of loyalty. Instead, they willingly chose to face the entire force of the enemies' war machine, regardless of how outnumbered they were or how supposedly formidable these foes were, and died a resplendent death, the likes of which only the heroes from the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; have ever surpassed.\nA soldier's duty is to this truth. Beyond this, there is nothing to be said. \nTo these courageous heroes, the Bureau of Galactic Wide Web Forums of the Ministry of Truth dedicates this small paragraph, so that their example leads all of our citizens, present and future."}
{"id": "4154", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4154", "title": "Matar Bay", "text": "Matar Bay is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt;. On October 28th, 2184, it became the first planet to fall to the malevolent Jet Brigade assault brigade of the Automatons.\nTopography.\nThe landscape of Matar Bay shares some similarities with the pre-great war Scottish highlands, leading some &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; to call the planet Space Scotland. The planet is well suited to human habitation, with the misty highland terrain prepossessing lush grass-life, several large continent sized lakes and vast oceans. Rocky outcrops expose the skeleton of the mountain landscape with a vegetative skin of heath and grasses covering most of it. Swathes of flowering heather together with patches of moss and pasture form a visually diverse but integrated landscape.\nMuch like old-scotland back on &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, Matar Bay does not have a dry season or a wet season, instead, rainfall is fairly consistent across the year, with some months wetter than others and thunderstorms being a common occurrence. The planet also possesses a unique native wildlife in the form of luminescent floating jellyfish which can be seen floating in the air, ranging in size from the size of a human palm to being larger than a Super Bowling Ball. Whilst appearing to be non-aggressive, field observations have noted that larger specimens also have the ability to shoot out their own bolts of electricity, seemingly at random. Investigations into whether this electric sting is lethal or not are ongoing.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nMatar Bay had laid in harmonious peace with Super Earth since its colonization up until the month of April 2184. As the Automatons, their motherboards bitter with defeat after their complete eradication in &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;, launched a sudden invasion of the Valdis Sector, taking over Cyberstan and igniting a second round of conflict in the Western Galactic Rim. As the Helldivers scrambled, Matar Bay's colonial defenses would be eventually overwhelmed and it would inevitably fall into the mechanical grip of the Automaton regime.\nEver since, it has been illegally and unjustly occupied by the tyrannical machines, who have made use of its as a pivot from which they can spread their socialist terror upon &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;, then the neighboring &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt; and as a nexus from which they most likely attacked &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;'s Petafactory and pushed towards Meissa and &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt; and, subsequently, attempted 2 takeovers of the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nOperation Starslayer.\nMatar Bay would not see much action itself after its invasion. From May to June, it would endure unimaginable horrors under the iron fist of the Automatons. However, in July, a glimmer of hope would emerge from an unlikely source: Meissa.\nWhile the Helldivers fought to defend X-45 in hopes of recovering lost blueprints from the First Galactic War, they would secure Vega Bay, Wasat and Meissa as a buffer zone, the first two having been previously recovered during Operation Valiant Resistance in June.\nWith Meissa secured, small sorties and raids would be sent towards Matar Bay, in order to weaken its defenses, as most of the Helldiver Corps focused on defending X-45.\nAfter 6 days, the blueprints would be recovered in X-45, with Super Earth having gained new possibilities and reclaimed many of its lost colonies.\nOperation Andromeda.\nAfter enduring 3 months of occupation, Super Earth High Command, having finally regrouped and regained ground after the &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23TCS%20Failure\"&gt;disaster at Meridia&lt;/a&gt; and their victories at &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers would launch a new offensive with the ultimate goal of severing the Automaton Forces in half, which would strike a decisive blow to the robotic foes.\nAfter successfully recovering Meissa during &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Starslayer\"&gt;Operation Starslayer&lt;/a&gt;, Super Earth now stood a fighting chance against the Automatons. Despite the tragic loss of a SEAF Garrison on Aesir Pass, the order was given for the Helldivers to capture Matar Bay, alongside with Martale, Marfark and Aesir Pass. Matar Bay would be swiftly captured on July 13th, with the operation successfully concluding on July 15th\nOperation Righteous Expunge.\nShortly after Operation Andromeda, Matar Bay would remain in relative peace, although still having impending danger coming towards it from nearby Choohe, a fortified planet right at the triple border between the Andromeda, Lacaille and Valdis Sectors. On July 19th, the Automatons would try to punch through Matar Bay to rescue their encircled southern garrisons, but would be successfully repelled.\nOperation Brute Force.\nSince its liberation, Matar Bay would once again breathe the air of freedom, as the weakened and defeated machines were expunged out of the encirclement. However, the Automatons would begin amassing their forces in order to attempt an even worse offensive. On August 11th, the Automatons punched through &lt;a href=\"Curia\"&gt;Curia&lt;/a&gt; for the first time in the war, initiating an invasion of the &lt;a href=\"Marspira%20Sector\"&gt;Marspira Sector&lt;/a&gt;. As such, the Helldivers were ordered to defend the Marspira Sector by all means necessary and, by August 18th, they would mostly succeed, repelling the Automaton offensive and sending them back into their occupied fief. However, the Helldivers would once again be ordered away towards the Terminid front in order to contain the new threat presented by the mysterious &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;Gloom&lt;/a&gt;.\nSeeing an opportunity, the Automaton garrison in Choohe launched an assault towards Matar Bay in conjunction with the Tarsh's Automaton Vanguard, which launched an assault onto &lt;a href=\"Mastia\"&gt;Mastia&lt;/a&gt;. This happened while the Helldivers were occupied defending &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt; from the incoming Terminid onslaughts that were now bolstered by the odious nebula.\nHowever, the Automatons did not count with the indomitable spirit of Liberty that resides within the heart of every man, woman and child over 7 that is enlisted into the Helldiver Corps as, shortly after the defense of &lt;a href=\"Esker\"&gt;Esker&lt;/a&gt; and the liberations of &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers would successfully repel both Terminid offensives on Estanu and Socorro then quickly turn towards Matar Bay, repelling the Automaton offensive at the last minute, then quickly turning back towards Mastia and Erata Prime.\nOperation Jet Brigade.\nMatar Bay would remain free ever since its final defense on August 18th. It's colonists, having endured the worst of the Automaton Occupation, were doing the best they could to try and recover all of what had been lost during those tragic months. However, the Automatons were looking to recover their lost claims, as their expansionist thirst remained ever unquenchable. As such, on October 18th, they deployed a new horrid foe in the form of The Jet Brigade, a special force of Automatons equipped with jetpacks and heavy armor, all of it based on stolen SEAF technology\nSuper Earth High Command would receive the emergency alert and immediately issued the order for all Helldivers to deploy onto Matar Bay immediately, as the Jet Brigade showed signs indicating that the Automatons knew about the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt;'s existence but were now doing a brute force attempt at finding out its location.\nMatar Bay would fall on October 19th, but not after its defenders gave their lives while taking out as many Jet Brigade bots as they could with them, their heroic sacrifice causing heavy losses to the horrid Automaton strike force. The loss of these brave defenders was not in vain.\nThe enemy was ruthless, efficient, but they weren't nearly fast enough, for these heroes had already clipped their wings. And thanks to them, we defeated the Jet Brigade at Marfark, safeguarded the Democracy Space Station and sent the Automatons home packing. \nOur victory was so close, many in the Helldiver corps wish that they could have lived to see it. But they belong to Matar Bay now. \nTheir bodies and guns. Everything...except their courage. \nThat they have given to Super Earth. \nAnd with it, we can rebuild.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nAnd surely enough, Matar Bay would rebuild. After Liberty Day, Super Earth High Command would designate a series of high priority objectives that would all need urgent Helldiver intervention. Among those were the recovery of &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; and the defense against further Automaton territorial conquests, but most importantly, the Helldivers were tasked with liberating Matar Bay and capturing certain databases established by the Automatons on the planet, which High Command discovered to contain information regarding the foundries where Jet Brigade platoons are assembled. \nAs such, the Helldivers, seeking to prevent another massacre like that of Matar Bay, decided to immediately dive onto the planet, halting all other efforts towards other planet's liberation and even having to draw away all defenders from the Gellert Sector in order to expedite the liberation of the grassy martyr planet.\nFor the entirety of the first day, the Helldivers faced down the machines with all the might of Super Earth's taxpayer Super Credits, raining orbital hellfire onto the entrenched robots. However, their progress was slow and few gains were being achieved. Some in the corps began to falter, seeing how Matar Bay was taking so long to liberate and how much other objectives still needed to be done. However, fortune would smile at Liberty as usual and a massive, planetwide storm would sweep its surface, as if the planet itself was repulsed at the socialist filth polluting its pristine grasslands. \nThis strike could not have been more fortunately timed, as the Automatons at Matar Bay had also sent away a strike force to attempt another assault at Marfark, which meant that the Automaton garrison at Matar Bay was pretty much completely defenseless\nWith the Automaton forces on the planet decimated, the Helldivers would redouble their efforts; as the colonists and remaining colonial defenders of Matar Bay, spared of any suffering by the storm and still resisting against their mechanized occupiers, would join forces with the Helldivers in order to reclaim their planet home back into the righteous control of Freedom.\nMatar Bay would be swiftly recaptured, with the assault at Marfark being halted in its cracks and the martyrs buried beneath the grass having been adequately avenged.\nOperation Iron Rain.\nSince the victory in late October at Matar Bay, the often beleaguered planet would finally see some semblance of peace for the next month. It would finally begin to recover from the atrocities committed by the vile and wicked Jet Brigade. \nHowever, the Automatons revolted at the terms of peace and rebuilding. On November 28, 2184, roughly a month after the planet's liberation, the robots at neighboring &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; would send 12 battalions toward the planet to regain a foothold in the Andromeda Sector. The attack would be very sickeningly timed with &lt;a href=\"Bore%20Rock\"&gt;Bore Rock&lt;/a&gt; being attacked a few hours earlier by the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the Major Order tasking the Helldivers with exterminating Terminids, the Automatons faced relatively little resistance at Matar Bay and regained control of the planet by the next morning.\nOperation Jetclipper.\nHowever, Matar's chance for freedom would arrive just as quickly as said freedom had been unjustly taken from them. Following a quick reorganization of the corps in the face of an assault at Marfark, the Helldivers would capitalize on the momentum of this assault, repelling it after 40 hours of defense. Then, on December 1st, the Helldivers would turn up on Matar Bay, racing to capture it as quickly as they could in order to open a pathway back into Choohe, with the purpose of liberating Choohe and securing intel regarding the factories where the Jet Brigade was being assembled.\nAfter some 16 hours of fighting, on December 2nd, the Helldivers managed to liberate Matar Bay once more, enabling the progression of the operation into Choohe."}
