{"id": "4411", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4411", "title": "Meissa", "text": " is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt;. This world is covered in plant life and receives heavy rainfall and fog. At nighttime, beautiful green moonlight can be seen peeking through the fog occasionally. On April 20th, Meissa become a frontline planet. Although Meissa is a world of nature and democracy, an &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; offensive risks the planet being converted into a planet of machines and machinations. \nTopography.\nMeissa is a relatively flat world with some rocky features. The air is filled with plant debris and ash, and the planet is often very foggy. Rain is nearly constant. Large oceans and many lakes also are found here. Plant life like trees and tall grass is uniformly found everywhere. Other life forms like small flying bugs that glow red or blue are also present. &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; should be aware of the dangers of the rain and the volcanoes here. The volcanoes have the potential to create patches of fire in key areas.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nFailure of the Terminid Control System - Defense of Meissa (April 20th - April 21st).\nAutomaton forces began to assault Meissa on April 20th. This attack was part of their &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Rampart\"&gt;wider joint-offensive with the Terminids.&lt;/a&gt; So far, Helldiver forces have been too overstretched to respond in force to the attack on Meissa. There was no substantial change to this part of the front on April 21st. S.E.A.F forces were reported overrun the next day. \nDeclaration of the Galactic War on Tyranny - Liberation Campaign of Meissa (April 22nd - Middle of May 2184).\nMeissa fell into Automaton hands after the failure to defend the planet. The sudden crisis in Umlaut sector caused Helldivers to rush into east .The liberation percentage averaged at 1.05% per day. With the Automatons already having secured Charon Prime, their offensive continued to the south into &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Choepessa%20IV\"&gt;Choepessa IV&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Later, fighting would reach &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt; from here. By no later than May 13th, the planet fell. The liberation campaign for Meissa was slow and drawn out, only making the nectar of inevitable victory ever more sweet. However since May 13th, only a skeleton crew of Helldivers fought on the planet, with nearly all of forces being occupied elsewhere. The liberation campaign would gradually come to an end over the next week, leaving the planet fully in automaton hands.\nOperation Valiant Resistance - Summer Liberation Campaign (June 10th. Ongoing).\nHelldiver forces returned to the planet on June 10th. These soldiers were those brave enough to continue the offensive began all the way on &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt;, during &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Firewall\"&gt;Operation Valiant Resistance.&lt;/a&gt; The successful operation, which concluded with the capture of &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt;, opened the way to Meissa's jungle surface once again. By the next day however, most of this force of ~13,000 had dissipated due to a new offensive on &lt;a href=\"Aesir%20Pass\"&gt;Aesir Pass&lt;/a&gt;. That offensive was the opening volley in &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Trolley%20Problem\"&gt;Operation Trolley Problem.&lt;/a&gt; The force on Meissa was miniscule until July 3rd. Liberation progress nearly reset by July 3rd. But on this day, a new defense order began to protect the &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X system&lt;/a&gt;. \nAs Helldiver forces shifted to the Ymir Sector, Meissa became a target again. ~15,500 Helldivers assaulted the planet on July 3rd. By July 4th, the system was about halfway liberated. The size of the Helldiver force dropped to ~5,000 as combat began on the true objective of &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt;. On July 5th, X-45 was liberated. Helldiver forces on Meissa swelled to ~10,000, bolstering reclamation efforts. \nLoss of momentum did not seem to occur following the assaults on &lt;a href=\"Vega%20Bay\"&gt;Vega Bay&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt;. The defense of these planets are critical to maintaining supply lines to Meissa and X-45. Around the same time of the defense of &lt;a href=\"Vega%20Bay\"&gt;Vega Bay&lt;/a&gt;, The Helldivers successfully reasserted control of Meissa, cutting off the attack on &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt; and opening up FTL Lines to &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;.\nShortly after the liberation of Meissa a hastily put together force of Automatons, originating from &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;, made landfall on the planet, engulfing the beautiful jungle world in war once more. This attack was barely resisted, leading to a Helldiver victory on July 6th."}
