{"id": "5453", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5453", "title": "Merak", "text": "Merak is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. This planet is the farthest that Helldivers have ever spread democracy onto, as well as being the closest that the SEAF has ever gotten to &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Veld\"&gt;Veld&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nOperation: Legitimate Undertaking.\nFollowing the failure and conclusion of &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Legitimate%20Undertaking\"&gt;Operation: Legitimate Undertaking&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Penta\"&gt;Penta&lt;/a&gt; was freed from the horrible rule of the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;toasters&lt;/a&gt; and allowed the Helldivers to a enter Merak and the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The planet was compared to &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon creek&lt;/a&gt; due to it being a bot owned ionic forested world however it was never as brutal as the creek and only averaging a few thousand Helldivers at once.\nThis forade into Merak would be short-lived, as the failure of the Terminid Control System forced Super Earth High Command to divert all forces back to the Terminid front, driving away most forces from the Automaton front and allowing Penta to fall once more, cutting off Merak from liberty's reach since.\nUntil October 2184, there was only 1 Super Destroyer still orbiting the planet, at least judging by its signal still being received back in Super Earth. However, they have since gone silent, their status unknown.\nTo this lone warrior, we dedicate this one line of the tale, for they truly stand as the brightest spark of Freedom in the fight against the Automatons."}
{"id": "6026", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6026", "title": "Merga IV", "text": "Merga IV is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3257", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3257", "title": "Meridia", "text": "Meridia was one of the four planets that resided within the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Its general terrain consisted of vast ponds and heavily forested areas.\nAs one of the Barrier Planets, Meridia was subject to the mass dispensing of Termicide by the Terminid Control System. The massive TCS was designed to permanently prevent the spread of the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;fascist bugs&lt;/a&gt; to the Umlaut Sector. However, on the 29th of April, the unthinkable happened. A preliminary investigation by the Ministry of Science revealed that some terminids were exposed to non-lethal doses of Termicide, causing mutations that allowed them to resist the effects of the termicide. On Meridia specifically, the terminids also gained the ability to reproduce much more rapidly, with this effect only being exacerbated with continuous exposure to the Termicide. These mutations caused the planet to be overwhelmed in just mere hours, turning it into a &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; nearly comparable with the Terminid home planet. \nHigh Command had deemed the planet a lost cause until Operation Enduring Peace began, with the aim of destroying Meridia with &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt;. On the 2nd of June, 2184, Meridia was successfully collapsed into a &lt;a href=\"Biomes\"&gt;black hole&lt;/a&gt;. On the 24th of December, 2184, it was confirmed that the black hole was instead a &lt;a href=\"Biomes\"&gt;wormhole&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nPreviously, Meridia was populated by dense jungle vegetation. Federation scientists were able to categorized a number of tropical tree and plant species native to the planet. Deep, warm oceans bordered the edges of Meridia's continental landmass, which was contiguous around the planet. Citizens were warned not to approach any of the multiple active volcanoes sighted near inhabited zones. \nBut after the failure of the &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Control%20System\"&gt;Terminid Control System&lt;/a&gt;, the ruthless &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;bugs&lt;/a&gt; turned Meridia into a &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;, the likes of which had never been seen before...\nTopography after the TCS Failure.\nThe topography and ecology of Meridia was changed drastically after the loss of the planet on the April 29th, following the failure of the TCS Towers. Orbital observations by the Super Earth Navy confirmed that Meridia had been transformed from a lush, blue and green jungle world to a gigantic, undemocractic insect hive. The atmosphere and oceans became a sickly brown, filled with a mix of termicide and mutated &lt;a href=\"Spore%20Spewer\"&gt;terminid spores&lt;/a&gt;. The bugs bred like rats, choking the life out of most other fauna and flora on the surface.\nThe Ministry of Science concluded that Meridia had undergone a process of proto-terraforming (or Termaforming) that effectively turned the entire planet into one gargantuan nest, dubbed a \"Terminid Super Colony\". The terrain now consisted of dead indigenous plant life interspersed with vast terminid mound and hive structures, including 'forests' of &lt;a href=\"Spore%20Spewer\"&gt;spore spewers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shrieker%20Nest\"&gt;shrieker nests&lt;/a&gt;. Meridia's numerous active volcanoes were the only remnants of the planet left untouched by the bugs.\nThe implications, as fascinating as they are, have been horrifying for the scientific community. Meridia stands as stark proof that the Terminids can essentially, and probably irreversibly, DESTROY the environments of planets. Prior to its destruction, Meridia stood as a monument to scientific hubris as the only &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;. We can only pray now that this once beautiful world will be the exception, rather than the rule going forward.\nTopography after Operation Enduring Peace.\nAfter Meridia became a Terminid &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers were left with no choice but to collapse it into a singularity using &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt;. Immense gravitational forces so strong that everything, including light, is dragged inward, resulting in reduced visibility beyond the event horizon. High-energy radiation of X-rays and gamma rays emitted as matter accelerates and speeds up heat buildup to such a degree that everything is annihilated in a brilliant (yet dangerous) display of energetic particles.\nSuper Destroyers returning to where Meridia once was following Operation Enduring Peace have found that the only thing that remains of the planet is a beautiful, purple black hole. All celestial bodies that were once in the system are now gone, having been consumed by the massive void. Helldivers have also reported strange, disconcerting noises emanating from the black hole while in orbit, but Super Earth High Command has dismissed these reports, asking Helldivers to divert their attention to more productive purposes such as liberation campaigns, or major orders.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations prior to the Second Galactic War.\nInstallation of the TCS System.\nDuring the months of February and March, the Helldivers valiantly dropped onto Meridia (along with its neighboring planets in the Umlaut Sector) to install the infrastructure necessary for the deployment of the Terminid Control System (TCS). These campaigns were quick and successful, allowing for subsequent pushes into the Draco and Mirin Sectors and establishing a definitive frontline against the Terminids.\nFailure of the TCS System.\nDue to a completely unprecedented process known as &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hormesis\"&gt;hormesis&lt;/a&gt;, Terminids exposed to non-lethal doses of Termicide eventually developed genetic adaptations to the neurotoxin. The first sprouts of these mutations appeared in March, in the form of the &lt;a href=\"Shrieker\"&gt;Shriekers&lt;/a&gt;, fascist flying abominations that preyed upon Super Earth's noble colonists. However, the existence of Shriekers themselves would not be enough of a concern, especially because they appeared around the time that the battles for Malevelon Creek and the rest of the Xzar and Severin Sectors were ongoing in the automaton front.\nThe real disaster occured in April 29th 2184, when continuous exposure to non-lethal doses of Termicide caused the Terminids on Meridia to develop a hyper-reproductive adapation to it. Before Helldivers could be scrambled, Meridia had been completely overwhelmed, becoming a Terminid &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;. With the rest of the planets in the Umlaut Sector at risk of suffering the same tragic fate, the Helldivers were quickly and successfully dispatched to deactivate the rest of the TCS System.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Ministry of Truth&lt;/a&gt; would like to hereby request one minute of silence in commemoration to all the lost colonists of Meridia, as well as to inform the readers that the traitorous scientists responsible for the defect in the TCS System have been thoroughly and meticulously investigated, trialed and executed.\nSecond Galactic War.\nUp until Operation Emancipator.\nBoth prior and after the declaration of the Galactic War on Tyranny, the &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; at Meridia had been causing immense trouble. Nearby systems suffered from regular Terminid outbreaks caused by abnormally high levels of spore production from the &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;, with &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heeth\"&gt;Heeth&lt;/a&gt; both seeing three consecutive bug incursions prior to Operation Freedom's Calling. Within the Umlaut Sector, other planets such as &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Erata%20Prime\"&gt;Erata Prime&lt;/a&gt; frequently had to be re-liberated by the valiant Super Earth Armed Forces.\nWhile the Helldivers were occupied liberating the Petafactory in &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; at Meridia would be responsible for causing yet another outbreak at Angel's Venture. While the Helldivers, in a display of their usually impeccable military prowess, managed to defend &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt; and liberate &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;, this siege was most likely the last straw for Super Earth High Command in regards to the question of the Terminid &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony's&lt;/a&gt; fate.\nOperation Enduring Peace.\nEventually agreeing that simply nuking the planet from orbit wasn't thorough enough (as by now the Terminids had burrowed deep into Meridia's crust), Super Earth High Command authorized the weaponization of the exotic &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt;, liberated from the tentacles of the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. The Dark Fluid was designed to destroy the Meridia &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; by injecting massive amounts of the fluid into the planet's crust, which would eventually cause the planet to collapse in on itself. However, in order to use this newly developed weapon on Meridia, a path had to be cleared there first.\nThus High Command authorized &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%2520Enduring%2520Peace\"&gt;Operation Enduring Peace&lt;/a&gt;, the first phase of which was to secure a route to &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; and to hold the staging ground until sufficient quantities of Dark Fluid could be weaponized and deployed. Such was the priority of this operation that all other territorial losses were considered acceptable to ensure its success.\nOn the morning of May 30, 2184, with Phase 1 of the operation completed, Super Earth High Command gave the final order: Helldivers were to initiate the deployment of the Dark Fluid, which was to be delivered in backpacks that would be then loaded and drilled into the planet's surface. Once a critical mass was reached, the Dark Fluid would accrete into a superdense mass, triggering total planetary implosion of the &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; and utterly annihilating its hyper-reproductive Terminids.\nHowever progress would be slow during the first two days of the operation, with Helldivers reporting a level of resistance that had never been witnessed before. The Terminids had managed to reach a 10% level of planet-wide resistance to liberation, which meant that any and all progress was almost immediately undone by the unyielding plague. The assault on the &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; also appeared to have spurred an increase in Terminid outbreaks on other planets, with scientists likening this response to a kicked hornet's nest, from the beloved childhood pastime.\nNot only that, but many Helldivers also reported bug breaches directly beneath the Tectonic Drill used to deploy the Dark Fluid on Meridia, hindering operations significantly. Fortunately, on the second day of the operation, the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; was able to engineer upgrades to the drill so that they now propagated anti-fascist ultrasonic frequencies through the ground, preventing Terminid breaches in its immediate vicinity. Determination and bravery allowed the Helldivers to make a dent in the Terminids' numbers, reducing the level of planet-wide resistance from 10% down to ~5.5%, creating much needed breathing room to deploy the Dark Fluid into the planet's crust. \nTo make matters worse, Helldivers also reported a seemingly infinite number of shriekers rising out of the ground on Meridia after deploying the Dark Fluid, even after dealing with all visible shrieker nests. Reports detailed swarms big enough to block out portions of the sky, making extraction significantly more difficult for unprepared squads who were unable to deal with the fascist \"cloud\" of shriekers bearing down on them.\nDestruction of Meridia.\nAs the sun rose for the last time on Meridia, sensors on the orbiting fleet detected a decrease in Terminid spawning on the &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Moradesh\"&gt;Moradesh's&lt;/a&gt; scientists identified this as evidence of early Dark Fluid accretion stages: micro-bubbles had began to form beneath the planet's crust, disrupting Terminid hives. With tectonic integrity beginning to decrease in the final hours of the operation, the future of the Liberty teetered on the abyss. One final push was all that remained...\nThen, at 15:25 SEST, on June 2nd, 2184, Meridia became the first planet to be destroyed by use of Dark Fluid. All Super Destroyers in orbit received the order to make an emergency FTL jump to &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. A gravitational disturbance was confirmed in the Meridia system, with the planet, its sun, and every other celestial body in its solar system soon disappearing from the face of the galaxy.\nSuper Destroyers returning to where Meridia once was found that the only thing that remained of the planet was a beautiful, purple &lt;a href=\"Biomes%23Black%20Hole\"&gt;Black Hole&lt;/a&gt;. Disturbing, strange noises fill the space surrounding Meridia. The destruction of the system marked the end of Operation Enduring Peace, which was an overwhelming success for Super Earth.\nThe destruction of Meridia did come not a moment too soon. The Meridia black hole continues to draw in every &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; spore within several billion kilometers, causing interstellar spore levels to sharply decrease in every nearby system. Though the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; continue their rampant spread across the galaxy, without the accelerating effect of the &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt;, containment is now once again possible.\nThe destruction of an entire planet is a tragedy, but the tyrannical Terminids left Super Earth without any other choice. Only the honorable sacrifices of countless Helldivers prevented the bug menace from spreading even further. A Victory Fund has been initiated to support the few remaining Meridian-born Helldivers during their future battles.\nOn December 2nd, 2184, the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; concluded all reports on Meridia, all evidence suggesting Meridia is nothing more than an ordinary black hole.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nAny pretenses that the illuminate would return through the Meridia black hole were thoroughly dissuaded following the battle of &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt;, as the Squ'ith actually appeared out of the &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Front\"&gt;galactic south&lt;/a&gt;, rather than the completely normal Meridia black hole. However following repeated battles with the Squ'ith (and likely perpetuated by battle fatigue) a new theory emerged that the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; that federation faced was in fact a \u201cvanguard\u201d force, paving the way for the main invasion fleet.On the 19th of December, 2184, Helldivers started noticing novel electromagnetic phenomena in vicinity of the Meridian Black Hole. High Command was of course well aware of the situation and closely monitoring it with experts in the field. However some Helldivers pilgrimaging to Meridia soon discovered that the black hole had changed, it's purple hues now more pronounced.\nMany Helldivers also noted that the Illuminate seem to be moving towards Meridia, reinforcing the belief that the squids are heading to the black hole -- gathering colonists from the populous galactic south along the way. High Command has yet to Comment on this development (partially due to The Ministry of Defense's strategists and analysts being under review following the &lt;a href=\"New%20Stockholm\"&gt;New Stockholm&lt;/a&gt; debacle) though High Command is aware of the situation, which is being closely monitored by experts in the field. Helldivers are advised to avoid distractions and focus their full attention on repelling the Illuminate threat.\nFollowing the conclusion of Operation Squid Game however, Astronomers have reported novel anomalous phenomena in the form of fluctuations in the event horizon and electromagnetic flares in the vicinity of the Meridian Singularity. Since the exotic substance known as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt; was found on Illuminate worlds at the end of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; and was used to collapse the planet into a black hole, High Command concluded that the recent changes to the Meridian Singularity, so shortly following the reappearance of the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt;, may indicate a deeper connection. Indeed the Meridian Singularity may be no ordinary black hole, as many leading government experts have long suspected.\nNaturally these developments demanded further investigation. High Command thus ordered the construction of a new Center of Science on &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt;. However the Helldivers first had to clear the planet and nearby area of any &lt;a href=\"Terminid\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; infestation in order to facilitate its safe construction. Thanks to decisive Fascism-repulsion operations by the Helldivers in vicinity of Fenrir III, the construction of a new Center of Science was completed safely. Top &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astrophysics\"&gt;astrophysicists&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; immediately convened there to closely study the Meridian Singularity and instantly the project yielded valuable insights.\nThe Singularity was not, as many uninformed laypeople had assumed, a typical black hole. It is, in fact, the first observed instance of a wormhole: a tunnel in spacetime connecting two disparate points in space. Much more remains to be investigated as it is likely that the wormhole was formed following the implosion of Meridia by dark matter unclear if the wormhole formed recently, or if it has existed for some time already. A connection to the recent &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; attacks is one of many threads being pursued."}
