{"id": "6540", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6540", "title": "Mines", "text": "This page contains information on all minelayers present in Helldivers 2, including: MD-6 Anti-Personnel Minefield, MD-I4 Incendiary Mines, Anti-Tank Mines\nGeneral Tips.\nAll minefields are dispensed from a scattering device housed inside a . The mines are thrown in a spiral pattern some distance from the center, and arm themselves shortly afterward. The pattern is less dense towards the outer edge. Any mines that encounter vertical surfaces will adhere with triggers facing outward.\nMine stratagems have a fairly quick cooldown time, allowing many minefields to be active at once. Barring any compromises by the game engine in the name of optimization, mines will persist through the remainder of the mission.\nMines can be set off by nearby explosions, including neighboring mines. Mines can also be set off by corpses of enemies; this sometimes results in a single enemy triggering multiple mines. Mines can also be set off by direct fire.\nFollowing the initial drop and scattering action, minefields do not draw further aggression from enemies. However, enemies will respond to the sound of any mines detonating near them, possibly attracting the entirety of an undemocratic patrol. Enemies will not intentionally engage with a minelayer, and will often halt while one is dispensing. Such delays can be beneficial to Helldivers attempting to limit undesired encounters."}
{"id": "6379", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6379", "title": "Ministries and Megacorporations", "text": "Ministries.\nMinistries are Governmental Branches of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; that are tasked with specific duties. Every Ministry has a Megacorporation that is at the head of the Ministry.\nMegacorporations.\nSuper Earth has many Mega Corporations ranging from banking to cybernetic implants.\nStrohmann Media.\nStrohmann Media is a Mega-Corporation that is the main source of news and information on the GWW. Strohmann Media is the parent company of Strohmann News a News channel that covers Liberty's latest in the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. \nStrohmann Media is officially the Mega-Corporation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Ministry of Truth&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe name \"Strohmann\" is a play on the idea of a \"&lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Straw_man\"&gt;straw man argument&lt;/a&gt;\", a fallacy in which someone in a debate misrepresents their opponent's argument in order to make it easier to attack.\nMorgunson.\nMorgunson is a Mega-Corporation that provides weaponry to the civilians of Super Earth. Morgunson is the parent company of Morgunson Defense an arms manufacture known for Hunting, Warfare, Home Defense but most of all Tradition.\nMorgunson is officially the Mega-Corporation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defense&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nMorgunson is a play on words of \"More\" \"Gun\" \"Son\".\nPermaCura.\nPermaCura is a Mega-Corporation that specialises in life saving treatment. PermaCura is the parent company of Permacura Biopharma the producer of &lt;a href=\"Stim\"&gt;Combat Stims&lt;/a&gt;. \nPermaCura is officially the Mega-Corporation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Unity\"&gt;Ministry of Unity&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nPermaCura could be two companies, Perma and Cura, but this is not confirmed.\nUlterior.\nUlterior is a Mega-Corporation that specialises in mining and resource gathering to feed the Super Earth war machine. Ulterior is the parent company of Ulterior Industry's a company that \"E-710 runs on.\"\nUlterior is officially the Mega-Corporation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Expansion\"&gt;Ministry of Expansion&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrustor.\nTrustor is a Mega-Corporation that specialises in banking and economics. Trustor is also the producer of Eagle Sweat and sponsor of the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;DSS&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the game file Trustor is listed as being the Mega-Corperation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Intelligence\"&gt;Ministry of Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; as they are referenced as being the same Ministry. Some Helldivers have put forward the idea that Trustor is actually the Mega-Corperation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Prosperity\"&gt;Ministry of Prosperity&lt;/a&gt; as the ministry manages Super Earth's economy.\nC.O.B Genetics.\nC.O.B Genetics is a Mega-Corporation that specialises in genetics and agriculture. C.O.B Genetics is known for making genes better and operation well within standard safety protocols. The C.O.B Genetics logo appears on the &lt;a href=\"Activate%20E-710%20Pumps\"&gt;E-710 Pumps System Terminal&lt;/a&gt; but is altered to be a corn on the cob beetle next to the C.O.B Genetics name.\nIn the game file C.O.B Genetics is listed as being the Mega-Corperation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Prosperity\"&gt;Ministry of Prosperity&lt;/a&gt;. Some Helldivers have put forward the idea that C.O.B Genetics is actually the Mega-Corperation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Science\"&gt;Ministry of Science&lt;/a&gt; because of C.O.B Genetics focus on genes and food, as well as the Ministry of Prosperity only dose beverages and not agriculture.\nAmpudyne.\nAmpudyne is a Mega-Corporation that specialises in robotics and &lt;a href=\"Grenades%20%28Helldivers%202%29\"&gt;grenades&lt;/a&gt;. The robotic part used in the &lt;a href=\"Steeled%20Veterans\"&gt;Steeled Veterans Warbond&lt;/a&gt; were manufactured by Ampudyne as well as &lt;a href=\"Grenades%20%28Helldivers%202%29\"&gt;grenades&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the game files, Ampudyne is listed as being the Mega-Corperation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Employment\"&gt;Ministry of Employment&lt;/a&gt;. Some Helldivers have put forward the idea that Ampudyne is actually the Mega-Corperation of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Humanity\"&gt;Ministry of Humanity&lt;/a&gt; because of the Ministry's responsible of maintaining the health of Super Earth citizens with would make sense given Ampudyne specialises in robotic implants and limbs keeping a human alive.\nAdmiral Defense.\nAdmiral Defense, officially shortened to AM Defense, is a defense contractor that specialized in providing military gear to the SEAF's line infantry. However, in December 2184 they would begin construction work on a new factory with the aim of expanding their services towards the provision of gear to the Helldiver Corps, having secured a multi-trillion Supercredit contract with the government. As of the time of writing, no logos have been show for AM Defense.\nIt is expected that once they complete their multi-complex factory hub at Achernar Secundus, fleetwide deployment of the &lt;a href=\"M-102%20Fast%20Recon%20Vehicle\"&gt;Fast Recon Vehicle&lt;/a&gt; (FRV) will be possible.\nSt\u00e5hl Arms.\nDue to the reemergence of the Illuminate extremists -- as well as the amount of ammo, stratagems, and lives of heroes used to combat them -- the Federation's Q4 defense budget for 2184 was put under unexpected strain. To address this issue, the Ministry of Defense entered into a contract with reputable arms manufacturer St\u00e5hl Arms. All Helldivers were then effective immediately granted access to six new items, including two weapons and one armor set."}
{"id": "4355", "revid": "15866885", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4355", "title": "Ministry of Defense", "text": "The Ministry of Defense (MoD) is an executive ministerial department of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. It is responsible for providing, managing and maintaining the military forces needed to deter and wage war as well as protect the security of the federation against all enemies, and &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;non-human&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;realized&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;potential&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith the declaration of the Galactic War on Tyranny, Mobilisation across all sectors of the industry and economy has begun; with billions of able-bodied citizens from across the Federation having already volunteered for conscription.\nCollectively referred to as S.E.A.F (&lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;Super Earth Armed Forces&lt;/a&gt;), the defenders of the Federation are split into different branches, including the Super Earth Army, the Navy, Colonial Guard and of course the &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Helldiver Corps&lt;/a&gt;, whom receive their &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders\"&gt;orders&lt;/a&gt; directly from High Command. Raw recruits typically go through a rigorous 72-hour S.E.A.F. basic training course, before being assigned to a branch or being given more specialized training, such as the 8-week training course in Superior Packing Methodology (SPM) for Super Destroyer Crew's, or the \"Real Deal\" Helldiver training on &lt;a href=\"Mars\"&gt;Mars&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor more detailed information on the branches of the Super Earth Armed forces, see &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;, for more on the Helldiver corps itself, see &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.\nSubordinate Departments of the Ministry of Defense.\nDirectorate of Helldiver Readiness.\nOperating under the oversight of Helldiver Readiness Command, a major command of the Super Earth Armed Forces which in turn operates under the Ministry of Defense. The Directorate of Helldiver Readiness is responsible for turning raw recruits into sufficiently fully trained Helldivers. As such, the Directorate Operates hundreds of training bases on &lt;a href=\"Mars\"&gt;Mars&lt;/a&gt;, able to process as many as 48,000 raw recruits a day, all under the watchful eye of &lt;a href=\"General%20Brasch\"&gt;General Brasch&lt;/a&gt;.\nDepartment of Heroic Sacrifice Affairs.\nWhether due to enemy action or friendly fire, casualties are an unfortunate consequence of war. Every day heroes of the federation are injured, maimed and killed in various gruesome ways, with it being the responsibility of the department of Heroic Sacrifice Affairs to deal with these casualties. One of the department's most important military duties is to provide a \"death\" notification to the deceased's next of kin, whether they be a partner, close relative, pet or neighbor.\nThe Terminid Supercolony on &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; for example could not have been destroyed without the brave sacrifice of many, many Helldivers. In their honor, the Department of Heroic Sacrifice affairs would issue personalized memorandums to their designated next-of-kin. We will always remember [Helldiver Name]."}
{"id": "6377", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6377", "title": "Ministry of Employment", "text": "The Ministry of Employment (MoE) is a Ministry of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; that is in charge of the employment of &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; into the SEAF. The Ministry of Employment only apprise on the &lt;a href=\"Helldiver%20Contract%20of%20Employment\"&gt;Helldiver Contract of Employment&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4359", "revid": "15866885", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4359", "title": "Ministry of Expansion", "text": "The Ministry of Expansion (MoE) is an executive ministerial department of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. It is responsible for terraforming and resource extraction as well as the expansion, management and development of Super Earth's colonies on planets all across the Galaxy. Each colony is managed by a Colonial Overseer, with entire planets being overseen by a Planetary Overseer who are elected into office, much like other Super Earth officials. All though ultimately report to the Ministry of Expansion.\nColony infrastructure.\nStandardized Colonial Agricultural Garrisons (SCAGs) are designed with the settler in mind! Friendly and homey, the sufficiently sized housing accommodations for our enterprising interstellar farmers come complete with solar engineering/electrical kit, S.E.A.F. emergency distress beacon, and the colony's choice of:\nEach sufficiently sized housing module will generously include:**\nFeed the Expansion of Super Earth!\n\"*Note: All crops are genetically modified for the planet\u2019s conditions. Side affects may include: Constipation. Skin rash or dermatitis. Diarrhea. Dizziness. Drowsiness. Dry mouth. Headache. Insomnia.\"\n\"**Note: Requisitions to millions of habitats around the known territories of the galaxy may result in misdirected allocations. Ensure you inspect your sufficiently sized housing module on receipt and report any discrepancies to your regional requisitions office. Average response time may be several years, so don't delay!)\""}
{"id": "4356", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4356", "title": "Ministry of Humanity", "text": "The Ministry of Humanity (MoH) is an executive ministerial department of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey are responsible for maintaining healthy, productive voters by managing education, healthcare, social grading and genetic management. Additionally, when &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;DSS&lt;/a&gt; required over 1.3 million skilled workers, the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Humanity\"&gt;Ministry of Humanity&lt;/a&gt; authorized the relocation of an unprecedented number of colonists, indicating that they may work closely with, is subordinate to, or have the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Employment\"&gt;Ministry of Employment&lt;/a&gt; as a subordinate agency.\nThe Ministry of Humanity is also what gives the people of Super Earth their food, education, medical practices, and genetically advancing the next line of Humans to be stronger. It is said by them that you must fill out a form before performing any action that may result in a child. The loading screen tip states, \"Remember to fill in your C-01 permit before any act that could result in a child.\"\nTrivia.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//x.com/helldivers2/status/1755245795014541813\"&gt;Ministry of Humanity Poster - X(Twitter)&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "4884", "revid": "46883485", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4884", "title": "Ministry of Intelligence", "text": "The Ministry of Intelligence (MoI) is one of the executive ministerial departments of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. It acts as the federation's primary intelligence agency, responsible for the collection, analysis, and exploitation of information in support of law enforcement, galactic security and military operations. The primary role of the Ministry is to collect, analyze, and distribute intelligence as required by the federation.\nIt's means of information gathering can be both overt and covert and may include espionage, communication interception, cryptanalysis, evaluation of public sources and cooperation with other institutions, such as the Super Earth Armed forces and the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defense&lt;/a&gt;. Presumably it is part of a wider Super Earth Intelligence Community, working alongside the likes of the Ministry of &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Ministry of Truth&lt;/a&gt;. However in all likelihood the Ministry of Intelligence is primarily concerned with enemies outside of the federation; most prominently the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;. Indeed, their interrogators have managed to successfully extracted information from captured bots, by uploading captured hard-drives to bot husks in &lt;a href=\"SEAF\"&gt;SEAF&lt;/a&gt; possession and exposing them to Unpleasant Sensory Experience Simulations.\nThe Ministry also maintains a fleet of \"Security\" Surveillance Satellites, one of which was instrumental in discovering the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; \"Petafactory\" on the planet of &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;, allowing SEAF forces to capture the planet before it could become fully operational and modify it into a second Morgunson Arsenal, allowing the construction of a new dual-autocannon Exosuit variant: the &lt;a href=\"EXO-49%20Emancipator%20Exosuit\"&gt;EXO-49 EMANCIPATOR EXOSUIT&lt;/a&gt;.\nOperations.\nSwift Disassembly and the Reclamation.\nThe most recent success and failure of the ministry is the discovery of &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;\"\"\"The Reclamation\"&lt;/a&gt; through the use of the above mentioned methods, which was then correctly identified as a massive invasion of unprecedented scale. They were also able to identified a long-range communications array deep in Automation space on the planet of &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt;. Following the arrays capture, analysts were able to determine that the bots were broadcasting outside the Galactic Frontier, however the analysts were unable to learn more due to the deletion of most of the data. Never the less they were able to identify blueprints for automaton &lt;a href=\"Gunship\"&gt;aerial gunships&lt;/a&gt;, allowing the hardworking factory laborers of Super Earth to accelerate production of anti-air weapons.\nFollowing the success of Operation Swift Disassembly, it was assumed that all any threat from the Automaton's and their \"Reclamation\" had passed. Out of an abundance of caution, SEAF teams were dispatched to &lt;a href=\"Tibit\"&gt;Tibit&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Maia\"&gt;Maia&lt;/a&gt; to search what remains of Automaton facilities and servers for any additional intelligence. Unfortunately super earth's analysts were unable to discover the existence of the Automaton's main fleet, or their plans for a surprise invasion of the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lacaille%20Sector\"&gt;Lacaille Sector&lt;/a&gt; until they launched their invasion several days later... a black mark on the Ministry's record if there ever was one...\nDatabase One.\nAlthough the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;' ultimate objective is all too clear (the utter destruction of our way of life as their rigid programming cannot tolerate our unbridled Freedom), many gaps remain in our military intelligence regarding the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;. The originating location of the Invasion Fleet is yet unknown and the socialist toasters focus on &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; remains unexplained, save for wild speculation.\nThat changed with the discovery of the large &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; Data Center on the planet of &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt;, designated Database One. It's vast stores of data could answer many questions, although remote hacking was impossible due to being protected by exceptionally robust encryption protocols, though this also meant that whatever data was stored there was clearly important, given how much effort had been expended to keep it hidden.\nTo this end SEAF High Command lunched Operation: Valiant Resistance. After three days the Helldivers were able to liberate the planet and capture Database One intact, which allowed for intrepid SEAF Cyberwarfare Specialists to manually extract the data and breach it's encryption. Although it will take months to sift through the truly monumental amount of data recovered, several key discoveries have already been made.\nChief amongst these was that the Automatons appear to be planning some sort of massive terraforming project on &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; itself. Additionally decoded data includes detailed recordings of the impact of the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; Supercolony on &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt;. Other keywords are also referenced numerous times throughout the data trove, though without additional details: Vessel 00, Nucleus, The Final Collective, and others.\nAs the SEAF and Helldiver Corps push towards Cyberstan, our analysts continue to decode the vast database, so that new intel may be gleaned that will aid in our resistance.\nOperation Jet Clipper.\nAlthough the &lt;a href=\"Automatons%23Jet%2520Brigade\"&gt;Jet Brigade&lt;/a&gt; and it's campaign of terror, where homesteads were pillaged and citizens were murdered, is long over, the threat of further despoiling remains. Though the Jet Brigade was summarily routed by the Helldivers during Operation Balance of Liberty, the factories that produced them were still out there, ready to spew out more gravity-defiling calculators-at-arms. Fortunately decryption of Automaton database intel revealed that the Jet Brigade used &lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; as a staging ground. Liberating this staging ground would likely reveal information on the Jet Brigade factories.\nUnfortunately Choohe was liberated behind schedule, with whatever secrets about the Jet Brigade it may have contained been scrubbed from servers and databases. Fortunately not all was not as an impressive number of memory drives were recovered from the dismantled Automatons. High Command had also ordered the dismantling of any remaining Automatons that operated alongside the Jet Brigade and may still have important data stored on their internal drives. Thanks to the swift actions of the Helldiver Corps, such drives were not in short supply, with the chance of finding useful intel a statistical inevitability.\nAs soon as their contents have been uploaded to bot husks in SEAF possession, they will be ready for interrogation. This is all but guaranteed to yield results, as soon as all 89,601,000 drives have been thoroughly interrogated."}
{"id": "6378", "revid": "46883485", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6378", "title": "Ministry of Prosperity", "text": "The Ministry of Prosperity (MoP) is a ministry of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, it manages Super Earth's economy and ensure a steady flow of resources to the most deserving. As part of this, they ensure every colonist has access to the latest consumer goods and beverages. These include: Dr. Democracy, Mr. Taste, Prof. Delicious, and Yummm, Esq. Note that the Ministry of Prosperity asks that anyone who is consuming a case of Democracy Drafts Premium Light Beer to please refrain from operating heavy machinery.\nThe ministry of Prosperity also seems to be the ones who run the Superstore, where &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbonds&lt;/a&gt; can be purchased by Helldivers using supercredits. The reviews on the store however have been devised by Super Earth's &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Ministry of Truth&lt;/a&gt; after an analysis to reflect the most accurate possible opinions of loyal Super Earth citizenry. In other words, these are not real reviews.\nFestival of Reckoning.\nBetween December 25th to the 28th, citizens across the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation&lt;/a&gt; observe one of Super Earth's most special holidays. A joyous celebration of love, family, and the pursuit of peace: the Festival of Reckoning. The 3-day Festival of Reckoning makes use of the specially-allocated Reckoning Fund, set aside each year to finance an exhilarating expenditure of ordnance against the enemies of Democracy. Families gather to witness the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; avenge all the loved ones lost during the year.\nEach of the 3 days has a special theme, determined by the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Prosperity\"&gt;Ministry of Prosperity&lt;/a&gt;. For the year of 2184, on the First Day of Reckoning, the Helldivers were given access to a bounty of &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Napalm%20Barrage\"&gt;Incendiary Weaponry&lt;/a&gt;. On the Second Day meanwhile, the Helldivers are given access to a bounty of &lt;a href=\"Eagle%20500kg%20Bomb\"&gt;Explosive weaponry&lt;/a&gt;. The Third Day of the Festival of Reckoning meanwhile is the most special day: the Feast of the Electorate, celebrating the first Free and Managed election. Helldivers are given access to a truly overflowing bounty of all manner of weaponry. As families and communities watch the death toll rise, they also can take advantage of deep discounts on consumer goods. The higher the death toll, the greater the savings.\nDuring the first day of the festival, the Spirit of Reckoning would also leave a present for all Helldivers who proved their virtue this year through unhesitating sacrifice in defense of Freedom. Thus all Helldivers found the &lt;a href=\"StA-X3%20W.A.S.P.%20Launcher\"&gt;StA-X3 W.A.S.P. LAUNCHER&lt;/a&gt; Stratagem waiting in their Armory. A Vengeful Festival to all!\nThanks to the Helldivers, all of &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;'s citizens are reminded all of the true meaning of the Festival of Reckoning: that our loved ones are never truly lost, so long as they are righteously avenged. The death toll has risen; the spirit of Reckoning has completed its intergalactic voyage; the deep discounts have been capitalized on; and the memory of those lost this year have been avenged. With the passing of another truly Vengeful Festival, we return to our daily lives, with full hearts and reinvigorated commitment to the unyielding pursuit of peace."}
{"id": "5079", "revid": "46883485", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5079", "title": "Ministry of Science", "text": "The Ministry of Science (MoS) is an executive ministerial department of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. It presumably fills the need for both civil and military scientific research and development, relying on the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; to obtain samples on which to perform experiments on.\nThe Ministry of Science is also responsible for developing and funding certain experimental infrastructure projects, such as the &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Control%20System\"&gt;Terminid Control System&lt;/a&gt;, the Terminid Research Initiative, development for Termicide 1.0 and 2.0, and for developing ways to deploy the mysterious Dark Fluid.\nMoradesh Project.\nScientists on &lt;a href=\"Moradesh\"&gt;Moradesh&lt;/a&gt; were the ones responsible for developing a way to combat the Meridia Supercolony. With the hope being that the \"Super weapon\" developed would be Liberty's salvation. The details of this project remained highly classified, with the only guarantee being that the Ministry of Science's best minds worked hard to bring this secret weapon to fruition and that it would involve the use of exotic &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Dark Fluid is a form of synthesized exotic matter liberated from the following the First Galactic War. In a scientific breakthrough following the opening of a micro-blackhole in the research facility on Moradesh (speaghettifying twelve facility staff before fizzling out), our scientists had just engineered a solution to the Terminid Supercolony on &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe project would be an unadulterated success as at 15:25 SEST, on June 2nd, 2184, Meridia became the first system to be destroyed by use of Dark Fluid. All &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyers&lt;/a&gt; in orbit received the order to make an emergency FTL jump to Super Earth or the nearby &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; system. A gravitational disturbance was confirmed in the Meridia system, with the planet of Meridia, it's sun and every other celestial body in its solar system soon disappearing from the face of the galaxy as a beautiful purple black hole appeared in place of the Supercolony.\nNot long after the Moradesh Research Facility was decommissioned following the total exhaustion of all Dark Fluid stores. The tireless scientists who contributed to the \"Moradesh Project\" were all awarded the Super Citizenship Medal of Freedom.\nTerminid Research Initiative.\nIn order to better predict certain previous unforeseeable outcomes when dealing with the Terminids, the Ministry of Science has begun a &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; Research Initiative.\n&lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; evolution is known to accelerate under duress. Therefore, in order to observe potential outcomes, applying controlled duress to the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; will be necessary to scientific progress. Thus the Helldivers were ordered to kill over one hundred million &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; -- which was accomplished in a little over eight hours. Sure enough, this aided the work of Super Earth's scientists considerably, both thanks the efficacious bug-eradication methodologies as well as behavior observed in the field.\nOne key ancillary finding was that &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; produce higher quality E-710 when harvested under extreme duress. This finding will guide future E-710 acquisition policy, assuring our access to uninterrupted FTL travel capabilities. Additionally close observation of the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; did uncover a new behavior: the construction of spore-producing towers, roughly the size of small skyscrapers.\nWhilst the Ministry of Science has deemed that this new behavior to be harmless, it will be closely monitored just in case. In any case, the Terminid Research initiative was continued into Operation Glorious Xenocide where Helldivers demonstrated a commitment to scientific progress equaled only by their fervor for Democratic supremacy. Thanks to their efforts, the Ministry of Science was able to gather even more data to further ongoing Terminid research efforts.\nWhile no clear method of termination has proved to produce more E-710 than any other, the Ministry of Science's top researchers all agreed that establishing this beyond doubt was well worth the expenditure. However, with the large quantities of data gathered, one new finding did emerge: Terminid mutations, rather than appearing randomly as previously hypothesized actually decreased in frequency as proximity to Super Earth increased. Indeed it now appears that genetic variants are perpetuating from deep within Terminid space. The explanation for this new phenomenon is yet unknown, and more investigation is necessary."}
{"id": "4354", "revid": "15866885", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4354", "title": "Ministry of Truth", "text": "The Ministry of Truth (MoT) is an executive ministerial department of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, presumably headed by a still unknown \"Minister of Truth\". This ministry is responsible for providing information based on facts and democratic values to the public, serving as the main source of truthful propaganda for the Federation through all of the channels it possesses control over, from the Galactic Wide Web to the many possible bandwidths of interstellar transmissions. All posters speaking about the other Ministries and the rest of the Federation at large are created and distributed by the Ministry of Truth in order to give the most accurate and factual information possible to their citizens, in order to deter any and all treasonous dissident thoughts.\nBy and large, the Ministry of Truth is responsible for the dissemination of news and war reports. As reported by the Ministry, their reporting and evaluations have an accuracy rating of 100%. Any evidence to the contrary, or &lt;a href=\"Terminate%20Illegal%20Broadcast\"&gt;news garnered from outside official channels&lt;/a&gt;, is dissident propaganda and should be reported to the nearest Loyalty or Democracy Officer.\nAttached Agencies and Officers.\nDemocracy Officers.\nThe Ministry of Truth is the Ministry which every &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Officer\"&gt;Democracy Officer&lt;/a&gt; reports to, with their role being to motivate Helldivers and other SEAF personnel to fight for Managed Democracy and \"optimize their Citizenship\". Judging by their appearance, the Democracy Officers appear to be seasoned combat veterans, employed by the Ministry of Truth to dispense inspirational quotes for the troops as well as update them on the war effort. It can be assumed that they also merit out corporal punishment (including execution or relocation to a freedom camp) should they find any dissident activity (such as deserting). \nThe Democracy Officers are not to be confused with the Loyalty Officers; these are mentioned by the &lt;a href=\"Service%20Technician\"&gt;Service Technician&lt;/a&gt; and the Super Destroyer announcements, which encourage Citizens to report any dissident activity to their \"local Loyalty Officer\". Judging by their role as active police who quell internal threats to the Federation's security, it would seem the Loyalty Officers instead belong to the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Unity\"&gt;Ministry of Unity&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrohmann News.\nThe Ministry of Truth is also in charge of supervising Super Earth's largest news channel \"Strohmann News\" which Helldivers are able to watch aboard their Super Destroyers. Strohmann News uses the same logo as the Ministry.\nTruth Enforcers.\nWith the addition of the \"Truth Enforcers\" warbond, an organization called the \"Truth Enforcers\" was introduced. Judging by the two available uniforms, the UF-50 Bloodhound and the UF-16 Inspector, the \"Truth Enforcers\" possibly serve the role of a politically-aligned paramilitary component of the Ministry of Truth or the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Unity\"&gt;Ministry of Unity&lt;/a&gt; akin to the role filled by the \"Waffen-SS\" in Germany during World War 2 or the Sith Troopers from \"Star Wars\", the latter appearing to be a clear inspiration for the UF-50 Bloodhound Armor.\nGiven the nature of the equipment found in the Warbond, the \"Truth Enforcers\" can be assumed to be tasked with eliminating any dissidents (as designated by the Ministry of Truth) that reside both among the military corps and the civilian population, with the UF-16 Inspector Armor possibly being a glimpse at the officer's attire of a member of this organization, while the UF-50 Bloodhound armor serves as the core infantry of this organization, embedded within the ranks of the Helldiver Corps.\nAccording to the description of the \"Pride of the Whistleblower\" cape, The Truth Enforcers have an award called the \"Informant of the Month\", which awards the recipient a cape called \"Pride of the Whistleblower\". The name of this cape, and the nature of its implied affiliations also indicate that this organization carries out infiltration and espionage tasks, as well as (possibly) extrajudicial executions of dissidents.\nAccording to the UF-16 Inspector Armor, the Truth Enforcers also have a series of famous mystery novels named after them \"Truth Enforcers: Enforcers of Truth\", much like how the exploits of the Viper Commandos were portrayed in the classic comic book series \"Tales of the Viper Commandos.\" The armor calls to mind those paragons of patriotism who protect us from treasonous lies.\nDemocratic Investigation Agency.\nIt is highly possible that the Democratic Investigation Agency serves the role of an \"Inquisition\" within Super Earth and, therefore, reports back to the Ministry of Truth or the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Unity\"&gt;Ministry of Unity&lt;/a&gt;, behaving much like a secret police."}
{"id": "6376", "revid": "15866885", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6376", "title": "Ministry of Unity", "text": "The Ministry of Unity (MoU) is an executive ministerial department of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. It is responsible for maintaining the internal safety of the Federation by ensuring that all citizens are united as one and stamping out any threats to Super Earth's security from within, namely disloyalty, dissident activity, and expression of treasonous thoughts.\nWhile unseen physically within either of the games, it can be assumed that the \"Loyalty Officers\" mentioned by the Service Technician are part of the Ministry of Unity. While not outright stated, it can be assumed that Loyalty Officers are akin to a police or security force, ensuring the loyalty of local neighborhoods and civilian facilities, thus separating them from the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Ministry of Truth&lt;/a&gt;'s Democracy Officers, who prevent un-democratic thoughts from taking root in military personnel by providing motivational quotes."}
{"id": "6028", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6028", "title": "Mintoria", "text": "Mintoria is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draupnir\"&gt;Draupnir&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nMintoria was, much like the rest of the planets in the Gellert Sector, not more than just a blip in the spreadsheet of Super Earth's Ministry of Expansion. Having been spared the horrors of the First Galactic War, this planet didn't see much colonization efforts due to its remoteness and the apparent lack of resources, which allowed Mintoria a relative peace that other planet colonies could not have.\nBut if there is something that the Automatons are simply built to hate...it is peace.\nBy October 2184, Mintoria had been disconnected from the ongoing galactic war since the very start, much like the rest of the Gellert Sector. Its remoteness and lack of colonists meant that finding itself detached from the FTL Network back in April, when the nearby Valdis sector fell, was just as unimportant and commonplace as the color of the grass on the planet.\nHowever, in late October 2184, the Automatons would make an advance towards the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Colonists on Mintoria and its' sister planet &lt;a href=\"Blistica\"&gt;Blistica&lt;/a&gt; would watch in horror as bordering &lt;a href=\"Zefia\"&gt;Zefia&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Yed%20Prior\"&gt;Yed Prior&lt;/a&gt; would fall to the robots in the &lt;a href=\"Tanis%20Sector\"&gt;Tanis Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The colonists' worst fears would be confirmed as their peaceful lives would be shattered on October 28th when the Automatons would invade both Mintoria and Blistica simultaneously, with the robots on Zefia attacking Mintoria. Due to the then-Major Order pushing the Helldivers to liberate &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;, as well as efforts to liberate &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;, both planets would show no resistance to the Automatons and would be easily captured by the next day.\nOperation Iron Rain.\nAs both Mintoria and Blistica would be located on the galactic fringe of the galaxy, both planets would see little to no liberation attempts for the next month. This would prove to be costly, as in the early morning hours of November 25th, the Automatons from both planets would send a combined force of 16 Battalions toward their northern neighbor, &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt;. Zzaniah would be attacked at the same time that the Terminids launched a massive assault on &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt;. As a result, few Helldivers would answer the call to defend Zzaniah, and it would fall by the early morning of November 27th. This defeat would cut off Super Earth from any supply lines towards either Mintoria or Blistica, leaving both planets under the full, despotic control of the Automatons.\nOperation Crop Dust.\nOn December 5th, 2184, orders were given to liberate Mintoria, along with &lt;a href=\"Blistica\"&gt;Blistica&lt;/a&gt; as well as &lt;a href=\"Esker\"&gt;Esker&lt;/a&gt;, all of which are locked behind enemy lines. Such mentioned planets have been identified as being rich in salt-mines, which is needed in order to rectify the shortage of chlorine and finally commence the production of MD-8 Gas Mines and its requisition to all Super Destroyers. However, Mintoria, along with Blistica, are not accessible due to &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt; being under Automaton control. The Helldivers are currently working to liberate Zzaniah Prime and re-open the floodgates to both Mintoria and Blistica, which will finally enable them to be liberated. The colonists trapped on both planets wait eagerly.\nMintoria had essentially been abandoned by the Automatons, with no shipments of supplies reaching the planet and leaving its resistance rate against liberation at zero. As such, once Esker was liberated on December 8th, the Helldivers immediately moved all available manpower to Mintoria, as the alloted time for the operation was running short. Mintoria was liberated by the end of the day, allowing the Helldivers to relocate to Blistica, which showed unusual difficulty despite its light resistance rate."}
{"id": "3330", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3330", "title": "Mirin Sector", "text": "The Mirin Sector is an inhabited area of galaxy on the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;Eastern Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. Located on Galactic North-East from &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, it consists of 4 planets."}
