{"id": "3506", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3506", "title": "Mort", "text": "Mort is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nA swamp planet, Mort is largely covered in dense, tree-lined wetlands. Its terrain is a grayish-crimson color, and its flora consists mainly of large, vine-covered trees, tentacle-like plants, as well as underlying brush. Its geography is largely rocky and hilly, though it is spaced out with large open patches of wet sandy lowlands, often with small lakes and inlets. The planet is covered in a very thick, crimson-orange fog, which significantly reduces visibility.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nFirst Battle of Mort (February 27th).\nDuring the Automaton surprise offensive Mort was the primary theater of fighting during February 27th, and gained notoriety by how close and brutal the fighting was. The planet was only saved by minutes as both the Helldivers and Automatons were close to winning the planet.\nOperation Enduring Bulwark.\nMort would return to the forefront of the galactic campaign two months later, following the sinister syncronicity of the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; launched large-scale assaults. Whilst the bugs were held at bay, the bots had broken the containment of the Menkent line, causing the galactic west to fall into chaos. The Automatons had reached Mort on the April 25th and after days of chaos, the Helldivers would finally rally, choosing the planet as the place that they would make their stand against the socialist toasters.\nSecond Galactic War.\nSecond Battle of Mort.\nHolding the planet would be vital, as Mort's fall would give the Automatons a foothold in yet another sector. Fortunately thanks to the tenacity of the Helldivers (and the Automaton offensive overstretching itself) Mort would hold, preventing this breakout and delivering Super Earth it's first successful defense on the Automaton in over a week.\nOperation Xzar Lockdown.\nMort would have spent the month of May and the first 3 weeks of June in relative peace, as it sat right next to the deadlocked &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt;, which the Automatons would promptly use to spread their socialism into Mort on the late hours of June 21st, attacking while the Helldivers were busy with Operation Hive Breaker in the Eastern Sectors. Underdefended, Mort would fall and allow the Automatons to launch a dual assault on Ingmar and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt;, in a pincer attack. Mort would be quickly defended and saved, however it would remain under potential attack due to an open FTL Supply Line between Mort and the enemy controlled &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3929", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3929", "title": "Mortar Emplacement", "text": "Mortar Emplacement.\nThe Mortar Emplacement is an Optional Objective contained within an &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; outpost. It attempts to shoot at enemy targets within range. To complete the Objective, Helldivers must destroy the Mortar Emplacements. It can spawn with &lt;a href=\"Automaton%20Fabricator\"&gt;Automaton Fabricators&lt;/a&gt;, ammo, and Samples around it.\nObjective Steps.\nThe Mortar Emplacement is an &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; tactical asset that constantly launches mortar shells at Helldivers within range. Incoming artillery shells can be heard by their whistling sound while airborne, along with the projectile itself glowing red and leaving a red trail behind them. \nWhile relatively inaccurate, their large range and constant firing make them a high priority threat that should be dealt with immediately.\nTactics.\n--&gt;"}
