{"id": "5781", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5781", "title": "Navi VII", "text": "Navi VII is one of the seven planets in &lt;a href=\"L%27estrade%20Sector\"&gt;L'estrade Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Its general landscape consists of sparsely growing jungle, with patches of denser forests, large lagoons and rocky hills. Constant rainstorms fall with constant volcanic eruptions cause a constant trouble in this paradise.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Mantes\"&gt;Mantes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Meissa\"&gt;Meissa&lt;/a&gt; and old &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt;, this planet offers a mix of dense vegetation and open fields. Most of the planet consists of islands, either solid or separated by massive lagoons. While the water is relatively shallow, straying through middle of said lagoons will often end up with painful and unpleasant drowning. Elevation changes are rare and small\nNotable flora consists of explosive thorn bulbs, which may prove extremely dangerous to any exosuit that might walk over them.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nNavi VII is one of many planets overrun by terminids during initial breakout in February of 2184. Since then, it remains outside reach of Helldivers and Liberty. \nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Brute Force.\nAmidst the month of August, a mysterious nebula of Terminid spores appeared around the vicinity of &lt;a href=\"Enuliale\"&gt;Enuliale&lt;/a&gt;. This nebula would grow until it engulfed all planets in the Sten and L'estrade Sectors, Navi VII and other planets in the Mirin and Draco Sectors being engulfed by August 27th. Due to the high concentration of spores, SEAF Satellites can no longer relay information back to Super Earth about the situation on Navi VII, leaving its fate unknown"}
