{"id": "5949", "revid": "56447", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5949", "title": "New Stockholm", "text": "New Stockholm is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Hanzo%20Sector\"&gt;Hanzo Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Although covered in large glaciers and rivers of thick ice, the planet is also highly populated, as can be expected of a planet given the former name of Prosperity City.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Heeth\"&gt;Heeth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;, although much more urbanized.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nFollowing the attack on &lt;a href=\"Genesis%20Prime\"&gt;Genesis Prime&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mog\"&gt;Mog&lt;/a&gt;, it became painfully clear to the whole Federation that the no-longer-eradicated illuminate were not backing down and indeed expanding their front of attack. Whilst the &lt;a href=\"SEAF\"&gt;SEAF&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver Corps&lt;/a&gt; fought the squids on the emerging battlefronts on &lt;a href=\"Valmox\"&gt;Valmox&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Kerth%20Secundus\"&gt;Kerth Secundus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defense&lt;/a&gt; Strategists attempted to analyze the Illuminate attack patteren, in order to provide insight into their malevolent plans and figure out where they would attack next.\nAfter several days, the analysts concluded with a high degree of certainty that the illuminates next attack would be on &lt;a href=\"New%20Stockholm\"&gt;New Stockholm&lt;/a&gt;. Preparations for invasion began immediately, which included a planet wide evacuation put into effect order to prevent any more citizens from having their &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;votes&lt;/a&gt; stolen for them. Meanwhile army reserves were called up and New Stockholm's major urban centers fortified, with the SEAF ready to make the squids bleed for every inch of ground on the jewel of the Hanzo sector...\n... or they would have, had the illuminate actually bothered to show up. Instead, the Squ'ith attacked &lt;a href=\"Andar\"&gt;Andar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Acubens%20Prime\"&gt;Acubens Prime&lt;/a&gt;, both in sectors to the east and west of the &lt;a href=\"Hanzo%20Sector\"&gt;Hanzo sector&lt;/a&gt;. Naturally this was a considerable embarrassment for the Strategists of the Ministry of Defense, with their attack pattern analysis methodology requiring redress. The process has since been placed under review until further notice.\nFTL Timeline.\nTo be added...\nTrivia.\nNew Stockholm is assumed to be named after the capital of Sweden, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockholm\"&gt;Stockholm&lt;/a&gt;, which in the world of Helldivers has been renamed Prosperity City."}
