{"id": "3819", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3819", "title": "Nivel 43", "text": "Nivel 43 is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Mirin%20Sector\"&gt;Mirin Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nNivel 43 is an ashy, rocky planet. It has little to no flora, with only small patches of sparse grey grass and plants, with some occasionaly having purple flowers. It is covered in a persistent light gray fog.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nNivel 43's distance from &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; and non-strategic position kept it under frequent tyranny of the despotic &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;. After the unexpected failure of the Terminid Control System on the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Barrier Planets&lt;/a&gt;, the tide of fascist insectoids overtook Nivel 43 along with the entire Mirin Sector.\nSecond Galactic War.\nThe judicious destruction of the &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; supercolony on May 30, 2184 allowed the SEAF to push forward into Terminid-occupied territory. \nOperation Hive Breaker.\nShortly after multiple overwhelming victories on the Automaton Front, the Helldivers were directed to liberate five planets illegally occupied by the Terminids: &lt;a href=\"Estanu\"&gt;Estanu&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fori%20Prime\"&gt;Fori Prime&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt;, and Nivel 43. Though Nivel 43's location meant it would be liberated last, it had not been forgotten. Despite the Terminids' sloppy attempts to slow down the SEAF through outbreaks on &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Esker\"&gt;Esker&lt;/a&gt;, Nivel 43 was finally liberated on June 21, 2184.\nFalstaff and Jin Xi Lockdown.\nHowever, Nivel 43, ignored as usual, would fall to a Terminid assault on June 25th, as the Helldivers were occupied with the protection of the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It would be stuck on a deadlock since then, as the Helldivers then began racing to secure the following key planets in the nearby &lt;a href=\"Falstaff%20Sector\"&gt;Falstaff&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi&lt;/a&gt; Sectors.\nHowever, despite this victory, Nivel 43's Terminid Hives managed to shield themselves from democracy, as they would launch another dual barrage of intergalactic spores onto both Hellmire and Esker, while Estanu would be under attack from a Terminid spore barrage coming from Fori Prime, which inevitably would create a triple defense situation that succesfully locked Nivel 43 away from the Helldivers' reach...for now.\nOperation Benevolent Sanitation.\nWith their position secured, the Terminids at Nivel 43 mostly stood by as their spawns on Esker went on to launch a massive superonslaught onto &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt; on August 6th. In their devious machinations, the Bugs at Nivel 43 would send an assault onto Erson Sands on August 7th by creating a new FTL line, which forced the Helldivers to abandon it in order to concentrate on the defense of Socorro.\nWith Erson Sands taken, the bugs were able to conduct the next part of their plan. Originating around &lt;a href=\"Enuliale\"&gt;Enuliale&lt;/a&gt;, a massive cloud of intergalactic Terminid spores had begun engulfing the planets in the L'estrade Sector that were under Terminid control. And soon enough, it began to expand onto other neighboring planets that were controlled by the Bugs, with Erson Sands and Nivel 43 being engulfed and SEAF Satellites being unable to monitor the situation on these 2 planets any further.\nThe situation on Nivel 43 is now unknown."}
{"id": "5627", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5627", "title": "Nublaria I", "text": " is one of the six planets in the &lt;a href=\"Celeste%20Sector\"&gt;Celeste Sector&lt;/a&gt;. While so far it has been spared the horrors of the Second Galactic War, it has seen its fair share, having been one of the few planets to see action in the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nFirst Galactic War.\nBattle of Nublaria.\nNot much is known about how the Nublaria system got caught up in the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. The only available record regarding its presence is made in the official description for the &lt;a href=\"Viper%20Commandos\"&gt;PH-9 Predator&lt;/a&gt; Light Armor.\nAccording to the armor's description, a soldier (possibly a Helldiver) by the callsign of Jackle 6, a veteran of the Viper Commandos, held off an entire brood of Terminids using nothing but a machine gun, a pocket knife and Orbital Laser Strikes.\nJudging by the current state of peace, freedom and democracy in the planet, it can be safely said that Jackle 6's actions that day gave Super Earth a peerless, unmatched victory over the Bugs.\nWhile to this day it has remained a peaceful planet colony, it has seen the fascist shadow of the Terminids loom upon it on one occasion during the Second Galactic War, when the Terminids made a desperate attempt to infest &lt;a href=\"Moradesh\"&gt;Moradesh&lt;/a&gt; through &lt;a href=\"Cirrus\"&gt;Cirrus&lt;/a&gt;. The bugs tried hard, and got so far as to overwhelm the defenses at Cirrus, but in the end, their vain attempts wouldn't even matter, as a day later, the Helldivers heroically destroyed the Meridian &lt;a href=\"Supercolony\"&gt;Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; during Operation Enduring Peace, immediately collapsing their offensive in Cirrus and allowing the &lt;a href=\"Celeste%20Sector\"&gt;Celeste Sector&lt;/a&gt; to breath a sigh of relief."}
