{"id": "3821", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3821", "title": "Omicron", "text": "Omicron is one of the seven planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"L%27estrade%20Sector\"&gt;L'estrade Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Omicron is the farthest planet that Super Earth forces have ever managed to spread Democracy into, marking the summit of the Terminid Front. It is the only planet with supply lines leading out of its sector but it is also the only planet disconnected from the rest of its own system.\nTopography.\nOmicron stands as the Terminids' attempt at mockery of beautiful &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;. It possesses perennial forests and shrubs that can allure even the most loyal of Helldivers, only for them to be gnawed and maimed by the merciless insectoids. High caution is advised, as its sights and landscapes have been deviously left untouched in order to stun Helldivers with their siren call, leaving them exposed to many unforeseen ambushes.\nNevertheless, Omicron's temperate montane climate also makes it very alluring for colonization efforts, with many comparing it to the ancient Alps and the ancient \"Black Forest\" of Sector 4 or the ancient forests that could once be found on the northern portions of Sector 7.\nHistory.\nOmicron itself has never been the target of any Super Earth High Command issued orders. However, the brave Helldivers took it upon themselves to conduct several expeditions into Omicron, going so far as to reaching around 80% liberation of the planet in April 2184, only being unable to fully liberate it due to the failure of the Terminid Control System and the Automaton Invasion of Cyberstan, which left it unable to be accessed. Below, the tales of the expeditions into Omicron have been logged by the Super Earth Digital Archive of Valorous Acts.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nFirst Expedition - March 2184.\nThe planet was once the site of a military Expedition. A small expedition of at least three thousand super destroyers commanded by the Helldivers attempted to liberate the world during the initial &lt;a href=\"Mirin%20Sector\"&gt;Mirin Sector&lt;/a&gt; Offensive during the slow march to Zagon Prime, and after the initial liberation of &lt;a href=\"Oshaune\"&gt;Oshaune&lt;/a&gt;. Omicron had also become the world with the highest known Terminid resistance recorded at the time.\nHelldivers were swarmed very quickly after landing and incurred heavier than usual casualties, which started discouraging Helldivers from assaulting the planet. The expedition hastily retreated after &lt;a href=\"Oshaune\"&gt;Oshaune&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt; fell, which coincided with the commencement of Operation Swift Disassembly in the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;, leaving only a few stranded Helldivers on Omicron who were listed as Missing-In-Action, as well as a number of unaccounted-for Super Destroyers that were still running surveys in the L'estrade Sector. High Command would reportedly express interest in eventually returning to Omicron and bringing the rest of the L'estrade Sector back under SEAF control in future campaigns.\nSecond Expedition - April 2184.\nA number of weeks after the First Expedition, &lt;a href=\"Oshaune\"&gt;Oshaune&lt;/a&gt; was again liberated and the Helldivers mounted another expedition into the L'estrade Sector, now with four times the manpower. Starting with Omicron once again, the level resistance encountered on the planet was interestingly lower compared to the first expedition, with skeletal remains of giant unknown Terminid creatures being sighted more often. \nLater however, in an act of sinister syncronicity, both the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; launched large-scale assaults across the galaxy. The second L'estrade Expedition was put on hold, with the Helldivers being pulled back in a more organized manner compared to the last time and in an effort to defend Super Earth's citizens on two fronts at once.\nEventually Oshaune was once again liberated a week later, and the second Expedition resumed again but with numbers reduced to just over three thousand Helldivers active on Omicron upon resumption of the expedition, the number would swell to over forty thousand a day later. Omicron would be mostly liberated eventually as the Helldivers had secured most of the planet on April 29th, largely avenging the shameful defeat incurred more than a month earlier. \nHowever, due the failure of the TCS system, the Helldivers had to put a stop to any plans of fully liberating Omicron. With the TCS causing the bugs to mutate at a rapid pace, all SEAF forces were ordered to the Umlaut Sector, with the remaining Terminids on Omicron launching a fierce counter attack now that the majority of Super Earth's forces were off world. Progress made on Omicron was quickly lost, with only some operational successes like the successful evacuation of civilians, scientists and high-value assets.\nSecond Galactic War.\nApparition of the Gloom.\nFurther opportunities to deploy onto Omicron would be permanently destroyed on August 2184, when a mysterious nebula formed around &lt;a href=\"Enuliale\"&gt;Enuliale&lt;/a&gt;. This nebula, composed by extremely high densities of intergalactic Terminid spores, would slowly begin to expand across the planets controlled by the Terminids, eventually engulfing Omicron and fully blocking it from further SEAF surveillance, as the satellites around Omicron's orbit stopped transmitting information back to Super Earth, like with all other planets engulfed by what is now known as &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt;.\nBy September 10th, there was only 1 Super Destroyer above Orbit, its status was only known to be operational at best. By October 3rd the Super Destroyer's signal went dead. It can only be assumed that all crew are lost and the ship is simply floating in High Orbit or the ship was pulled by Omicron's gravity and crashed onto the planet or crashed into one of Omicron's Moons. Whatever the case, the SEAF will eventually learn of its actual fate. It is also likely the ship is moving away from the planet on autopilot through the use of its subspace engines and limping back to Super Earth space by itself although this will take a very many years and eventually the E-710 on board will be exhausted leaving the ship adrift in space and by extension the Gloom.\nTrivia.\nOmicron is Greek for the Letter \"little O\" and is the value of 70 in the system of Greek numerals"}
{"id": "6350", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6350", "title": "Operation Modifiers", "text": "Operation Modifiers are non-specific type of effect that can randomly be applied to &lt;a href=\"Objectives\"&gt;missions&lt;/a&gt; at any time, and can effect gameplay across all planets and missions.\nOnly &lt;a href=\"Planets%20and%20Sectors\"&gt;planets&lt;/a&gt; that are under a liberation campaign will be subject to Operation modifiers, whereas planets under defence campaigns are completely absent of any Operation Modifiers.\nList of Modifiers.\nThere are 6 Operation Modifiers in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\nFaction specific Modifiers.\nThere are 2 faction specific Operation Modifiers in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\nRemoved Modifiers.\nThere are 3 removed Operation Modifiers in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3837", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3837", "title": "Operations", "text": "\"Not to be confused with &lt;a href=\"Helldiver%20Operations\"&gt;Helldiver Operations&lt;/a&gt;, which serves to archive major orders and other events\"\nIn &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;, a Operations is a set of &lt;a href=\"Objectives\"&gt;Missions&lt;/a&gt; that are grouped together on the . While some rewards are applied at the time of collection or at the end of each operation, most are affected by difficulty, and Squad Impact only gets applied upon completion of the last objective in a operation.\nAfter the second difficulty, operations have more than one mission. They can be completed in any order, but all of them must be completed for the squad impact to count. \nDifficulties.\nOperations can be one of nine difficulties, from Trivial to Super Helldive. Each difficulty has different rewards."}
