{"id": "4398", "revid": "55876533", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4398", "title": "Orbital EMS Strike", "text": "The Orbital EMS strike is an defensive utlity strike fired from the Super Destroyer. The stratagem deploys a medium-large field of blue electricity on a designated area. Most enemies caught inside the initial impact field will be stunned, unable to attack or move. Enemies entering the lingering field will only be slowed, but not stunned. Heavy enemies remain unaffected by the EMS Strike however, save for the Hulk. Fellow Helldivers caught in the field will also be slowed and unable to sprint, but will still be able to dive.\nSTATS:\nCall in time: 2 Seconds\nUses: Unlimited\nCooldown Time: 75 Seconds\nTACTICS:\n\u2022 The Orbital EMS Strike stuns most enemies, including Chargers, Devastators and Beserkers, giving a Helldiver a window to eliminate a patrol without alerting them, or breathing room to easily dispatch a pursuing group of enemies.\n\u2022 Nearly all heavy enemies such as Tanks, Bile Titans, Factory Striders and Cannons are completely unaffected by EMS, negating its effectiveness against these units. Strangely, Hulks are still affected by the EMS.\n\u2022 Enemies hit with the initial impact will be completely stunned for 5-10 seconds before regaining mobility, albeit slowed.\n\u2022 This stratagem can also be used to cover a retreat or to slow enemy advances.\n\u2022 This stratagem can be used in tandem with the Orbital Gas Strike and other AOE stratagems such as the Cluster Bomb or Airburst Strike to increase their effectiveness.\n\u2022 This stratagem is useful against both Automatons and Terminids, but may see more effectiveness against the Terminids due to their tendency to group up in pursuit of a Helldiver.\n\u2022 While it is non-lethal, the field will still significantly slow down any Helldiver caught within in its range. It can be a good idea to inform your fellow Helldivers you are deploying an EMS Strike, so they know what to expect."}
{"id": "3834", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3834", "title": "Orbital Gas Strike", "text": "The Orbital Gas Strike (or just Gas) is an area-denial corrosive gas shell - launched from the bridge of the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt; - that appears in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt costs 4000 &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Requisition\"&gt;Requisition Slips&lt;/a&gt; to unlock.\nAny enemies - or friendlies - that come in contact with the corrosive gas will begin taking high amounts of damage; due to the powerful dissolving properties of the substance melting through armour and flesh alike. Those coated in gas will continue to take damage for a few seconds after leaving the effective area. \nThe gas is not a neurotoxin like mustard gas, instead it is a corrosive substance, such as acid; this is why it is able to affect &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:\nNotes.\nInstead of dealing the same damage as fire, it now does half damage, but blinds and confuses enemy units, making them attack each other. This is incredibly useful in a pinch or to throw-and-forget, as they\u2019ll be focused on each other to acknowledge your retreat"}
