{"id": "6759", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6759", "title": "Overseer", "text": "The Overseer is a medium infantry &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; equipped with an arcane energy staff that acts as both a ranged and melee weapon. Centuries old, Overseers are formidable, calculating warriors who direct the hordes of &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt;, using them as expendable cannon fodder upon the frontlines, both to overwhelm SEAF forces as well as conserve their own limited numbers.\nPhysiology.\nThe Overseers are bipedal aliens, almost always being taller than the average human (as the Helldivers are several inches shorter than the Overseers). In terms of general anatomy, they're mostly anthropomorphic, with their limbs, joints and general physiology being similar in some degree to humans. \nIt appears that Overseers, if not the Illuminate at large, possess &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digitigrade\"&gt;digitigrade&lt;/a&gt; lower limbs; much unlike humans, who possess plantigrade legs. Each of the Illuminate's limbs possesses 3 appendages, all of equal length for a total of 12 \"fingers\", 6 on their lower limbs and 6 on their superior limbs. While they can stretch the joints in their superior limbs and are capable of full motion in them, they are unable to stretch their knees when running, but will some times fully stretch their legs when idle and out of combat. \nThe Overseers are clad in a white armor made out of an unknown alien material that is highly durable, requiring ammunition capable of medium armor penetration to effectively deal damage to them. Additionally, Overseers are equipped with a small, blue Energy Shield that can only be effectively punctured by ammunition capable of Heavy Armor Penetration, although enough damage will eventually disable it. Despite this, parts of their dark blue skin can be seen when their armors are damaged, indicating that they're part of the \"warrior\" caste of the Illuminate.\nThey can turn their heads independently, as seen in the \"Omens of Tyranny\" trailer, indicating that they possess necks and, possibly, spinal cords similar to that of humans."}
{"id": "4817", "revid": "47523383", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4817", "title": "P-113 Verdict", "text": "The P-113 Verdict is a semi-automatic pistol. It is unlocked in the &lt;a href=\"Polar%20Patriots\"&gt;Polar Patriots&lt;/a&gt; Warbond.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe recent patch gave the Verdict the ability to penetrate medium armor. It functions as a bridge between the &lt;a href=\"P-2%20Peacemaker\"&gt;Peacemaker&lt;/a&gt;'s RoF and handling and the &lt;a href=\"P-4%20Senator\"&gt;Senator&lt;/a&gt; accuracy and power.\nThis makes it a very versatile sidearm as it is capable of dealing with all types of fodder enemies, and it's RoF is quick enough to deliver decent burst damage to anyone who gets too close. However, it is still limited by it's small magazine size and somewhat cumbersome iron sights that makes precision aim challenging."}
{"id": "6794", "revid": "47063379", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6794", "title": "P-11 Stim Pistol", "text": "The P-11 Stim Pistol is a Special Sidearm that allows to user to fire Stims at fellow Helldivers, allowing the user to aid their teammates from a distance"}
{"id": "3678", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3678", "title": "P-19 Redeemer", "text": "The P-19 Redeemer is a machine pistol sidearm. The weapon features a miniature, low-profile red dot sight, a rail-mounted flashlight, and a fire selector for semi and full-auto fire.\nRole.\nDealing 15 less damage than the &lt;a href=\"P-2%20Peacemaker\"&gt;P-2 Peacemaker&lt;/a&gt;, the Redeemer makes up for this by being full automatic, along with having a blistering rate of fire and double the magazine size, allowing it to dish out more damage per second in comparison. Its strength is also its weakness, however, and Helldivers with poor firing discipline may find themselves quickly running out of ammunition for the gun.\nThe weapon has fairly low recoil, but poor accuracy. It is recommended to only use full auto at close range, and stick to bursts or single shots when engaging enemies farther than 15m. The weapon's high RoF and magazine allows it to chew through lightly-armored enemies, and even devastators when shot in the head up-close. "}
{"id": "5748", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5748", "title": "P-2 Peacemaker", "text": "The P-2 Peacemaker is the standard SEAF sidearm. It features a simple, striker-fired design, an oversized, full-hand trigger guard, and a rail-mounted laser-flashlight combo module.\nIt is the first weapon Helldivers use during basic training, and the first sidearm issued to them on their first day.\nRole.\nThe Peacemaker has a balanced combination of accuracy, power, and ergonomics. While it's not as specialized as the other sidearms, the Peacemaker is an easy-to-use fallback weapon that does its job well-enough against light-armored troops at close range."}
